name: iShares Mortgage Real Estate Capped ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle tracks a market-capitalization-weighted index primarily composed of U.S. Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) focused on holding residential and commercial mortgages. While investing at least 80% of its assets in securities reflecting its underlying index, it is non-diversified and utilizes a capping methodology limiting individual constituent weights to 22.5%, with quarterly rebalancing. The underlying index employs specific eligibility screens and includes provisions to potentially add mortgage finance or savings associations under certain conditions. The fund retains flexibility to invest up to 20% of its assets in derivatives, such as futures, options, and swaps, along with cash and cash equivalents.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the residential and commercial mortgage real estate, mortgage finance and savings associations sectors of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
REM tracks a market-cap-weighted index of residential and commercial mortgage REITs.

REM holds a broad, concentrated portfolio of residential and commercial mortgage REITs that mirrors the broad neutral benchmark for the mortgage REIT space. Constituent eligibility for its Underlying Index is subject to five screens, namely: size, liquidity, invested assets, free float and Unrelated Business Taxable Income (UBTI) screen. A capping methodology is also utilized in which Index constituents are capped at a 22.5% weight and rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Furthermore, constituents that are classified as Savings Associations or Mortgage Finance are included in the funds reserve list and will be added to the Index only when the number of constituents falls below 20. Each constituent will then be capped at 3% individually and 30% in aggregate.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in S-2 certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the FTSE NAREIT All Mortgage Capped Index composed of U.S. real estate investment trusts ("REITs") that hold U.S. residential and commercial mortgages. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in S-2 certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco MSCI Global Climate 500 ETF
merged_description: This passively managed exchange-traded fund aims to replicate the performance of a global equity index comprising approximately 500 stocks selected for meeting specific environmental and climate criteria relative to their industry peers. Investing at least 90% of its assets in the underlying index components (including ADRs and GDRs), the fund draws from a broad international universe, excluding companies involved in controversial business activities or significant ESG-related controversies. Its core strategy employs an optimization process designed to significantly reduce portfolio-wide greenhouse gas emissions intensity (targeting 10% for revenue-related and 7% for financing-related emissions) and increase exposure to companies with science-based carbon reduction targets, all while managing country and sector weights relative to a parent index. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index as well as ADRs and GDRs that represent securities in the underlying index. The index, which is designed to track the performance of approximately 500 stocks included in the ACWI ex Select Countries index that meet certain environmental and climate criteria relative to their peers, as determined by the index provider, including their own reductions in carbon and greenhouse gas emissions. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: KLMT is passively managed to hold 500 stocks from a broad global equity universe, meeting specific environmental and climate criteria. The index excludes companies involved in controversial business activities or implicated in controversies with potential negative ESG impact. It employs a methodology consistent with international norms, evaluating each company's reputational and brand risks across five ESG categories: environment, human rights & community impact, labor rights & supply chain, customers, and governance. Eligible stocks are selected and weighted using an optimization process focused on emission intensity and reduction targets. This process aims to (i) reduce revenue-related GHG emissions intensity by 10%, (ii) reduce financing-related GHG emissions intensity activities by 7%, and (iii) increase weight in companies with SBTi-approved GHG emissions reduction target(s). Country and sector weights are capped to align closely with the parent index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the MSCI ACWI Select Climate 500 Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index as well as ADRs and GDRs that represent securities in the underlying index. The index, which is designed to track the performance of approximately 500 stocks included in the ACWI ex Select Countries index that meet certain environmental and climate criteria relative to their peers, as determined by the index provider, including their own reductions in carbon and greenhouse gas emissions. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Columbia India Consumer ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers concentrated exposure to the Indian consumer market by tracking the performance of the Indxx India Consumer Index. The index employs a free-float adjusted, market capitalization-weighted methodology and includes up to 30 Indian consumer companies listed on the National Stock Exchange or Bombay Stock Exchange, selected via a proprietary process. Characteristically, the fund invests heavily (typically over 95% of assets) in these index constituents, which cover both consumer cyclical and non-cyclical sectors, potentially including firms of all market capitalizations for broader industry representation. Reflecting its focused approach, the fund is classified as non-diversified and its underlying index undergoes annual rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in Indian consumer companies included in the index and the advisor generally expects to be substantially invested at such times, with at least 95% of its net assets invested in these securities. The index is a maximum 30-stock free-float adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to measure the market performance of companies in the consumer industry in India, as defined by Indxx's proprietary methodology. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
INCO tracks a market-cap-weighted index of 30 Indian consumer-sector stocks listed on the National Stock Exchange or the Bombay Stock Exchange.

INCO tracks a float-adjusted, market capitalization-weighted index of just 30 India-listed consumer stocks. Unlike our benchmark, INCO targets both the consumer cyclicals and non-cyclicals sector. As a result, INCO offers broader industry exposure, whereas our benchmark concentrates its holdings in the cyclical sector. INCO's strategy creates a broader and arguably more balanced exposure than our concentrated, market-like benchmark. The fund may invest in companies of all market capitalizations, and its Index is rebalanced and reconstituted annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond to the price and yield performance of the Indxx India Consumer Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in Indian consumer companies included in the index and the advisor generally expects to be substantially invested at such times, with at least 95% of its net assets invested in these securities. The index is a maximum 30-stock free-float adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to measure the market performance of companies in the consumer industry in India, as defined by Indxx's proprietary methodology. It is non-diversified.

name: Simplify Downside Interest Rate Hedge Strategy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified ETF aims to hedge against falling long-term interest rates and potentially benefit from market stress associated with increased fixed income volatility. It allocates assets between interest rate derivatives and income-producing debt instruments, seeking to achieve its objectives while also providing the potential for income.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF. The adviser seeks to achieve the fund’s investment objective by allocating the fund’s assets between interest rate related derivatives and interest income producing debt instruments. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to hedge interest rate movements arising from falling long-term interest rates, and to benefit from market stress when fixed income volatility increases, while providing the potential for income. The fund is an actively managed ETF. The adviser seeks to achieve the fund’s investment objective by allocating the fund’s assets between interest rate related derivatives and interest income producing debt instruments. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Global Wind Energy ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to track the performance of an index comprising global companies actively engaged in the wind energy industry, investing at least 90% of its assets in the constituent common stocks and depositary receipts. The underlying index employs a modified float-adjusted market-capitalization weighting methodology, allocating approximately 60% to 'pure-play' wind energy companies and 40% to 'diversified sector' firms involved in the industry, applying distinct and strict weighting caps to individual holdings within each category. Characterized as non-diversified, the fund's index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually to maintain its targeted exposure to the global wind energy sector.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index provides a benchmark for investors interested in tracking public companies throughout the world that are active in the wind energy industry. In order to be eligible for inclusion in the index, a security must be issued by a company that is actively engaged in some aspect of the wind energy industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FAN tracks an index of companies involved in the wind energy industry, weighted according to float-adjusted market cap with strict limits on individual holdings.

FAN is a global renewable energy ETF that specifically targets the wind industry. FAN saves roughly 60% of its weighting for 'pure-plays' in the wind industry and allocates the remaining 40% to 'diversified sector' companies involved in the industry. The top five pure-play companies are capped at 8% weight each, with a 4% cap for the remainder. All diversified sector companies have a 2% cap. It follows a 'wind energy' mandate. The fund changed its name from First Trust ISE Global Wind Energy Index Fund to First Trust Global Wind Energy ETF on 12/14/2016. The underlying index methodology changed on 6/20/17, affecting the funds weighting and position limits. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield of an equity index called the ISE Clean Edge Global Wind Energy TM Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index provides a benchmark for investors interested in tracking public companies throughout the world that are active in the wind energy industry. In order to be eligible for inclusion in the index, a security must be issued by a company that is actively engaged in some aspect of the wind energy industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Goldman Sachs Dynamic New York Municipal Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to provide a high level of current income that is exempt from federal, New York State, and New York City personal income taxes. Its core strategy involves investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in fixed-income securities issued by or on behalf of New York state and its political subdivisions. While primarily holding investment-grade municipal bonds typically within a two- to eight-year duration range, the fund incorporates flexibility, allowing investment of up to 30% in non-investment-grade debt and the ability to hold securities from defaulted issuers. It is non-diversified and employs a combination of top-down and bottom-up fundamental analysis, potentially integrating ESG factors. Investors should note the fund may allocate significantly to private activity bonds, the interest from which could be subject to the Alternative Minimum Tax (AMT), and may also gain exposure through other investment companies.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in fixed income securities issued by or on behalf of the state of New York and its political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities thereof and other states, territories and possessions of the United States. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GMNY seeks a high level of current income by investing in municipal securities exempt from federal and New York state income tax. The actively managed fund mainly holds investment grade bonds with a two- to eight-year duration.

GMNY utilizes an active approach to a niche segment of the US muni bond space. The fund holds USD-denominated muni bonds issued by the state of New York and its political subdivisions, seeking interest income exempt from federal and New York state income tax. The fund may allocate its assets entirely to private activity bonds, whose interest may be a preference item for the federal alternative minimum tax. It may also get exposure through affiliated or unaffiliated investment companies, including other ETFs. Despite its focus on investment grade bonds, the fund can invest up to 30% in non-investment-grade bonds and may purchase securities of issuers in default. In constructing the portfolio, the fund adviser incorporates both a top-down approach and a bottom-up analysis. As part of its fundamental selection process, the adviser may integrate ESG factors alongside traditional fundamental metrics. Typically, the portfolio duration will range between two and eight years.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of current income that is exempt from regular federal income tax and New York State and City personal income taxes. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in fixed income securities issued by or on behalf of the state of New York and its political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities thereof and other states, territories and possessions of the United States. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Janus Henderson Mortgage-Backed Securities ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks a high level of total return, consisting of both income and capital appreciation, primarily by investing in mortgage-related instruments. Under normal conditions, it invests at least 80% of its assets in a portfolio of mortgage-related fixed income securities of varying maturities, focusing mainly on agency mortgage-backed securities (MBS). However, its active mandate allows for up to 20% investment in non-agency MBS or other fixed income types, utilizing a bottom-up, loan-level fundamental analysis approach to identify potentially mispriced securities with the goal of outperforming the broader MBS market. The fund may also invest in derivatives.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing mainly in mortgage-related instruments. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80%, and often times substantially all, of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in a portfolio of mortgage-related fixed income instruments of varying maturities. Additionally, the fund may invest in derivatives.
description_etfcom:
JMBS is an actively managed fund of mortgage-backed securities. The fund seeks a high level of total return.

JMBS holds a portfolio primarily consisting of agency MBS, though the funds active mandate means that up to 20% may be invested in non-agency MBS or other fixed income securities. The funds manager performs a bottom-up, loan-level fundamental analysis in an effort to identify mispriced securities. JMBS seeks a return of at least 50 bps higher than the Bloomberg US MBS Index, after fees.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of total return consisting of income and capital appreciation. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing mainly in mortgage-related instruments. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80%, and often times substantially all, of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in a portfolio of mortgage-related fixed income instruments of varying maturities. Additionally, the fund may invest in derivatives.

name: AltShares Merger Arbitrage ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund tracks a global index designed to capture returns from a merger arbitrage strategy, focusing on publicly announced stock-for-stock mergers and acquisitions across developed markets and all capitalizations. Its core approach involves taking long positions in takeover targets (typically 30-50 holdings) while simultaneously shorting the acquiring companies to hedge against declines in the acquirer's stock price. A distinctive feature is its strategy to hedge foreign currency exposure back to the US dollar. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in index constituents or related instruments like swaps, reconstitutes and rebalances twice monthly, and is classified as non-diversified. It may also hold cash under specific circumstances, such as when deals are completed or target opportunities are limited.
description_original: The fund seeks to track the performance of the index, which is designed to reflect a global merger arbitrage strategy. Under normal market conditions, it will invest at least 80% of its net assets (including borrowings for investment purposes) in the constituents of the index and in financial instruments with economic characteristics similar to such constituents such as swaps on such constituents. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
ARB tracks a global USD-hedged index that uses a merger arbitrage strategy by providing long exposure to takeover targets and short exposure the acquiring company.

ARB is the first ETF by AltShares Trust and the first merger arbitrage fund that hedges foreign currency exposure. The fund is passively managed to invest in a developed market index of all-cap equities, focused on publicly-announced stock-for-stock mergers or acquisitions. The fund takes long positions on 30-50 takeover targets, while shorting the acquiring firms to hedge the acquirers stock price decline. The index rebalances and reconstitutes twice a month. ARB hedges its FX risks against the USD using forward currency or futures contracts. The fund may also hold positions in cash when the number of takeover targets are not met or when deals are consummated.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that closely correspond, before fees and expenses, to the performance of its underlying index, the Water Island Merger Arbitrage USD Hedged Index. The fund seeks to track the performance of the index, which is designed to reflect a global merger arbitrage strategy. Under normal market conditions, it will invest at least 80% of its net assets (including borrowings for investment purposes) in the constituents of the index and in financial instruments with economic characteristics similar to such constituents such as swaps on such constituents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Funds Global X Emerging Markets Great Consumer ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks long-term capital growth by primarily investing in equity securities connected to emerging markets, focusing specifically on companies positioned to benefit from increasing consumption and growing purchasing power within these economies. Advised and sub-advised, the fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in companies either based in emerging markets or economically tied to them. The strategy targets firms of all sizes across various sectors and from at least three different countries, selecting those expected to gain from demographic trends, industrialization, and wealth accumulation driving consumer demand. Eligible companies generally must be listed, organized, derive significant revenue (e.g., 50%+), or hold substantial assets (e.g., 50%+) within emerging market regions, identified through a bottom-up selection process guided by a risk management framework. The fund transitioned from a mutual fund structure in mid-2023.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF advised by the Adviser and sub-advised by the Sub-Adviser that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, measured at the time of purchase, in equity securities: (i) of issuers in emerging markets; and/or (ii) that are tied economically to emerging markets.
description_etfcom:
EMC is an actively managed fund that invests in companies across multiple sectors that are positioned to benefit from the increasing consumption and growing purchasing power of consumers from the emerging markets.

EMC seeks long-term capital growth through a consumer-focused investment strategy. The fund invests in companies of all sizes that are expected to benefit from both direct and indirect economic effects of increasing consumption activities and purchasing power of emerging market consumers. The adviser believes that emerging markets will experience rapid growth driven by key trends such as population growth, industrialization, wealth accumulation, increasing consumption among youths, and the pursuit of a higher quality of life. Eligible firms must be listed, organized under the laws of, derive at least 50% of their revenue from, or have at least 50% of their assets in emerging markets. Such companies may be of various sectors and from at least three different countries. The portfolio is constructed using a bottom-up approach, subject to a risk management framework. On May 15, 2023, EMC converted from a mutual fund to an actively managed ETF, with $471 million in assets.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital growth. The fund is an actively managed ETF advised by the Adviser and sub-advised by the Sub-Adviser that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, measured at the time of purchase, in equity securities: (i) of issuers in emerging markets; and/or (ii) that are tied economically to emerging markets.

name: Fidelity MSCI Real Estate Index ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to mirror the performance of the U.S. real estate sector by tracking the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index, investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent securities. Its portfolio provides broad exposure, encompassing U.S. REITs and other real estate companies across the entire market-capitalization spectrum, as defined by the GICS sector classification. While generally following a market-cap weighting, the underlying index employs a capping methodology (limiting single group entities to 25% and the aggregate weight of issuers over 5% to 50%) to ensure diversification. The fund may not hold every security in the index and its distributions are typically taxed as ordinary income.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index, which represents the performance of the real estate sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index.
description_etfcom:
FREL tracks a cap-weighted index of US REIT and real estate companies across the entire market-cap spectrum.

FREL is one of ten Fidelity ETFs that track MSCI sector indexes. The fund targets companies in the US real estate sector as defined by the GICS sector classification scheme. The fund is both broad and representative, and it differs mostly by including a handful of non-REIT real estate firms. To meet diversification requirements, the funds underlying index employs a capping methodology, such that no group entity exceeds 25% of index weight and the aggregate weight of issuers with over 5% weight in the index are capped at 50% weight of the portfolio. Prior to December 1, 2020, FREL tracked the unconstrained MSCI USA IMI Real Estate Index. Like all real estate ETFs, FRELs distributions are taxed as ordinary income.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index, which represents the performance of the real estate sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Real Estate 25/25 Index.

name: USCF Midstream Energy Income Fund
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily targets high current income, with capital appreciation as a secondary objective, by investing in a concentrated portfolio of midstream energy companies. Under normal conditions, it allocates at least 80% of its assets to equity securities of U.S. and Canadian firms of any market capitalization engaged in energy transportation, storage, gathering, and processing. Employing a bottom-up fundamental analysis focused on quality, the strategy typically holds 20-25 positions, evaluating metrics like income generation, distribution growth and coverage, leverage, and persistent cash flow stability, while also integrating ESG criteria into the research. This non-diversified fund invests significantly in the energy sector (over 25% of assets), holds both MLP and C-corp structures, and generally includes a substantial allocation (typically 30-40%) to Canadian issuers.
description_original: The fund will seek to achieve its investment objectives by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of its net assets in equity securities of U.S. and Canadian companies of any market capitalization deemed by the Sub-Adviser to be engaged in the midstream energy sector. It will invest more than 25% of the value of its total assets in the energy, oil, and gas industries. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: UMI actively invests in a narrow selection of about 20 to 25 believed to be high quality midstream energy companies that pay distributions. The fund adviser applies a bottom-up fundamental approach to energy infrastructure companies focused on transportation, storage, gathering and processing. Key metrics include income, growth of income, distribution coverage and leverage. The fund adviser also screens for persistent cash flow generation by evaluating contract quality and direct-commodity price exposure. In addition, ESG criteria are integrated in the funds research. UMI primarily invests in US and Canadian companies of any market-cap, with Canadian securities generally taking up 30% to 40% of the funds holdings. Investors should note that the fund may hold both energy infrastructure MLPs and C-corporations, which are taxed differently.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of current income; as a secondary objective, the fund seeks capital appreciation. The fund will seek to achieve its investment objectives by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of its net assets in equity securities of U.S. and Canadian companies of any market capitalization deemed by the Sub-Adviser to be engaged in the midstream energy sector. It will invest more than 25% of the value of its total assets in the energy, oil, and gas industries. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Trust - iShares MSCI USA Quality GARP ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a Growth at a Reasonable Price (GARP) strategy, focusing on large- and mid-cap U.S. equities that exhibit favorable growth, value, and quality characteristics. Starting with a broad U.S. stock universe, it first selects companies demonstrating stronger growth potential based on several metrics, including earnings and sales growth trends. Subsequently, the portfolio construction tilts towards those selected stocks that also display attractive value (such as P/E and P/B ratios) and quality (like ROE and leverage) traits relative to their sector peers. Rebalanced quarterly, this non-diversified fund invests primarily in the component securities of its underlying index and notably underwent a significant strategy, name, and index change in mid-2024.
description_original: GARP focuses on large- and mid-cap US growth stocks that exhibit value and quality traits, or growth at a reasonable price. The selection process begins with the MSCI USA Index, where each stock is assigned a growth score based on five criteria: long-term and short-term forward EPS growth rates, historical EPS and sales per share growth trends, and current internal growth rate. Stocks with higher growth scores are selected until they represent approximately 50% of the parent index. Each stock receives a tilt score, which considers value (P/B, forward P/E, and EV/CFO) and quality (ROE, D/E, and earnings variability) metrics relative to its sector. The portfolio is then tilted toward securities that score favorably on both metrics, with weights adjusted for portfolio diversification. Index rebalancing is done quarterly. Before June 3, 2024, the fund was named iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF under the ticker STLG and tracked the Russell US Large Cap Factors Growth Style Index.
description_etfcom: GARP focuses on large- and mid-cap US growth stocks that exhibit value and quality traits, or growth at a reasonable price. The selection process begins with the MSCI USA Index, where each stock is assigned a growth score based on five criteria: long-term and short-term forward EPS growth rates, historical EPS and sales per share growth trends, and current internal growth rate. Stocks with higher growth scores are selected until they represent approximately 50% of the parent index. Each stock receives a tilt score, which considers value (P/B, forward P/E, and EV/CFO) and quality (ROE, D/E, and earnings variability) metrics relative to its sector. The portfolio is then tilted toward securities that score favorably on both metrics, with weights adjusted for portfolio diversification. Index rebalancing is done quarterly. Before June 3, 2024, the fund was named iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF under the ticker STLG and tracked the Russell US Large Cap Factors Growth Style Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of MSCI USA Quality GARP Select Index which is designed to measure the performance of the large- and mid‑capitalization segments of the U.S. equity market, as defined by the index provider. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily S&P Biotech Bull 3X Shares
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks to provide daily investment results corresponding to 300% of the daily performance of an equal-weighted index focused on the US biotechnology sub-industry. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in a combination of financial instruments, such as swap agreements and other derivatives, along with securities of the index and related ETFs, to achieve its daily leveraged objective. While concentrating exposure in biotechnology and medical research, it may also include significant pharmaceutical holdings. Due to its daily leverage target and rebalancing mechanism, this fund is designed for short-term trading purposes; long-term returns can significantly deviate from the stated multiple of the index's performance because of compounding effects, making it generally unsuitable for buy-and-hold investors.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments and securities of the index, exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or ETFs that track the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the biotechnology sub-industry based on the Global Industry Classification Standards ("GICS"). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: LABU is a daily 3x leveraged bet on an equal-weighted index of US biotech stocks. The vast majority of the fund's exposure is to biotechnology and medical research but also captures significant exposure to pharmaceuticals as well. As a leveraged product, the fund is not a buy-and-hold investment. It gets its leverage exposure through a portfolio of derivatives contracts that gets rebalanced at the end of each trading day. Because of that, the fund's return for periods longer than a day becomes path-dependent and is likely to be different from 3x the return of the index for the same period. This makes LABU suitable primarily for short-term traders. Over time, compounding effects can lead to profound differences in expected returns relative to the index.
description_yahoo: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the performance of the biotechnology sub-industry based on the Global Industry Classification Standards ("GICS"). The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the S&P Biotechnology Select Industry Index ("index"). The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the performance of the biotechnology sub-industry based on the Global Industry Classification Standards ("GICS"). The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares ESG Aware MSCI USA Small-Cap ETF
merged_description: This ETF focuses on U.S. small-capitalization companies demonstrating strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics, primarily by investing at least 90% of its assets in the components of an optimized index. The underlying index aims to deliver investment results comparable to a broad U.S. small-cap benchmark while allocating more heavily to companies with favorable ESG profiles, as assessed by MSCI. Its construction involves screening the U.S. small-cap universe to exclude companies involved in specific activities such as tobacco, controversial weapons, civilian firearms manufacturing and retail, thermal coal, and oil sands, as well as those implicated in severe business controversies. Companies are evaluated on their exposure and response to key ESG issues relative to industry peers, and the index, comprising roughly 1,000 securities, is optimized quarterly to maximize exposure to these higher-rated ESG firms while maintaining parent index characteristics.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The underlying index is an optimized equity index designed to produce investment results comparable to the MSCI USA Small Cap Index (the "parent index"), while reflecting a higher allocation than that of the parent index to companies with favorable ESG profiles (as determined by MSCI).
description_etfcom:
ESML tracks an index of US small-cap companies with high environmental, social, and governance factor scores as determined by MSCI.

ESML launched at a time of high investor sensitivity to producers and retailers of civilian firearms. The fund holds about 1,000 US small-cap companies with the highest ESG ratings. The index screens the US small-cap universe to exclude securities of companies involved in tobacco or controversial weapons, producers and retailers of civilian firearms, thermal coal and oil sands, as well as companies involved in severe business controversies. For each industry, MSCI identifies key ESG issues (such as climate change, resource scarcity, and demographic shifts). Each company is then rated based on their exposure and strategic response to the key issues, in comparison to their industry peers. The index is then optimized quarterly to maximize exposure to companies with higher ESG ratings, while providing investment results comparable to those of the parent index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The underlying index is an optimized equity index that is designed to produce investment results comparable to the MSCI USA Small Cap Index (the "parent index"), while reflecting a higher allocation than that of the parent index to companies with favorable ESG profiles (as determined by MSCI).
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Small Cap Extended ESG Focus Index. name: YieldMax SQ Option Income Strategy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund aims to generate monthly income while providing capped exposure to the price movements of Block, Inc. (SQ) stock through a synthetic covered call strategy. It achieves this by creating synthetic long exposure to SQ using various options (both standardized exchange-traded and FLEX) and simultaneously writing short-term, out-of-the-money call options (typically 5-15% above the current price) to generate income; this inherently limits potential gains if the underlying stock appreciates significantly. The strategy is collateralized primarily by cash and short-term US Treasury securities. Notably, the fund does not invest directly in SQ shares, meaning investors receive no dividends from the underlying stock. It maintains its non-diversified investment approach consistently, regardless of adverse market or economic conditions, without taking temporary defensive positions.
description_original: The fund will seek to employ its investment strategy as it relates to SQ regardless of whether there are periods adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
SQY seeks to provide current income and capped gains on the Block stock (SQ) through a synthetic covered call strategy, collateralized by cash and US Treasurys. The actively managed fund uses both standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options.

SQY aims to generate monthly income while providing exposure to the price returns of the stock, Block, Inc. (SQ), subject to a cap on potential investment gains. The fund utilizes a synthetic covered call strategy via standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options, which consists of three elements: i) synthetic long exposure, ii) covered call writing, and iii) US Treasurys. The synthetic long exposure seeks to replicate the price movements of SQ by purchasing and selling at-the-money call and put options that generally have six-month to one-year terms. To generate income, the fund writes call options with an expiration of one month or less and a strike price 5%-15% above SQs current share price. This limits the funds participation in potential gains if SQ shares increase in value. Lastly, the fund holds cash and short-term Treasury securities as collateral. Note: the fund does not invest directly in shares of Block. Thus, investors are not entitled to any SQ dividends.
description_yahoo: The fund will employ its investment strategy as it relates to SQ regardless of whether there are periods of adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P SmallCap Financials ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to replicate the performance of an index focused on small-capitalization U.S. companies operating within the financials and real estate sectors, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS®). It typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities making up this index, which includes firms involved in banking, investment services, insurance, and Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs). By concentrating almost exclusively on small- and micro-cap stocks, the fund offers a distinct exposure compared to the large-cap dominated financial sector, deliberately avoiding industry giants. The underlying index utilizes a market-capitalization weighting methodology, modified with capping rules to improve diversification, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. description_etfcom:
PSCF tracks a market-cap-weighted index of financial services companies in the US small-cap market.

PSCF holds securities of small-cap financial services companies in the US that are hand-picked by an S&P Committee. Aside from the usual financial services like banking, investment services and insurance, the fund may also include real estate investment trusts (REITs). PSCF has quite a divergent performance, being a small-cap-focused fund in a sector biased on large-caps. Holding small- and micro-caps almost exclusively, the funds weighted average market cap falls far below the sector's average. This tilt steers PSCF away from financial giants. Still, as market conditions change quickly in financials, PSCF's small-cap and growth biases represent a different take on a large-cap-dominated industry. In addition, aside from market-cap-weighting, the index also applies a capping methodology to diversify exposure. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.

name: Invesco Dynamic Building & Construction ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified exchange-traded fund provides focused exposure to the U.S. building and construction industry by seeking to track the results of a specialized, factor-based index. Investing at least 90% of its assets in the index components, the fund selects approximately 30 U.S. common stocks from a pool of large, liquid companies based on metrics like price and earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. The portfolio includes companies engaged in construction and related engineering services for various property types, as well as home improvement material manufacturers, specialized machinery providers, installation/maintenance services, and land developers. Its unique weighting methodology is tiered by market capitalization, allocating a greater weight (around 60%) to smaller-cap stocks compared to larger ones (around 40%), with components equally weighted within their respective tiers, and the index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying intellidex. The underlying intellidex was composed of common stocks of U.S. building and construction companies. These companies are engaged primarily in providing construction and related engineering services for building and remodeling residential properties, commercial or industrial buildings, etc. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PKB tracks an index of building and construction companies, selected using multiple factors and weighted in tiers.

PKB covers the US building and construction industry including home improvement material manufacturers, specialized machinery providers, installation/maintenance services, and land developers. The fund builds a portfolio from the 2,000 largest, most liquid stocks on the NYSE, NYSE MKT and NASDAQ, based on price and earnings momentum, quality, management action and value. The 30-stock portfolio is tiered by market cap and equally weighted within groups, with a small-cap tilt. Of the top-ranked stocks, the larger ones receive 40%, and the smaller ones get 60% of the index weight. The index is rebalanced quarterly starting February. Prior to August 28, 2023, the fund traded under the name Invesco Dynamic Building & Construction ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. name: Hartford Schroders Commodity Strategy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks long-term total return primarily through investments in a diverse range of commodity-related derivative instruments, with an emphasis on futures contracts. Its portfolio may also include swaps, structured notes, options, other commodity-focused ETFs, and equities of commodity-related companies, all strategically invested via a Cayman Islands-based subsidiary. The fund's managers dynamically adjust exposure and allocations across various commodities based on fundamental, quantitative, and technical research, which may also incorporate ESG considerations. While individual positions can be both long and short, the overall strategy aims for net long exposure to commodities.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing in a range of commodity related derivative instruments, primarily futures contracts and other commodity linked derivative instruments (including but not limited to futures on commodities, commodity related securities or commodity indices and swaps on physical commodities), and structured notes.
description_etfcom: HCOM is an actively managed ETF that invests in a range of commodity-related derivative instruments, primarily futures contracts, but also other commodity-based ETFs, options on commodity indices, equities of commodity-related companies, swaps, and structured notes. These investments are made exclusively through a subsidiary organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands. The exposure and allocation to various commodities is expected to change from time to time based on the fund advisers fundamental, quantitative, and technical research. The research may also include some ESG factors as well. Individual positions may be both long and short yet resulting in net long exposure to a particular commodity. name: iShares Global Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on large global infrastructure companies across both developed and emerging markets, aiming to track a corresponding market-cap-weighted index. Its portfolio provides diversified exposure across three core infrastructure sectors: transportation (targeted at 40% weight with 30 stocks), utilities (targeted at 40% weight with 30 stocks), and energy (targeted at 20% weight with 15 stocks). The fund holds a concentrated selection of roughly 75 companies, chosen based on size, with specific allocations ensuring representation from both developed (60 stocks) and emerging markets (15 stocks). Within each sector, holdings are market-cap weighted, subject to a 5% cap on individual securities. Adhering to its investment objective, the fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities matching its underlying index characteristics, potentially utilizing the remaining portion for derivatives or cash equivalents, and rebalances its holdings semi-annually.
description_original: The index is designed to track performance of the stocks of large infrastructure companies in developed or emerging markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents,.
description_etfcom:
IGF tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global infrastructure companies.

IGF is one of the oldest funds in the global infrastructure segment. With a broad definition of infrastructure firms, it offers a reasonable take on the segment as it holds diversified positions across three sectors: energy, transportation, and utilities. After categorizing eligible securities into three sectors, the fund selects the largest stocks according to market cap, having 15 stocks from the emerging markets with no more than 10 for any single sector and 60 stocks from the developed markets. Overall, IGF holds a concentrated portfolio of 75 global infrastructure companies, subject to count and weight constraints such that the transportation and utilities sector each consists of 30 securities having 40% weight and the energy sector contains 15 securities taking 20% weight of the portfolio. Stocks are cap-weighted within each sector, with no individual security having a weight greater than 5%. The index rebalancing occurs on a semi-annual basis.

name: Invesco NASDAQ Future Gen 200 ETF
merged_description: This passively managed exchange-traded fund seeks to track an index composed of non-financial companies listed on the NASDAQ stock exchange. It specifically targets companies beyond the largest 200, excluding those found within the Nasdaq-100 and Nasdaq Next Generation 100 indexes. The fund invests at least 90% of its assets in the index components, focusing on identifying innovators through a unique screening process that assesses the estimated value of a company's patent portfolio relative to its market capitalization, selecting the top 200 based on this ratio. Consequently, the portfolio often exhibits a tilt towards small- and mid-cap stocks and employs an equal-weighting methodology. As a non-diversified fund, it may experience concentration in particular sectors and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index excludes securities of issuers included in the Nasdaq-100 Index® (an index that measures the performance of 100 of the largest Nasdaq-listed non-financial companies by market capitalization) and the Nasdaq Next Generation 100 Index® (an index that measures the performance of the 100 largest Nasdaq-listed companies outside of the NASDAQ-100 Index® based on market capitalization). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: QQQS is passively managed to hold a portfolio of non-financial, NASDAQ-listed companies of any market capitalization. The index screens out companies in the NASDAQ-100 Index and the NASDAQ Next Generation 100 Index, effectively screening out the largest 200 stocks listed on NASDAQ. As a result of the screening process, the portfolio will tend to tilt towards small- and mid-cap stocks and can become concentrated in particular sectors. The index looks for innovators by screening for high quality patents. It uses data from an independent provider to determine an estimated value of each eligible companys patent portfolio, quantifying intangible assets such as intellectual property and research development activities. Then eligible companies are ranked by the ratio of patent value estimate to their market capitalization and the top 200 securities are selected. The resulting portfolio is weighted equally. The index rebalances quarterly and reconstitutes semi-annually.

name: ARK Fintech Innovation ETF
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital growth, this actively-managed exchange-traded fund concentrates on the theme of financial technology (Fintech) innovation, targeting companies introducing technologically enabled products or services that could potentially reshape the financial sector. It primarily invests (at least 80% of its assets) in domestic and foreign equity securities of companies, regardless of market capitalization, that derive significant revenue or market value from Fintech innovation or whose primary business focuses on this theme. Examples of included innovations might involve transaction technologies, blockchain, risk transformation, frictionless funding, customer platforms, and new intermediaries. Due to its focused investment approach, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed ETF that will invest under normal circumstances primarily (at least 80% of its assets) in domestic and foreign equity securities of companies that are engaged in the fund's investment theme of financial technology ("Fintech") innovation. A company is deemed to be engaged in the theme of Fintech innovation if (i) it derives a significant portion of its revenue or market value from the theme of Fintech innovation, or (ii) it has stated its primary business to be in products and services focused on the theme of Fintech innovation. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
ARKF is an actively managed fund of stocks related to financial technology innovation.

The fund invests in domestic and foreign equity securities of companies (of any market-cap) within this theme. Some examples of such applications are transaction innovations, blockchain technology, risk transformation, frictionless funding platforms, customer facing platforms, and new intermediaries.

name: ProShares Russell US Dividend Growers ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle is designed to track an index focused on companies within the Russell 3000 Index distinguished by exceptionally long histories of dividend growth, specifically requiring at least 35 consecutive years of increased annual dividend payments and meeting certain liquidity standards. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in securities mirroring the index or similar instruments, it targets a minimum of 40 qualifying stocks, although companies with slightly shorter dividend growth records may be included if necessary to meet this target. A distinctive characteristic is its equal-weighting methodology applied to the selected holdings, which differentiates its composition and sector exposures from traditional dividend strategies; this is further managed by a 30% cap on individual sector weights, reviewed quarterly, with the index reconstituted annually.
description_original: The index, constructed and maintained by FTSE International Limited, targets companies that are currently members of the Russell 3000 Index, have increased dividend payments each year for at least 35 years, and meet certain liquidity requirements. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities.
description_etfcom:
TMDV tracks an equal-weighted index of Russell 3000 constituents that have increased dividend payments annually for at least 35 years.

TMDV builds on ProShares lineup of dividend growers ETFs by providing a total market approach. The fund tracks an index that selects minimum of 40 stocks only from the Russell 3000 Index that have increased their dividends for at least 35 consecutive years, then equal-weights those holdings. If there are fewer than 40 stocks meeting the criteria, the index will include companies with shorter dividend growth histories. Equal-weighting causes the fund to deviate from overweighting traditional dividend-paying sectors. A cap of 30% is placed on each sector. If at a quarterly rebalance, a sector cap is breached, companies in the applicable sector are removed beginning with the lowest yield. The index is reconstituted annually during the June rebalance.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the Russell 3000 Index that have consistently increased dividends each year for at least the last 35 years. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the Russell 3000® Dividend Elite Index (the "index"). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the Russell 3000 Index that have consistently increased dividends each year for at least the last 35 years. name: Simplify Volt Fintech Disruption ETF

name: First Trust California Municipal High Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily seeks to provide current income exempt from both federal and California state income taxes, with long-term capital appreciation as a secondary objective. To achieve this, it invests at least 80% of its assets in municipal debt securities, predominantly from California issuers, that pay interest exempt from these taxes. The fund employs a flexible strategy, holding bonds across various maturities (maintaining a weighted average maturity under 14 years) and credit ratings, including investment-grade and high-yield securities. Notably, it can allocate up to 50% of its assets to non-investment grade (high-yield or "junk") bonds, reflecting a significant tolerance for credit risk to potentially enhance income, targeting California investors seeking tax-advantaged income through active management in the state's municipal bond market.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objectives by investing at least 80% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in municipal debt securities that pay interest that is exempt from regular federal income taxes and California income taxes. It will invest no more than 50% of its net assets in Municipal Securities that are, at the time of investment, not investment grade, commonly referred to as "high yield" or "junk" bonds.
description_etfcom:
FCAL is an actively managed fund that targets fixed income securities of various maturities and credit ratings, with interest income that is exempted from federal and California state income tax.

FCAL utilizes an active approach to a niche pocket of the municipal bond space. The fund targets municipal securities with interest income that is exempted from federal and California state income tax. The fund generally will hold muni bonds issued by the state of California and its political subdivisions. FCAL has a long leash, it can hold investment-grade, high-yield, and distressed securities. The fund will keep its weighted average maturity under 14 years. Overall, FCAL might appeal to investors in California who are looking for tax-exempted income and are willing to pay a premium for active management.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide current income that is exempt from regular federal income taxes and California income taxes, and its secondary objective is long-term capital appreciation. name: Defiance Daily Target 2X Long Uranium ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified exchange-traded fund aims to deliver two times (200%) the daily percentage change of the Global X Uranium ETF (URA), before accounting for fees and expenses. It utilizes swap agreements based on the URA, thereby providing leveraged exposure to companies engaged in uranium mining, production, and related nuclear component activities tracked by the underlying ETF. The fund rebalances its portfolio daily to maintain the target 200% leverage. Conceived as a high-risk, short-term tactical instrument, its returns over periods exceeding a single day can significantly diverge from the 2x objective due to the effects of daily compounding. Collateral for its swap agreements may include T-bills, money market funds, and short-term debt. Trading for this security is set to conclude after April 16, 2025, following its delisting.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that attempts to achieve two times (200%) the daily percentage change in the share price of the underlying security by entering into swap agreements on the underlying security. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
URAX seeks to provide 2x leveraged exposure to the daily share price movement of the Global X Uranium ETF (URA), less fees and expenses.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 16, 2025. URAX uses swap agreements to make bullish bets on (URA) Global X Uranium ETFs share price. URA tracks a market cap-weighted index that focuses on pure-play companies engaged in the production and mining of nuclear components. The fund maintains a daily leveraged exposure equivalent to 200% of the funds net assets through daily rebalancing. As a geared product, the fund is intended as a short-term tactical tool, rather than as a long-term investment vehicle. As a result, returns may deviate from the expected 2x if held for longer than a single day due to compounding. This strategy is high-risk and does not include a defensive position as part of its overall process. Additionally, the fund could potentially lose money over time, even if URA's performance strengthens. The fund is expected to invest in T-bills, money market funds, short-term bond ETFs, and corporate debts as collateral.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of two times (200%) the daily percentage change in the share price of the Global X Uranium ETF. The fund is an actively managed ETF that attempts to achieve two times (200%) the daily percentage change in the share price of the underlying security by entering into swap agreements on the underlying security. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Principal Quality ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital growth by primarily investing in U.S. equity securities. Employing a proprietary quantitative model, it selects large- and mid-cap companies from the S&P 500 and S&P 400 indices perceived to exhibit higher quality, growth potential, and pricing power. Quality assessments consider factors like profitability, earnings quality, balance sheet strength, and solvency, while pricing power measures a company's ability to increase prices without reducing demand. The resulting portfolio encompasses both growth and value styles and is typically rebalanced annually, although the manager retains discretion for adjustments.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund primarily invests in equity securities. For security selection and portfolio construction, Principal Global Investors, LLC (“PGI”) uses a proprietary quantitative model designed to identify equity securities in the S&P 500 Index or S&P 400 Index that exhibit higher quality, growth potential, and pricing power. The fund invested significantly in one or more industries within the healthcare sector.
description_etfcom:
PSET utilizes a proprietary quantitative model to actively invest in large- and mid-cap companies that are perceived to exhibit higher quality, growth potential, and pricing power.

PSET actively invests in equity securities in the S&P 500 Index or S&P 400 that they believe exhibit higher quality, growth potential, and pricing power. The fund manager uses a proprietary quantitative model to identify and select companies for inclusion. Higher quality is measured by a companys profitability, earnings quality, balance sheet strength, and solvency. Pricing power is the extent to which a company can raise the prices of its products without reducing the demand for them. The fund adviser uses internal and external resources to develop and refine its investment themes, and to identify and take advantage of trends that may impact the fund and its holdings. The fund is rebalanced annually, but may make any adjustments at its discretion. Prior to June 17, 2022, the fund tracked the NASDAQ US Price Setters Index. Prior to Sep. 30, 2020, the fund name was Principal Price Setters Index ETF.

name: PIMCO RAFI ESG U.S. ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to provide total return by tracking a rules-based index composed of U.S. large- and mid-cap equities, investing at least 80% of its assets in these components under normal circumstances. Its core strategy integrates fundamental analysis—considering factors like sales, cash flow, dividends/buybacks, and book value—with comprehensive ESG criteria. The index construction begins with fundamental weighting, then applies ESG screening, excluding companies with low rankings across specific signals (environment, social, governance, financial discipline, diversity) and those significantly involved in industries such as tobacco, gambling, weapons, and fossil fuels (including coal, tar sands, and oil shale). Final constituent weights are based on fundamental measures but adjusted to favor companies with stronger overall ESG profiles, aiming for performance distinct from traditional market-capitalization-weighted approaches through this combined methodology.
description_original: The Fund seeks to provide total return that closely corresponds, before fees and expenses, to the total return of the RAFI ESG US Index.
description_etfcom:
RAFE tracks an index of US companies that are selected and weighted by a combination of fundamental and ESG criteria.

RAFE aims to outperform market-cap-weighted indexes by integrating fundamental and ESG criteria. Selection begins with US large- and mid-cap equities ranked by a fundamental weight considering de-levered sales, cash flow, dividend plus buybacks over the past five years, and most recent book value. The stocks in the top 86% of cumulative fundamental weight are considered. An ESG score is calculated based on five signals: environment, social, governance, financial discipline, and diversity. Companies ranking in the bottom 10% by fundamental weight, for each respective signal are excluded from the index. In addition, companies having major involvement in tobacco, gambling, weapons civilian and military, fossil fuels, coal, tar sands, and oil shale are excluded. Selected companies are weighted by their fundamental weight and adjusted by respective overall ESG scores. The index is reconstituted annually in March and rebalanced on a quarterly staggered basis of 25%.
description_yahoo: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing under normal circumstances at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the RAFI ESG US Index. The underlying index is constructed by RAFI Indices, LLC using a rules-based approach within publicly traded U.S. equities to create an integrated ESG strategy which overweights companies that rate well across various ESG themes and excludes companies with a major involvement in industries such as tobacco, gaming, weapons and fossil fuels.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide total return that closely corresponds, before fees and expenses, to the total return of the RAFI ESG U.S. Index. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing under normal circumstances at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the RAFI ESG US Index. The underlying index is constructed by RAFI Indices, LLC using a rules-based approach within publicly traded U.S. equities to create an integrated ESG strategy which overweights companies that rate well across various ESG themes and excludes companies with a major involvement in industries such as tobacco, gaming, weapons and fossil fuels.

name: iShares ESG Advanced MSCI EAFE Index ETF
merged_description: This investment tracks a market-capitalization-weighted index composed of large- and mid-cap companies from developed markets, excluding the U.S. and Canada. Its core strategy focuses on companies demonstrating favorable environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics relative to their sector peers. The approach involves extensive screening, explicitly excluding firms involved in controversial business activities such as tobacco, weapons, gambling, nuclear power, and predatory lending, alongside a notable exclusion of the fossil fuel industry. Typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the underlying index components, the portfolio is reviewed quarterly for rebalancing and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to reflect the equity performance of large- and mid-capitalization developed market companies, excluding the U.S. and Canada, with favorable ESG ratings while applying extensive screens, including removing fossil fuel exposure. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DMXF tracks a market cap-weighted, ESG-screened index of large- and mid-cap stocks from the developed markets outside North America.

DMXF is designed to capture companies with favorable ESG ratings relative to their sector peers while avoiding those that are involved in controversial business activities. In constructing the portfolio, companies in the broad MSCI EAFE Index are rated based on their ESG risk and opportunities management, and controversies scores (0-10, 10 being the most desirable). Securities that have a BBB-rating or above and a score of 3 or above are selected for the portfolio. Companies excluded are those involved in adult entertainment, alcohol, gambling, tobacco, GMO, weapons, nuclear power, firearms, for-profit prisons, and predatory lending, based on revenue thresholds. Companies in the energy sector and industry tied to fossil fuel are also screened out. The index is market-cap weighted with quarterly review for rebalance.
description_yahoo: The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index that is designed to reflect the equity performance of large- and mid-capitalization developed market companies, excluding the U.S. and Canada. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investments results of the MSCI EAFE Choice ESG Screened Index. The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index that is designed to reflect the equity performance of large- and mid-capitalization developed market companies, excluding the U.S. and Canada. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index.

name: Simplify Propel Opportunities ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund pursues long-term capital growth through an opportunistic, multi-asset strategy, concentrating significantly (over 25% of net assets) in the biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, healthcare technology, and life science tools and services industries. Reflecting its non-diversified approach, the fund invests across various equity and fixed-income securities, including common and preferred stocks, convertible bonds, corporate notes and bonds, structured notes, and related ETFs, often focusing on small- and mid-cap companies. Investment decisions are guided by evaluating an issuer's scientific proposition, the likelihood of product success, and profit potential, with notable flexibility regarding currency, country, issuer size, or debt characteristics. The strategy may also incorporate derivatives (up to 20% of assets) for leverage or hedging purposes.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund. The Sub-Adviser concentrates the fund's investments (i.e., invests more than 25% of its net assets) in the securities of issuers in the biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, healthcare technology, and life science tools and services industries. The Sub-Adviser employs an actively managed opportunistic multi-asset strategy that focuses on common stock, preferred stock, convertible bonds, structured notes, corporate notes and bonds, and ETFs that primarily invest in the preceding security types. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SURI actively manages a multi-asset strategy by investing in equity and fixed income securities of companies in the biotech, pharmaceuticals, healthcare technology, and life science tools and services industries. Investments include common and preferred stocks, convertible bonds, structured notes, corporate notes and bonds, and ETFs. There are no restrictions as to the currency, issuer capitalization, or country for equities, and debt credit quality, maturity, structure, or issuer type for debt securities. The management team identifies attractive investment opportunities by evaluating the scientific proposition of the issuer, the probability that the science will lead to a product or treatment, and projected profits from each successful product or treatment. The fund typically includes small- and mid-caps. SURI may invest up to 20% in derivatives to leverage exposure and partially hedge against market declines. It holds cash and cash-like instruments as collateral.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term growth of capital. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund. The Sub-Adviser concentrates the fund's investments (i.e., invests more than 25% of its net assets) in the securities of issuers in the biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, healthcare technology, and life science tools and services industries. The Sub-Adviser employs an actively managed opportunistic multi-asset strategy that focuses on common stock, preferred stock, convertible bonds, structured notes, corporate notes and bonds, and ETFs that primarily invest in the preceding security types. The fund is non-diversified.

name: AdvisorShares Vice ETF
merged_description: Operating contrary to popular ESG themes, this actively managed ETF seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in companies associated with "vice" activities. Under normal market conditions, the fund allocates at least 80% of its net assets into primarily U.S. exchange-listed equity securities, including common stock, preferred stock, and ADRs. Eligible companies must derive at least 50% of their net revenue from specific industries: tobacco and alcoholic beverages, the broader food and beverage sector, or gaming-related businesses such as casinos, sports betting, lottery services, and associated technology. While the active manager possesses broad discretion in security selection, the fund maintains a mandate to invest at least 25% of its assets in the consumer staples sector.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in securities of (i) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from tobacco and alcoholic beverages, (ii) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from the food and beverage industry, and (iii) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from gaming activities. It invests primarily in U.S. exchange listed equity securities, including common and preferred stock and ADRs.
description_etfcom: VICE is managed contrary to popular ESG themes, the fund focuses solely on vice activitiesit invests in US-listed companies that generate at least 50% of their revenue from alcohol or tobacco, food and beverage, or gaming-related businesses. Gaming-related businesses include casinos, sports betting (including esports and racetracks), lottery services, gaming technology and equipment. VICE can invest across the industry spectrum but is mandated to keep at least 25% of its investments in the consumer staples sector. Other than this, the funds active manager has broad discretion in which companies to select. Prior to Nov. 1, 2020, the fund traded under the ticker ACT and focused on alcohol, cannabis, and tobacco related-stocks.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in securities of (i) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from tobacco and alcoholic beverages, (ii) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from the food and beverage industry, and (iii) companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from gaming activities. It invests primarily in U.S. exchange listed equity securities, including common and preferred stock and ADRs.

name: iShares Interest Rate Hedged Long-Term Corporate Bond ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides exposure to long-term, U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade corporate bonds, while simultaneously seeking to minimize the interest rate risk typically associated with such assets.
