The underlying index is composed of the equity securities of the 50 largest companies by market capitalization that derive the most revenue from an Emerging and Frontier Market and classified as in the consumer or technology sector.
description_etfcom:
KEMQ tracks a committee-selected, tier-weighted index of 50 emerging market technology companies.

KEMQ provides concentrated exposure to emerging market tech companies as determined by index committee. The fund starts with a pool of companies classified under RBICS tech categories such as internet retail, internet software/services, payment processing, and E-commerce software. Eligible companies are then screened for size and liquidity measures. Of the remaining securities, the top 50 companies by market-cap are included, with the largest 10 securities each having 3.5% weight, the next 20 getting 2.5% each, and the bottom 20 receiving 0.75% each. The index constituents are adjusted quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that track the price and yield performance of the Solactive Emerging Market Consumer Technology Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of the equity securities of the 50 largest companies by market capitalization that derive the most revenue from an Emerging and Frontier Market and classified as in the consumer or technology sector.

name: Fidelity Crypto Industry and Digital Payments ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to mirror the performance of a global index comprising companies involved in cryptocurrency, blockchain technology, and digital payments processing. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the equity securities and depositary receipts of firms within this index, selecting those that derive at least 50% of their revenue from these relevant activities, such as crypto mining, related financial services, blockchain development, or digital payment facilitation. Crucially, the fund provides this exposure without directly or indirectly investing in cryptocurrencies. Its portfolio composition targets at least 60% allocation to crypto and blockchain-related stocks, with the remainder in digital payment companies, weighted based on average daily trading volume and rebalanced quarterly. The fund operates on a non-diversified basis.
description_original: The fund ormally invests at least 80% of assets in equity securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies engaged in activities related to cryptocurrency, related blockchain technology, and digital payments processing. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FDIG tracks an index of global companies related to cryptocurrency, blockchain technology, and digital payments processing, selected based on revenue derived from the relevant themes, and weighted by average daily trading volume.

FDIG seeks to track an index of global equities engaged in the crypto and digital payments processing industries. The crypto stocks eligible for inclusion are those that relate to crypto miners, provide financial services to support cryptos issued on a blockchain, and other blockchain technologies. The fund does not directly or indirectly invest in any digital asset. The digital payment stocks are those that facilitate payment activities through processes and protocols. Companies included must derive at least 50% of their revenue from the relevant themes. At least 60% of the fund will be made up of crypto stocks, while the remainder of the fund will be made up of 20 digital payment stocks. Weightings are based on average daily trading volume. Rebalancing occurs quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in equity securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies engaged in activities related to cryptocurrency, related blockchain technology, and digital payments processing. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity Crypto Industry and Digital Payments IndexSM. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in equity securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies engaged in activities related to cryptocurrency, related blockchain technology, and digital payments processing. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Dow Jones Select MicroCap Index Fund
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to mirror the performance of an index targeting U.S. stocks within the bottom two market-capitalization deciles, typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's constituent securities. The core concept emphasizes selecting micro-cap companies that exhibit comparatively strong fundamentals and higher liquidity relative to the broader micro-cap segment, employing screens for financial strength. While focusing on micro-caps, this selective quality and liquidity approach may result in the fund holding companies closer to the small-cap space. The underlying market-cap weighted index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly, a process which could introduce sector biases.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks of U.S. micro-capitalization companies which are publicly traded in the United States. The index is designed to measure the performance of micro-cap stocks issued by U.S. companies that are comparatively liquid and have strong fundamentals relative to the micro-cap segment as a whole.
description_etfcom:
FDM tracks an index of U.S.-listed stocks in the bottom two market-cap deciles. Only stocks that meet fundamental and liquidity thresholds are included in the index.

FDM calls itself a micro-cap fund, and for the most part it is, but the fund leans hard toward the small-cap space. FDM's underlying index is market-cap weighted and screens for financial strength, looking at metrics like trailing P/E and P/B. Sector biases result, investors should verify sector weightings. The index and fund are reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. FDM captures a segment that is difficult to reach and uses a full replication index strategy. Comparatively, these aspects tend to increase management expenses.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of micro-cap stocks issued by U.S. companies that are comparatively liquid and have strong fundamentals relative to the micro-cap segment as a whole.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Dow Jones Select MicroCap Index SM. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of micro-cap stocks issued by U.S. companies that are comparatively liquid and have strong fundamentals relative to the micro-cap segment as a whole.

name: WisdomTree Emerging Markets ESG Fund
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily invests in emerging market equity securities, utilizing a model-based, quantitative approach. Its strategy focuses on selecting companies demonstrating potential for positive returns based on a combination of fundamental factors, such as value and quality, and technical factors, like momentum and correlation. Integral to its selection process is the incorporation of favorable environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. Portfolio holdings are weighted using a modified market-capitalization methodology that favors constituents with larger market caps and higher sustainability scores. The fund is classified as non-diversified. It is important to note that this fund is scheduled to close, with January 26, 2024, anticipated as its final trading day.
description_original: The fund is actively managed using a model-based approach. It seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in equity securities of issuers in emerging markets that exhibit certain characteristics that the fund's investment adviser believes to be indicative of positive future returns as well as incorporating favorable environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") characteristics based on a model developed by the adviser. The adviser employs a quantitative model to identify which securities the fund might purchase and sell and opportune times for purchases and sales. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
RESE is actively managed to invest in emerging market equities selected for various factors and ESG characteristics.

The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 26, 2024. RESE uses active management with a multi-factor approach to create its portfolio of emerging market stocks. The fund uses both fundamental and technical factors, such as value, quality, momentum and correlation. RESE also utilizes an ESG screen based on a composite sustainability score that is calculated by an independent third party ESG research. Holdings are weighted on a modified market-cap basis, giving heavier weight to constituents with higher market-cap and positive sustainability scores. Note: Prior to March 16, 2020, the fund traded as DVEM, held dividend-paying stocks and tracked the WisdomTree Emerging Markets Dividend Index.
description_yahoo: The fund is actively managed using a model-based approach. It seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in equity securities of companies that exhibit the highest potential for returns based on proprietary measures of fundamental factors (e.g., value and quality) and technical factors (e.g., momentum and correlation), as well as favorable environmental, social, and governance (“ESG”) characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree Cybersecurity Fund
merged_description: This investment fund tracks an index focused on cybersecurity and security-oriented technology companies listed on developed market exchanges. Eligible constituents are primarily involved in the cybersecurity theme, deriving at least 50% of their revenue from related activities, and must demonstrate significant revenue growth over the trailing three years. A key feature is its unique weighting methodology, which scores companies based on both their degree of cybersecurity focus and their revenue growth rate, systematically overweighting firms that score highly on both metrics. Consequently, the fund offers concentrated exposure to the cybersecurity sector, is non-diversified, and its underlying index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in cybersecurity and security-oriented technology that generate a meaningful part of their revenue from cybersecurity activities and are experiencing revenue growth. To the extent the index concentrates in the securities of a particular industry or group of industries, the fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
WCBR tracks an index of developed market companies primarily involved in cybersecurity and security-oriented technology.

WCBR tracks an index of companies primarily involved in cybersecurity and security-oriented technology, listed in developed markets. Eligibility starts by selecting at least 25 companies who derive at least 50% of their revenue from the cybersecurity theme, and also exhibit growth greater than 7% over the trailing three years (5% for old constituents). The index then weights these companies by assigning two scores to each stock: Focus Scores are based on the degree of involvement in the cybersecurity theme and Revenue Growth Scores are based on annual revenue growth over the trailing three years. Companies who receive high scores on both metrics are overweighted, while companies who receive low scores on both metrics are assigned a underweighted. All others are assigned a 1x weight. The Index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance of the WisdomTree Team8 Cybersecurity Index. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in cybersecurity and security-oriented technology that generate a meaningful part of their revenue from cybersecurity activities and are experiencing revenue growth. To the extent the index concentrates in the securities of a particular industry or group of industries, the fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. It is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity Sustainable Low Duration Bond ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to provide a high level of current income consistent with capital preservation by primarily investing in global short-term bonds demonstrating positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It commits at least 80% of its assets to investment-grade debt securities and associated repurchase agreements, selected through a process combining traditional credit analysis with a proprietary, data-driven ESG framework. This ESG assessment evaluates issuer sustainability practices, considers alignment with UN Sustainable Development Goals, and recognizes green or sustainable bond designations. While diversifying across different market sectors and maturities, the fund specifically targets a portfolio duration of one year or less and maintains a dollar-weighted average maturity of no more than two years.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in investment-grade debt securities (those of medium and high quality) of all types that the Adviser believes have positive environmental, social and governance (ESG) benefits and repurchase agreements for those securities. The advisor normally maintains a dollar-weighted average maturity of two years or less. The fund allocates assets across different market sectors and maturities.
description_etfcom:
FSLD is actively managed to provide exposure to a variety of global short-term bonds perceived to have positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics. The fund invests at least 80% in investment-grade bonds.

FSLD aims for a high level of current income by actively targeting various types of short-term global bonds with perceived ESG benefits and repurchase agreements. The fund selects bonds using both traditional credit analysis and ESG screens, with at least 80% of assets invested in investment-grade bonds. The fund employs a proprietary ESG ratings process that uses a data-driven framework that considers the issuers sustainability practices, underlying pool of assets, and any third-party designations as green, sustainable or sustainability-linked bonds. The advisor also considers an issuers alignment to the UN Sustainable Development Goals to gauge tangible environmental or social impact. Other considerations include credit quality, security-specific features, current and potential future valuation, and trading opportunities. FSLD intends to maintain duration of one year or less and a dollar-weighted average maturity of no more than two years.
description_yahoo: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in investment-grade debt securities (those of medium and high quality) of all types that the Adviser believes have positive environmental, social and governance (ESG) characteristics and repurchase agreements for those securities. The advisor normally maintains a dollar-weighted average maturity of two years or less. The fund allocates assets across different market sectors and maturities.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to obtain a high level of current income consistent with preservation of capital. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in investment-grade debt securities (those of medium and high quality) of all types that the Adviser believes have positive environmental, social and governance (ESG) characteristics and repurchase agreements for those securities. The advisor normally maintains a dollar-weighted average maturity of two years or less. The fund allocates assets across different market sectors and maturities.

name: iShares S&P Small-Cap 600 Value ETF
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to U.S. small-capitalization companies considered to possess strong value characteristics. It aims to track an index that selects these value-oriented stocks from a broader small-cap universe based on three specific fundamental metrics: book value-to-price, earnings-to-price, and sales-to-price ratios. To achieve its objective, the fund primarily invests, committing at least 80% of its assets, in the securities comprising its target index or investments with substantially similar economic characteristics. The remaining assets, up to 20%, may be held in cash, cash equivalents, or utilized for certain futures, options, and swap contracts. The index methodology includes an annual rebalancing.
description_original: The index measures the performance of the small-capitalization value sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
IJS tracks an index of small-cap US stocks. The index uses three factors to select value firms from the S&P 600.

IJS provides exposure to the US small cap companies that are considered undervalued by the market relative to other companies. The Underlying Index selects value stocks from the S&P SmallCap 600 with the strongest fundamental characteristics that includes, book value to price ratio, earnings to price ratio and sales to price ratio. The underlying index undergoes annual rebalance once every December.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underling index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P SmallCap 600 Value IndexTM composed of small-capitalization U.S. equities that exhibit value characteristics. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underling index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.

name: Direxion Daily Cloud Computing Bull 2X Shares
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides 2x leveraged exposure, resetting daily, to the Indxx USA Cloud Computing Index. Its objective is to achieve 200% of the index's daily performance by investing primarily (at least 80% of assets) in financial instruments like swap agreements, index securities, and related ETFs. The underlying index tracks US-listed companies, including those represented by American Depositary Receipts (ADRs), that derive significant revenue from cloud computing infrastructure, platforms, or services—encompassing software-as-a-service, platform-as-a-service, infrastructure-as-a-service, and related hardware distribution. As a non-diversified fund with daily rebalancing, it is intended for short-term tactical use, as compounding effects can cause its long-term returns to differ significantly from twice the underlying index's cumulative performance.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index is provided by Indxx, LLC and includes domestic companies that deliver cloud computing infrastructure, platforms, or services. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CLDL provides 2x leveraged daily exposure to a market-cap-weighted US equity index of companies involved in the cloud computing industry.

CLDL seeks to deliver 200% of the daily performance of the Indxx USA Cloud Computing Index. The index includes US-listed firms that allow dynamic scaling by offering on-demand computing services such as servers, storage, network, and operating systems over the internet. Companies must derive majority of their revenues from activities related to cloud computing infrastructure, platforms and services. These companies license and deliver software over the internet by subscription, provide a platform to create software and virtualized computing via internet, make or distribute related hardware, and also offer shared resources services like shared storage, servers, and storage pools. Index constituents are capped at 5% each and undergoes annual rebalance and reconstitution. CLDL isnt designed for long-term investors as the fund rebalances daily. As a result, compounding and path dependency make its long-term returns difficult to predict when compared with its underlying index.
description_yahoo: The index is provided by Indxx, LLC and includes common stock and American depositary receipts of companies that deliver cloud computing infrastructure, platforms, or services. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 200% of the daily performance of the Indxx USA Cloud Computing Index. The index is provided by Indxx, LLC and includes common stock and American depositary receipts of companies that deliver cloud computing infrastructure, platforms, or services. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.

name: First Trust S-Network Global E-Commerce ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to mirror the performance of an index focused on the global e-commerce industry, investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's component securities, including common stocks and depository receipts from companies listed on major global exchanges. The underlying index targets companies primarily operating within four distinct business segments: content navigation, online retail, online marketplaces, and e-commerce infrastructure. It uniquely selects the top 15 largest companies by market capitalization from each of these segments and applies an equal weighting methodology across all chosen firms. This non-diversified portfolio is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets in the common stocks and depository receipts that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies with securities listed on recognized global securities exchanges that are engaged in the global e-commerce industry. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ISHP invests in the largest stocks, by market capitalization, of the global e-commerce industry. The index includes companies primarily engaged in the following business segments: (1) content navigation, (2) online retail, (3) online marketplace, and (4) e-commerce infrastructure. Content navigation companies derive their revenues from advertisers paying to use the search results, social media feeds, email systems, banner ads, etc. to efficiently target their ads. The index ranks the companies in each segment by market-cap. Then, the top 15 companies from each of the four business segments are selected and equally weighted. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. Prior to Jan. 26, 2022, the fund name was First Trust Nasdaq Retail ETF (Ticker: FTXD). It followed the Nasdaq US Smart Retail Index, which selected US securities by liquidity and weighted them using multiple factors.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies with securities listed on major global recognized exchanges that are engaged in the global e-commerce industry. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund’s fees and expenses) of an equity index called the S-Network Global E-Commerce Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies with securities listed on major global recognized exchanges that are engaged in the global e-commerce industry. It is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree Emerging Markets ex-State-Owned Enterprises Fund
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provides exposure to emerging market equities by specifically excluding state-owned enterprises (SOEs), operating on the premise that private companies may be managed more effectively. It defines an SOE as a company with over 20% government ownership. The fund seeks to track the performance of a modified float-adjusted market-capitalization-weighted index, normally investing at least 80% of its assets in constituent securities or economically similar investments. This underlying index starts with emerging market companies meeting liquidity and market cap screens, removes the identified SOEs, and then weights the remaining securities by market capitalization, subject to certain adjustments, with constituents rebalanced annually.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of common stocks in emerging markets, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: XSOE is designed around the premise that private corporations run more effectively than those controlled by the government. The fund aims to provide broad emerging market exposure, excluding state-owned enterprises (SOEs) that tend to dominate the financial and energy sectors in most emerging market economies. The fund defines an SOE as one with more than 20% government ownership. The selection universe starts with the emerging market companies from across various sectors that meet its market cap, liquidity, and tradability screens. From this, the fund removes all state-owned enterprises (SOEs) and all remained securities are then weighted by market capitalization, subject to adjustments relative to country and sector weights prior to the removal of SOEs. The index constituents rebalance annually.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of common stocks in emerging markets, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree Emerging Markets ex-State-Owned Enterprises Index (the "index"). Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of common stocks in emerging markets, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.

name: AAM S&P 500 High Dividend Value ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund tracks a rules-based index derived from the S&P 500, focusing on companies demonstrating both high dividend yield and high free-cash-flow yield, indicative of sustainable distributions. The index construction screens S&P 500 constituents based on these fundamental yield factors, removes outliers, and scores the remaining securities. To ensure diversified sector exposure, it selects the top five scoring companies from each economic sector and applies an equal weighting across all chosen constituents. This sector-constrained, equal-weighting approach may help mitigate value traps but could lead to underweights in larger sectors and overweights in smaller ones compared to the broader market. The index reconstitutes semi-annually, and the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in S&P 500 equities that have paid a dividend within the past year.
description_original: The index is a rules-based, equal-weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to the constituents of the S&P 500® Index that exhibit both high dividend yield and sustainable dividend distribution characteristics, while maintaining diversified sector exposure. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in equity securities that (i) are included in the S&P 500 Index and (ii) have had a positive indicated annual dividend yield within the past year.
description_etfcom: SPDV follows an index of US companies that screens for fundamental factors. Index construction begins by selecting companies from the S&P500 index with high, positive dividend and free-cash-flow yields. Outliers are removed from the selection pool. Using a statistical normalization model, each security is scored based on its dividend and free-cash-flow yields. The top five constituents are selected from each sector and weighted equally. Diversifying the portfolio across economic sectors in this manner should help avoid value traps, though it also means that SPDV will underweight the largest sectors while overweighting the smallest. The index is reconstituted semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P 500 Dividend and Free Cash Flow Yield Index. The index is a rules-based, equal-weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to the constituents of the S&P 500® Index that exhibit both high dividend yield and sustainable dividend distribution characteristics, while maintaining diversified sector exposure. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in equity securities that (i) are included in the S&P 500 Index and (ii) have had a positive indicated annual dividend yield within the past year.

name: First Trust Expanded Technology ETF
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing at least 80% of its assets in the common stocks of US large-cap companies whose businesses are principally derived from or dependent upon technology. It provides an "expanded technology" exposure, holding not only traditional information technology companies but also tech-reliant firms classified within sectors like communication services and consumer discretionary. The portfolio typically consists of around 50 companies selected using a quantitative model assessing factors such as return on equity, momentum, and free cash flow growth. Holdings are generally market-cap weighted within specific constraints and the portfolio is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. The fund concentrates its investments (over 25% of assets) in the information technology sector group and is considered non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the common stocks of companies identified by it’s investment advisor as either information technology companies or consumer discretionary and communication services companies whose operations are principally derived from and/or dependent upon technology (such companies are collectively referred to herein as “Expanded Technology Companies”). The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in the industries or group of industries comprising the information technology sector. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
XPND actively invests in US stocks whose businesses are derived from or dependent on technology.

XPND aims to provide an expanded tech exposure in the US large-cap segment. Aside from holding conventional technology stocks, the fund may also include tech-dependent companies that are classified as communication services or consumer discretionary (particularly internet & direct marketing retail) under GICS. XPND holds approximately 50 companies that are selected using a quantitative model, which considers factors such as return on equity, momentum and free cash flow growth. The resulting portfolio is generally market-cap-weighted with weights typically ranging from 0.25% to 4.50%. Since XPND is actively managed, the fund adviser has the discretion to adjust portfolio weights and exclude certain securities. The portfolio is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the common stocks of companies identified by it’s investment advisor as either information technology companies or financial companies and communication services companies whose operations are principally derived from and/or dependent upon technology ( “Expanded Technology Companies” ). The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in the industries or group of industries comprising the information technology sector. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the common stocks of companies identified by it’s investment advisor as either information technology companies or financial companies and communication services companies whose operations are principally derived from and/or dependent upon technology ( “Expanded Technology Companies” ). The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in the industries or group of industries comprising the information technology sector. It is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard High Dividend Yield Index Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle employs a passive indexing strategy designed to track the performance of the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index. It focuses on building a diversified portfolio of US common stocks characterized by high dividend yields, specifically selecting companies ranking in the top half based on forecasted dividends over the next 12 months. Notably, REITs are excluded from the selection process, contributing to a more conservative profile. The fund aims for full replication by holding constituent stocks weighted by market capitalization, rather than dividend size, in proportions closely mirroring the index, thereby offering broad exposure to dividend-paying companies.
description_original: The manager employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that pay dividends that generally are higher than average. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of the fund's assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_etfcom:
VYM tracks the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index. The index selects high-dividend-paying US companies, excluding REITS, and weights them by market cap.

VYM offers a diversified, conservative approach to high dividend yield in a low-cost wrapper. The fund`s broad basket stems partly from its comparatively lax dividend screens: Firms are ranked by forecast dividends over the next 12 months, those in the top half are selected. Stocks that make the cut are weighted by market cap rather than dividends, an approach also used by our benchmark. As a result, the broad portfolio aligns well with our benchmark by firm size, yield, and sector exposure. REITs are out of bounds too, in keeping with the conservative approach. The fund is a possible choice for those looking for broad dividend focus.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index that measures the investment return of common stocks of companies that are characterized by high dividend yield. The manager employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that pay dividends that generally are higher than average. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of the fund's assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.

name: KraneShares MSCI One Belt One Road Index ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle focuses on capturing the performance of companies expected to benefit from China's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, particularly those involved in related infrastructure development connecting China with Eurasian countries. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in securities mirroring its underlying index, which tracks global listed companies demonstrating high revenue exposure to this initiative. The portfolio construction employs market-capitalization principles but maintains a distinct geographical allocation, targeting approximately 45% exposure to Chinese companies and 55% to non-Chinese companies, with individual country weights outside of China capped at 10%.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the equity market performance of listed companies with high revenue exposure to the Chinese government's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, as determined by the provider of the underlying index.
description_etfcom:
OBOR tracks a market-cap-selected, tier-weighted index of companies likely to benefit from China's One Belt, One Road initiative.

OBOR targets companies likely to benefit from China`s One Belt, One Road initiative, which is a framework adopted by the Chinese government to emphasize cooperation and connection between China and other Eurasian countries. More specifically, the fund`s underlying index targets companies that stand to profit from China`s infrastructure spending. The portfolio allocates 45% of its weight to Chinese companies and 55% to non-Chinese companies. Within each category, individual constituents are market-cap weighted, with individual countries (other than China) capped at 10%.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance of the MSCI Global China Infrastructure Exposure Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the equity market performance of listed companies with high revenue exposure to the Chinese government's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, as determined by the provider of the underlying index.

name: WisdomTree Battery Value Chain and Innovation Fund
merged_description: This passively managed fund aims to track the performance of an index focused on the global Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (BESS) value chain and associated innovation themes. It provides exposure to global equity securities of companies significantly involved in this area, requiring at least 50% revenue derivation from relevant activities. The underlying index methodology spans the entire value chain—encompassing raw materials, manufacturing, enabling components, and emerging technologies—and also includes companies introducing or servicing innovative technologies. Securities are selected and ranked based on their involvement intensity in the value chain combined with a risk score assessing quality and momentum factors. The portfolio construction initially weights the core value chain segments equally, then weights individual holdings by an adjusted intensity rating, subject to an issuer cap, with semi-annual rebalancing and reconstitution. As a result of its targeted investment approach, the fund is concentrated and non-diversified.
description_original: The adviser employs a “passive management” investment approach designed to track the performance of the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in the investment themes of Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (“BESS”) and Innovation. The fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: WBAT is passively managed to provide exposure to the global battery & energy storage solutions value chain. The index divides the value chain into four segments: (i) raw materials, (ii) manufacturing, (iii) enablers or building block components, and (iv) emerging technologies. The selection universe also includes companies which introduce or service innovative technologies. Eligible companies must derive at least 50% revenue from any of the value chain segments or from innovation. To select securities, the index ranks companies based on an intensity rating that indicates a companys involvement in the battery & energy storage solutions value chain, and a composite risk score which combines quality and momentum factors. The four value chain segments are initially weighted equally in the portfolio. Securities within each segment are then weighted according to an adjusted intensity rating, subject to a 3.5% single issuer cap. The index reconstitutes and rebalances semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree Battery Value Chain and Innovation Index (“Index”). The adviser employs a “passive management” investment approach designed to track the performance of the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in the investment themes of Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (“BESS”) and Innovation. The fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Themes Cybersecurity ETF
merged_description: This passively managed exchange-traded fund provides concentrated exposure to the cybersecurity industry by tracking an index of relevant companies from developed markets. To qualify for inclusion, firms must derive a significant portion of their revenue, typically at least 50%, from digital security or cybersecurity operations. The portfolio focuses on approximately the top 35 eligible companies, weighted by market capitalization, resulting in a non-diversified investment. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising its underlying index, which may include American and Global Depositary Receipts (ADRs/GDRs), and reconstitutes its holdings on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The index is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the cybersecurity industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
SPAM seeks to track a concentrated index of stocks from developed markets that derive their revenues from digital security software. Stocks are weighted based on market capitalization.

SPAM is passively managed, providing targeted exposure to the largest companies, by market capitalization, in digital security software. In order to be considered for inclusion, a company must generate at least 50% of its revenue from the industry, define by RIBCS. All eligible securities are ranked and weighted by their market capitalization, selecting the top 35 names for inclusion in the index. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly bases in February, May, August, and November. Additionally, the fund may lend securities representing up to one-third of its total assets.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of Solactive Cyber Security Index. The index is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the cybersecurity industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard Industrials Index Fund Admiral Shares
merged_description: This investment vehicle employs a passive indexing strategy designed to mirror the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. It invests across large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies primarily operating within the industrials sector, as classified by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). Utilizing a full replication approach, the fund seeks to hold substantially all constituent securities in approximately the same weights as the underlying index. Notably, this fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_yahoo: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.

name: VictoryShares THB Mid Cap ESG ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks capital appreciation by investing primarily in a concentrated portfolio of approximately 30 mid-cap equity securities, defined as companies within the capitalization range of the Russell Mid Cap Index at the time of purchase. Utilizing a bottom-up, fundamental research approach, the strategy focuses on identifying high-quality U.S. companies believed to offer the highest potential adjusted return, calculated using proprietary quality assessments and risk measures. The quality evaluation considers management strength, financial health, industry positioning, and ESG ratings derived from a proprietary, industry-specific financial materiality framework. While predominantly holding common stocks, the fund allows for limited exposure (up to 10%) to foreign securities, including ADRs and GDRs; however, please note this security is being delisted, with its last day of trading scheduled for April 23, 2025.
description_original: The adviser pursues the fund’s investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of mid-cap companies. The adviser considers “mid-cap companies” to be companies with market capitalizations that, at the time of initial purchase, are within the capitalization range of companies comprising the Russell Mid Cap Index. Generally, the adviser expects the fund will hold approximately 30 securities. The equity securities in which the fund invests are primarily common stocks. In addition, the fund may invest in foreign securities, including ADRs and GDRs.
description_etfcom:
MDCP is an actively managed ETF that provides exposure to high-quality mid-cap US stocks with positive ESG ratings.

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 23, 2025. MDCP actively invests in mid-cap stocks using a bottom-up, fundamental research investment process. The portfolio comprises about 30 stocks believed to offer the highest adjusted return, which is calculated by applying a proprietary quality assessment and risk measures to each securitys pre-adjusted expected return. The quality assessment identifies high-quality companies based on their management, financial strength, industry position, and ESG rating. The ESG rating is derived using a proprietary methodology from an internal financial materiality map that considers how material various ESG factors are to a companys specific industry. The fund focuses on common stocks and expects to invest only 10% or less in foreign securities, ADRs, and GDRs. On February 1, 2024, the fund dropped ESG from its name. This change did not affect the funds investment strategy.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation. The adviser pursues the fund’s investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of mid-cap companies. The adviser considers “mid-cap companies” to be companies with market capitalizations that, at the time of initial purchase, are within the capitalization range of companies comprising the Russell Mid Cap Index. Generally, the adviser expects the fund will hold approximately 30 securities. The equity securities in which the fund invests are primarily common stocks. In addition, the fund may invest in foreign securities, including ADRs and GDRs.

name: iShares Global Comm Services ETF
merged_description: This fund offers focused exposure to the global communication services sector by tracking a market-capitalization-weighted index drawn from a broad universe of international stocks. It primarily invests (at least 80%) in the securities comprising its underlying index, which measures the performance of companies within this specific sector worldwide. To manage concentration, the index incorporates capping rules that limit the maximum weight of any single company and the aggregate weight of larger constituents. Despite these caps, the fund's targeted sector focus leads to a non-diversified classification, allowing for potentially significant single-stock impact within its specialized portfolio.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index is designed to measure the performance of global equities in the communication services sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IXP tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global communication services companies, drawn from 1,200 global stocks selected by S&P.

IXP delivers a market-cap weighted portfolio of global communication services stocks as defined by S&P. The well-established fund changed indexes on June 24, 2019 to a capped version which at quarterly rebalance limits single positions at 22.5% and caps aggregate positions over 4.5% at 45% total. Such index variants are not unusual and still allow for plenty of single-name impact. Moreover, stock selection resulting from the underlying industry classification system (GICS ) is likely a larger driver of returns. (Major changes in GICS communication sector occurred in Fall 2018.) The index pulls from a universe of 1,200 global stocks selected by S&P.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Global 1200 Communication Services 4.5/22.5/45 Capped IndexTM. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index is designed to measure the performance of global equities in the communication services sector. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily FTSE China Bull 3X Shares
merged_description: This investment product aims to provide three times (300%) the daily performance, before fees and expenses, of the FTSE China 50 Index by utilizing financial instruments such as swap agreements, index securities, and related ETFs for at least 80% of its assets. The underlying index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid Chinese companies listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, focusing specifically on these HK-traded large-caps while excluding A-shares and solely US-listed Chinese stocks, which can result in significant sector bets. As a non-diversified fund with daily leverage resets, compounding effects mean its performance over periods longer than one day can significantly differ from three times the index's cumulative return, making it an aggressive tool intended for short-term trading rather than a buy-and-hold investment.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, securities of the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies currently trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
YINN provides daily 3x leveraged exposure to a market-cap-weighted index of the 50 largest Chinese stocks traded in Hong Kong.

YINN is an aggressive daily bet on Chinese large-cap equities, delivering 3x leveraged exposure to about 50 large and liquid names traded in Hong Kong. The fund's underlying equity exposure doesn't aim for comprehensive all China exposure since it excludes A-shares traded on the mainland and names listed solely in the US. Given the underlying index, big sector bets can be expected. The fund rebalances its leveraged exposure daily, so over the long haul, compounding effects can lead to profound differences in expected returns relative to the index. Thus, it is not a buy-and-hold investment and should not be expected to provide index leverage returns greater than a one-day period. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies currently trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the FTSE China 50 Index. The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies currently trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity Metaverse ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to track the performance of an index comprising global companies significantly involved in establishing and enabling the Metaverse, considered the future state of the internet. Investing primarily in stocks and depositary receipts, the fund targets companies deriving substantial revenue (typically at least 50%) from relevant sectors such as computing hardware, digital infrastructure, design and engineering software, gaming technology, web development, content services, smartphones, and wearable technology. The underlying index employs quality screens and ranks constituents based on thematic relevance, including revenue significance and natural language processing scores, to select approximately 50 holdings. These holdings are weighted by market capitalization, subject to liquidity constraints and a 4.5% cap on individual securities, with the portfolio rebalanced quarterly. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities represented in the index and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products or services related to establishing and enabling the Metaverse. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FMET tracks a market cap-weighted index of equities that provides global exposure to the future state of the internet: the metaverse.

FMET holds stocks and depositary receipts of globally listed companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products related to the metaverse. Eligible companies must derive at least 50% of their revenue from (i) computing hardware, (ii) digital infrastructure, (iii) design & engineering software, (iv) gaming technology & software, (v) web development & content services, and (vi) smart phone & wearable technology. The index uses quality screens based on trailing or next 12-month revenues, operating cash flow, sales growth, and analyst coverage to filter out companies that pose significant risks. Then securities are ranked for thematic relevance, which is a composite of total significant revenue, percent of significant revenue, and a natural language processing (NLP) score. Approximately 50 stocks are selected and the portfolio is weighted according to market capitalization, subject to liquidity constraints and a 4.5% single weight capping. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity Metaverse IndexSM. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products or services related to establishing and enabling the Metaverse. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF
merged_description: This investment fund tracks an index comprised of U.S. stocks selected for their history of consistent dividend growth, aiming for sustainable increases over time. To qualify for inclusion, companies must demonstrate at least a five-year record of raising dividends while maintaining a payout ratio no higher than 75% of earnings. The underlying index, representing a subset of a broad U.S. market benchmark covering approximately 97% of domestic stock market capitalization, weights its holdings by dividend dollars. Adhering to a policy of investing at least 80% of its assets in securities that mirror its index, the fund offers exposure to dividend growth within a portfolio that largely resembles the broader market despite potential mild sector deviations.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar® US Market IndexSM, which is a diversified broad market index that represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks.
description_etfcom:
DGRO tracks an index of US stocks that are selected by dividends, dividend growth and payout ratio, then weighted by dividend dollars.

DGRO offers a straightforward execution of a dividend growth strategy. The fund aims to find stocks that pay steadily increasing dividends by requiring a 5-year track record of increasing dividends while ensuring that the firms pay out no more than 75% of earnings. Both factors in tandem aim for sustainable growth. While mild sector bets abound, overall the fund looks pretty marketlike. The US total market space is an active battleground for a crowded space, and DGRO is placed competitively within the segment.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar® U.S. Market IndexSM, which is a broad market index that represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Morningstar® U.S. Dividend Growth IndexSM. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar® U.S. Market IndexSM, which is a broad market index that represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks.

name: Nuveen Sustainable Core ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks favorable long-term total return by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of sustainable companies. It focuses on large-cap US companies ranking in the top 50% based on a proprietary ESG factor model, which emphasizes themes like energy transition and innovation, inclusive growth, and strong governance. The selection process combines quantitative models, fundamental research, third-party data, and discretionary judgment by the sub-adviser, acknowledging the subjective nature of sustainable investing and allowing for themes to be revised based on market conditions.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to pursue its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of sustainable companies.
description_etfcom: NSCR utilizes an ESG factor model to evaluate companies based on their adherence to specific ESG themes. The fund targets large-cap US companies ranking in the top 50% of this model, emphasizing themes such as energy transition and innovation, inclusive growth, and strong governance. The selection process integrates quantitative models, fundamental research, and discretionary judgment exercised by the sub-adviser. While the fund seeks to capitalize on attractive investment opportunities within its universe, it acknowledges the qualitative and subjective nature of sustainable investing. Therefore, there is no guarantee that every investment will perfectly align with designated themes or maintain its ranking within the ESG factor model over time. Sustainable company determination utilizes proprietary models, fundamental research, and third-party data. The sub-adviser has the discretion to revise or modify themes based on market conditions, relevance, and other factors.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks favorable long-term total return. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to pursue its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of sustainable companies.

name: First Trust Indxx Innovative Transaction & Process ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to global companies significantly involved in the blockchain ecosystem by tracking an index designed to capture their performance. It commits to investing at least 90% of its net assets in the common stocks and depositary receipts constituting this index. The selection methodology focuses specifically on companies identified through public information as either 'Active Enablers' (developing blockchain technology or services) or 'Active Users' (employing blockchain technology), deliberately excluding firms only in the exploratory phase. A distinctive feature is its weighting approach: the portfolio is equally divided between the 'Enabler' and 'User' categories, and components within each of these groups are also equally weighted. The underlying index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually to maintain its focus on active participants poised to benefit from blockchain's ongoing development and application.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of companies that are either actively using, investing in, developing, or have products that are poised to benefit from blockchain technology and/or the potential for increased efficiency that it provides to various business processes.
description_etfcom:
LEGR tracks an index of global equities selected based on their exposure to the development or usage of blockchain technology.

LEGR offers global exposure to firms with varying degrees of investment in blockchain technology. Various types of public information are used in this assessment including annual reports, press releases, industry reports, and news outlets. Based upon this research, firms are separated into three tiers of blockchain investment: Active Enablers, which are firms developing blockchain technology, products, or services, either for internal use or for sale, Active Users, firms using blockchain technology, generally supported by an Active Enabler, and Active Explorers, which are firms that have announced their intention to incorporate blockchain into their business, but without at least one active use case or test case. Active Enablers and Active Users are selected for inclusion in LEGR. Holdings are equally divided between Active Enablers and Active Users. Component securities within each grouping are equally weighted. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an index called the Indxx Blockchain Index (the "index"). The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of companies that are either actively using, investing in, developing, or have products that are poised to benefit from blockchain technology and/or the potential for increased efficiency that it provides to various business processes.

name: Nuveen Winslow Large-Cap Growth ESG ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by primarily investing in U.S. large-cap equity securities, targeting companies that exhibit both strong potential for above-average earnings growth and positive Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) characteristics relevant to long-term performance. Utilizing a fundamental, bottom-up approach potentially screening the Russell 1000 index, it incorporates quantitative growth metrics and qualitative ESG factors identified by independent research, while also applying exclusionary screens against sectors like nuclear weapons, civilian firearms, tobacco, and thermal coal. Under normal conditions, at least 80% of its net assets are invested in these large-cap equities, though it retains the flexibility to allocate up to 20% to non-U.S. equity securities. A distinctive feature is its non-transparent structure, which avoids daily holdings disclosure, instead publishing a proxy portfolio daily and revealing actual holdings monthly with a 30-day lag; the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund is actively managed and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of large-cap U.S. companies that exhibit ESG characteristics. It, under normal market conditions, invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets in exchange-traded equity securities of companies with large capitalizations at the time of purchase. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-U.S. equity securities listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange contemporaneously with the shares of the fund. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
NWLG is an actively managed, non-transparent fund with exposure to US large-cap stocks screened for both growth and positive ESG characteristics. The fund utilizes the Natixis/NYSE non-transparent model.

NWLG primarily invests in large-cap US companies exhibiting positive environmental, social and governance (ESG) factors that are relevant to their long-term financial performance. The fund specifically screens the Russell 1000 Index for both quantitative (focuses on companies potential for above-average future earnings growth) and qualitative (consists of various ESG factors, as determined by independent ESG research providers) measures through a fundamental, bottom-up approach. An exclusionary screen is also applied to remove companies engaged in the manufacturing and production of: nuclear weapons, civilian firearms, tobacco and thermal coal. The fund is actively managed and may have a non-US exposure of up to 20%. Unlike traditional ETFs, NWLGs non-transparent structure does not disclose its actual holdings daily and instead publishes a proxy portfolio on its website. Actual holdings will be disclosed on a monthly basis with a 30-day lag.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. The fund is actively managed and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of large-cap U.S. companies that exhibit ESG characteristics. It, under normal market conditions, invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets in exchange-traded equity securities of companies with large capitalizations at the time of purchase. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-U.S. equity securities listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange contemporaneously with the shares of the fund. It is non-diversified.

name: Pacer Military Times Best Employers ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of an index focused on companies recognized for their veteran-friendly employment practices. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the U.S.-listed stocks comprising this index, generally mirroring their proportional weights. Eligibility for the index requires companies to have been included on the "Best for Vets List" for the preceding three consecutive years, possess a minimum market capitalization of $200 million, and meet defined liquidity thresholds. The fund operates under a non-diversified strategy.

Constituent selection involves scoring companies based on their technology involvement, applying liquidity screens, and targeting approximately 200 stocks, often with a bias towards smaller capitalizations. The fund adheres to a policy of investing at least 80% of its assets in securities mirroring its underlying index, which is reconstituted and rebalanced annually.

description_etfcom:

Eligible stocks must be in the Morningstar Global Equity Index family. The selection and weighting of companies is done with a somewhat-opaque method, using fundamental research to score companies along a three-point scale based on exponential technology involvement while applying liquidity screens. It then ranks the remaining stocks by exposure to the exponential technology themes with bias to small caps, up to five stocks within each theme are considered until the final constituents reach 200. The Underlying Index is equal weighted and is reconstituted and rebalanced annually.

name: BondBloxx B Rated USD High Yield Corporate Bond ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers targeted exposure to the B-rated segment of the high-yield corporate bond market, tracking an index composed of fixed-rate, U.S. dollar-denominated corporate bonds specifically rated B (typically B1-B3 based on an average from major rating agencies). It commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in these below-investment-grade securities, utilizing direct holdings or derivatives, with derivatives potentially comprising up to 20% of net assets. Eligible bonds must have at least $250 million outstanding, meet minimum issuance and remaining maturity requirements, and be from issuers with primary risk exposures in FX-G10 countries. Holdings are generally market value-weighted, capped at 2% per issuer, but shift to equal weighting if fewer than 50 bonds qualify. This non-diversified fund, part of a suite focusing on specific credit niches, notably holds cash flows from bond payments without reinvestment between its monthly index rebalancings.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in high-yield, below-investment grade bonds denominated in U.S. dollars of corporate issuers, either directly or indirectly (e.g., through derivatives). It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
XB tracks a market value-weighted index that specifically invests in USD-denominated corporate bonds with a credit rating of B (or its equivalent), based on an average of three main credit rating providers.

XB is part of an ETF suite that targets specific niches of the high-yield corporate bond market. This fund invests in USD-denominated corporate bonds that are rated B1 through B3, based on an average of Moodys, S&P, and Fitch. Eligible debt securities must be issued by companies having risk exposures as FX-G10 member countries, with at least $250 million outstanding face value. Bonds should have a maturity of at least 18 months at the time of issuance and at least one year remaining to maturity. Holdings are weighted according to market value, with each issuer capped at 2%. The fund has no limit to the number of issuers to be selected. If fewer than 50 qualify for inclusion, holdings will be weighted equally. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in derivatives such as swaps, options, and futures contracts. Note: Although cash flows from bond payments are retained until each monthly rebalancing, it does not earn any reinvestment income while being held in the index.

It is non-diversified.

From this group, it uses a predictive model incorporating fundamental and technical metrics—like valuation, profitability, leverage, and stability—to select approximately 75 stocks considered most likely to continue accelerating their dividend payments. Holdings within the portfolio are weighted based on a blend of yield and income stability, and the fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in these securities, with the index undergoing annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing.

name: MicroSectors FANG+ Index 3X Leveraged ETN
