MOON tracks a tier-weighted index that selects US-listed companies seeking innovative technologies.

The security was delisted.The last day of trading on an exchange is July 19, 2024. MOON targets US companies that pursue innovative and disruptive technologies, or moonshot innovators. The selection universe is drawn from companies in the S&P Kensho New Economy indices or from the Wireless Telecommunication or Internet industries. To construct the portfolio, the index picks the top 50 companies with the highest early-stage composite innovation scores. This score is based on a natural language processing (NLP) algorithm used for keyword searches relating to the theme and on the companies research and development expense ratio to revenue. While MOON may include stocks of all capitalizations in its portfolio, the fund aims to focus on mid- and small-cap stocks and exclude mega-cap stocks. Furthermore, the index applies modified equal-weightingstocks are first equal-weighted, and then adjusted to meet liquidity, industry group, and diversification constraints. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted semi-annually.

name: Simplify Tara India Opportunities ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily, under normal circumstances at least 80% of its assets, in equity securities of Indian issuers. Indian issuers are generally defined as entities organized or principally traded in India, or deriving a majority of their business activities, revenues, or assets from the country. The investment strategy targets companies positioned to benefit from key Indian themes such as the expanding middle class, growing economic participation, and government initiatives in defense, green energy, and exports. Employing a bottom-up selection process without market capitalization restrictions, the managers identify high-quality companies with strong growth potential through rigorous screening, company-specific research, analysis of key performance indicators, and valuation modeling. The portfolio is continuously monitored to maintain diversification and adapt to market developments.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of Indian issuers. The manager define Indian issuers as entities: (i) organized in India; (ii) having a class of securities whose principal securities market is in India; (iii) deriving more than 50% of total revenues or earnings from goods produced, sales made, or services provided in India; or (iv) maintaining more than 50% of its employees, assets, investments, operations, or other business activity in India.
description_etfcom: IOPP invests in equity securities of Indian issuers positioned to benefit from its key themes relating to the countrys growing middle class, sectors with increasing economic participation, and the governments focus on defense, green energy, and exports. The fund invests in Indian companies perceived as high quality with potential for long-term growth and capital appreciation. The actively managed fund invests in companies with no restriction to market capitalization. The portfolio managers use a bottom-up selection process that identifies stocks through company-specific research and analysis. The process starts with 800-1,000 stocks that are screened using multiple factors, such as an evaluation of a companys competitive position, management, growth potential, and track record. Companies are further narrowed down using KPIs, model building, and valuations. To maintain the portfolio and ensure diversification, securities are monitored by tracking news and analyzing quarterly results.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of Indian issuers. The manager define Indian issuers as entities: (i) organized in India; (ii) having a class of securities whose principal securities market is in India; (iii) deriving more than 50% of total revenues or earnings from goods produced, sales made, or services provided in India; or (iv) maintaining more than 50% of its employees, assets, investments, operations, or other business activity in India.

name: Hoya Capital High Dividend Yield ETF
merged_description: This ETF focuses on generating income through high dividend yields by investing in a diversified portfolio of 100 U.S.-listed real estate-related securities, tracking a rules-based index. Its strategy involves holding both common and preferred stocks from REITs and real estate operating companies, specifically targeting high-yield opportunities across various property sectors and market capitalizations (large, mid, and small). The portfolio construction allocates across distinct segments, including select "Dividend Champions," market-cap-weighted REITs chosen for yield, and actively-traded, high-yielding real estate preferred stocks, using criteria such as dividend yield and debt ratios. Committing to invest at least 80% of its assets (plus borrowings) in securities that have recently paid dividends, the fund rebalances its holdings semi-annually to maintain its high-yield real estate focus.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that is designed to provide diversified exposure to 100 U.S.-listed real estate-related securities that collectively provide income through high dividend yields. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in dividend-paying securities, which includes equity securities that have paid a dividend in the prior 12 calendar months. The fund will invest in all of the component securities of the index in approximately the same proportion as in the index.
description_etfcom: RIET targets the real estates highest dividend-yielders. The fund includes US-listed common and preferred stocks of REITs and real estate operating companies. Eligible firms are initially grouped into three market-cap tiers (large-, mid, and small-cap) and 14 real estate property sectors (healthcare, industrial, infrastructure, residential, data center, net lease, retail, land/agriculture, storage, lodging, office, specialty, and home and commercial financing). The funds diversified portfolio aims to hold 100 fixed-weighted stocks comprising: a) 10 Dividend Champions (15% weight)selected from each property sector based on market-cap, dividend yield, and debt ratio, b) 10 large-, 25 mid, and 25 small-cap REITs (75% weight)identified based on dividend yield, with a maximum of six firms per property sector in each tier, and c) 30 Preferreds (10% weight)which are the most actively-traded and highest dividend-yielding real-estate preferred stocks. The index rebalances semi-annually.
description_yahoo: The index is a rules-based index that is designed to provide diversified exposure to 100 U.S.-listed real estate-related securities that collectively provide income through high dividend yields. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in dividend-paying securities, which includes equity securities that have paid a dividend in the prior 12 calendar months.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Hoya Capital High Dividend Yield Index (the “index”). The index is a rules-based index that is designed to provide diversified exposure to 100 U.S.-listed real estate-related securities that collectively provide income through high dividend yields. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in dividend-paying securities, which includes equity securities that have paid a dividend in the prior 12 calendar months.

name: ProShares Online Retail ETF
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of an index comprising global companies that derive their principal revenue from online retail or other non-store sales channels, such as mobile or app purchases, specifically excluding online travel businesses. It primarily invests (at least 80% of assets) in the securities within this index or instruments with similar economic characteristics. Utilizing a modified market-capitalization weighting methodology, the fund applies caps to individual holdings and the aggregate weight of the largest positions, as well as limiting non-US exposure, which can result in significant concentration in major online retail leaders. The fund is non-diversified, and its underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced monthly to maintain its focus on the evolving online retail landscape.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of publicly traded companies that principally sell online or through other non-store sales channels, such as through mobile or app purchases, rather than through "brick and mortar" store locations. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ONLN is part of a suite of ProShares products that focus on retail disruption, alongside EMTY and CLIX. The fund tracks an index of global companies that mainly sell online or through other non-store sales channels, such as mobile or app purchase and excludes online travel companies. ONLN competes with Amplifys similar fund, IBUY. The biggest difference between the two is in the weighting of components unlike the equal-weighted IBUY, components of ONLN are held on a modified market-cap basis. That gives a big boost to the largest stocks in the segment, like Amazon and Alibaba. The modified market cap adjusts to the following: individual company weight may not exceed 24% of the index and the sum of all companies weighing more than 4.5% may not exceed 50% of the indexs value. A cap of 25% is placed on non-US holdings. The index is reconstituted annually in June and rebalanced monthly.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of U.S.-listed companies deemed to be “Online Retailers.”Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the ProShares Online Retail Index (the index). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of U.S.-listed companies deemed to be “Online Retailers.”Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity MSCI Industrials Index ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides comprehensive, market-cap-weighted exposure to the broad US industrials sector by seeking to track the performance of an underlying index representing this segment of the U.S. equity market. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities included in its benchmark index, which employs a 25/25 capping methodology to meet diversification requirements. Utilizing a representative sampling strategy, the fund may not hold every security within the index, aiming instead for a portfolio that effectively mirrors the index's characteristics and performance, with quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Industrials 25/25 Index, which represents the performance of the industrial sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Industrials 25/25 Index.
description_etfcom:
FIDU tracks a market-cap-weighted index of stocks in the broad US industrials sector.

FIDU is one of the US sector funds, tracking MSCI indexes, launched by Fidelity in October 2013. It provides comprehensive plain-vanilla exposure to the broad industrials sector through a relatively liquid and efficient portfolio. Prior to December 1, 2020, the fund tracked the MSCI USA IMI Industrials Index, an uncapped version of the present index. To meet diversification requirements, FIDU now uses a 25/50 capping methodology. Notably, instead of replicating the underlying index, the fund uses a representative sampling strategy. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Industrials 25/25 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Industrials 25/25 Index, which represents the performance of the industrial sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Industrials 25/25 Index.

name: ProShares S&P 500 Dividend Aristocrats ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on S&P 500 companies with a proven track record of consistently increasing dividends for at least 25 consecutive years. It aims to track the performance of an index representing these dividend growers, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in index components or instruments with similar economic characteristics. The portfolio holds a minimum of 40 stocks, employs an equal-weighting methodology, and caps any single sector's weight at 30%. This specific construction results in a concentrated portfolio that may overweight traditional dividend-paying sectors, exhibit a distinct midcap tilt, potentially deviate from broad market exposure, and show different sensitivity to market movements. The underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly to maintain its targeted exposure.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index contains a minimum of 40 stocks, which are equally weighted, and no single sector is allowed to comprise more than 30% of the index weight. It seeks to remain fully invested at all times in securities and/or financial instruments that, in combination, provide exposure to the returns of the index without regard to market conditions, trends or direction.
description_etfcom:
NOBL tracks an equal-weighted index of S&P 500 constituents that have increased dividend payments annually for at least 25 years.

NOBL only selects companies from the S&P 500 that have increased their dividends for at least 25 consecutive years. Holdings are equal-weighted, with sector weights capped at 30%. NOBLs methodology causes it to overweight traditional dividend-paying sectors. With a concentrated portfolio of at least 40 names, the fund might skew away from market-like exposure. Its methodology substantially limits NOBL's selection universe, and the fund has a pronounced midcap tilt. However, the fund may be less sensitive to market movements than other vanilla funds in the segment. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the S&P 500 Index that have consistently increased dividends each year for at least 25 years. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the S&P 500® Dividend Aristocrats® Index (the "index"). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the S&P 500 Index that have consistently increased dividends each year for at least 25 years. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics.

name: Vanguard Global Capital Cycles Fund Investor Shares
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital appreciation, this non-diversified fund invests globally in equity securities. Its core strategy aims to generate above-average compounded returns by targeting companies and industries characterized by declining capital spending, while actively avoiding businesses with easily replicable models or assets. The portfolio typically includes holdings across a range of sectors, market capitalizations, and encompasses stocks from both developed and emerging markets.
description_original: The fund invests in U.S. and foreign equity securities. It seeks to generate above average compounded returns by purchasing securities in companies and industries where capital spending is declining, and seeks to avoid companies, assets, and business models that can be easily replicated. The fund typically invests across a range of sectors, a mix of developed and emerging markets stocks, and typically holds companies across the market capitalization spectrum. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund invests in U.S. and foreign equity securities. It seeks to generate above average compounded returns by purchasing securities in companies and industries where capital spending is declining, and seeks to avoid companies, assets, and business models that can be easily replicated. The fund typically invests across a range of sectors, a mix of developed and emerging markets stocks, and typically holds companies across the market capitalization spectrum. It is non-diversified.

name: Janus Henderson Net Zero Transition Resources ETF
merged_description: This actively managed global equity fund focused on companies contributing to or benefiting from the transition to net zero carbon emissions, targeting themes such as carbon reduction, energy transition, sustainable mobility, sustainable industry, and sustainable agriculture. It also incorporated firms positioned to benefit from the demand for natural resources, investing primarily across the materials, energy, utility, agricultural, industrial, and consumer staple sectors under normal circumstances. The strategy aimed for a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio of approximately 25-50 holdings of any market capitalization, selected using ESG screens, bottom-up fundamental analysis considering growth and quality, and exclusions for controversial activities and UN Global Compact violators. Please note, this security has been delisted, with its final day of trading on an exchange being October 19, 2023.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in equity securities of companies whose products, services and activities are considered by the adviser as contributing to or benefiting from the goal of achieving “net zero” carbon emissions through the decarbonization of the global economy, such as carbon reduction, energy transition, sustainable mobility, sustainable industry, and sustainable agriculture. The fund will invest in global companies, primarily in the materials, energy, utility, agricultural, industrial and consumer staple sectors. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 19, 2023. JZRO is actively managed to invest in companies that are believed to contribute to the goal of achieving net zero carbon emissions such as those involved in carbon reduction, energy transition, sustainable mobility, sustainable industry, and sustainable agriculture. The fund also screens for firms that are positioned to benefit from the demand for natural resources. JZRO aims to hold about 25-50 globally-listed equities of any market-cap. Companies involved in controversial activities and UN global compact violators are excluded from the investment universe. To select securities, the fund manager applies ESG screens and uses a bottom-up, fundamental approach that factors in growth potential, competitive positioning and operational quality, return on capital, risk profile, and strategy.

name: ARK Transparency ETF
merged_description: This investment fund concentrates its portfolio, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the components of its benchmark index, which includes stocks and depositary receipts. The core strategy revolves around corporate transparency; its underlying index is designed to track approximately 100 companies demonstrating high transparency scores, determined through a proprietary methodology developed by the index provider. Investors should note that this fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that are included in the fund’s benchmark index and depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to track the price movements of stocks of approximately 100 companies that receive high scores for transparency based on a proprietary scoring methodology developed by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity MSCI Consumer Discretionary Index ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to mirror the performance of the U.S. consumer discretionary sector by generally tracking the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index. Investing at least 80% of its assets in index constituents, it provides exposure to large-, mid-, and small-cap U.S. companies within the sector, identified using GICS standards and weighted by market capitalization. The fund utilizes a sampling strategy, holding a representative selection rather than every security in the index, to achieve an investment profile similar to its benchmark. Notably, the underlying index incorporates a 25/50 capping rule to manage concentration by limiting single issuer weights and the aggregate weight of large holdings, although the fund itself is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the consumer discretionary sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FDIS tracks a market-cap-weighted index of stocks in the US consumer discretionary sector.

FDIS delivers exposure to large-, mid- and small-cap companies in the consumer discretionary sector, tracking an index that uses GICS to define sector firms, then selecting and weighting the stocks by market cap. The index also uses a capping constraint to meet diversification requirements, such that no more than 25% of the funds assets may be invested in a single issuer and the aggregate weight of issuers with over 5% weight are capped at 50% of the funds total asset. FDIS uses a sampling strategy to track the index, which means the fund may not hold all the securities in the underlying index but hold securities that collectively provide an investment profile similar to the index. Prior to December 1, 2020, the fund tracked an uncapped version of its index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the consumer discretionary sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Discretionary 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Roundhill Cannabis ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks capital growth by investing globally within the cannabis and hemp ecosystem. It primarily holds exchange-listed equity securities, including common stocks, depositary receipts, and REITs, alongside total return swaps. Under normal conditions, at least 80% of its assets are invested in companies deriving a minimum of 50% of their net revenue from, or investing a majority of their assets in, the legal cannabis and hemp industry, encompassing producers, distributors, and related service providers across all market capitalizations. A distinctive feature is its use of total return swaps, notably to gain exposure to U.S. multi-state operators, complementing its holdings identified through qualitative analysis and weighted on a modified market capitalization basis within a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-listed equity securities and total return swaps intended to provide exposure to the cannabis and hemp ecosystem. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in equity securities, including common stock and depositary receipts, of companies and REITs that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from, or invest a majority of their assets in, the cannabis and hemp ecosystem (“Cannabis Companies”). It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
WEED is an actively managed portfolio of equities and total return swaps that provide exposure to the global cannabis and hemp ecosystem.

WEED seeks capital growth by actively investing in companies and real estate investment trusts (REITs) that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from the legal cannabis and hemp industry. This includes producers and/or distributors, business to business providers, and business to consumer providers. The fund may hold stocks and depositary receipts of companies of any market capitalization, that operate in emerging, frontier, and developed market countries. The fund may also primarily invest in total return swaps which are utilized to gain exposure to US multi-state operators (MSOs). To identify a universe of cannabis companies, a companys thematic relevance is determined through qualitative factors such as public filings and press releases. The resulting portfolio is weighted on a modified market capitalization basis.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks capital growth. The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-listed equity securities and total return swaps intended to provide exposure to the cannabis and hemp ecosystem. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in equity securities, including common stock and depositary receipts, of companies and REITs that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from, or invest a majority of their assets in, the cannabis and hemp ecosystem (“Cannabis Companies”). It is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Energy ETF
merged_description: This fund provides exposure to the U.S. energy sector by investing in companies classified within the S&P 500® Energy Index, employing an equal-weighting methodology. This strategy assigns similar importance to each holding upon quarterly rebalancing, distinguishing it from market-cap-weighted approaches and covering various energy sub-industries. Generally investing at least 90% of its assets in the underlying index components, the fund uniquely ensures a minimum of 22 constituents; if fewer than 22 energy companies are available in the S&P 500®, the index incorporates the largest S&P MidCap 400® energy companies to reach this minimum threshold.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Energy Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the energy sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_etfcom:
RSPG tracks an equal-weighted index of US energy companies in the S&P 500.

RSPG is a large-cap sector fund tracking an equal-weighted index that provides exposure to the energy segment of the S&P 500. The fund holds US energy companies, stretching across multiple sub-industries from the broadly defined energy space. During quarterly rebalances, the index imposes a 22 company minimum count while featuring an equal-weight play. In cases where fewer than 22 companies are viewed eligible, the index will turn to selecting the largest energy companies in the S&P MidCap 400 Index based on market-cap until the minimum count is reached. Prior to March 21,2022, the fund tracked the S&P 500 Equal Weight Energy Index. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYE.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Energy Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the energy sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: WisdomTree India Hedged Equity Fund
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provides exposure to the Indian equity market by tracking an index of companies incorporated, listed, and traded in India. The underlying index selects the top 75 companies based on market capitalization and trading volume, weighting them by market cap subject to individual (10%) and sector (30%) limits, and undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalancing. A key feature is its currency hedging strategy, which utilizes forward and futures contracts to neutralize the impact of fluctuations between the Indian rupee and the U.S. dollar. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its net assets in the constituent securities of its benchmark index, aiming to deliver returns focused on the Indian market performance while mitigating currency risk.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in the constituent securities of its index. WisdomTree, the index provider and parent company of WisdomTree Asset Management, Inc. has created the index to provide exposure to companies incorporated, listed, and traded in India, while at the same time “hedging” or neutralizing exposure to fluctuations in the value of the Indian rupee relative to the U.S. dollar. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: INDH seeks to mirror the performance of an index targeting stocks of companies incorporated and listed on the Bombay (Mumbai) Stock Exchange. The Index selects the top 75 companies based on market capitalization and trading volumes for a one-year period. Weights are also based on a firms market capitalization, with individual company exposure capped at 10% and sector exposure at 30%. The index undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalancing. Additionally, INDH employs a hedging strategy using currency forward and futures contracts to reduce the impact of the currency exchange rate fluctuations between the Indian Rupee and the US Dollar. This approach aims to buffer against currency volatility to balance returns and maintain focused exposure to the Indian market.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree India Hedged Equity Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in the constituent securities of its index. WisdomTree, the index provider and parent company of WisdomTree Asset Management, Inc. has created the index to provide exposure to companies incorporated, listed, and traded in India, while at the same time “hedging” or neutralizing exposure to fluctuations in the value of the Indian rupee relative to the U.S. dollar. The fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree International High Dividend Fund
merged_description: This fund aims to track a fundamentally weighted index of high-dividend-yielding companies located in developed international markets, specifically excluding those in the United States and Canada. Its underlying index selects constituents primarily from the top 30% by dividend yield within a broader international equity universe, typically featuring firms from developed Europe and the Asia-Pacific region. Index components are weighted based on the cash dividends paid over the prior year, with individual security weights capped during annual rebalancing. Under normal conditions, the fund invests at least 95% of its assets in these index securities or economically similar investments and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 95% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of companies with high dividend yields selected from the WisdomTree International Equity Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DTH tracks a dividend-weighted index of developed-market stocks, excluding the US and Canada, ranked in the top 30% by dividend yield of the WisdomTree DEFA Index.

DTH provides exposure to the international developed market by tracking an index with the top 30% of securities by dividend yield from the WisdomTree International Equity Index. The fund avoids all North American companies (not just US firms), so Canadian firms are excluded. Fund constituents are typically domiciled in developed Europe and Asia-Pacific countries. Companies ranking outside the top 35% by dividend yield are removed from the index. Securities are weighted in the Index based on dividends paid over the prior annual cycle. They are then weighted by dividend yield and capped at 5% during annual rebalancing.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, at least 95% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of companies with high dividend yields selected from the WisdomTree International Equity Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree International High Dividend Index. Under normal circumstances, at least 95% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of companies with high dividend yields selected from the WisdomTree International Equity Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: T. Rowe Price Dividend Growth ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund aims for both dividend income and long-term capital growth by primarily investing (at least 80% of assets) in global large- and mid-cap stocks demonstrating a strong history of, or potential for, paying dividends; this allocation can include equities, ADRs, certain synchronously traded foreign stocks, and related futures. The core strategy emphasizes companies expected to achieve sustainable, above-average growth in both earnings and dividends, selected based on active analysis of financial health, competitive positioning, and valuation. Utilizing a non-transparent structure, the fund discloses its actual holdings quarterly with a delay, instead providing a daily proxy portfolio designed to closely track the underlying assets' performance, a feature which could potentially lead to greater deviations between the ETF's price and its net asset value during market volatility.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of the fund's assets in stocks that have a strong track record of paying dividends or are expected to pay dividends over time (even if not currently paying dividends) (or futures that have similar economic characteristics). It primarily invests in exchange-traded securities that trade synchronously with the fund's shares, cash, and cash equivalents. The fund may also invest inADRs and common stocks listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange synchronously with the fund's shares (i.e., during the U.S. listing exchange's trading hours).
description_etfcom:
TDVG is an actively-managed, non-transparent fund of global, large- and mid-cap companies with sustainable, above-average growth in earnings and dividends. The fund utilizes the T. Rowe non-transparent model.

TDVG is one of the first ETFs to be offered by the issuer. They chose to use a non-transparent structure which only discloses actual fund holdings 15 days after each quarter end. The fund manager actively selects stocks they believe to have good financials and growth prospects, such as (1) a competitive current dividend yield (2) either a track record of, or the potential for, above-average earnings and dividend growth potential (3) a sound balance sheet and cash flow, (4) a sustainable competitive advantage and leading market position and (5) attractive valuations. Due to its unique structure, the fund holdings are represented in a proxy portfolio published daily on the issuers website. This proxy portfolio is designed to closely track the daily performance of the funds holdings. As such, it is important to take into consideration such a structure could result in greater price disparity during volatile markets.
description_yahoo: The fund normally invests at least 80% of the fund's assets in stocks that have a strong track record of paying dividends or are expected to pay dividends over time (even if not currently paying dividends) (or futures that have similar economic characteristics). It primarily invests in exchange-traded securities that trade synchronously with the fund's shares, cash, and cash equivalents. The fund may also invest in ADRs and common stocks listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange synchronously with the fund's shares (i.e., during the U.S. listing exchange's trading hours).
description_morningstar: The investment seeks dividend income and long-term capital growth. The fund normally invests at least 80% of the fund's assets in stocks that have a strong track record of paying dividends or are expected to pay dividends over time (even if not currently paying dividends) (or futures that have similar economic characteristics). It primarily invests in exchange-traded securities that trade synchronously with the fund's shares, cash, and cash equivalents. The fund may also invest in ADRs and common stocks listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange synchronously with the fund's shares (i.e., during the U.S. listing exchange's trading hours).

name: iShares ESG Advanced MSCI USA ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund focuses on large- and mid-capitalization U.S. equities selected for strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) profiles, tracking a corresponding market-cap-weighted index derived from a broad US benchmark. It targets companies with above-average ESG ratings (BBB or higher) relative to sector peers, evaluating them on key sector-specific issues. The investment strategy incorporates extensive exclusions, removing firms involved in controversial activities such as nuclear weapons, genetic engineering, palm oil, private prisons, and predatory lending, as well as broadly eliminating fossil fuel exposure across the energy sector, excepting those primarily focused on alternative energy. Typically investing at least 90% of its assets in index constituents, the fund follows a quarterly review process and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to reflect the equity performance of large- and mid-capitalization U.S. companies with favorable environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) ratings while applying extensive screens, including removing fossil fuel exposure. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: USXF is passively managed to invest in US equities with above average ESG ratings relative to its sector peers. The underlying index starts with the MSCI USA Index (the parent) and excludes companies engaged in controversial activities like nuclear weapons, genetic engineering, palm oil, private prisons, and predatory lending. Firms in the energy sector per GICS methodology, including those involved in fossil fuels, reserve ownership, related revenues and power generation are also excluded, with the exception of firms having bulk of their revenues tied to alternative energy. The remaining companies are ranked based on a sector-specific ESG Key Issues (e.g. carbon emissions) selection and weighting model, only those with above average scores (BBB and up) are selected. The market cap-weighted index is reviewed quarterly and excludes small-cap firms.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Choice ESG Screened Index (the “underlying index”). The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to reflect the equity performance of large- and mid-capitalization U.S. companies with favorable environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) ratings while applying extensive screens, including removing fossil fuel exposure. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index. It is non-diversified.

name: AOT Growth and Innovation ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in U.S.-listed equity securities demonstrating high growth potential due to low marginal cost business models, often benefiting from technological innovations that reduce their cost structures. Eligible companies typically have a minimum market capitalization of $800 million, with the fund excluding REITs, Business Development Companies (BDCs), and depositary receipts (like ADRs/GDRs). Using proprietary fundamental research and a top-down process to identify attractive sectors and marginal cost leaders, the advisor selects a concentrated portfolio of 40 to 90 stocks based on fundamental quality screens. Portfolio holdings are weighted according to their perceived attractiveness rather than market capitalization and are generally rebalanced monthly, subject to advisor discretion, with positions typically sold upon reaching attractive valuations or experiencing changes in growth rates.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (ETF) that invests in U.S. listed equity securities that have high growth potential based on a low marginal cost business model. It’s investment universe consists of publicly traded equity securities listed in the United States with a minimum market capitalization of $800 million. The Sub-Adviser also excludes REITs, Business Development Companies (“BDCs”), American Depository Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depository Receipts (“GDRs”).
description_etfcom:
AOTG actively invests in a growth portfolio of low marginal cost companies in the US. Stocks are selected based on proprietary fundamental research and criteria.

AOTG actively manages a narrow portfolio of US-listed equities that are believed capable of future growth due to low marginal cost business models. Eligible securities do not include business development companies or depositary receipts. The fund identifies sectors suitable for low marginal cost companies and then uses a top-down process to assess an overall industrys attractiveness for marginal cost production. Marginal cost leaders include companies that benefit from technological innovations which reduce their cost structure. The fund adviser uses fundamental quality screens to select their top 40 to 90 stocks. The resulting portfolio is weighted according to each securitys attractiveness aside from market capitalization. Holdings are typically sold when a company achieves an attractive valuation or realizes a change in growth rate. The fund is generally rebalanced monthly, although it is subject to the advisers discretion.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (ETF) that invests in U.S. listed equity securities that have high growth potential based on a low marginal cost business model. It’s investment universe consists of publicly traded equity securities listed in the United States with a minimum market capitalization of $800 million. The Sub-Adviser also excludes REITs, and Business Development Companies (“BDCs”).
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (ETF) that invests in U.S. listed equity securities that have high growth potential based on a low marginal cost business model. It’s investment universe consists of publicly traded equity securities listed in the United States with a minimum market capitalization of $800 million. The Sub-Adviser also excludes REITs, and Business Development Companies (“BDCs”).

name: First Trust Indxx Global Agriculture ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund aims to mirror the performance of a market-capitalization weighted index focused on global companies engaged directly or indirectly in improving agricultural yields. It normally invests at least 90% of its assets in the common stocks and depositary receipts comprising this index. Companies included typically derive at least 10% of their revenue from key sub-industries such as agricultural chemicals, fertilizers, seed manufacturing, irrigation equipment, and farm machinery. A distinguishing feature is its inclusion of farmland companies, offering unique exposure within the global agriculture sector. The underlying index reconstitutes annually and rebalances quarterly to maintain its focus.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is a market capitalization weighted index designed to measure the performance of companies that are directly or indirectly engaged in improving agricultural yields. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FTAG provides access to global firms involved in improving agricultural yields. Specifically, the fund consists of the following sub-industries: chemicals and fertilizers, seed manufacturers, irrigation equipment providers and farm machinery companies. The portfolio also includes farmland companies which is a unique feature in the global agriculture space. From a selection universe of eligible companies, the fund selects those that generate at least 10% of their revenue from the mentioned sub-industries and weights them according to market-cap. The index reconstitutes annually and rebalances quarterly. Prior to December 18, 2015, FTAG tracked a completely unrelated index of platinum miners under the fund name, First Trust ISE Global Platinum Index Fund (PLTM).
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Indxx Global Agriculture Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is a market capitalization weighted index designed to measure the performance of companies that are directly or indirectly engaged in improving agricultural yields. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X MLP & Energy Infrastructure Covered Call ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a covered call strategy focused on the energy infrastructure sector. It achieves this by primarily holding shares of an underlying ETF composed of US-listed midstream energy infrastructure Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs) and corporations. Concurrently, it systematically writes one-month, at-the-money call options covering up to 100% of its holdings. The fund aims to generate income from the premiums received for selling these options, which potentially enhances yield but caps the upside appreciation potential of the underlying assets. This strategy seeks to replicate the performance of a specific buy-write index, utilizes FLEX options held to expiration, is rebalanced quarterly, and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes (if any), in the constituent securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of a theoretical portfolio that employs a covered call strategy, as determined by Cboe Global Indices, LLC. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
MLPD tracks an index of long positions in the Global X MLP & Energy Infrastructure ETF (MLPX) and writes one-month, at-the-money call options on up to 100% of the underlying portfolio.

MLPD aims to provide growth potential and yield by combining long positions in the Global X MLP & Energy Infrastructure ETF (MLPX) with short-covered call options, in equal notional amounts. MLPX is a vanilla ETF comprised of at least 20 US-listed midstream energy infrastructure MLPs and corporations. The fund maintains a theoretical portfolio of stocks from the reference index, while also writing a succession of one-month, at-the-money FLEX call options on each share. These call options represent 100% of the portfolio value and are held until expiration, either expiring or settling in cash. Additionally, these contracts are collateralized by the equity portfolio. While this strategy potentially generates income through the options premium, it does place a drag on the appreciation potential. The index is rebalanced quarterly in February, May, August, and November.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Cboe MLPX ATM BuyWrite Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes (if any), in the constituent securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of a theoretical portfolio that employs a covered call strategy, as determined by Cboe Global Indices, LLC. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X S&P 500 Risk Managed Income ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks investment results corresponding to a risk-managed income index based on the S&P 500. It primarily holds the constituent stocks of the S&P 500 while employing a specific options collar strategy on the index. This strategy involves systematically selling monthly at-the-money call options while simultaneously buying monthly 5% out-of-the-money put options. The core objective is to generate income, primarily through the net credit received from these option premiums, while the purchased puts provide a measure of downside risk management. As a trade-off for the income generation and downside buffer, the sold call options cap the fund's potential upside participation in market rallies. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the Cboe S&P 500 Risk Managed Income Index ("underlying index"). The underlying index measures the performance of a risk managed income strategy that holds the underlying stocks of the S&P 500® Index and applies an options collar strategy (i.e., a mix of short (sold) call options and long (purchased) put options) on the S&P 500® Index.
description_etfcom: XRMI holds the constituents of the S&P 500 Index while employing an options collar strategy which involves buying 5% out-of-the-money put options and selling at-the-money covered call options in an amount that corresponds to the value of the portfolio. The funds exchange-traded put option positions are purchased on a monthly basis and will be held until their one-month maturity. At expiration, these options are either exercised or settled in cash. The options collar strategy seeks to generate a net-credit, meaning that the premium received from the sale of the call options will be greater than the premium paid when buying the put options. Investors should note that selling at-the-money call options caps the funds upside potential. In addition, buying and selling shares other than the monthly purchase and expiration dates of the options may result in different returns and buffer protection.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Cboe S&P 500 Risk Managed Income Index ("underlying index"). The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the Cboe S&P 500 Risk Managed Income Index ("underlying index"). The underlying index measures the performance of a risk managed income strategy that holds the underlying stocks of the S&P 500® Index and applies an options collar strategy (i.e., a mix of short (sold) call options and long (purchased) put options) on the S&P 500® Index.

name: SPDR Galaxy Digital Asset Ecosystem ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing across the digital asset ecosystem. Its strategy combines holding equity securities of global companies poised to benefit from the growing adoption of blockchain and cryptocurrency industries, such as miners and service providers, with targeted exposure to the price movements of bitcoin and ether. This cryptocurrency exposure is gained indirectly through instruments like futures contracts, related exchange-traded funds, and spot exchange-traded products, acquired via a Cayman Islands subsidiary and typically limited to 25% of the portfolio. Employing a fundamental, bottom-up analysis that considers macroeconomic trends and blockchain-specific data, the sub-adviser dynamically adjusts holdings, particularly modulating the direct crypto-related asset exposure based on market conditions to pursue growth or reduce risk. The fund is non-diversified and may also hold cash or money market instruments for liquidity and collateral purposes.
description_original: The SPDR Galaxy Digital Asset Ecosystem ETF (DECO) seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation through the selection of companies that stand to benefit from the growing adoption of the blockchain and cryptocurrency industries, as well as cryptocurrency exposures through ETFs and futures.Galaxy Digital Capital Management (Galaxy) will use its deep understanding of the digital asset ecosystem and expertise in blockchain technology to actively manage the portfolio.DECO is an actively managed solution from a leader in the digital asset economy that enables investors to pursue potential growth from the further adoption of digital assets.
description_etfcom: DECO provides exposure to the growing digital asset ecosystem. The fund invests in companies expected to thrive as blockchain technology becomes more widely adopted, focusing on blockchain-related activities, such as Bitcoin miners and crypto service providers. Simultaneously, it gains exposure to cryptocurrency price movements through ETFs and futures contracts, focusing on bitcoin and ether. Portfolio selection is based on a fundamental, bottom-up analysis, using macroeconomic trends like interest rates and inflation, as well as blockchain data like transaction volumes and mining activity. While crypto positions rely on market conditions, it adjust heavily to direct crypto-related assets when favorable and reduce risk during downturns. Additionally, exposure to cryptocurrencies is limited to 25% and is acquired indirectly through a Cayman Islands subsidiary. The fund may hold cash equivalents or money market instruments for liquidity and collateral purposes.
description_yahoo: The Sub-Adviser seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing, directly or indirectly, in (i) equity securities of foreign and domestic companies within the crypto asset and blockchain industries, (ii) exchange-traded funds (“ETFs”) that primarily hold bitcoin and/or ether futures contracts (“Crypto Asset Futures ETFs”), (iii) bitcoin and ether futures contracts (“crypto asset futures”), and (iv) exchange-traded products that hold bitcoin or ether as a reference asset (“Spot Crypto Asset ETPs”). The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long term capital appreciation. The Sub-Adviser seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing, directly or indirectly, in (i) equity securities of foreign and domestic companies within the crypto asset and blockchain industries, (ii) exchange-traded funds (“ETFs”) that primarily hold bitcoin and/or ether futures contracts (“Crypto Asset Futures ETFs”), (iii) bitcoin and ether futures contracts (“crypto asset futures”), and (iv) exchange-traded products that hold bitcoin or ether as a reference asset (“Spot Crypto Asset ETPs”). The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily Pharmaceutical & Medical Bull 3X Shares ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to provide three times the daily performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P Pharmaceuticals Select Industry Index. To achieve this 3x daily leveraged exposure, the fund invests primarily (at least 80% of assets) in financial instruments, including derivatives such as swap agreements. The underlying index uses a modified equal-weighting approach and comprises US stocks from the S&P Total Market Index classified within the GICS pharmaceuticals sub-industry. As a non-diversified fund that resets its leverage daily, it is designed as a short-term trading tool; due to the effects of compounding, its long-term returns may differ significantly from the index's performance.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index is a modified equal-weighted index that is designed to measure performance of the stocks comprising the S&P Total Market Index that are classified in the GICS pharmaceuticals sub-industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PILL provides 3x daily exposure to a modified equal-weighted index of pharmaceutical companies in the US.

PILL seeks to deliver investment results of 3x the daily performance of the S&P Pharmaceuticals Select Industry Index, a modified equal-weighted index that measures the performance of pharmaceutical companies, as defined by GICS, on the S&P Total Market Index. The fund uses derivatives and swaps to achieve its target exposure. As a levered product with daily resets, PILL is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. As a result, long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to August 2, 2019, the fund aimed to provide 3x leveraged exposure to the Dynamic Pharmaceutical Intellidex Index.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is a modified equal-weighted index that is designed to measure performance of the stocks, defined as pharmaceutical and medical stocks, comprising the S&P Total Market Index that are classified in the GICS pharmaceuticals sub-industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the S&P Pharmaceuticals Select Industry Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is a modified equal-weighted index that is designed to measure performance of the stocks, defined as pharmaceutical and medical stocks, comprising the S&P Total Market Index that are classified in the GICS pharmaceuticals sub-industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity High Dividend ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks returns that generally correspond to an underlying index focused on high-dividend-paying companies. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent securities, typically large and mid-capitalization stocks selected based on criteria including high dividend yield, a low dividend payout ratio, and expectations for continued dividend payment and growth. The portfolio construction starts with a universe of large U.S. and developed international stocks, although holdings are primarily U.S.-based, with international exposure capped at 10%. Sectors with higher overall dividend yields receive greater weight, while individual stock weights within sectors are based on modified market capitalization, and no single sector exceeds a 35% allocation.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the underlying index and in depository receipts representing securities included in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization high-dividend-paying companies that are expected to continue to pay and grow their dividends.
description_etfcom: FDVV invests in U.S. and developed international equities that exhibit high dividend yield, a low dividend payout ratio, and high dividend growth. The selection universe begins with 1,000 of the largest U.S. stocks and the largest 1,000 developed-market international stocks. These stocks are scored and selected according to their dividend yield, dividend payout ratio, and dividend growth. Sectors with higher overall dividend yield are given higher weight relative to sectors with lower dividend yield. Within each sector, each stock is weighted based on a modified market capitalization. FDVV invests mostly in U.S. stocks, with a 10% maximum on international stocks, as well as a 35% cap on any individual sector. Prior to November 9, 2017 the fund tracked the Fidelity Core Dividend Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity High Dividend Index℠. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the underlying index and in depository receipts representing securities included in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization high-dividend-paying companies that are expected to continue to pay and grow their dividends.

name: Vanguard Real Estate Index Institutional
merged_description: This investment seeks to provide high income and moderate long-term capital appreciation by tracking the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Real Estate 25/50 Index. This index measures publicly traded equity REITs and other real estate-related investments, offering focused exposure to the US real estate market. To replicate the index, the advisor invests all, or substantially all, of the fund's assets—either directly or through a wholly owned subsidiary—in the constituent stocks, holding them in approximately the same proportions as their index weightings. Notably, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The advisor attempts to track the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets-either directly or indirectly through a wholly owned subsidiary, which is itself a registered investment company-in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide a high level of income and moderate long-term capital appreciation by tracking the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Real Estate 25/50 Index that measures the performance of publicly traded equity REITs and other real estate-related investments. The advisor attempts to track the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets-either directly or indirectly through a wholly owned subsidiary, which is itself a registered investment company-in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Columbia Seligman Semiconductor & Technology ETF
merged_description: This ETF seeks capital appreciation by concentrating its investments, under normal market conditions, with at least 80% of its net assets allocated to securities of semiconductor, semiconductor equipment, and related technology companies. While primarily holding US equities such as common, preferred, and convertible stocks, it may also gain foreign exposure through depositary receipts. The fund invests across companies of all market capitalizations, typically holding between 30 and 50 securities, and operates as a non-diversified portfolio, underscoring its focused approach within the semiconductor and technology landscape.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in securities of semiconductor, semiconductor equipment and related technology companies (Semiconductor and Tech Companies). The fund may invest in securities of companies of any size, including small- and mid-capitalization companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SEMI invests in US equity securities, such as common and preferred stocks, as well as convertible securities, of technology and technology-related companies. Investment exposure may span sectors like information technology, communications services, consumer discretionary, financials, healthcare, media, consumer electronics, semiconductors, internet commerce, advertising, environmental, aerospace, and defense industries, all of which use technology to drive innovation or enhance business operations. Holdings may include companies of any size. The fund may also gain exposure to foreign companies through depositary receipts. Overall, the fund will hold between 30 and 50 securities, though this number may vary depending on market conditions.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation. Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in securities of semiconductor, semiconductor equipment and related technology companies (Semiconductor and Tech Companies). The fund may invest in securities of companies of any size, including small- and mid-capitalization companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: BlueStar Israel Technology ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund offers focused exposure to the Israeli technology sector by investing at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings, primarily in the securities and depositary receipts of companies comprising an underlying index. The portfolio includes companies engaged in a wide spectrum of technology-related sectors, such as information technology, biotechnology, healthcare equipment and supplies, defense technology, clean energy and water technology, and life sciences tools and services. Eligibility for inclusion is broad, encompassing companies linked to Israel through incorporation, headquarters, founding, stock exchange listing, significant revenue generation, majority management presence, or substantial research and development operations within the country. The underlying index employs a market-capitalization weighting methodology, imposes a 7.5% cap on individual holdings, and is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The index tracks the performance of exchange-listed Israeli technology operating companies. Such companies may be engaged in a wide spectrum of technology related sectors, including information technology, biotechnology, clean energy and water technology and defense technology. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index and in depositary receipts representing such securities. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ITEQ offers broadly defined exposure to Israeli technology companies. To be eligible, a company must be classified in Information Technology in GICS and must operate in any of the following tech-related industries: biotechnology, healthcare equipment and supplies, defense technology, clean energy and water technology, and life sciences tools and services. Aside from having broad tech exposure, the fund also broadly defines Israeli companies. To be included, a company may be incorporated, headquartered, founded, or listed in an exchange in Israel. Companies that derive significant revenue, have majority of management, or have an R&D center in Israel are also eligible. The semi-annually rebalanced index is weighted by market capitalization, subject to a 7.5% single security cap. Before January 29, 2024, ITEQ traded as BlueStar Israel Technology ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the component securities of the BlueStar Israel Global Technology Index™, or BIGITech®. The index is comprised of Israeli Technology Companies. Such companies are engaged in a wide spectrum of technology related sectors, including information technology, biotechnology, clean energy and water technology and defense technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that generally correspond (before fees and expenses) to the total return performance of the BlueStar Israel Global Technology Index™. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the component securities of the BlueStar Israel Global Technology Index™, or BIGITech®. The index is comprised of Israeli Technology Companies. Such companies are engaged in a wide spectrum of technology related sectors, including information technology, biotechnology, clean energy and water technology and defense technology. The fund is non-diversified.

name: FT Energy Income Partners Enhanced Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks a high level of total return with a distinct emphasis on generating current income for shareholders. Under normal conditions, it invests at least 80% of its assets globally in securities of, or providing exposure to, companies within the broader energy sector, including those involved in exploration, production, transportation, and distribution of traditional and renewable energy sources, as well as potentially holding MLPs and their affiliates. A core feature is its strategy to enhance income through writing both covered call options on individual stocks and naked call options on energy indexes or ETFs. The fund selects investments based on yield, growth potential, valuation, and sensitivity to sector dynamics like technological changes and policy shifts, operating as a non-diversified portfolio concentrated within the energy industry.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities of, and/or investments that provide exposure to, Energy Companies. The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in any one industry or group of industries constituting the energy sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
EIPI is an actively managed fund that seeks total return with a focus on distributions. The fund invests globally within the broader energy market, while combining both covered and naked call options writing strategies to enhance income.

EIPI aims to provide a balanced mix of income and growth for shareholders by focusing on pure-play companies within the global energy sector. It includes firms engaged in the exploration, production, transportation, and distribution of energy sources like natural gas, crude oil, and renewable energy. The fund may also hold MLPs and MLP affiliates. The adviser aims to capitalize on the sectors dynamic nature, focusing on the influence of technological advancements and government policies. Stocks are chosen based on yield, growth potential, and valuation, including stable cash flows, sustainable dividend payout ratios, increasing per-share earnings, and positive changes in value resulting from business restructuring or government policies. To boost income, the fund utilizes single stock covered call writing, along with naked call writing on energy indexes and ETFs. EIPI launched with $1 billion in assets through the conversion of four closed-end funds that were consolidated.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of total return with an emphasis on current distributions paid to shareholders. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities of, and/or investments that provide exposure to, Energy Companies. The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in any one industry or group of industries constituting the energy sector. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard Materials Index Fund
merged_description: This ETF employs an indexing strategy seeking to mirror the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Materials 25/50. It provides broad exposure to the U.S. materials sector by investing substantially all its assets in the index's constituent stocks, maintaining proportions similar to their market-capitalization weighting within the benchmark. The fund includes large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies classified under GICS within the materials sector, encompassing diverse sub-industries such as chemicals, construction materials, metals, mining, paper, and packaging. The underlying index is rebalanced quarterly to maintain its representative nature.
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Materials 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the materials sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
The fund tracks a market cap-weighted index of companies in the US materials sector.

The fund offers broad exposure to the US basic materials segment thanks to a highly representative market cap-weighted index. The fund holds materials companies, stretching across multiple sub-industries from the broadly defined space. The underlying index uses GICS classification to include companies that manufacture chemicals, construction materials, glass, paper, forest products, and packaging products, as well as metals, minerals, and mining companies. Certain investment limits are applied for RICs to help ensure diversification. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the materials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Materials 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the materials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco International BuyBack Achievers ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to track the results of an index focused on international companies engaging in significant share buybacks. Maintained by Nasdaq, Inc., the underlying index identifies foreign companies classified as "International BuyBack Achievers™" based on a proprietary methodology. To qualify, companies selected from a global ex-US universe must have reduced their outstanding shares by at least 5% over the past year, subject to liquidity and market capitalization requirements. The index employs a modified market-cap weighting scheme, is reconstituted annually, and rebalanced quarterly. The core investment concept rests on the idea that substantial share repurchases can signal management's view of the stock being undervalued. This fund is considered non-diversified and generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities comprising its target index.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index.
