The composite score considers the following factors: dividend yield (70% weight), payout ratio (15%), and dividend growth (15%). High-scoring stocks are selected such that country and sector representation is roughly market-like, relative to the broader developed international equity market, and are weighted by market cap within each country/sector group. Sectors with higher dividend yields are over weighted, while sectors with lower yields are underweighted. The index is rebalanced annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity ® International High Dividend Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the Fidelity ® International High Dividend Index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large- and mid-capitalization developed international high dividend-paying companies that are expected to continue to pay and grow their dividends.

name: The 3D Printing ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides focused exposure to the global 3D printing industry by seeking to track the performance of a specialized index. As the first ETF dedicated to this theme, it invests primarily (at least 80% of assets) in companies involved in 3D printing and related businesses, including depositary receipts, drawn from the US, other developed markets, and Taiwan. The underlying index utilizes a tiered structure, assigning specific weights to distinct business lines such as hardware, software, printing centers, scanners/measurement, and materials, while equally weighting the individual stocks within each business line. This non-diversified fund is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that are included in the fund's benchmark index, depositary receipts representing securities included in the index or underlying stocks in respect of depositary receipts included in the index. The index is designed to track the price movements of stocks of companies involved in the 3D printing industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PRNT tracks a tiered, equal-weighted index composed of stocks that are directly involved in 3D printing and 3D printing-related businesses.

PRNT is the first ETF on the market that focuses specifically on 3D printing. Eligible securities include equities based in the US, non-US developed markets, and Taiwan. The underlying index focuses on five different business lines related to 3D printing: i) 3D printing hardware, ii) CAD and 3D printing software, iii) 3D printing centers, iv) scanners and measurement, and v) 3D printing materials. Each business line receives 50%, 30%, 13%, 5%, and 2%, weight in the index respectively. Within each business line, selected securities are given an equal weight. PRNT is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that closely correspond, before fees and expenses, to the performance of the Total 3D-Printing Index ("index"). The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that are included in the fund's benchmark index, depositary receipts representing securities included in the index or underlying stocks in respect of depositary receipts included in the index. The index is designed to track the price movements of stocks of companies involved in the 3D printing industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Roundhill IO Digital Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This passively managed exchange-traded fund provided targeted exposure to approximately 40 global companies that generated the majority of their revenue from digital infrastructure assets, defined as the high-tech physical assets enabling efficient data storage and transmission. It tracked an index utilizing a specific optimization strategy based on growth (40% weight), value (10% weight), and soundness (50% weight) factors to rank and select constituents. The index construction prioritized U.S. companies up to a 65% allocation limit before adding top-ranked firms from other developed and emerging markets, subject to caps, to reach its target number of holdings. Characterized as non-diversified, the fund aimed to invest at least 80% of its assets in these digital infrastructure companies, typically holding all index components in their approximate weights, and underwent semi-annual rebalancing. Trading for this fund ceased in December 2023.
description_original: The index tracks the performance of digital infrastructure companies. Digital infrastructure is comprised of the high-tech physical assets that support the efficient storage and transmission of data, powering the internet. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in digital infrastructure companies. The fund generally will invest in all of the component securities of the index in approximately the same proportions as in the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
BYTE is a passively managed ETF that provides exposure to 40 global stocks that earn majority of their revenues from digital infrastructure assets. The fund is optimized using growth, value, and soundness factors.

The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 12, 2023. BYTE tracks an index that provides exposure to digital infrastructure companies that that have high-tech physical assets supporting the efficient storage and transmission of data. The index aims to optimize its holdings using three factors: growth, value, and soundness (GVS). Companies are ranked based on these GVS factors and weighted according to a proprietary ranking methodology. GVS factor weightings are expected to be 40% growth, 10% value, and 50% soundness. The fund selects US companies until the geographic threshold of 65% is met. The highest GVS-ranked companies from emerging countries and other developed markets are then selected, also subject to their respective caps until the index reaches a total of 40 constituents. The index committee may make assessments to adjust metrics, weightings, and geographic limits. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually every March and September.

name: iShares Genomics Immunology and Healthcare ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to capture long-term growth and innovation opportunities within the genomics, immunology, and bioengineering sectors by tracking a specialized global index. It primarily invests in companies from developed and emerging markets identified as potential beneficiaries of advancements in these fields, specifically within the biopharmaceutical and healthcare equipment and services industries. The underlying index employs a distinct methodology, selecting its top 50 constituents based not only on market capitalization, size, and liquidity but also via a keyword scoring system evaluating relevance to genomics and immuno-biopharmaceutical technologies. This selection process results in a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio where holdings are market-cap weighted, individual securities are capped at 4%, and the index rebalances semi-annually. The fund maintains at least 80% exposure to index components or similar investments, allowing up to 20% in certain derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies that could benefit from the long-term growth and innovation in genomics, immunology and bioengineering. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IDNA tracks a market-cap-selected and -weighted index of global stocks involved in genomics, immunology, and bioengineering.

IDNA holds a concentrated portfolio of global companies in the biopharmaceutical and healthcare equipment and services industries that could benefit from the long-term growth and innovation in genomics, immunology and bioengineering. In addition to these industry screens, companies must also meet certain size and liquidity measures for index eligibility. The underlying index then assigns a Relationship Keyword Score to each of the eligible companies using the FactSet Supply Chain Relationships database in search for keywords related to Genomics and Immuno Biopharmaceutical products and technologies. The top 50 names with the highest scores are included in the index. Holdings are weighted by market-cap and are constrained such that no individual security exceeds 4% weight of the portfolio. The index rebalances semi-annually.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies that could benefit from the long-term growth and innovation in genomics, immunology and bioengineering. -null-.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE® FactSet® Global Genomics and Immuno Biopharma IndexTM. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies that could benefit from the long-term growth and innovation in genomics, immunology and bioengineering. -null-.

name: Fidelity MSCI Communication Services Index ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to the U.S. communication services sector by seeking to track the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index. The underlying index represents companies of all market capitalizations within this sector, which includes telecommunications, media, and entertainment industries, and weights them based on market capitalization. Utilizing a representative sampling approach, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities but may not hold every constituent or match exact weightings. While the index incorporates 25/50 diversification rules to limit issuer concentration, the fund is classified as non-diversified and its index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the communication services sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FCOM tracks a market-cap-weighted index of stocks in the US communication services sector.

FCOM is one of ten October 2013 launches from Fidelity that track MSCI sector indexes. The fund targets the broad US communication services sector, as classified by GICS, to include both the telecommunications and the media and entertainment industry. FCOM captures stocks of all capitalization within the segment but weights the holdings in the portfolio based on market-cap. The funds manager uses a representative strategy, which means the ETF may not hold all of the securities of the index or in the exact proportion. Certain investment limits are applied for RICs to help ensure diversification, such that no group entity exceeds 25% of index weight and the aggregate weight of issuers with over 5% weight in the index are capped at 50% of the portfolio. The index is rebalanced quarterly
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the communication services sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Communication Services 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X SuperDividend U.S. ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund targets U.S. equity securities that exhibit both high dividend yields and low volatility characteristics. It tracks an equally weighted index of 50 companies selected from the U.S. market, prioritizing firms with consistent dividend payment histories and lower relative volatility (beta). The final selection consists of those ranking highest in dividend yield. The portfolio includes common stocks as well as pass-through structures like Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs) and Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs), which can influence sector exposures. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising its underlying index, which is reconstituted annually with quarterly reviews.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index tracks the performance of 50 equally-weighted common stocks, including Master Limited Partnerships ("MLPs") and Real Estate Investment Trusts ("REITs") that rank among the highest dividend yielding equity securities in the United States.
description_etfcom:
DIV tracks an equally weighted index of 50 high-dividend, low-volatility securities.

DIV combines a low-volatility strategy with a high-dividend-yield mandate. The fund's index pulls from the entire US equity space and screens for firms with large, consistent dividends and low volatility to Indxx's market benchmark. Companies should have paid consistent dividends over the last two years and are perceived to have lower relative volatility, as measured by their beta. Stocks are ranked and those with the highest dividend yields are selected. The equally weighted, 50-firm portfolio includes MLPs and REITs, two pass-through structures with unique tax implications. This gives DIV pumped-up exposure to financials and energy, while the low-volatility strategy helps explain exposure to utilities. The index is reconstituted annually, subject to quarterly reviews.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx SuperDividend ® U.S. Low Volatility Index ("underlying index"). The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index tracks the performance of 50 equally-weighted common stocks, including Master Limited Partnerships ("MLPs") and Real Estate Investment Trusts ("REITs") that rank among the highest dividend yielding equity securities in the United States.

name: Vanguard Dividend Appreciation Index Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle employs a passive indexing strategy designed to track the performance of the S&P U.S. Dividend Growers Index. It focuses on U.S. common stocks from companies demonstrating a consistent history of dividend growth, specifically those that have increased their annual dividends for at least ten consecutive years. Notably, the strategy excludes the top 25% of otherwise qualifying companies based on their indicated dividend yield. The underlying portfolio is market-capitalization weighted, with individual security weights capped at 4%, and reconstitutes annually, emphasizing sustainable dividend growth rather than high current yield.
description_original: The adviser employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that have a record of increasing dividends over time. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_etfcom:
VIG tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US companies that have increased their annual dividends for 10 or more consecutive years.

VIG focuses on dividend growth. The fund specifically selects US-listed firms that have increased their dividend payments for the past 10 years, while excluding the top 25% highest-yielding companies based on indicated annual dividend yield (IAD). This results in a portfolio that typically carries only moderately higher yield than our vanilla benchmark. Holdings are market-cap-weighted, with individual security weights capped at 4%. The index reconstitutes annually. Overall, VIGs strategy provides a sustainable growth play based on dividends. Prior to September 20, 2021, the fund tracked the Nasdaq US Dividend Achievers Select Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the S&P U.S. Dividend Growers Index that measures the investment return of common stocks of companies that have a record of increasing dividends over time. The adviser employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that have a record of increasing dividends over time. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.

name: iShares Virtual Work and Life Multisector ETF
merged_description: This fund aimed to invest in global companies enabling virtual work and remote lifestyles by tracking a market-cap-weighted index. Its underlying index included equities from both developed and emerging markets, selecting companies primarily deriving revenue from products, services, or technologies supporting 'Tele-Work' and 'Tele-Life' across various sectors, including virtual entertainment, wellness, and learning. Holdings were market-cap weighted with a cap on individual securities, and the fund operated under a non-diversified classification. Importantly, this investment product was delisted, with its final trading day occurring on August 12, 2024.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of equity securities issued by companies that provide products, services, or technologies that support remote work ("Tele-Work") or remote lifestyle ("Tele-Life"), as determined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IWFH tracks a market-cap-weighted index that invests in companies around the globe that are involved in supporting individuals virtual and remote way of working and living.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is August 12, 2024. IWFH invests in equities from 41 developed or emerging markets and across multiple sectors, which support Tele-work and Tele-lifestyles. The Index selects securities based on fundamental research that allow a virtual way of life across entertainment, wellness and learning. The starting universe considers the most liquid, publicly-traded companies, classified using FactSets Revere Business Industry Classification System (RBICS) based on their primary lines of business, revenue data and a related keyword search. Selected companies are those that derive a majority of their revenues from 33 RBICS industries considered as Virtual Work and Life products and services providers. Holdings are market-cap-weighted with individual stocks capped at 2%. The Index undergoes annual reconstitution and semi-annual rebalance.

name: Global X FinTech ETF
merged_description: This ETF offers focused exposure to the global financial technology (FinTech) sector by tracking a market-cap-weighted index composed of companies predominantly operating in developed markets. Investing at least 80% of its assets in index constituents, the fund targets firms deriving significant revenue from providing FinTech products and services across various themes, including mobile payments, marketplace or peer-to-peer lending, financial analytics software, and blockchain or alternative currency technologies. The portfolio aims to hold up to 100 companies, weighted by market capitalization but subject to constraints capping individual security weights and the aggregate allocation to the largest holdings, with annual rebalancing. Straddling the financials and technology sectors, the fund's holdings reflect opportunities and risks inherent to both areas, and it is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies in developed markets that provide financial technology products and services, including companies involved in mobile payments, peer-to-peer (P2P) and marketplace lending, financial analytics software and alternative currencies, as defined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FINX tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies in developed markets that derive significant revenues from providing financial technology products and services.

FINX offers cross-sector exposure to the emerging financial technology (FinTech) theme. The fund specifically includes developed markets securities with significant exposure to at least one of six FinTech themes: mobile payments, marketplace lending, crowdfunding, enterprise solutions, blockchain and alternative currencies, and personal finance software and automated wealth management services. Since the stocks straddle the line between financials and technology, they can benefit from but are also susceptible to sector-wide shocks to either sector. FINX aims to hold up to 100 FinTech companies, selected and weighted by market-cap. Constituents are then constrained such that no individual security exceeds 6% weight and the aggregate weight of securities with over 5% allocation is capped at 40% weight of the portfolio. The index rebalances and reconstitutes annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx Global Fintech Thematic Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies in developed markets that provide financial technology products and services, including companies involved in mobile payments, peer-to-peer (P2P) and marketplace lending, financial analytics software and alternative currencies, as defined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Expanded Tech Sector ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides exposure to an expanded definition of the technology sector by tracking a market-cap-weighted index of North American equities, although holdings are predominantly concentrated in the US. Beyond traditional technology stocks, the index incorporates select companies from communication services and consumer discretionary sectors, such as internet retail firms, reflecting evolving sector classifications. Adhering to a policy of investing at least 80% of its assets in index components or economically similar investments, the fund implements an 8.5% cap on individual security weights. Characterized as non-diversified, its underlying index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. A significant portion of the underlying index is represented by securities of companies in the technology industry or sector. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IGM tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US and Canadian technology companies.

IGM offers a broad coverage of the North American technology sector. Aside from conventional technology stocks, the fund also includes tech-related stocks from other sectorsspecifically internet retail companies. While IGM is a North American fund, nearly all its assets are allocated to the US. Seeking to provide a diversified exposure to the tech industry, its market-cap-weighted index caps each security's weight at 8.5%. The index is reconstituted semi-annually and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to December 24, 2018, the fund was tracking the S&P North American Technology Index. The change in index was due to a new Communications Services sector developed at the end of 2018.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of an index composed of North American equities in the technology sector and select North American equities from communication services and consumer discretionary sectors. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. A significant portion of the underlying index is represented by securities of companies in the technology industry or sector. It is non-diversified.

name: Ishares ESG Aware MSCI USA Growth ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to track an index composed of U.S. large- and mid-cap companies demonstrating both growth potential and positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. Growth attributes are identified using metrics such as forward and historical earnings per share and sales growth trends. The selection process screens out companies involved in controversial businesses (like weapons or tobacco) or facing significant climate change issues, then evaluates remaining firms based on their ESG risk exposure and management strategies, using sector-specific scoring and peer comparisons. While investing at least 90% of its assets in index constituents, the portfolio construction favors higher ESG-rated companies, also considering market capitalization and constraints relative to a parent index. The underlying index is reviewed and rebalanced quarterly, and the fund itself is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The underlying index is an optimized equity index designed to reflect the equity performance of U.S. companies that exhibit growth characteristics as well as positive ESG characteristics. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents as well as in securities not included in the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: EGUS tracks an index of large- and mid-cap US growth stocks perceived to have positive ESG characteristics. The parent index identifies growth stocks through long-term and short-term forward EPS growth rates, current internal growth rate, long-term historical EPS growth trend, and long-term historical sales per share growth trend. Securities are then screened to exclude companies involved in controversial businesses and issues (e.g., weapons, tobacco, climate change issues). All selected securities are assigned an ESG score that evaluates a companys exposure to key ESG issues based on business segment and geographic risk, as well as their strategies and programs to manage these risks and opportunities. Using a sector-specific weighting model, companies are rated and ranked against industry peers. The quantitative process leans toward higher-rated stocks while also considering market-cap and constraints based on the parent index. The index is reviewed and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Growth Extended ESG Focus Index. The underlying index is an optimized equity index designed to reflect the equity performance of U.S. companies that exhibit growth characteristics as well as positive ESG characteristics. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents as well as in securities not included in the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Nasdaq® Clean Edge® Smart Grid Infrastructure UCITS ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to mirror the performance of an index targeting the global smart grid and electrical energy infrastructure sector. It commits at least 90% of its assets to the common stocks and depositary receipts of companies within this index, focusing on businesses involved in electric grid modernization, smart meters and devices, network communications, energy storage and management, and enabling software. The fund holds a concentrated portfolio of global equities, including both 'Pure Play' companies (deriving over 50% revenue from the sector) and 'Diversified' companies (less than 50% revenue), after screening for minimum liquidity and market capitalization. To enhance exposure to the core theme, it employs a tiered, market-cap-based weighting scheme that allocates a collective 80% weight to 'Pure Play' firms and 20% to 'Diversified' ones, with the portfolio rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted semi-annually.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index includes companies that are primarily engaged and involved in electric grid, electric meters and devices, networks, energy storage and management, and enabling software used by the smart grid infrastructure sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: GRID is concentrated fund targeting global equities determined to be in the smart grid and electrical energy infrastructure sector as determined by Clean Edge. The fund includes companies that are either Pure Play more than 50% revenues or Diversified less than 50% revenues are derived from the smart grid and electrical energy infrastructure sector. The sector may include business in electric grid, electric meters and devices, networks, energy storage and management, and enabling software. GRID also screens for minimum liquidity and market cap. To enhance exposure to the smart grid market, the index provider uses a tiered weighting scheme. Securities are initially market cap weighted. Then a collective weight of 80% for Pure Play and 20% for Diversified are allocated. The Index is reconstituted semi-annually and rebalanced quarter.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Nasdaq Clean Edge Smart Grid Infrastructure Index TM. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index includes companies that are primarily engaged and involved in electric grid, electric meters and devices, networks, energy storage and management, and enabling software used by the smart grid infrastructure sector. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Big Data Refiners ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides focused exposure to the global big data industry, encompassing companies from both developed and emerging markets. It seeks to track an index composed of businesses centrally involved in providing analytics, software, hardware, or computing infrastructure essential for managing, analyzing, storing, or extracting value from large datasets. To be included, companies must derive a significant portion of their revenue (typically 75%, potentially lowered to 50% if needed to reach a minimum number of holdings) from these specific big data activities and meet minimum market capitalization ($500 million) and liquidity ($1 million average daily trading value) requirements. The underlying index employs a market-capitalization weighting methodology, limits individual security weights to 4.5%, and is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually. The fund primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the index components or similar instruments and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests in securities that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index consists of companies that provide analytics and infrastructure for managing and extracting information from large data sets. The fund will invest in all of the component securities of the index in approximately the same proportion as the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: DAT provides exposure to an index of developed and emerging market companies that have businesses related to the big data market. The fund primarily selects securities classified in one of the nine RBICS sub-industries that generate at least 75% of their revenue from managing, analyzing, storing, or extracting large sets of data. In situations where fewer than 25 companies meet the criteria, the revenue threshold will be lowered to 50% with the next highest revenue percentage companies are selected to complete the list. Constituents must also meet investability and liquidity requirements including a minimum market-cap of $500 million and three-month average daily trading value of at least $1 million. The fund employs a market-cap-weighting scheme with individual security capping at 4.5%. The Index is reconstituted and rebalanced semiannually in June and December.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies that provide services related to analytics, software, hardware, and computing infrastructure for managing and extracting information from large structured and unstructured data sets. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the FactSet Big Data Refiners Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies that provide services related to analytics, software, hardware, and computing infrastructure for managing and extracting information from large structured and unstructured data sets. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.

name: Global X Millennials Consumer ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to capture the investment performance of companies positioned to benefit from the consumer spending habits of the Millennial generation, defined as individuals born between 1980 and 2000. Investing primarily in U.S.-listed securities, the fund aims to track an underlying index by allocating over 80% of its assets to the index's components. The index methodology identifies companies deriving significant revenue from, or having substantial exposure to, spending categories deemed relevant to millennials—such as clothing, entertainment, travel, food, education, financial services, housing, and health—using proprietary research and scoring systems. Selected companies are weighted by market capitalization within the portfolio, subject to constraints including a maximum and minimum percentage limit per holding, and the index undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund invests more than 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to the millennial generation consumption trends, (collectively, "Millennial Companies"), as defined by the index provider. The millennial generation refers to the demographic in the U.S. with birth years ranging from 1980 to 2000.
description_etfcom:
MILN tracks an index composed of US-listed companies that derive a significant source of their revenue from spending categories determined to be associated with millennials - people born between 1980 and 2000.

MILN invests in companies that are determined to have significant exposure with the millennial generation's spending habits. The index uses a proprietary fundamental research process to determine which spending categories are relevant to millennials. These categories include clothing, entertainment, travel, food, education, financial services, housing, and health. The portfolio will have a maximum of 15 stocks, a minimum of five are selected for each spending category. US companies with relevant exposure to these categories are scored by the level of their exposure. Firms determined to have significant exposure to the stated spending categories are then scored by a proprietary scale that determines which companies have a higher focus on millennials. These selected companies are weighted by market cap, with a maximum of 3% and a minimum of .3% for any given holding. The index undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalance.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx Millennials Thematic Index. The fund invests more than 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to the millennial generation consumption trends, (collectively, "Millennial Companies"), as defined by the index provider. The millennial generation refers to the demographic in the U.S. with birth years ranging from 1980 to 2000.

name: Global X Cannabis ETF
merged_description: This investment product provided focused exposure to developed market companies active in the cannabis, hemp, and CBD sectors by tracking a specific index from Solactive AG. The underlying index targeted legally-operating, exchange-listed firms, primarily selecting pure-play companies deriving significant business (at least 50% revenue, earnings, or assets) from cannabis-related activities like production, distribution, supporting financial services, or pharmaceutical applications. Uniquely, it also included a selection of pre-revenue companies anticipated to meet these criteria in the future. Companies were selected and weighted based on market capitalization, with the portfolio typically holding the top 40 pure-play and top 10 pre-revenue firms, rebalanced quarterly. The fund, which invested primarily in the index constituents (including ADRs/GDRs) and was non-diversified, ceased trading and was delisted on February 16, 2024.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies that are active in the cannabis industry (collectively, " Cannabis Companies"), as defined by Solactive AG, the provider of the underlying index ("index provider"). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
POTX tracks an index of developed market companies related to cannabis, hemp & CBD.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is on February 16, 2024. POTX offers straightforward exposure to cannabis equities in developed markets. The funds underlying index targets pure-play firms of any capitalization with at least 50% of revenue, earnings or assets in the production and distribution of cannabis & hemp, financial services that support the industry, and pharmaceutical applications. The index also has a forward-looking aspect: companies expected to meet these conditions in the future are eligible, and are classified in a pre-revenue category. The language emphasizes that all firms must be publicly-traded, legally-operating businesses. Stocks are selected and weighted based on market-cap, with the 40 highest ranked pure-play firms and 10 highest ranked pre-revenue firms included in the portfolio. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.

name: First Trust Dow Jones International Internet UCITS ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to replicate the performance of an index focused on non-U.S. companies whose primary business is internet-related, investing at least 90% of its assets in the constituent common stocks and depositary receipts tracked by this S&P Dow Jones Indices-sponsored benchmark. Its strategy specifically targets 40 of the largest international firms in the space, equally divided between two distinct groups: 20 leaders in internet commerce (including online retail, advertising, and streaming) and 20 top providers of internet services (such as access, infrastructure, cloud software, and related equipment). Utilizing a market-cap weighting approach with a 10% cap on individual holdings, the fund provides concentrated exposure, resulting in a non-diversified portfolio heavily weighted towards large-cap stocks, which is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is developed, maintained and sponsored by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. The index is designed to measure the performance of securities of non-U.S. issuers whose primary business focus is Internet-related. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FDNI offers reasonable exposure to global ex-US internet firms. The fund divides eligible companies into two groups: internet commerce and internet services. Internet commerce firms provide goods and services through the internet, including online retail, advertising, publishing, gaming, and content streaming. Meanwhile, internet service firms provide internet access or other internet-related products or services, such as e-commerce infrastructure, cloud software, and telecom equipment. FDNI holds 40 names20 of the largest in each group. This produces a somewhat narrow view of the market, with heavy large-cap exposure. The fund is also market-cap-weighted, with individual weights capped at 10%. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks the results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund’s fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Dow Jones International Internet Index (the “index”). The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is developed, maintained and sponsored by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. The index is designed to measure the performance of securities of non-U.S. issuers whose primary business focus is Internet-related. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Virtus Duff & Phelps Clean Energy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks capital appreciation by investing globally, allocating at least 80% of its net assets to equity securities of clean energy companies. Eligible companies derive a significant portion (at least 50%) of their value—assessed through metrics like revenue, profits, and assets dedicated to clean energy—from activities such as clean energy production, providing related technology and equipment, or energy transmission and distribution across various sectors including utilities, industrials, and technology. The portfolio is constructed using a bottom-up, fundamental research approach that evaluates investment outlook, regulatory factors, and financial health. Although the fund is non-diversified, individual stock positions are capped at 10%.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of clean energy companies. The sub-adviser defines clean energy companies as those that derive at least 50% of their value from one or more of the following clean energy businesses: (a) the production of clean energy; (b) the provision of clean energy technology and equipment; or (c) the transmission and distribution of clean energy. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
VCLN is an actively managed fund that invests in clean energy companies from around the world.

VCLN is actively managed to provide exposure to clean energy stocks from around the world. Companies from utilities, industrials, technology, and energy sectors should have at least 50% of their value in three clean energy business segments: (1) clean energy production, (2) provision of technology and equipment, and (3) transmission and distribution of clean energy. In identifying these businesses, stocks are evaluated based on their reported/estimated revenue, profits, assets, and capital expenditures dedicated to clean energy. A bottom-up, research-driven process is then employed to select the final portfolio. The fund identifies superior clean energy stocks using an in-depth fundamental business analysis, which includes a qualitative and quantitative assessment of investment outlook, regulatory and political events, and financial strength. Individual stocks are capped at 10%.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of clean energy companies. The sub-adviser defines clean energy companies as those that derive at least 50% of their value from one or more of the following clean energy businesses: (a) the production of clean energy; (b) the provision of clean energy technology and equipment; or (c) the transmission and distribution of clean energy. It is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Exchange-Traded Fund Trust II - SandP 500 High Dividend Growers Etf
merged_description: This passively managed ETF targets potential future dividend growth within the S&P 500, investing in the top 100 companies selected for the highest forecasted dividend yield growth. Eligibility requires a positive forecasted yield and a minimum five-year history of stable or increasing dividends. Distinctively, the portfolio weights its holdings based on forecasted dividend yield, differing from traditional backward-looking approaches. While implementing constraints like a 4% cap on individual stocks and a 30% cap on sectors, and rebalancing semi-annually, the fund invests at least 90% of its assets in its underlying index components and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: DIVG is passively managed to invest in US companies that have both consistent dividends historically and have high forecasted dividend yield growth. The underlying index screens eligible stocks from the S&P 500 Index. To be considered for inclusion, a stock must have a positive forecasted dividend yield and increased or maintained dividends for at least five consecutive years. The top 100 companies with the highest forecasted dividend yield growth are included in the portfolio. In a similar fashion, the index uses dividend yield forecasts for weighting instead of backward-looking dividend data. Constituents are weighted according to their forecasted dividend yield, with single issuer weights capped at 4% and GICS sector weights at 30%. The index rebalances semi-annually in April and October.
description_etfcom:
DIVG tracks a yield-weighted index of 100 companies in the S&P 500 with the highest forecasted dividend yield growth.

DIVG is passively managed to invest in US companies that have both consistent dividends historically and have high forecasted dividend yield growth. The underlying index screens eligible stocks from the S&P 500 Index. To be considered for inclusion, a stock must have a positive forecasted dividend yield and increased or maintained dividends for at least five consecutive years. The top 100 companies with the highest forecasted dividend yield growth are included in the portfolio. In a similar fashion, the index uses dividend yield forecasts for weighting instead of backward-looking dividend data. Constituents are weighted according to their forecasted dividend yield, with single issuer weights capped at 4% and GICS sector weights at 30%. The index rebalances semi-annually in April and October.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the underlying index, which is designed to measure the performance of a subset of companies within the S&P 500® Index that have the highest forecasted dividend yield growth. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P 500® High Dividend Growth Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the underlying index, which is designed to measure the performance of a subset of companies within the S&P 500® Index that have the highest forecasted dividend yield growth. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity MSCI Consumer Staples Index ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to provide returns that generally correspond to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index, offering focused exposure to the U.S. consumer staples sector as defined by GICS classifications. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities, which are selected and weighted based on market capitalization, though it may not hold every constituent security. The underlying index employs a 25/50 capping methodology, limiting individual group entity weights to 25% and ensuring that the combined weight of all issuers exceeding 5% does not surpass 50% of the index. Reflecting its concentration in a single sector, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the consumer staples sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FSTA is one of ten Fidelity ETFs that track MSCI sector indexes. The fund offers exposure to the consumer staples sector as defined by the GICS sector classification scheme. Like competitor VDC, FSTA tracks an index that uses GICS to define sectors, then selects and weights the stocks by market-cap. To meet diversification requirements, the funds underlying index employs a capping methodology, such that no group entity exceeds 25% of index weight and the aggregate weight of issuers with over 5% weight in the index are capped at 50% weight of the portfolio. Prior to December 1, 2020, FSTA tracked the unconstrained MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples Index.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the consumer staples sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the consumer staples sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Consumer Staples 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: SPDR Dow Jones Global Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This fund seeks to mirror the performance of a float-adjusted, market-capitalization-weighted global index focused on publicly traded real estate securities. Investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent securities and related depositary receipts, it offers diversified exposure across the market-cap spectrum with over 200 holdings. The portfolio primarily includes commercial and residential REITs, specialized real estate firms, and operators from the US, developed, and emerging markets, though it tends to favor REITs over developers and often carries a significant allocation to the United States. Companies eligible for inclusion must primarily own and operate real estate assets, deriving substantial revenue from these activities and meeting minimum size requirements. The underlying index undergoes quarterly reviews.
description_original: The SPDR Dow Jones Global Real Estate ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the Dow Jones Global Select Real Estate Securities IndexSM (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the publicly traded real estate securities in the U.S., as well as, developed and emerging marketsFor inclusion in the index, companies must be both an equity owner and operator of commercial and/or residential real estate, have a minimum float adjusted market capitalization of at least $200 million, derive at least 75% of its total revenue from the ownership and operation of real estate assets
description_etfcom:
RWO tracks a cap-weighted index of global REITs and real estate companies. The fund invests across the market-cap spectrum.

RWO provides diversified exposure to the global real estate industry, with its 200+ holdings spanning multiple sectors, including commercial and residential REITs, real estate developers, specialized REITs, and investment management fund operators. The fund tilts significantly toward commercial REITs, while shying away from real estate developers. While global in nature, RWO overweights the US while being a bit light on Asia coverage. Overall, RWO can boast strong global real estate exposure. The index is reviewed quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is a float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to measure the performance of publicly traded global real estate securities.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the Dow Jones Global Select Real Estate Securities Indexsm based upon the global real estate market. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is a float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to measure the performance of publicly traded global real estate securities.

name: Xtrackers S&P ESG Dividend Aristocrats ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund aims to mirror the performance of an index targeting U.S. companies known for consistent dividend growth and adherence to specific responsibility criteria. Constituents are selected from the S&P High Yield Dividend Aristocrats universe, requiring at least 20 consecutive years of annual dividend increases. These companies are further screened based on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors, including S&P DJI ESG scores, involvement in controversies, exclusion of certain business activities, and alignment with UN Global Compact principles. The portfolio is weighted by indicated annual dividend yield, subject to capping and liquidity rules, and undergoes annual rebalancing with quarterly reviews. Characterized as non-diversified, the strategy focuses on providing exposure to high-yielding stocks with a strong history of dividend growth that also meet defined sustainability standards.
description_original: The fund, using a "passive" or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of constituents from the S&P High Yield Dividend Aristocrats Index that meet certain environmental, social and governance ("ESG") criteria. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SNPD is a passively managed fund of companies that have consistently increased dividends while meeting certain ESG criteria. Starting with an initial universe of US companies across all market sizes, the fund considers stocks that have annual dividend increases for at least 20 years. The fund then excludes stocks that have no or low S&P DJI ESG scores. Furthermore, firms involved in relevant ESG controversies and specific business activities, as well as those against the principles of UN Global Compact, are screened out. The portfolio is weighted by their indicated annual dividend yield, subject to capping and liquidity constraints. The indicated annual dividend yield is measured by multiplying the latest dividend payment by the annual frequency of payments. The index is reviewed quarterly and rebalanced annually. On February 10, 2025, both the fund and its index dropped and replaced ESG name claims with Scored and Screened. The change has no effect on the funds strategy.
description_yahoo: The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of constituents from the S&P High Yield Dividend Aristocrats Index that meet certain environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) criteria. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P ESG High Yield Dividend Aristocrats Index. The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of constituents from the S&P High Yield Dividend Aristocrats Index that meet certain environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) criteria. It is non-diversified.

name: SP Funds S&P Global REIT Sharia ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to track the performance of a market-cap-weighted index comprising global Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) that adhere to Sharia principles. It provides exposure to REITs listed in both developed and emerging markets, which are rigorously screened for compliance with Islamic religious law. This involves assessing factors like debt levels and permissible income sources, while excluding businesses engaged in prohibited activities such as gambling, alcohol, or tobacco. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in these selected Sharia-compliant REITs, is rebalanced monthly, and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The index includes all REIT securities listed in developed and emerging markets and included as constituents of the S&P Global BMI Shariah Index, a comprehensive global Sharia-compliant index of publicly-traded equity securities. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in the component securities of the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
SPRE tracks a market-cap-weighted index of Shariah-compliant global REITs.

SPRE is passively managed to provide exposure to all Shariah-compliant constituents of the broader S&P Global REIT universe. The underlying index considers all REIT securities listed in both developed and emerging markets that meet minimum market-cap and trading value requirements. Securities are then screened for compliance with Islamic religious laws, such as: maintaining lower debt levels, permissible income below acceptable levels and maintain prescribed cash or asset levels. In addition, the index removes securities involved in business activities that are not Shariah-compliant such as gambling, alcohol, or tobacco. The underlying index is rebalanced and reconstituted monthly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P Global All Equity REIT Shariah Capped Index. The index includes all REIT securities listed in developed and emerging markets and included as constituents of the S&P Global BMI Shariah Index, a comprehensive global Sharia-compliant index of publicly-traded equity securities. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in the component securities of the index. It is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Technology ETF
merged_description: This investment fund focuses on the information technology sector by investing at least 90% of its assets in the components of an underlying index. This index includes common stocks of all companies within the S&P 500® classified under the information technology sector according to GICS standards. Uniquely, the fund tracks an *equal-weighted* version of this index, meaning each technology stock receives the same allocation, regardless of its market capitalization. This approach contrasts sharply with market-cap weighted funds, resulting in significantly less concentration in mega-cap tech stocks and potentially leading to different sector exposures, such as higher weights in areas like semiconductors and lower weights in software & IT services compared to traditional benchmarks. The portfolio is rebalanced quarterly to maintain its equal-weight structure.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Information Technology Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the information technology services sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_etfcom:
RSPT tracks an equal-weighted index of S&P 500 technology companies.

RSPT provides broad coverage of large technology companies but its equal-weighting scheme skews it away from having a market-like portfolio. A pure market-cap benchmark would invest heavily in its top securities, which are the mega-caps in the tech industry. Instead, RSPT allocates only a fraction of its overall assets to its top ten holdings. This produces sector tilts such as an overweight to semiconductors and an underweight to software & IT services. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYT.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Information Technology Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the information technology services sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: ALPS / Kotak India ESG Fund - Investor
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital appreciation, this fund focuses its investments primarily on Indian companies, integrating Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) criteria into its selection process. It commits, under normal market conditions, to investing at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings) in a diverse range of equity and equity-linked securities of these Indian firms. The portfolio spans companies across all market capitalization sizes and may include common stocks, preferred stocks, convertible securities, rights, and warrants.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity and equity-linked securities of “Indian companies.” Equity securities in which the fund can invest may include common stocks, preferred stocks, convertible securities, rights and warrants to buy common stocks. The Advisor intends to invest in companies of all capitalization sizes.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity and equity-linked securities of “Indian companies.” Equity securities in which the fund can invest may include common stocks, preferred stocks, convertible securities, rights and warrants to buy common stocks. The Advisor intends to invest in companies of all capitalization sizes.

name: Themes Airlines ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund aims to track the performance of a concentrated index representing the global airline industry, focusing specifically on the largest companies by market capitalization within developed markets. The underlying index selects approximately the top 30 eligible companies, emphasizing those deriving significant revenue from airline operations, and weights them using a free-float adjusted market capitalization methodology. Adhering to its investment objective, the fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising this index, including associated American and Global Depositary Receipts. Reflecting its targeted approach, the portfolio is non-diversified, offering concentrated exposure to the sector, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing; it may also lend out a portion of its securities.
description_original: The index is a free float adjusted, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the airlines industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
AIRL seeks to track a concentrated index of the largest airline stocks from developed markets. Stocks are weighted based on market capitalization.

AIRL is passively managed, providing targeted exposure to the largest companies, by market capitalization, in the airline industry. In order to be considered for inclusion, a company must generate at least 50% of its revenue from the industry, define by RIBCS. All eligible securities are ranked and weighted by their market capitalization, selecting the top 30 names for inclusion in the index. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly bases in February, May, August, and November. Additionally, the fund may lend securities representing up to one-third of its total assets.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive Airlines Index. The index is a free float adjusted, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the airlines industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: VanEck Retail ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers concentrated exposure to the retail sector by aiming to replicate the performance of a market-cap-weighted index comprising the 25 largest US-listed companies deriving at least 50% of their revenues from retail. Eligible companies span various retail segments, including distribution, wholesale, online, direct mail, TV, multi-line, specialty, and food/staples retailing. While focused on US-listed entities, the portfolio often consists of dominant global giants, thereby providing significant exposure to major worldwide retail operations. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index, is considered non-diversified due to its narrow holding base, and follows a semi-annual index review process.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. To be initially eligible for the index, companies must generate at least 50% of their revenues from retail. Retail includes companies engaged primarily in retail distribution; wholesalers; online, direct mail and TV retailers; multi-line retailers; specialty retailers; and food and other staples retailers. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
RTH tracks a market-cap-weighted index of the 25 largest US-listed companies that derive most of their revenue from retail.

RTH provides a different yet comprehensive take on retailers. The fund's claim of global scope is limited by its objective of only investing in companies also listed in the United States. RTH began tracking a new, capped index in December 2011, but still retains the concentrated exposure typical of its HOLDRS roots. Investors looking for exposure to global retailers will find concentrated exposure to US retail giants that dominate worldwide. The fund's exposure makes it less risky than our global benchmark, making RTH a relatively safe place to get exposure to the retail space. The index is reviewed semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® US Listed Retail 25 Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. To be initially eligible for the index, companies must generate at least 50% of their revenues from retail. Retail includes companies engaged primarily in retail distribution; wholesalers; online, direct mail and TV retailers; multi-line retailers; specialty retailers; and food and other staples retailers. The fund is non-diversified.

name: VanEck ETF Trust
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of the MarketVector™ US Listed Office and Commercial REITs Index, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent securities. It offers focused exposure to the U.S. office and commercial real estate sectors by targeting the top 25 REITs listed on U.S. exchanges within these categories. The selection process ranks eligible REITs based on criteria including free-float market capitalization and liquidity, prioritizing Office REITs to reach the target count of 25 holdings. The underlying index utilizes a tiered, modified float-adjusted market-cap weighting methodology, applying constraints such as a 10% maximum weight per security and a 20% aggregate cap for certain commercial REITs. Although its index incorporates weighting rules, the fund itself is classified as non-diversified and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in Office and Commercial Real Estate Companies. The index is comprised of equity securities of Office and Commercial Real Estate Companies and is intended to give investors a means of tracking the overall performance of U.S exchange-listed real estate investment trusts ("REITs") involved in the office and commercial real estate markets. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DESK tracks a tiered modified market-cap weighted index composed of US-listed Office and Commercial REITs. The fund targets the top 25 highest ranked Office and Commerical REITs based on market cap and liquidity.

DESK strives to replicate a US index focused on office and commercial real estate investment trusts (REITs). REITs must satisfy market cap and revenue criteria to be eligible for inclusion. They are then ranked via a two-step process, each relying on the free-float market cap and three-month average daily trading volume of the stocks respectively. Securities are then grouped within Office and Commerical REITS and ranked again based on the sum of their ranks in each of the categories mentioned above. The top 25 Office REITs constitute the index, complemented by the top Commerical REITS if needed. The index maintains a target coverage of 25 companies at all times. It also follows a range tiered modified float-adjusted market-cap weighting scheme, capping security weight at 10% and the aggregate weight of Other Commerical REITs at 20%. A 5%-50% rule is also imposed to ensure diversification. The index undergoes quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of MarketVector™ US Listed Office and Commercial REITs Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in Office and Commercial Real Estate Companies. The index is comprised of equity securities of Office and Commercial Real Estate Companies and is intended to give investors a means of tracking the overall performance of U.S exchange-listed real estate investment trusts ("REITs") involved in the office and commercial real estate markets. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ALPS International Sector Dividend Dogs ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to mirror the performance of a rules-based index targeting high dividend-yielding stocks, often referred to as "Dividend Dogs," from developed international equity markets, excluding North America. It specifically applies a modified "Dividend Dogs" strategy by selecting the five companies with the highest dividend yields within each of the ten major economic sectors from its eligible universe. This methodology results in an equal-weighted portfolio of approximately 50 holdings, designed to provide significant dividend yield while maintaining balanced sector exposure and mitigating biases common in traditional yield strategies. The underlying index undergoes annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund seeks investment results that replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index is a rules-based index intended to give investors a means of tracking the overall performance of the highest dividend paying stocks (i.e. "Dividend Dogs") in the S-Network Developed Markets (ex NA) Index.
description_etfcom:
IDOG tracks an equal-weighted index that selects the five companies with the highest dividend yield in each of the 10 GICS sectors from international developed markets.

IDOG launched at the end of June 2013 with a mandate to provide a high dividend yield from a portfolio of stocks with a balanced sector profile. The idea is to apply a modified version of the Dogs of the Dow strategy to a global universe of stocks. The term global is also modified, as IDOG only selects stocks from developed economies, excluding the US and Canada. The fund takes the 5-highest-yielding stocks from each of the 10 major sectors, for a total of 50 holdings. The goal is to eliminate the counter-cyclical sector biases present in traditional yield-weighted dividend strategies by picking the same number of stocks from each sector. The Underlying Index is reconstituted annually with quarterly rebalance. The fund's sibling fund, SDOG, applies the same strategy to the S&P 500.
description_yahoo: The fund seeks investment results that replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index is a rules-based index intended to give investors a means of tracking the overall performance of the highest dividend paying stocks (i.e. "Dividend Dogs") in the S-Network Developed International Equity 1000 Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the performance of the S-Network® International Sector Dividend Dogs Index. The fund seeks investment results that replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index is a rules-based index intended to give investors a means of tracking the overall performance of the highest dividend paying stocks (i.e. "Dividend Dogs") in the S-Network Developed International Equity 1000 Index.

name: Tema ETF Trust - Tema Luxury ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term growth by investing primarily in a global portfolio of companies providing luxury goods and services, characterized by their premium pricing due to high quality and craftsmanship.
