The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 200% of the daily performance of the MVIS Global Junior Gold Miners Index. The index tracks the performance of domestic and foreign, including developing and emerging, small- and mid-capitalization companies that are involved in the gold and silver mining industry. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.

name: Global X Interest Rate Hedge ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified fund seeks to provide a hedge against sharp increases in long-term U.S. interest rates and potentially benefit from periods of heightened interest rate volatility or market stress. Its investment strategy primarily involves using derivative instruments, specifically focusing on long interest rate payer swaptions (often over-the-counter contracts based on the 10-year swap rate with relatively short expirations) and/or long put options on U.S. Treasury ETFs or futures. Typically, the portfolio holds a substantial portion in cash equivalents while allocating a smaller percentage (around 15%, potentially up to 25%) to these derivative positions, aiming to achieve a short-term inverse correlation to long-term Treasury bonds and a positive correlation with movements in longer-term interest rates.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange traded fund that seeks to achieve its investment objective primarily by investing in (1) long put options position(s) on exchange traded funds that primarily invest in U.S. Treasuries and/or long put options position(s) on U.S. Treasury futures, and/or (2) long interest rate payer swap options (“swaptions”). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
RATE is an actively managed fund, using over-the-counter swaptions, which seeks to provide a hedge against sharp increases in long-term US interest rates. The fund is also expected to benefit during periods of market stress when interest rate volatility rises.

RATE aims to provide a tactical hedge against sharply rising long-term interest rates while positioning the portfolio to benefit during periods of increased interest rate volatility. While the fund has the ability to use put options on US Treasury ETFs and/or Treasury futures, the portfolio typically consists of 85% cash equivalent collateral and 15% payer swaption contracts. The swaption exposure may fluctuate up to 25%. Swaption contracts are based on the 10-year rate swap and typically have less than a year to expiration. Contracts are typically out-of-the-money when purchased, subjecting the fund to some interest rate risk. The 10-year rate swap is benchmarked to the 10-Year Secured Overnight Financing Rate (SOFR). As such, strategy looks to produce a short-term inverse correlation to long-term treasury bonds and a high correlation to longer-dated interest rate movements. Global X actively manages the portfolio. Prior to November 14, 2022, the fund traded under the ticker IRHG.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide a hedge against sharp increases in long-term U.S. interest rates and is expected to benefit during periods of market stress when interest rate volatility is elevated. The fund is an actively managed exchange traded fund that seeks to achieve its investment objective primarily by investing in (1) long put options position(s) on exchange traded funds that primarily invest in U.S. Treasuries and/or long put options position(s) on U.S. Treasury futures, and/or (2) long interest rate payer swap options (“swaptions”). The fund is non-diversified.

name: SPDR Portfolio S&P 500 High Dividend ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers focused exposure to high dividend-yielding stocks within the US large-cap equity space by tracking an index composed of the 80 highest-yielding companies selected from the S&P 500 Index, which includes common stocks and REITs. Its straightforward strategy selects constituents based purely on indicated yield, without incorporating dividend quality or sustainability screens, and then equally weights these holdings. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index, the fund aims to provide a high level of dividend income alongside the potential for capital appreciation, often positioned as a low-cost, core portfolio component.
description_original: The SPDR Portfolio S&P 500 High Dividend ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P 500 High Dividend Index (the “Index”)A low cost ETF that seeks to provide a high level of dividend income and the opportunity for capital appreciationThe Index is designed to measure the performance of the top 80 high dividend-yielding companies within the S&P 500 IndexOne of the low cost core SPDR Portfolio ETFs, a suite of portfolio building blocks designed to provide broad, diversified exposure to core asset classes
description_etfcom:
SPYD tracks an index of the 80 highest-yielding stocks selected from the S&P 500. Stocks are equally-weighted.

SPYD offers a no-nonsense approach to high yield in the US large-cap space. The fund ranks all dividend payers in the S&P 500 by indicated yield (the most recent dividend, multiplied by dividend frequency, divided by share price) and selects the top 80. SPYD does not include any of the dividend sustainability or quality screens that are baked into some peer ETFs. SPYD equally weights its portfolio while some similar, income-focused funds weight by yield. It is worth noting that SPYD is placed in the large-cap segment due to its S&P 500 univers.
description_yahoo: Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of 80 high dividend-yielding companies within the S&P 500® Index. The S&P 500 Index focuses on the large capitalization U.S. equity market, including common stock and real estate investment trusts ("REITs").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the S&P 500 High Dividend Index. Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of 80 high dividend-yielding companies within the S&P 500® Index. The S&P 500 Index focuses on the large capitalization U.S. equity market, including common stock and real estate investment trusts ("REITs").

name: Pacer Nasdaq International Patent Leaders ETF
merged_description: This strategy-driven exchange-traded fund aims to capture international growth by investing in innovative non-US companies distinguished by their valuable patent portfolios. It tracks a rules-based, market capitalization-weighted index drawn from a global ex-US large- and mid-cap universe. A proprietary methodology, utilizing third-party data and considering factors like R&D spending and intellectual property, estimates the dollar value of each company's patent holdings to select the top 100 constituents for the index. The fund typically employs a replication strategy, investing in all components of its underlying index, which rebalances semi-annually. Due to its focus on patent leaders, the fund is non-diversified, potentially leading to increased concentration in specific sectors or countries.
description_original: A strategy-driven exchange traded fund that seeks to capture international growth by tracking the top 100 ranked companies by patent valuation from an index universe of large & midcap non-US companies.
description_etfcom: PATN uses a different measure to invest in innovative companies, patent valuations. Companies are initially screened from a global ex-US large- and midcap stock index for research and development spending and patents held. Patent portfolios are ranked and valued by a third-party data provider. Using a proprietary methodology, each company is evaluated based on intangible assets, such as intellectual property, research and development activities, and patents held. The process includes data from patent offices, corporate filings, economic data, and actual values from previously traded patents. The valuation model provides an estimated dollar value for each companys patent portfolio. The top 100 stocks, based on patent portfolio value, are selected for the funds underlying index. The fund is non-diversified, therefore more assets may be concentrated within certain sectors and countries. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually in June and December.
description_yahoo: The index is a rules-based full market capitalization-weighted index that consists of companies from the Nasdaq Global Ex United States Large Mid Cap Index with the most valuable patent portfolios. The fund will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it will invest in all of the component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Nasdaq International Patent Leaders Index. The index is a rules-based full market capitalization-weighted index that consists of companies from the Nasdaq Global Ex United States Large Mid Cap Index with the most valuable patent portfolios. The fund will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it will invest in all of the component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares U.S. Tech Breakthrough Multisector ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on U.S.-listed companies engaged in cutting-edge research and development expected to drive technological breakthroughs. It tracks a rules-based, modified market-cap-weighted index, selecting firms significantly involved in five key thematic areas: robotics and artificial intelligence, cybersecurity, cloud and data technology, financial technology, and genomics and immunology. Company selection involves specific criteria including market cap, liquidity, and revenue derivation, with a distinct process using semantic search algorithms for the genomics and immunology segment. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the index components or similar investments, employs weighting limits for both individual securities and thematic segments, and is classified as non-diversified. The underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The underlying index measures the performance of U.S. listed companies engaged in cutting edge research and development of products and services in the areas of robotics and artificial intelligence, cyber security, cloud and data tech, financial technology, and genomics and immunology. It generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
TECB tracks an index of US equities that could benefit from breakthrough technologies, modified market cap weighted.

TECB tracks a rules-based equity index of US-listed companies engaged in the research and development of products and services in one of five thematic segments: (i) robotics and artificial intelligence, (ii) cyber security, (iii) cloud and data tech, (iv) financial technology, and (v) genomics and immunology. Companies are grouped based on RBICS. Eligible securities must meet market cap and ADTV requirements and significant revenue must be derived from specific themes, with an additional screen to the Genomics and Immunology theme. The index uses automated semantic search algorithms to identify supply chain relationships in the Genomics and Immuno Biopharmaceutical segment. A composite relationship score for each stock in the segment is calculated with the top 50 being selected. Weighting of the portfolio is a mix of segment weight, set at a minimum of 10%, and individual security, set at a maximum of 4%. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced semiannually.
description_yahoo: The underlying index measures the performance of U.S. listed companies engaged in cutting edge research and development of products and services in the areas of robotics and artificial intelligence, cyber security, cloud and data tech, financial technology, and genomics and immunology. It generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE® FactSet® U.S. Tech Breakthrough IndexTM. The underlying index measures the performance of U.S. listed companies engaged in cutting edge research and development of products and services in the areas of robotics and artificial intelligence, cyber security, cloud and data tech, financial technology, and genomics and immunology. It generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index.

name: First Trust Strategic Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund focuses on achieving capital appreciation alongside higher dividend income compared to broad market benchmarks by investing primarily in U.S. companies. Guided by a sub-adviser, it allocates at least 80% of its assets to equities of firms that not only pay dividends but are also expected to grow these dividends over time. The fund employs a quantitative screening methodology to construct its portfolio, typically comprising 60-80 securities selected from a universe of U.S. equities meeting specific market capitalization and liquidity requirements, while excluding REITs. This process evaluates companies based on economic strength, dividend payment history, consistency, and future growth potential, aiming to identify financially solid firms with strong dividend track records. Holdings may be categorized and weighted based on dividend growth and stability characteristics, with the portfolio undergoing monthly review and adjustments.
description_original: The fund is a multi-manager, multi-strategy actively managed ETF. Its investment categories will be: (i) high yield corporate bonds, and first lien senior secured floating rate bank loans; (ii) mortgage-related investments; (iii) preferred securities; (iv) international sovereign bonds; (v) equity securities of Energy Infrastructure Companies, certain of which are referred to as master limited partnerships; and (vi) dividend paying U.S. exchange-traded equity securities of companies and depositary receipts.
description_etfcom:
FDIV is actively managed, investing primarily in US companies that are forecasted to raise their dividends. The fund constructs its portfolio using a quantitative dividend screening methodology with the goal of generating above-average income.

FDIV employs a dividend strategy that uses quantitative methods to identify 60-80 companies with higher dividend yields and potential for capital growth. To achieve this, the fund focuses on US companies projected to increase their dividends. The selection process starts by considering a universe of US equity securities that meet the minimum market cap requirement, excluding REITs and organizations with low yield, liquidity and free float. The sub-adviser then assesses the economic strength of the remaining companies, factoring in dividend payment patterns, future growth and consistency over a five-year span to construct its portfolio. This process seeks to isolate firms perceived to have solid financials and a steady track record of paying high dividends. Furthermore, securities are categorized into High Yield Dividend Growth and High Yield Dividend Stability, with corporations ranking in the top 50 of both receiving more weight. FDIVs portfolio is reviewed and adjusted monthly.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that is sub-advised by MarketDesk Indices LLC (“Sub-Adviser”). The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowing for investment purposes, in a portfolio of U.S. companies that pay dividends and expect to grow the dividend over time.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation with a higher dividend yield compared to a broad-based index of U.S. large-cap dividend paying securities. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that is sub-advised by MarketDesk Indices LLC (“Sub-Adviser”). The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowing for investment purposes, in a portfolio of U.S. companies that pay dividends and expect to grow the dividend over time.

name: Main Sector Rotation ETF
merged_description: This actively managed ETF utilizes a "fund of funds" structure, investing primarily in sector-based equity ETFs to implement a dynamic sector rotation strategy. The core investment objective is to outperform the S&P 500 in rising markets while seeking to limit losses during declines. To achieve this, the advisor analyzes macroeconomic factors like growth forecasts and inflation trends, alongside fundamental analysis, to select sectors, industries, or sub-industries deemed undervalued and poised for near-term appreciation due to market catalysts. While primarily focused on US large-cap equities via its underlying holdings, the fund maintains flexibility, allowing up to 20% investment in securities of any market capitalization, country, or currency. The strategy includes selling holdings when price targets are met or they are no longer considered undervalued, and may occasionally incorporate a covered call writing strategy.
description_original: The fund utilizes a "fund of funds" structure to invest in sector-based equity ETFs. It seeks to achieve its objective through dynamic sector rotation. The Adviser focuses its research primarily on sector selection by carefully reviewing the sectors, industries, and sub-industries in the fund's portfolio. The Adviser chooses sectors it believes are undervalued and poised to respond favorably to financial market catalysts. The fund sells a security when it achieves its target price and is, in the opinion of the Adviser, no longer undervalued.
description_etfcom: SECTs active manager aims for outperformance by analyzing economic growth forecasts, inflation trends, and other macroeconomic and capital market fundamentals in order to identify opportunities for near-term price appreciation. This analysis determines allocations to various sectors, industries, and sub-industries. SECT generally focuses on US large-cap equities, and we classify it as such per the issuers claims, however, SECT may hold securities of any market capitalization or country, denominated in any currency, for up to 20% of the portfolio. The Fund may from time to time incorporate a covered call option writing strategy to achieve its goal.
description_yahoo: The fund utilizes a "fund of funds" structure to invest in sector-based equity ETFs. It seeks to achieve its objective through dynamic sector rotation. The Adviser focuses its research primarily on sector selection by carefully reviewing the sectors, industries, and sub-industries in the fund's portfolio. The Adviser chooses sectors the believes are undervalued and poised to respond favorably to financial market catalysts. The fund sells a security when it achieves its target price and is, in the opinion of the Adviser, no longer undervalued.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to outperform the S&P 500 in rising markets while limiting losses during periods of decline. The fund utilizes a "fund of funds" structure to invest in sector-based equity ETFs. It seeks to achieve its objective through dynamic sector rotation. The Adviser focuses its research primarily on sector selection by carefully reviewing the sectors, industries, and sub-industries in the fund's portfolio. The Adviser chooses sectors the believes are undervalued and poised to respond favorably to financial market catalysts. The fund sells a security when it achieves its target price and is, in the opinion of the Adviser, no longer undervalued.

name: iShares U.S. Aerospace & Defense ETF
merged_description: This ETF aims to mirror the performance of a market-cap-weighted index focused on the U.S. aerospace and defense sector, as defined by S&P Dow Jones Indices. It primarily holds U.S. equities from manufacturers, assemblers, and distributors engaged in producing commercial and military aircraft, related parts, and defense equipment like radar and weapons systems, encompassing a mix of large-, mid-, and small-cap companies. Employing a representative sampling strategy, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or similar securities. Although classified as non-diversified with significant concentration risk typical of the sector, it applies weighting caps, limiting individual holdings to 22.5%, and rebalances its underlying index quarterly. Up to 20% of assets may be held in derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents.
description_original: The index measures the performance of the aerospace and defense sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by SPDJI. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
ITA tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US manufacturers, assemblers and distributors of airplane and defense equipment.

ITA tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US-listed manufacturers, assemblers and distributors of aircraft and aircraft parts primarily used in commercial or private air transport and producers of components and equipment for the defense industry, including military aircraft, radar equipment and weapons. The fund caps its holdings to meet diversification requirements, limiting a single company to 22.5% of the funds assets, and preventing completely unbiased exposure to the top few that dominate the industry. Concentration risk remains high despite the caps, reflecting the undiversified nature of the industry. Despite this, ITA still allocates holdings to a mixture of large, mid, and small-cap companies. The fund uses a representative sampling strategy instead of replicating the underlying index. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace & Defense Index composed of U.S. equities in the aerospace and defense sector. The index measures the performance of the aerospace and defense sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by SPDJI. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ERShares Entrepreneur ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund offers exposure to approximately 30 US mid- and large-capitalization companies deemed highly entrepreneurial based on proprietary screening criteria. It primarily invests in equity securities, such as common and preferred stocks along with sponsored ADRs and GDRs, traded on major US exchanges. While actively managed, the strategy largely employs an index-tracking approach for about 85% of its assets, following a specialized index of 30 stocks selected using factors like momentum, growth, value, and leverage. The remaining portion allows for opportunistic investments, potentially including private equity. The portfolio is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly, typically resulting in moderate turnover. Unique features include a potential AUM cap, which could cause the fund to trade like a closed-end fund if reached, and possibly lower fees or related opportunities for major investors. A significant strategy overhaul occurred in late August 2024, shifting the focus and composition, meaning its prior performance record under a different mandate is not indicative of potential future results.
description_original: The fund invests primarily in equity securities of mid and large capitalization companies traded on the NASDAQ, the New York Stock Exchange or other major U.S. exchanges. Equity securities include common stocks, preferred stocks, convertible preferred stocks, American Depositary Receipts (ADRs) (sponsored only) and Global Depositary Receipts (GDRs) (sponsored only). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
XOVR is interesting. Major investors or partners in the receive lower management fees and related P/E opportunities. The fund aims to provide exposure to the top 30 US large-cap, most entrepreneurial stocks, either public or private, selected based on very proprietary measurements.

XOVR places a cap on the AUM for the fund, thus when reached, the fund will trade more like a closed-end fund. Investors should monitor AUM levels. The fund is actively managed but uses roughly 85% of the assets to track an index. The index is computed by the London Stock Exchange, which consists of 30 stocks that meet a minimum threshold for entrepreneurial factors. The index is constructed using a bottom-up analysis of factors such as momentum, sector, growth, value, leverage, market-cap, and geographic orientation. XOVR will hold the majority of its assets in tracking the index, with a balance held in private equity. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly, with 15-20 percent quarterly turnover rate. Important to note, prior to August 29,2024, the fund was actively managed, trading under the ticker ENTR with a focus on US large-cap growth stocks. However, given the changes to composition, portfolio weights, frequency of trades, and the added exposure to private equity, the performance in XOVR is expected to diverge from previous performance.

name: VanEck Oil Refiners ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to replicate the performance of a global index focused specifically on the oil refining industry. It primarily invests (normally at least 80% of assets) in the equity securities and depositary receipts of companies worldwide that generate at least 50% of their revenues from crude oil refining activities, converting crude into products like gasoline, diesel, and jet fuel. The underlying index employs a market-capitalization weighting methodology, limiting the weight of any single company to 8%, thereby offering targeted, "pure-play" exposure to the global refining segment. This fund is considered non-diversified.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes equity securities and depositary receipts of companies in the global oil refining segment. To be initially eligible for the Oil Refiners Index, companies must generate at least 50% of their revenues from crude oil refining. Products of these companies may include gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, fuel oil, naphtha, and other petrochemicals. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CRAK tracks a market-cap index of global stocks issued by firms that earn at least 50% of their revenue from oil refining.

CRAK offers straightforward exposure to global oil refiners, with no direct peers in the global oil sector. CRAK (named for the spread between the input cost of oil and the selling price of refined product) holds stock in firms that generate at least half their revenue from refining operations. Holdings are weighted by market cap, limited to 8% weight each. Thus, the basket meets a reasonable definition of pure-play refinery exposure in an investable wrapper. In all, CRAK does just what it says on the tin: offer vanilla exposure to global oil refiners.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® Global Oil Refiners Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes equity securities and depositary receipts of companies in the global oil refining segment. To be initially eligible for the Oil Refiners Index, companies must generate at least 50% of their revenues from crude oil refining. Products of these companies may include gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, fuel oil, naphtha, and other petrochemicals. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Bitcoin Trend Strategy ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks to provide investment results corresponding to a specific Bitcoin trend-following index, before fees and expenses. Its core strategy involves dynamically allocating assets between long exposure to US exchange-traded Bitcoin futures contracts and short-term US Treasuries. This allocation is determined by a proprietary Bitcoin trend indicator, which uses calculations like exponential moving averages to gauge the trend's presence, direction, and strength. Based on the indicator's value, the fund adjusts its Bitcoin futures exposure anywhere from 0% up to 100%; assets not allocated to futures are invested in US Treasuries, potentially up to 100%. The fund primarily gains its Bitcoin futures exposure through a Cayman Islands subsidiary and invests at least 80% of its assets in index constituents or economically similar securities, including other US-listed Bitcoin Futures ETFs.
description_original: The fund invests least 80% of its total assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in the constituents of the index, and in other securities the Adviser determines have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of the constituents that comprise the underlying index, such as U.S. listed Bitcoin Futures ETFs. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: BTRN tracks an index that seeks to provide long-only exposure to US exchange-traded bitcoin futures contracts or a short-term US Treasury position. The index dynamically allocates between these two positions based on the value of a proprietary bitcoin trend indicator. The indicator aims to detect the presence, direction, and strength of the price trend of bitcoin. A combination of four exponential moving average calculations are considered in order to compute a single value of the average price of bitcoin over explicit periods. Based on this value, the index increases its allocation to bitcoin futures (up to 100%) when the value indicated is higher, and decreases (until 0%) when the value is lower. Any funds assets not allocated to the bitcoin futures position are subsequently allocated to the US Treasurys position, up to 100%. The fund seeks to gain exposure to BTC futures through investments in a Cayman Islands subsidiary.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the CoinDesk Bitcoin Trend Indicator Futures Index. The fund invests least 80% of its total assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in the constituents of the index, and in other securities the Adviser determines have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of the constituents that comprise the underlying index, such as U.S. listed Bitcoin Futures ETFs. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Inspire Global Hope ESG ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to replicate the performance of an index composed of approximately 400 global large-capitalization companies, generally with market capitalizations of $5 billion or greater, selected for alignment with specific biblical values. Investing at least 80% of its assets in index components, the fund utilizes a proprietary scoring system (requiring a score of zero or higher) to screen its universe of domestic, developed foreign, and emerging market equities. The methodology actively excludes companies involved in activities such as abortion, gambling, alcohol, and pornography, while prioritizing those contributing positively to areas like education, disease-fighting, aiding the poor, environmental stewardship, and employee relations. The underlying index targets an allocation of roughly 50% domestic, 40% developed foreign, and 10% emerging market securities, employing an equal-weighting scheme and rebalancing quarterly.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) and domestic equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of companies with a market capitalization of $5 billion or greater and which have an Inspire Impact Score® of zero or higher.
description_etfcom:
BLES follows an equal-weighted index of 400 large-cap stocks selected for their alignment with the Issuer's biblical values.

BLES is a principles-based fund that screens stocks for how closely they line up with biblical values and positive impact on the world, measured through a proprietary scoring system. The methodology starts by screening out companies that have any level of participation in any of the following: abortion, gambling, alcohol, pornography, the LGBT lifestyle, and more. After that filter, the index looks for companies that provide products and services towards education, fighting disease, helping the poor and marginalized, and Christian-themed products as defined by the Issuer. Other criteria are treatment of employees, community involvement, and environment. BLES plans to compose its portfolio as 50% domestic securities, 40% in developed foreign securities, and 10% in emerging market securities. The index is equally weighted and rebalanced quarterly. Between March 30 and August 19, 2022, the fund's name included a reference to 'ESG'. The name changes did not impact the fund strategy.
description_yahoo: The fund generallyinvests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) and domestic equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of large capitalization companies and which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate investment results that generally correspond to the performance of the Inspire Global Hope Index. The fund generallyinvests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) and domestic equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of large capitalization companies and which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.

name: Xtrackers International Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to mirror the performance of a free-float capitalization-weighted index concentrated on international real estate markets. It provides targeted exposure to publicly traded real estate securities, including REITs, across a spectrum of developed and emerging countries, uniquely excluding the United States, Pakistan, and Vietnam. The strategy encompasses companies of all market capitalization sizes. Utilizing a representative sampling approach, the fund generally invests a minimum of 80% of its assets in securities reflecting the risk and return profile of its underlying index, which undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund, using a "passive" or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, of the underlying index, which is a free-float capitalization weighted index that provides exposure to publicly traded real estate securities in countries outside the United States, excluding Pakistan and Vietnam. It will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the underlying index.
description_etfcom:
HAUZ tracks a market-cap weighted index of global real estate stocks, excluding the US, Pakistan, and Vietnam.

HAUZ brings a very specific exposure of international real estate by covering all developed and emerging countries minus the United States, Pakistan, and Vietnam. The fund includes all market-cap sizes and allows for REITs to be among its constituents. Weights are also based on free-float market-cap. HAUZ uses a representative sampling strategy in tracking the index, and will generally invest in a sample of securities whose risk, return and other characteristics match that of the underlying index. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, of the iSTOXX Developed and Emerging Markets ex USA PK VN Real Estate Index (the "underlying index"). The fund, using a "passive" or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, of the underlying index, which is a free-float capitalization weighted index that provides exposure to publicly traded real estate securities in countries outside the United States, excluding Pakistan and Vietnam. It will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the underlying index.

name: SPDR S&P Global Dividend ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to replicate the total return performance of an index focused on global dividend aristocrats. It targets high-yielding companies within the S&P Global BMI universe that have demonstrated a reliable dividend policy, defined by at least ten consecutive years of stable or increasing dividend payments. The strategy selects the top 100 qualifying stocks based on dividend yield and weights them accordingly. Diversification is enforced through rules limiting individual security weights to 3%, restricting country representation to a maximum of 20 stocks and 25% total weight, and capping GICS sector exposure at 25% weight. The fund invests substantially all (at least 80%) of its assets in the securities comprising its underlying index, including depositary receipts, offering focused exposure to established, high-dividend-paying global firms.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Global Dividend ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return of the S&P Global Dividend Aristocrats Index (the “Index”)Seeks to offer exposure to high dividend yielding global firms that follow a managed-dividends policy of having increasing or stable dividends for at least ten consecutive yearsThe Index includes the top 100 qualified stocks with highest indicated dividend yield, with no more than 20 stocks selected from each country and 35 stocks from each GICS sectorThe weight of each Index constituent is capped at 3%, and no single country or GICS sector can be more than 25% of the Index
description_etfcom:
WDIV tracks an index of 100 high-dividend-yielding stocks from the S&P Global BMI Index. Constituents are selected and weighted by dividends.

WDIV aims to find high dividends in the global equity space using the S&P Global Dividend Aristocrats Index, an index that focuses on long-term dividend stability or growth. The selection universe starts with the S&P Global BMI index constituents that have at least 10 consecutive years of increasing or stable dividends. Eligible securities should also meet the market-cap and liquidity screens. The index then selects the top 100 stocks with the highest dividend yield, with no more than 20 stocks from a single country. Selected securities are weighted based on dividends and rebalanced on an annual basis. In addition, the index constituents are reviewed semi-annually, so that no individual security has a weight greater than 3% and no single sector or industry group has more than 25% weight of the portfolio.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of high dividend-yield companies included in the S&P Global BMI that have followed a managed-dividends policy of increasing or stable dividends for at least ten consecutive years.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return of the S&P Global Dividend Aristocrats Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of high dividend-yield companies included in the S&P Global BMI that have followed a managed-dividends policy of increasing or stable dividends for at least ten consecutive years.

name: iShares International Select Dividend ETF
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to high dividend-paying equities from developed international markets, encompassing Europe, the Pacific, Asia, and Canada (EPAC). It seeks to track an index comprising 100 companies selected for their relatively high indicated dividend yields, specifically excluding Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs). The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in these index components or similar investments. A distinctive tiered weighting methodology is employed: countries are first weighted based on their aggregate dividend yield, and subsequently, securities within each country are weighted by their indicated annual dividends, subject to caps on individual holdings, sectors, and countries to manage diversification and turnover. This selection and weighting process, which undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalancing, can lead to significant tilts towards specific sectors, countries, or even mid- and small-cap stocks compared to broader market benchmarks.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of 100 high dividend-paying companies in the EPAC (Europe, the Pacific, Asia and Canada) region.
description_etfcom: IDV holds a portfolio of stable high dividend-paying companies in developed countries of Europe, the Pacific, Asia and Canada. The index selects the top 100 stocks by indicated dividend yield, excluding REITs. Individual holdings, subject to caps and buffers, are designed to diversify geographic exposure and limit turnover. IDV uses a tiered weighting systemcountries are first weighted based on their dividend yields, and then securities are weighted within each country by their indicated annual dividends, subject to constituent, sector and country caps. This process may result in significant sector and country tilts, as well as tilts toward mid- and small-caps. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones EPAC Select Dividend Index composed of relatively high dividend paying equities in non-U.S. developed markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of 100 high dividend-paying companies in the EPAC (Europe, the Pacific, Asia and Canada) region.

name: EventShares U.S. Legislative Opportunities ETF
merged_description: Seeking capital appreciation, this actively managed exchange-traded fund focuses its investment strategy on market segments anticipated to be influenced by U.S. government policy and regulation. It primarily invests in equity securities traded within U.S. markets, maintaining a strong domestic concentration by normally allocating at least 80% of its total assets to securities from U.S.-domiciled issuers. The core concept revolves around capitalizing on potential opportunities arising from legislative or regulatory shifts within the United States.
description_original: The investment seeks capital appreciation by investing in market segments that Active Weighting Advisors LLC (the "Advisor") believes will be impacted by U.S. government policy and regulation. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve its objective of capital appreciation by investing primarily in equity securities traded in the U.S. markets. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of issuers domiciled in the U.S.
description_yahoo:
The investment seeks capital appreciation by investing in market segments that Active Weighting Advisors LLC (the "Advisor") believes will be impacted by U.S. government policy and regulation.
 The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve its objective of capital appreciation by investing primarily in equity securities traded in the U.S. markets. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of issuers domiciled in the U.S.

name: Dimensional - US High Profitability ETF
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital appreciation, this ETF invests in a broad and diverse portfolio of readily marketable securities from large-cap U.S. companies. Employing an active management approach, the advisor selects companies determined to exhibit high profitability relative to their peers, assessing metrics such as cash flow, earnings, or operational profits in relation to book value or assets. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the portfolio's net assets are invested in U.S. companies. Holdings are weighted based on factors including market capitalization, relative price, and profitability characteristics, while short-term criteria like momentum, liquidity, and transaction costs can influence buy and sell decisions. The strategy may utilize derivatives for leverage or cash management and permits securities lending to generate additional income.
description_original: The portfolio is designed to purchase a broad and diverse group of readily marketable securities of large U.S. companies that the Advisor determines to have high profitability relative to other U.S. large cap companies at the time of purchase. As a non-fundamental policy, under normal circumstances, the portfolio will invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of U.S. companies.
description_etfcom:
DUHP invests in a broad and diverse group of large-cap US stocks actively selected based on perceived higher profitability relative to other US large-cap companies.

DUHP utilizes the issuer's expertise in combining research, portfolio design, portfolio management, and trading to generate long-term returns. From the broad US large-cap stock universe, the fund selects companies that are considered to have high profitability. A company is considered to have high profitability based on cash flows, earnings, or profits from operations in relation to its book value or assets. Stocks selected for the portfolio are weighted based on their market capitalization, relative price, and/or profitability characteristics. Buy and sell decisions can be based on short-term criteria such as stock momentum, market liquidity, and transaction costs. The fund may use derivatives to leverage exposure or manage cash. Lending of portfolio securities is permitted to generate additional income.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. The portfolio is designed to purchase a broad and diverse group of readily marketable securities of large U.S. companies that the Advisor determines to have high profitability relative to other U.S. large cap companies at the time of purchase. As a non-fundamental policy, under normal circumstances, the portfolio will invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of U.S. companies.

name: Simplify Volt Cloud and Cybersecurity Disruption ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund concentrated its investments globally within the cloud technology and cybersecurity disruption theme. It maintained a narrow, non-diversified portfolio primarily composed of U.S. and foreign equity securities from companies engaged in this sector, representing at least 80% of its net assets under normal conditions. The strategy also incorporated an option overlay applied to its equity holdings, potentially aiming to leverage performance. Notably, this fund has been delisted and its last day of trading was April 28, 2023.
description_original: The adviser and sub-adviser seek to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing in U.S. and foreign equity securities and equity securities of companies engaging in activities that are consistent with Fund's investment theme of cloud and cybersecurity disruption. The adviser applies an option overlay strategy to the fund's equity investments. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in domestic and foreign securities of companies that are engaged in the fund’s investment theme of cloud and cybersecurity disruption. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
VCLO actively selects a narrow portfolio of companies globally that focus on cloud technology and cybersecurity. The fund may also use options to leverage performance.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 28, 2023. QQD is actively-managed and seeks capital appreciation by primarily investing in ETFs with exposure to the companies listed on the NASDAQ-100 Index. While it does not frequently trade equities, it aims to maintain its exposure to the Index while applying a downside convexity option overlay strategy designed to hedge against market movements and add convexity to the fund. QQD purchases exchange-traded and over-the-counter put options on the Index or an Index ETF of up to 20%, in which selection is based on the Fund Advisers evaluation of relative value, strike price, and maturity. It is worth noting that the funds convexity reflects a non-linear relationship between its returns and that of the market. Moreover, while this strategy is intended to protect the fund from losses, it is not absolutely guaranteed
description_yahoo: The adviser and sub-adviser seek to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing in U.S. and foreign equity securities and equity securities of companies engaging in activities that are consistent with fund's investment theme of cloud and cybersecurity disruption. The adviser applies an option overlay strategy to the fund's equity investments. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in domestic and foreign securities of companies and ETFs that are engaged in the fund’s investment theme of cloud and cybersecurity disruption. It is non-diversified.

name: Teucrium Sugar Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to reflect the daily price changes of sugar futures. It achieves this exposure by investing primarily in sugar futures contracts, utilizing a distinct strategy that involves holding contracts with three different expiration dates simultaneously. This laddered approach is designed specifically to mitigate the adverse effects of contango often associated with rolling front-month futures contracts, differentiating it from simpler index-tracking methods. Structured as a commodities pool, the fund entails specific tax considerations, including the issuance of a K-1 form.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing under normal market conditions in Benchmark Component Futures Contracts. Under normal market conditions, the manager expects that 100% of the fund’s assets will be used to trade Sugar Futures Contracts and invest in cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
CANE tracks an index of sugar futures contracts. It reflects the performance of sugar by holding ICE Futures US sugar futures contracts with three different expiration dates.

CANE reflects the performance of sugar futures contract. It holds three sugar contracts at a time in a laddered fashion to mitigate the effects of contango. This method differentiates the fund from its GSCI benchmark, which holds the front-month futures contract. CANE's strategy can work in its favor should sugar fall into steep contango. The fund's commodities pool structure means a K-1 at tax time and a blended tax rate.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to have the daily changes in the Shares’ NAV reflect the daily changes of the price of sugar for future delivery, as measured by the Teucrium Sugar Index (“TCANE”). The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing under normal market conditions in Benchmark Component Futures Contracts. Under normal market conditions, the manager expects that 100% of the fund’s assets will be used to trade Sugar Futures Contracts and invest in cash and cash equivalents.

name: The Hoya Capital Housing ETF
merged_description: This investment fund provides exposure to the U.S. residential housing sector by tracking a rules-based index composed of 100 companies. Its composition spans four key business segments: home ownership and rental operations; home building and construction; home improvement and furnishings; and home financing, technology, and services. These segments are weighted based on their proportional contribution to U.S. GDP, while the selected top 100 companies within them are equally weighted. Employing a replication strategy to mirror the index, the fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in these housing-related firms and undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index composed of 100 companies that collectively represent the performance of the U.S. residential housing industry. Normally at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in real estate and housing-related companies. It will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it generally will invest in all of the component securities of the index in approximately the same proportion as in the index.
description_etfcom: HOMZ focuses on the US residential housing segment. Constituents of the fund are selected by screening for stocks with significant business operations in one of the four US Housing Industry business segments: 1) home ownership and rental operations, 2) home building and construction, 3) home improvement and furnishings, and 4) home financing, technology & services. The top 100 qualifying companies are included in the funds portfolio. Each of the four segments is weighted based on the proportional contribution to the US GDP, with individual stocks weighted equally within their respective segments. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Hoya Capital Housing 100 TM Index. The index is a rules-based index composed of 100 companies that collectively represent the performance of the U.S. residential housing industry. Normally at least 80% of the fund’s net assets will be invested in real estate and housing-related companies. It will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it generally will invest in all of the component securities of the index in approximately the same proportion as in the index.

name: KraneShares 90% KWEB Defined Outcome January 2026 ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified fund employs a defined outcome strategy centered on an underlying ETF that tracks China internet stocks. It aims to provide investors exposure to the underlying ETF's total return up to a predetermined cap, while offering a substantial buffer against the first 90% of potential downside losses over a specific outcome period, typically lasting two years. The fund achieves this risk-managed exposure primarily by investing at least 80% of its assets in the underlying ETF itself and utilizing options, including FLEX options referencing the ETF. This defined structure, with its corresponding upside cap and downside buffer, resets periodically, usually in January. Potential investors should recognize that the intended outcome is most likely achieved when holding shares for the entire period, the stated cap and buffer levels do not factor in fund expenses, and there is no guarantee the strategy will successfully meet its objectives.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (the “Underlying ETF”) and options, including FLexible EXchange® Options (“FLEX options”) that reference the underlying ETF. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
KBUF seeks to track the total return of the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (KWEB) up to a cap, with a 90% downside hedge over a two-year outcome period. The actively managed fund holds shares of the underlying ETF and options to obtain exposure.

KBUF utilizes a defined outcome strategy on the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (KWEB). It aims to provide long exposure to China internet stocks, up to a cap, while hedging some of the downside risks over a two-year period. The fund primarily invests in KWEB and options, including FLEX options on the underlying ETF. In exchange for preventing the realization of the first 90% of KWEB's losses, investors forego upside participation above a certain threshold. The upside cap and downside buffer reset every other year, in January. The specific defined outcome pursued may only be possible if an investor were to hold the shares for the entire outcome period. There is no guarantee the defined outcome of the strategy pursued will be realized by investors. The issuer publishes effective interim levels daily on its website. The targeted buffers and caps do not include the fund's expense ratio. For comparative purposes, KBUF investors need to double the stated expense ratio of the fund. Following January 24, 2025, KBUF has reset its outcome period and extended it to 2027.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investors with returns that match the total return of the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (the “Underlying ETF”) and options, including FLexible EXchange® Options (“FLEX options”) that reference the underlying ETF. The fund is non-diversified.

name: SPDR S&P Biotech ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to mirror the total return performance of an index representing the U.S. biotechnology sector, drawn from the broader S&P Total Market Index. Utilizing a modified equal-weighting methodology across its constituent securities, it provides exposure to biotechnology firms of various market capitalizations—large, mid, and small. This distinct approach results in less concentrated holdings, reduces single-stock risk, and gives greater emphasis to smaller companies compared to traditional market-cap weighting. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in index components using a sampling strategy, offering targeted, pure-play exposure to biotechnology with minimal pharmaceutical overlap, supported by quarterly index rebalancing.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Biotech ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Biotechnology Select IndustryTM Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the Biotechnology segment of the S&P TMI, which comprises the following sub-industries: BiotechnologySeeks to track a modified equal weighted index which provides the potential for unconcentrated industry exposure across large, mid and small cap stocksAllows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional sector based investing
description_etfcom:
XBI tracks an equal-weighted index of US biotechnology stocks.

XBI provides exposure to US biotech stocks, as defined by GICS, from a universe that invests across the market-cap spectrum. The fund equal-weights its portfolio, which in turn emphasizes small- and micro-caps and greatly reduces single-name risk. Thus, the weighted-average market-cap is much smaller than some competitors. Unlike other funds in this segment, XBI is a pure biotech play, with relatively small pharma overlap. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: In seeking to track the performance of the S&P Biotechnology Select Industry Index (the "index"), the fund employs a sampling strategy. It generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index represents the biotechnology segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Biotechnology Select Industry Index derived from the biotechnology segment of a U.S. total market composite index. The index represents the biotechnology segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").

merged_description: This investment vehicle utilizes a passive indexing approach aimed at tracking the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index/Consumer Staples 25/50. Its portfolio consists of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the consumer staples sector, classified according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The fund seeks to replicate its target index by investing substantially all of its assets in the underlying stocks, maintaining proportions closely aligned with their respective index weightings. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Global Materials ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to track the performance of a global index comprising significant companies within the materials sector, as determined by the index provider. Employing a sampling methodology, the fund invests primarily (at least 80% of assets) in securities mimicking its market-cap-weighted benchmark index. Consequently, the portfolio exhibits a notable large-cap orientation and may be concentrated in dominant multinational corporations within the sector. The fund rebalances quarterly and reserves the option to invest up to 20% of its assets in derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents.
description_original: The index measures the performance of companies that SPDJI deems to be part of the materials sector of the economy and that SPDJI believes are important to global markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
MXI tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global materials companies.

MXI is a basic materials fund that captures the sector-by-sector space reasonably, and its chief departure from the benchmark is in its large-cap tilt and heavy exposure to some industry heavyweights. Like the space it's capturing, MXI is a bit top-heavy with big multinationals dominating its top holdings, so investors must be aware of the funds portfolio before investing. MXI only uses a sampling method, which means it will invest in a sample of securities that collectively have an investment profile similar to that of the underlying index. The index and fund are market-cap-weighted and are rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Global 1200 Materials IndexTM composed of global equities in the materials sector. The index measures the performance of companies that SPDJI deems to be part of the materials sector of the economy and that SPDJI believes are important to global markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.

name: KraneShares 100% KWEB Defined Outcome January 2026 ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund employs a defined outcome strategy centered on an underlying China Internet ETF, investing primarily (at least 80% of net assets) in that ETF and related options, including FLEX options. Its objective is to offer investors upside participation in the underlying ETF's performance, up to a specified cap, while aiming to provide 100% protection against downside losses over a two-year outcome period. In exchange for this downside buffer, investors forgo potential gains beyond the cap. Both the cap and buffer reset biennially in January; following a reset after January 24, 2025, the current outcome period extends into 2027. While the fund seeks this specific outcome, achieving it is not guaranteed and may necessitate holding shares for the entire period. Notably, the targeted buffers and caps do not include the fund's expense ratio, which investors should effectively double for comparative analysis.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (the “Underlying ETF”) and options, including FLexible EXchange® Options (“FLEX options”), that reference the underlying ETF. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: KPRO utilizes a defined outcome strategy on the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (KWEB). It aims to provide long exposure to China internet stocks, up to a cap, while fully hedging downside risk over a two-year period. The fund primarily invests in KWEB and options, including FLEX options, that reference the underlying ETF. In exchange for preventing the realization of 100% of KWEB's losses, investors forego upside participation above a certain threshold. The upside cap and downside buffer reset every other year, in January. The specific defined outcome pursued may only be possible if an investor were to hold the shares for the entire outcome period. However, there is no guarantee the defined outcome of the strategy pursued will be realized by investors. The issuer publishes effective interim levels daily on its website. The targeted buffers and caps do not include the fund's expense ratio. For comparative purposes, KPRO investors need to double the stated expense ratio of the fund. Following January 24, 2025, KPRO has reset its outcome period and extended it to 2027.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investors with returns that match the total return of the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the KraneShares CSI China Internet ETF (the “Underlying ETF”) and options, including FLexible EXchange® Options (“FLEX options”), that reference the underlying ETF. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco MSCI Sustainable Future ETF
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI Global Environment Select Index, generally investing at least 90% of its assets in the underlying securities. The index comprises global companies identified as focusing on products or services that contribute to a more environmentally sustainable economy through the efficient use of limited natural resources. Specifically, included companies derive at least 50% of their revenue from activities related to alternative energy, energy efficiency, green building, sustainable water, pollution prevention and control, or sustainable agriculture. Furthermore, these companies are screened based on ESG controversies, business involvement, and sustainable impact metrics, and the portfolio undergoes quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in the securities of companies that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a custom index comprised of companies that the index methodology has determined focus on offering products or services that contribute to a more environmentally sustainable economy by making a more efficient use of limited global natural resources.
description_etfcom:
ERTH tracks an index of global companies focusing on contributing to a more environmentally sustainable economy.

ERTH holds a portfolio of companies worldwide that are involved in a more efficient use of limited natural resources specifically, they derive 50% or more of their revenue cumulatively from the following six Environmental Impact themes: alternative energy, energy efficiency, green building, sustainable water, pollution prevention and control, as well as sustainable agriculture. Additionally, companies are screened using ESG controversies, ESG business involvement, and sustainable impact metrics. The fund is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to March 24, 2021, the fund traded under a different name (Invesco Cleantech ETF) and ticker (PZD). It also previously tracked the Cleantech Index, which uses a proprietary selection and tiered equal-weighting model.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a custom index comprised of companies that the index provider has determined focus on offering products or services that contribute to a more environmentally sustainable economy by making a more efficient use of limited global natural resources.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the MSCI Global Environment Select Index. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a custom index comprised of companies that the index provider has determined focus on offering products or services that contribute to a more environmentally sustainable economy by making a more efficient use of limited global natural resources.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Income Advantage ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks total return through a combination of current income and long-term capital growth. Its strategy integrates two main elements: equity exposure designed to track the performance of the S&P 500 Equal Weight Index, either through direct stock holdings or via ETFs, and an options-based income strategy. This income component is implemented using equity-linked notes (ELNs) tied to the index or related ETFs, employing covered call and/or cash-secured put strategies intended to generate income and offer some downside protection, while also introducing counterparty risk. The fund manages overall risk by holding a substantial portion of its assets in cash or cash equivalents and through dynamic portfolio adjustments made by the adviser based on market conditions to balance yield, performance, and risk.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by: (1) investing in a portfolio of U.S. equity securities designed to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P 500® Equal Weight Index or U.S.-listed exchange-traded funds (ETFs) that seek to track the performance of the index, or both, and (2) utilizing an options-based income strategy implemented through equity-linked notes (ELNs) with exposure to either the Index or ETFs tracking the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: RSPA seeks to generate income and capitalize on market upsides through a mix of equities and options premiums. For its equity portfolio, the fund invests in equities and US-listed ETFs that aim to replicate the S&P 500 Equal Weight Index, an equal-weighted version of the S&P 500. For its options-based component, RSPA utilizes equity-linked notes (ELNs). These ELNs incorporate covered call and/or cash-secured put strategies, designed to provide income and some downside protection to the declines of its equity portfolio. This approach introduces counterparty risk. To further manage risks, RSPA holds a substantial portion of its assets in cash or cash equivalents, limiting its exposure to the volatility of the equity market. The adviser dynamically adjusts the portfolio based on market conditions to balance yield, performance, and risk. At its launch, the fund provided a fee waiver to attract investors. Prospective investors should review associated expenses before investing.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks total return through current income and long-term growth of capital. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by: (1) investing in a portfolio of U.S. equity securities designed to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P 500® Equal Weight Index or U.S.-listed exchange-traded funds (ETFs) that seek to track the performance of the index, or both, and (2) utilizing an options-based income strategy implemented through equity-linked notes (ELNs) with exposure to either the Index or ETFs tracking the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Cohen & Steers REIT ETF
merged_description: This investment fund provides focused exposure to the U.S. real estate market by tracking an index composed of relatively large and liquid Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs). Its core strategy targets major players anticipated to benefit from potential future industry consolidation and securitization. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in its underlying index components or economically similar investments. Constituent REITs are selected based on criteria including management quality, portfolio strength, and capital structure, then weighted using a free-float adjusted market capitalization methodology, subject to quarterly adjustments and an 8% cap per holding. Due to this targeted approach on realty majors, the fund exhibits notable sub-sector tilts, is classified as non-diversified, and does not represent the entire breadth of the U.S. real estate market.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The objective of the underlying index is to represent relatively large and liquid REITs that may benefit from future consolidation and securitization of the U.S. real estate industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ICF aims to capture the top end of the US real estate market, thanks to its exposure to relatively large and liquid REITs that may benefit from future consolidation and securitization of the industry. Its limited scope also produces notable sub-sector tilts. Index constituents are selected based on a review of several factors including management, portfolio quality, capital structure, as well as sector and geographic diversification. Moreover, these are weighted according to the total free-float adjusted market value of each REITs outstanding shares and are further adjusted quarterly, to ensure that no REIT holds more than 8% weight of the underlying index. Overall, ICF provides access to the realty majors even if it doesn't capture the full flavor of the US real estate market.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Cohen & Steers Realty Majors Index, which consists of REITs. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The objective of the underlying index is to represent relatively large and liquid REITs that may benefit from future consolidation and securitization of the U.S. real estate industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Indxx Global Natural Resources Income ETF
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to the global upstream natural resources sector by tracking an index of the 50 highest dividend-yielding companies in this space. Investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's common stocks and depositary receipts, the fund covers industries such as energy, materials, agriculture, water, and timber, with constraints on individual industry weights. Although global in scope, encompassing developed and emerging markets, it seeks significant non-US allocation and representation from multiple countries. Companies are selected for the index based on their high dividend yield but are weighted according to free-float adjusted market capitalization. As a non-diversified fund, it may hold concentrated positions and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and annual reconstitution.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index.
