The index is a free float adjusted market capitalization weighted index designed to measure the market performance of the 50 highest dividend yielding companies involved in the upstream segment of the natural resources sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FTRI offers exposure to the upstream segment of the natural resources sector, with a bias to dividend payers. Although the fund doesnt limit itself geographically, or between emerging and developed markets, it seeks to allocate 40% of its portfolio to non-US securities and include stocks from a minimum of three countries. The index includes 50 securities across the energy, materials, agriculture, water, and timber industriesas defined by index provider INDXXwith industry weights capped at 30%. FTRI selects stocks by dividend yield within these industries, and weights them by market-cap rather than yield. This at times produces concentrated stakes in top names. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. Note: Until December 2015, this fund tracked a radically different index as the First Trust ISE Global Copper ETF under the ticker CU.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Indxx Global Natural Resources Income Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is a free float adjusted market capitalization weighted index designed to measure the market performance of the 50 highest dividend yielding companies involved in the upstream segment of the natural resources sector. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard Global Environmental Opp StkInv
merged_description: This investment fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by focusing its investments primarily in the stocks of "environmental companies." Under normal circumstances, it commits at least 80% of its net assets, including any borrowings, to these specific equities. The portfolio is constructed globally, encompassing companies from both developed and emerging markets around the world. Notably, the fund may significantly concentrate its investments in particular geographic regions or countries, such as China, and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in stocks of “environmental companies”. It seeks to meet its investment objective by investing in a global portfolio of stocks of companies located in a number of countries throughout the world, including developed and emerging markets. The fund may invest a significant amount of its assets in a select geographic region or a particular country, such as the People’s Republic of China (“China”). It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in stocks of “environmental companies”. It seeks to meet its investment objective by investing in a global portfolio of stocks of companies located in a number of countries throughout the world, including developed and emerging markets. The fund may invest a significant amount of its assets in a select geographic region or a particular country, such as the People’s Republic of China (“China”). It is non-diversified.

name: JPMorgan Sustainable Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified fund invested globally in companies developing sustainable infrastructure solutions, aiming to benefit from related economic shifts. Its portfolio targeted firms across US, foreign, and emerging markets involved in sectors like electricity, renewables, transport, water, digital, sustainable logistics, medical, social housing, and education infrastructure, holding assets such as common stocks, REITs, and depositary receipts, potentially including significant small-cap exposure. The US-domiciled fund utilized a proprietary, multi-step selection process involving thematic relevance scoring, sustainability and exclusion screens, and fundamental bottom-up research to identify companies deemed socially conscious and environmentally responsible. Notably, this security has been delisted, with its last trading day set for March 21, 2025.
description_original: J.P. Morgan Exchange-Traded Fund Trust - JPMorgan Sustainable Infrastructure ETF is an exchange traded fund launched and managed by J.P. Morgan Investment Management Inc. The fund invests in the public equity markets of global region. It invests in stocks of companies operating electricity infrastructure, renewables infrastructure, transport infrastructure, water infrastructure, digital Infrastructure, sustainable logistics, medical infrastructure and social housing and education infrastructure sectors. It invests in stocks of companies that are deemed socially conscious in their business dealings and directly promote environmental responsibility. The fund employs fundamental analysis with bottom-up stock picking approach to create its portfolio. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. J.P. Morgan Exchange-Traded Fund Trust - JPMorgan Sustainable Infrastructure ETF is domiciled in the United States.
description_etfcom:
BLLD is actively managed and seeks to invest in companies from around the world that develop solutions to sustainable infrastructure and are positioned to benefit from those changes.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is March 21, 2025. BLLD actively invests in a portfolio of global companies that develop the infrastructure required to facilitate a sustainable and inclusive economy. The fund includes companies engaged in the sustainable infrastructure theme, which covers electricity, renewables, transport, water, digital, medical, social housing, and education infrastructures, as well as sustainable logistics. Starting with a broad universe of global stocks, the adviser implements a three-step selection process. First, a framework is applied to exclude companies involved in certain business activities or industries. Then, a proprietary system known as ThemeBot ranks stocks according to a thematic exposure score calculated based on textual relevance and revenue attributed to the sub-themes. Lastly, the adviser combines a proprietary sustainable investment inclusion process with fundamental research to select the stocks it believes are best positioned to achieve the funds investment objective.
description_yahoo: The fund invests primarily in common stocks, real estate investment trusts (REITs) and depositary receipts. The fund is not managed to an index and may invest in equity securities in both U.S. and foreign markets, including emerging markets. The fund may invest a significant portion of its assets in small capitalization companies and have significant positions in specific sectors or markets from time to time. It is non-diversified.

name: John Hancock Mortgage Backed Securities ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to generate a high level of current income while aiming to outperform its benchmark over a market cycle by primarily investing in the securitized credit markets. Under normal conditions, it allocates at least 80% of its assets to a diverse range of mortgage-backed securities (MBS), encompassing those issued or guaranteed by U.S. governmental entities as well as privately issued mortgage-related securities. The portfolio focuses predominantly on investment-grade MBS without targeting a specific maturity, although it retains the flexibility to invest up to 20% in non-investment grade securities. Employing a bottom-up strategy that incorporates sector analysis, trend evaluation, and fundamental research for security selection, the fund may also allocate up to 20% of its assets to non-MBS instruments, including other asset-backed securities, Collateralized Loan Obligations (CLOs), and cash equivalents.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in mortgage-backed securities. The fund may invest in mortgage-related securities issued or guaranteed by U.S. governmental entities and privately issued mortgage-related securities. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-mortgage-backed securities including other asset-backed securities and Collateralized Loan Obligations (CLOs) and cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
JHMB is actively managed and primarily invests in investment grade mortgage-backed securities issued or guaranteed by U.S. government and private entities with no specific limit to maturity.

JHMB focuses on the securitized credit markets. The fund actively invests in mortgage-backed securities issued or guaranteed by the US government and private entities. These may include residential and commercial mortgage-backed securities, and to-be-announced mortgaged contracts. The fund does not target a specific average maturity and primarily holds investment grade securities, with up to 20% in non-investment grade securities. JHMB utilizes a bottom-up strategy which looks at a sectors place in the business cycle, forward looking trends, and historical and technical factors to allocate among sectors. Fundamental research is used to individually select undervalued securities. The fund may also invest a small portion into CLOs, other asset-backed securities, nonagency, commercial MBS, and other USD denominated foreign securities.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of current income while seeking to outperform the benchmark over a market cycle. Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in mortgage-backed securities. The fund may invest in mortgage-related securities issued or guaranteed by U.S. governmental entities and privately issued mortgage-related securities. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-mortgage-backed securities including other asset-backed securities and Collateralized Loan Obligations (CLOs) and cash and cash equivalents.

name: Invesco Global Listed Private Equity ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund aims to replicate the investment results of the Red Rocks Global Listed Private Equity Index by investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's constituent securities, including ADRs and GDRs. Its portfolio comprises 40 to 75 globally listed companies involved in the private equity sector, such as business development companies (BDCs), alternative asset managers, master limited partnerships (MLPs), and similar entities. The underlying index employs a modified market-capitalization weighting, adjusting constituent weights based on "purity scores" that assess how closely each company follows a traditional private equity model of acquiring, enhancing, and selling private businesses; firms with less direct private company ownership receive lower scores. The index undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities (including American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs")) that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of securities, ADRs and GDRs of 40 to 75 private equity companies, including business development companies ("BDCs"), master limited partnerships ("MLPs"), alternative asset managers and other entities that are listed on a nationally recognized exchange.
description_etfcom:
PSP tracks a modified market-cap weighted index of publicly listed private equity firms.

PSP is passively managed to hold 40 to 75 securities in the private equity space that includes business development companies, alternative asset managers, master limited partnerships, and other similar vehicles that are listed on any nationally recognized exchange across the globe. The fund adjusts its market capitalization weighting based on purity scores. The scores are based on how companies pursue a private equity business model (buying private companies, enhancing them over 7 to 10 years, and then selling them). Firms such as alternative asset managers, holding companies, and investment banks, which have limited direct ownership of private companies, would receive lower purity scores. The index reconstitutes and rebalances its portfolio quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Red Rocks Global Listed Private Equity Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities (including American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs")) that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of securities, ADRs and GDRs of 40 to 75 private equity companies, including business development companies ("BDCs"), master limited partnerships ("MLPs"), alternative asset managers and other entities that are listed on a nationally recognized exchange.

name: Global X SuperDividend ETF
merged_description: This dividend-seeking fund provides exposure to a global portfolio of 100 equity securities selected for their high dividend yields, sourced from regulated stock exchanges worldwide, including emerging markets. It primarily invests (at least 80% of assets) in the components of its underlying index, utilizing stocks as well as American and Global Depositary Receipts. The selection process incorporates liquidity and stability screens, and the portfolio composition is distinctively equal-weighted across all holdings. This equal weighting is reset through annual rebalancing, while the constituents undergo quarterly reviews to monitor for dividend reductions or changes in dividend policy, ensuring a continued focus on high-yielding opportunities.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index tracks the performance of 100 equally-weighted companies that rank among the highest dividend yielding equity securities in the world, including emerging market countries.
description_etfcom:
SDIV tracks an equal-weighted index of 100 global securities with high yields.

SDIV is a dividend-seeking fund in the global equity market. Selection starts from a universe of companies listed on a regulated stock exchange, including emerging markets. The 100 highest-yielding stocks are chosen, subject to liquidity and stability screens. The index is reviewed quarterly based on dividend cuts or outlook on a companys dividend policy. Removed companies will be replaced by the next highest-yielding stocks from the universe that is excluded from the index. The index is rebalanced annually, assigning each stock with equal weights.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive Global SuperDividend ® Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index tracks the performance of 100 equally-weighted companies that rank among the highest dividend yielding equity securities in the world, including emerging market countries.

name: YieldMax AAPL Option Income Strategy ETF
merged_description: This ETF primarily aims to generate current income, with a secondary objective of providing exposure to the share price movements of Apple Inc. (AAPL), albeit with a cap on potential gains. It employs a synthetic covered call strategy using exchange-traded and FLEX options rather than holding AAPL stock directly. This involves creating synthetic long exposure to replicate AAPL's price action and simultaneously writing short-term call options, typically slightly above the current stock price, to generate income. Consequently, while benefiting from income generation, investors' participation in AAPL's potential upside is limited, and they retain full exposure to downside price movements without receiving any dividends paid by Apple. The fund is non-diversified, utilizes US Treasurys for collateral, and maintains its investment strategy consistently regardless of adverse market conditions.
description_original: The fund will seek to employ its investment strategy as it relates to AAPL regardless of whether there are periods adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: APLY aims to generate monthly income while providing exposure to the price returns of Apple stock (AAPL), subject to a cap on potential gains. The fund utilizes a synthetic covered call strategy via standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options, which consists of three elements: i) synthetic long exposure, ii) covered call writing, and iii) US Treasurys for collateral. The synthetic long exposure seeks to replicate the price movements of AAPL by purchasing and selling at-the-money calls and puts that have one- to six-month terms. To generate income, the fund writes call options with an expiration of one month or less and a strike price of approximately 0%-15% above AAPL's current share price. This limits participation in potential gains if AAPL shares increase in value. The short put positions fully expose investors to the downside of the stock. Note: the fund does not invest directly in AAPL stocks. Thus, investors are not entitled to any AAPL dividends.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks current income; the secondary investment objective is to seek exposure to the share price of the common stock of Apple Inc. (“AAPL”), subject to a limit on potential investment gains. The fund will seek to employ its investment strategy as it relates to AAPL regardless of whether there are periods adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Dbx Etf Trust - Xtrackers Us National Critical Technologies ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund invests at least 80% of its assets in an underlying index comprising large and mid-cap companies from developed markets. Its core strategy focuses on entities associated with critical emerging technologies deemed vital to U.S. national security and its allies, encompassing sectors such as biotechnology, AI, quantum science, advanced materials, and space technology. Company selection involves identifying firms within these designated fields and employing a proprietary methodology to assess geopolitical risk, specifically favouring those with lower levels of entanglement with nations considered adversarial to the U.S. Holdings are weighted by market capitalization and the index composition is reviewed quarterly. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index’s investment universe is derived from large and mid-cap companies in developed market countries included in the Solactive GBS Developed Markets Large & Mid Cap USD Index (the “Parent Index”). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CRTC is passively managed to hold stocks from developed market countries associated with sectors determined vital to maintaining US national security. A committee selects the stocks based on a proprietary rating system and weights holdings based on market-cap.

CRTC tracks an index of large- and mid-cap companies considered to support critical emerging technologies to the US and its allies. Companies must be associated with one of 14 critical technology sectors and pose a low geopolitical risk. The sectors are determined by a division of the US DoD and include biotechnology, quantum science, wireless tech, advanced materials, advanced computing or software, directed or renewable energy, human-machine interfaces, hypersonics, integration of systems, integrated sensing and cyber, microelectronics, space technology, AI and autonomy. A model developed by J.H. Whitney aims to quantify the level of entanglement that companies share with nation-states defined as adversarial to the US. Companies with a lower geostrategic risk rating are considered. A selection party determines the index holdings on the last Thursday of January, April, July, and October. Holdings are market cap weighted. Rebalance occurs ten days after the selection date.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive Whitney U.S. Critical Technologies Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index’s investment universe is derived from large and mid-cap companies in developed market countries included in the Solactive GBS Developed Markets Large & Mid Cap USD Index (the “Parent Index”). The fund is non-diversified.

name: BlackRock Future Tech ETF
merged_description: This security has been delisted, with its final day of exchange trading on August 12, 2024. Prior to delisting, the fund typically invested at least 80% of its assets in global equity securities of technology and technology-related companies, selected for their perceived rapid and sustainable growth potential stemming from the development, advancement, or use of innovative technology. It targeted firms across all market capitalizations, including those in emerging markets, which generated the bulk of their revenue from next-generation technology products, processes, or services across diverse sectors like software, hardware, semiconductors, and health care technology, based on the adviser's research. This non-diversified fund also had provisions to invest in IPOs, potentially utilize credit default swaps for risk management, and adopt a temporary defensive position by holding up to 100% in liquid short-term investments.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities issued by U.S. and non-U.S. technology and technology-related companies in any market capitalization range, selected for their rapid and sustainable growth potential from the development, advancement and use of technology. It may invest in companies of any market capitalization located anywhere in the world, including companies located in emerging markets. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security is delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is August 12, 2024. BTEK invests in technology companies globally that develop innovative and emerging technologies. The fund includes firms of varying market capitalizations and must generate the bulk of their revenues from the development, advancement, use or sale of new and emerging next generation, technology-related products, processes or services. The Adviser uses their own research and discretion to determine whether a company is a technology or technology-related company. Companies may include those software, hardware, electronic equipment, semiconductors, interactive media and services, internet retail, consumer finance, health care technology, and diversified telecom services. Securities are selected for their rapid and perceived sustainable growth. The fund may invest in IPOs and may enter in credit default swaps for risk management. During temporary defensive periods, the fund may invest up to 100% of its assets in liquid, short-term investments.
description_yahoo: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities issued by U.S. and non-U.S. technology and technology-related companies in any market capitalization range, selected for their rapid and sustainable growth potential from the development, advancement and use of technology. It may invest in companies of any market capitalization located anywhere in the world, including companies located in emerging markets.

name: SPDR S&P North American Natural Resources ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides targeted exposure to the North American natural resources sector by tracking an index of U.S. and Canadian companies engaged in commodities businesses. It invests substantially all, typically at least 80%, of its assets in the index components, which primarily consist of large- and mid-cap stocks. A defining characteristic is its specific allocation strategy across three key natural resource categories, rebalanced quarterly: Energy is set at 45%, Metals & Mining at 35%, and Agriculture at 20%. Within these categories, individual company holdings are weighted by market capitalization, with a cap preventing any single security from exceeding 10% of the index. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The SPDR S&P North American Natural Resources ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P BMI North American Natural Resources Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to U.S. and Canadian publicly traded large and mid cap companies within the sub‐industries of the energy, metals & mining or agriculture categoriesAt each quarterly Index rebalancing, the combined weight of securities of companies in the energy, metals & mining and agriculture categories are set at 45%, 35% and 20%, respectively
description_etfcom:
NANR tracks an index of US & Canadian firms involved in natural resources and commodities businesses.

NANR provides exposure to large- and midcap firms involved in commodity and natural resource businesses in the US and Canada. Using GICS classification, the fund selects and weights stocks from three sub-sectors in the natural resource space: energy (45%), metals and mining (35%), and agriculture (20%). Individual holdings are market-cap-weighted within each sub-sector, with no single security exceeding 10%. Launched in December 2015, the fund experienced huge initial inflows from Edelman Financial Services, which also had a hand in bringing it to market. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index comprises publicly traded U.S. and Canadian companies in the natural resources and commodities businesses that meet certain investability requirements and are classified within the subindustries of one of three natural resources categories: energy, metals & mining, or agriculture. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the S&P BMI North American Natural Resources Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index comprises publicly traded U.S. and Canadian companies in the natural resources and commodities businesses that meet certain investability requirements and are classified within the subindustries of one of three natural resources categories: energy, metals & mining, or agriculture. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco DWA Energy Momentum ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on investing in U.S. energy sector companies exhibiting strong price momentum, seeking to track the results of a Dorsey Wright relative strength index. The strategy involves investing at least 90% of assets in the index components, which comprises at least 30 energy stocks selected for their powerful relative strength characteristics. These stocks are chosen from a broad market universe based on momentum scores derived from upward price movements relative to peers, with higher-scoring securities receiving greater weight in the portfolio. The fund, which is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly, tends to have a small-cap tilt, a growth bias, and potentially carries higher risk.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the energy sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_etfcom: PXI follows a Dorsey Wright relative strength index that selects and weights US energy stocks by price momentum. Index construction begins by assigning a momentum score to the 2,000 largest constituents from the NASDAQ US Benchmark index. The score is based on upward price movements of the security compared to the benchmark and other eligible securities within the universe. The top 30 highest momentum-scoring stocks in the energy sector are then chosen for the index with higher scoring securities receiving greater weight. The portfolio tilts small, with a growth bias and somewhat higher risk. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco DWA Energy Momentum ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Energy Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the energy sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.

name: Invesco Dynamic Energy Exploration & Production ETF
merged_description: This investment fund concentrates at least 90% of its assets in the common stocks of U.S. companies involved in the exploration and production of energy resources, primarily crude oil and natural gas. It tracks a specialized index that employs a "dynamic" or "Intellidex" methodology, selecting and weighting companies based on specific investment merit criteria rather than market capitalization alone. These criteria encompass factors such as price momentum, earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value, aiming to identify potentially stronger performers within the energy E&P sector. Consequently, the fund is non-diversified, may exhibit a small-cap tilt, potentially includes exposure to related industries like integrated oil & gas due to a broader selection universe, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: The fund invests at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying intellidex. The intellidex was composed of common stocks of U.S. companies involved in the exploration and production of natural resources used to produce energy. These companies are engaged principally in exploration, extraction and production of crude oil and natural gas from land-based or offshore wells. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PXE tracks an index of U.S. energy exploration and production companies selected and weighted by growth and value metrics.

PXE attempts to pick winners in oil & gas exploration & production by following a complex tiered weighting methodology. The result is a fund that not only has a small-cap tilt, but interestingly, is more conservative than our benchmark. Its underlying index (Intellidex Index) evaluates companies based on investment merit criteria, including price momentum, earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. PXE's selection universe is broader than our benchmark's, allowing the fund to dip into other industries such as integrated oil & gas. The Fund is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco Dynamic Energy Exploration & Production ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The index was composed of common stocks of U.S. companies involved in the exploration and production of natural resources used to produce energy. These companies are engaged principally in exploration, extraction and production of crude oil and natural gas from land-based or offshore wells. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dynamic Energy Exploration & Production IntellidexSM Index. The fund invests at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The index was composed of common stocks of U.S. companies involved in the exploration and production of natural resources used to produce energy. These companies are engaged principally in exploration, extraction and production of crude oil and natural gas from land-based or offshore wells. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares U.S. Oil & Gas Exploration & Production ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to track an index composed of U.S. equities within the oil and gas exploration and production sector. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities or similar investments, potentially using the remaining assets for instruments like derivatives or cash to aid index tracking. The fund includes companies of various market capitalizations involved in exploration, drilling, production, and potentially refining and supply. Due to its focus on a specific sector and use of a market-capitalization weighting methodology, the portfolio is non-diversified and heavily concentrated in its largest holdings, while aiming to offer representative exposure to the U.S. E&P industry.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index, but which BFA believes will help the fund track the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IEO tracks a market cap weighted index of companies in the U.S. oil and gas exploration and production space according to Dow Jones.

IEO is a solid choice for representative exposure to the oil & gas exploration & production segment. The underlying index includes US companies, of all market-caps, that are engaged in exploration for and drilling, production, refining and supply of oil and gas products. Although its cap-weighting scheme, in this narrow space, makes the fund extremely top-heavy, with its top ten holdings comprising the majority of its overall portfolio. However, combining the excellent underlying liquidity with the Issuers securities lending program, IEO is a well-managed fund.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track theinvestment results of an index composed of U.S.equities in the oil and gas explorationand production sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Dow Jones Internet UCITS ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to mirror the performance of an index focused on the largest and most liquid U.S. companies within the internet industry. It typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities comprising this index, which requires companies to derive a significant portion (at least 50%) of their revenue from internet-related activities. The index construction methodology selects the top 15 companies from the internet commerce sub-sector and the top 25 from the internet services sub-sector based on a combined ranking of market capitalization and trading volume. Holdings are weighted using float-adjusted market capitalization, subject to constraints capping individual securities at 10% and limiting the total weight of the largest holdings, though the fund maintains a non-diversified profile due to its specific sector concentration.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the largest and most actively traded securities issued by U.S. companies in the Internet industry. The index is a composite of its two sub-indices, the Dow Jones Internet Commerce Index and the Dow Jones Internet Services Index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FDN tracks a market-cap-weighted index of the largest and most liquid US Internet companies.

FDN is designed to measure performance of the largest and most actively traded stocks of US internet companies. The index is a composite of two sub-indices involved in internet commerce and internet services. To be included in the index, 50% of its revenue must come from the Internet. Eligible securities are ranked first by three-month average float-adjusted market capitalization and then by three-month average share volume. A final rank is then calculated based on an equally weighted average of the securitys market capitalization and volume rankings. Securities are then sorted in descending order by final rank within their sub-industries, respectively. 15 securities from the Internet Commerce and 25 securities from the Internet Services with the best rankings are included. Securities are float-adjusted market capitalization weighted, subject to 10% cap for a single security. The aggregate weight of individual securities with weights of 4.5% or more is limited to 45% of the Index.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the largest and most actively traded securities issued by U.S. companies in the Internet industry. The index is a composite of its two sub-indices, the Dow Jones Internet Commerce Index and the Dow Jones Internet Services Index. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Dow Jones Internet Composite Index SM (the "index"). The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the largest and most actively traded securities issued by U.S. companies in the Internet industry. The index is a composite of its two sub-indices, the Dow Jones Internet Commerce Index and the Dow Jones Internet Services Index. It is non-diversified.

name: FlexShares International Quality Dividend Dynamic Index Fund
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to international, non-U.S. companies selected for a distinct blend of high earnings quality, significant dividend yield, and deliberately higher market sensitivity (beta). Sourced primarily from a large-cap international index but potentially including mid-cap equities, the strategy excludes companies ranking lowest on proprietary quality scores (based on management efficiency, profitability, and cash flow) and those not paying dividends. The portfolio is then optimized to emphasize these three core attributes – quality, yield, and a dynamic exposure reflected in a target beta 1 to 1.5 times higher than its parent index. Adhering to its mandate, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index, including relevant ADRs and GDRs, and reconstitutes its holdings quarterly.
description_original: The index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, possess greater financial strength and stability characteristics relative to the Northern Trust International Large Cap Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.
description_etfcom: IQDY aims to capture three attributes that don't always go together: high earnings quality, high dividends, and higher market risk. Quality and dividends often go hand in hand, but these traits are often associated with defensive plays rather than dynamic exposure. The index has a bias on large-caps by selecting its constituents from its parent index, Northern Trust International Large Cap Index but it may also invest in mid-cap stocks. Securities ranking in the lowest quintile of quality, as well as those which do not pay a dividend are excluded. Quality is scored using a proprietary methodology based on management efficiency, profitability, and cash flow. The remaining securities are optimized based on quality, dividend yield, and higher beta (1-1.5x higher than the parent index). The index is reconstituted quarterly starting each February.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, provide exposure to a high-quality income-oriented universe of long-only international securities issued by non-U.S.-based companies. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Northern Trust International Quality Dividend Dynamic IndexSM. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, provide exposure to a high-quality income-oriented universe of long-only international securities issued by non-U.S.-based companies. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.

name: Fount Metaverse ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund *tracked* a modified market-cap-weighted index targeting global companies significantly involved in developing, manufacturing, distributing, or selling products and services related to metaverse technology, encompassing segments like augmented reality, life log, mirror world, and virtual worlds. Utilizing a proprietary AI algorithm to forecast future metaverse-derived revenue, its index selected the top 50 eligible companies (minimum $300M market cap) anticipated to generate over half their revenue from this theme. The portfolio's weighting was modified market-cap based, factoring in expected metaverse revenue per segment. Characterized as non-diversified and committed to investing at least 80% of its assets in these metaverse companies under normal conditions, the fund ultimately ceased trading and was delisted in July 2023.
description_original: The fund invests in securities comprising the index. The index was designed to measure the performance of companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products or services related to metaverse technology (“Metaverse Companies”). Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amounts of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities of metaverse companies. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
MTVR tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index of globally-listed companies involved in the future iteration of the internetthe metaverse.

The fund was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is July 25, 2023. MTVR is passively managed to provide vanilla exposure to companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products and services related to metaverse technology. It includes the following segments of metaverse: augmented reality, life log, mirror world, and virtual world. The index uses a proprietary AI algorithm to analyze data from public filings and forecast each companys one-year forward revenue from metaverse technology. To be eligible for inclusion, a company must be expected to derive more than 50% of its revenue from metaverse and should have a minimum market capitalization of $300 million. The top 50 stocks by market capitalization are selected. The resulting portfolio is weighted using a modified market-cap-weighting methodology that factors in expected metaverse revenue per segment. The index is rebalanced on an annual basis.

name: First Trust Nasdaq Food & Beverage ETF
merged_description: This fund offers focused exposure to the U.S. food and beverage sector by investing at least 90% of its assets in the components of its underlying index, typically holding around 30 common stocks and depository receipts. The index methodology first selects companies based on liquidity within the broad food and beverage industry, including manufacturers, distributors, growers, and beverage producers. Subsequently, these selected companies are weighted using a multi-factor strategy that emphasizes strong growth characteristics (measured by price returns), attractive value (evaluated by cash-flow-to-price), and low volatility (assessed via historical price stability). This factor-based approach aims to capture specific performance drivers within the sector, and the fund itself is non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depository receipts that comprise the underlying index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the food and beverage sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and weighted based upon their cumulative score on three investing factors: volatility, value and growth. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FTXG follows a liquidity-selected, multi-factor-weighted index of US food & beverage companies.

FTXG is a liquidity-selected fund of 30 US food & beverage companies. These companies include brewers, distillers and vintners, manufacturers, distributors and packagers of food and beverage products, and companies that grow crops or raise livestock, operate fisheries or own nontobacco plantations. The 30 selected constituents are then ranked and weighted on three different factors: 1) strong growth, as exhibited by 3, 6, 9, and 12-month average price returns, 2) attractive value, evaluated by cash-flow-to-price, and 3) low volatility, based on historical price fluctuations.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the food and beverage sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and ranking. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Nasdaq US Smart Food & Beverage TM Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the food and beverage sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and ranking. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Academy Veteran Impact ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to generate current income by investing primarily in U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade mortgage-backed securities (MBS). Its core holdings consist mainly of MBS issued or guaranteed by government-sponsored enterprises (GSEs), such as Ginnie Mae, Fannie Mae, and Freddie Mac. Employing a bottom-up security selection approach, the fund specifically targets MBS where the underlying loans are identified, via reliable GSE mechanisms, as supporting U.S. service members, military veterans, or their survivors. Further emphasizing its commitment to this community, a portion of the fund's management fee is donated to veteran and military-related charities.
description_original: The fund will primarily invest in MBS that are issued and/or guaranteed by government-sponsored enterprises (each a “GSE”), such as the Government National Mortgage Association (Ginnie Mae), the Federal National Mortgage Association (Fannie Mae), and the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation (Freddie Mac). The fund will invest only in securities that are rated investment grade (that is, securities rated Baa3/BBB- or higher), or if unrated, determined to be of comparable credit quality by the Sub-Adviser.
description_etfcom: VETZ is an actively managed fund that invests in mortgaged-backed securities made to US service members, military veterans, their survivors, or veteran-owned businesses. The sub-adviser determines whether loans were made to these establishments by using a third-party data provider. This fund will only invest in fixed income securities rated investment grade and denominated in USD. The sub-adviser uses a bottom-up approach to select securities determined to be attractive investment opportunities. As an actively managed fund, the adviser may sell securities at any time if it believes they no longer meet the investment criteria. The sub-adviser will donate a portion of the funds management fee to veteran and military-related charities.
description_yahoo: The fund will primarily invest in MBS that are issued and/or guaranteed by government-sponsored enterprises (each a “GSE”), such as the Government National Mortgage Association (Ginnie Mae), the Federal National Mortgage Association (Fannie Mae), and the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation (Freddie Mac). The fund will only invest in MBS where the relevant GSE provides a reliable mechanism to determine whether loans included in MBS are made to U.S.service members,military veterans,or their survivors.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to generate current income. The fund will primarily invest in MBS that are issued and/or guaranteed by government-sponsored enterprises (each a “GSE”), such as the Government National Mortgage Association (Ginnie Mae), the Federal National Mortgage Association (Fannie Mae), and the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation (Freddie Mac). The fund will only invest in MBS where the relevant GSE provides a reliable mechanism to determine whether loans included in MBS are made to U.S.service members,military veterans,or their survivors.

name: Goldman Sachs Future Tech Leaders Equity ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital growth through a high-conviction, non-diversified portfolio focused on potential next-generation technology leaders. It invests globally, under normal circumstances committing at least 80% of its assets to equity in technology companies, including both U.S. and non-U.S. firms believed to be driving innovation or benefiting from technology enablement. Employing a bottom-up approach, the fund specifically excludes mega-cap tech stocks, targeting companies with market capitalizations under $100 billion that demonstrate potential for sustained growth and free cash flow generation. While concentrated in information technology, the portfolio may also encompass tech-enabled businesses in sectors like communication services, internet retail, and healthcare, with security selection incorporating fundamental analysis, valuation assessment, and potentially ESG factors.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in equity investments in U.S. and non-U.S. technology companies. The fund adviser seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing in technology companies that the adviser believes are driving technological innovation or benefitting from the enablement of technology, and have the potential to grow their business over many years. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: GTEK uses an active, bottom-up approach to build a high-conviction portfolio of potential next generation tech leaders. These are firms at various growth stages that are developing disruptive or emerging technologies. Since the fund focuses on growth potential, it notably excludes mega-cap tech companies that dominate the industry and only invests in globally-listed firms with less than $100 billion market-cap. While GTEK concentrates its investments in the information technology sector, it may also include tech-enabled firms in communication services, internet & direct marketing retail, and healthcare. To select securities, the fund adviser uses fundamental metrics to screen for quality and growth such as those indicating sustainable free cash flow generation. The fund also considers company valuation and may integrate ESG factors in the selection process.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in equity investments in U.S. and non-U.S. technology companies. The fund adviser seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing in technology companies that the adviser believes are driving technological innovation or benefitting from the enablement of technology, and have the potential to grow their business over many years. The fund is non-diversified.

name: VanEck ETF Trust - VanEck Robotics ETF
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of a global index comprising companies significantly involved in robotics and automation. It invests at least 80% of its assets in global robotics firms, including through depositary receipts, selecting companies that derive a minimum of 50% of their revenue from specific sub-industries such as industrial automation, robotic surgery, 3D printing, machine vision, and related software or components. The strategy targets large, liquid, high-growth companies considered leaders in driving future automation. Its underlying index employs a modified market-capitalization weighting methodology, tilting exposure towards defined sub-industry groups (50% robotics/manufacturing, 25% machine vision/software, 25% other key areas) and capping individual stock weights at 5%. This non-diversified fund utilizes an index that reconstitutes and rebalances semi-annually.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in Robotics Companies. The index is comprised of equity securities, which may include depositary receipts of global exchange-listed companies in the robotics industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IBOT tracks an index designed to provide exposure to companies involved in early adoption of commercial and industrial robotics, globally. Stocks are selected based on the amount of revenue tied to the theme. Holdings are weighted based on a modified market cap, tilting towards specific sub-industries.

IBOT aims to provide the total return, less expenses, of an index encompassing the largest and most liquid companies in the global robotics space. These are expected to be high-growth names powering the future of industrial automation. After meeting minimum trading and liquidity requirements, a company must derive at least 50% of their revenue from one of seven sub-industries: robots and manufacturing/industrial automation systems, robotic surgical systems, additive manufacturing (3D printing), robotics or manufacturing computer-aided design or other software, semiconductor manufacturing systems, machine vision, or embedded machine learning chips. Stocks selected are market cap-weighted, up to a 5% cap. The overall portfolio weighting tilts 50% to robotics/manufacturing, 25% to machine vision and robotics software, and 25% to embedded chips, robotic surgical systems and semiconductor manufacturing. The index reconstitutes and rebalances semiannually in June and December.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the BlueStar® Robotics Index (the “index”). The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in Robotics Companies. The index is comprised of equity securities, which may include depositary receipts of global exchange-listed companies in the robotics industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Global Tactical Commodity Strategy Fund
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks to provide total return with commodity exposure, aiming for attractive risk-adjusted returns and a relatively stable risk profile. It gains exposure primarily through a wholly-owned Cayman Islands subsidiary that invests in commodity futures contracts (both long and short), exchange-traded commodity-linked instruments, and commodity-linked total return swaps. The fund may also hold commodity ETFs and structured products. By limiting its investment in the subsidiary, it qualifies as a regulated investment company under the 1940 Act, differentiating it from commodity pools and allowing for equity-like tax treatment without K-1 forms. This active approach permits significant deviations from standard commodity benchmarks and potential sector biases, facilitated by a cash-only creation structure for operational simplicity.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve attractive risk adjusted returns by investing in commodity futures contracts, exchange-traded commodity linked instruments, and commodity linked total return swaps (collectively, "Commodities Instruments") through a wholly-owned subsidiary of the fund organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands (the "Subsidiary"). The advisor expects to gain exposure to these investments exclusively by investing in the Subsidiary.
description_etfcom: FTGC brought active management to the commodities space. The fund doesn't directly own futures contracts, but gains exposure to commodities through its holdings in a Cayman Islands-based subsidiary which holds futures contracts. The fund can also short futures, hold commodity ETFs, and structured products tied to commodities. Since the fund limits its holding in the subsidiary to 25%, it aims to qualify as a regulated investment company and is structured as a 1940 Act open-ended fund, as opposed to a commodities pool. Overall it doesn't look much like a front-month GSCI benchmark. Its sector biases can swing far from neutral exposure. Its cash-only creation structure makes things simple for larger investors. FTGCs structure means that it intends to be taxed like other equity funds, and does not distribute K-1 forms to its investors.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide total return by providing investors with commodity exposure while seeking a relatively stable risk profile. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve attractive risk adjusted returns by investing in commodity futures contracts, exchange-traded commodity linked instruments, and commodity linked total return swaps (collectively, "Commodities Instruments") through a wholly-owned subsidiary of the fund organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands (the "Subsidiary"). The advisor expects to gain exposure to these investments exclusively by investing in the Subsidiary.

name: AXS SPAC and New Issue ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks total return by primarily investing in Special Purpose Acquisition Companies (SPACs) and newly listed firms. It allocates at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings, to units and shares of SPACs with a minimum $100 million capitalization, alongside companies that completed an initial public offering within the last two years. Using fundamental analysis to evaluate potential investments, including company management and business models, the adviser selects opportunities within this specific market segment, focusing on SPACs—entities created for mergers or acquisitions—and recent IPOs. For liquidity or strategic purposes, up to 20% of assets may be held in cash, short-term high-quality debt securities, depositary receipts, or potentially other appropriate ETFs. The active management style may lead to high portfolio turnover.
description_original: In pursuing the fund's investment objective, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in units and shares of Special Purpose Acquisitions Companies (“SPACs”) that have a minimum capitalization of $100 million and companies that completed an initial public offering (“IPO”) within the last two years. The fund may also invest in depositary receipts for cash management purposes or due to a lack of suitable investment opportunities, the fund may hold up to 20% of its net assets in cash or similar short-term, high-quality debt securities.
description_etfcom:
SPCX is an actively-managed fund that aims to provide a broad exposure to Special Purpose Acquisitions Corporations (SPACs) and newly-listed firms.

SPCX is the first actively managed Special Purpose Acquisitions Corporations (SPACs) ETF in the market. The fund seeks capital appreciation by holding a broad portfolio of SPACs or blank check companies and firms that have completed their initial public offering (IPO) within the last two years. SPACs are companies that have no commercial operations or specific business plans and are formed to merge or acquire other businesses. The adviser uses fundamental analysis to identify favorable opportunities and to assess a companys management and business model. Additionally, the fund may invest in depositary receipts and may hold up to 20% of its assets in cash or other short-term debt securities. Due to frequent trading, SPCX may have a high portfolio turnover rate, which potentially leads to higher trading costs and capital gains distributions. Prior to August 5, 2022, the fund traded under the name The SPAC and New Issue ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in units and shares of Special Purpose Acquisitions Companies (“SPACs”) that have a minimum capitalization of $100 million and companies that completed an initial public offering (“IPO”) within the last two years. The fund may also invest in depositary receipts or appropriate ETFs for cash management purposes or due to a lack of suitable investment opportunities, the fund may hold up to 20% of its net assets in cash or similar short-term, high-quality debt securities.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide total return. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in units and shares of Special Purpose Acquisitions Companies (“SPACs”) that have a minimum capitalization of $100 million and companies that completed an initial public offering (“IPO”) within the last two years. The fund may also invest in depositary receipts or appropriate ETFs for cash management purposes or due to a lack of suitable investment opportunities, the fund may hold up to 20% of its net assets in cash or similar short-term, high-quality debt securities.

name: iShares MSCI Europe Financials ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to provide focused exposure to the financial sector within developed European equity markets. It tracks a free float-adjusted, market-capitalization-weighted index representing these specific stocks. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising its target index, utilizing a representative sampling approach rather than full replication. Composed primarily of large- and mid-cap European financial companies, the portfolio exhibits significant concentration, with potentially over 40% allocated to its top ten holdings, yet it is recognized as an efficiently managed option. The underlying index is reviewed quarterly and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to measure the combined equity market performance of the financials sector of developed market countries in Europe.
description_etfcom:
EUFN tracks a market-cap-weighted index of financials stocks in developed European markets.

EUFN seeks to provide exposure to the broad financial sector in developed European countries. The funds small basket of large- and midcap securities translates to higher concentration riskover 40% of its assets are dedicated to the top 10 holdings, so investors must be comfortable with EUFNs top names. EUFN is also an extremely well-managed fund, making it a markedly efficient option in the space. Notably, the fund uses representative sampling indexing, instead of replicating the index. The index is subject to a quarterly review, and is rebalanced on a separate semi-annual review.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI Europe Financials Index composed of developed market European equities in the financials sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index designed to measure the combined equity market performance of the financials sector of developed market countries in Europe.

name: Defiance Connective Technologies ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of a rules-based index concentrating on companies pivotal to the development and deployment of connective technologies, such as 5G and 6G networks. The portfolio holds approximately 50 U.S.-listed equity securities, including depositary receipts, from firms deriving at least 50% of their revenue from relevant business activities like core cellular network equipment, REITs and mobile network operators (MNOs), service assurance and network optimization, or enhanced mobile broadband and related infrastructure. Employing a tiered, modified market-capitalization weighting approach, the index caps individual securities at 5% and limits the weight of the three largest REITs and MNOs to 1.5% each, undergoing rebalancing and reconstitution semi-annually.
description_original: The fund uses a passive management approach to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is a rules-based index that consists of a tiered, modified market capitalization-weighted portfolio of the U.S.-listed equity securities, including depositary receipts, of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from business activities, products, or services.
description_etfcom:
SIXG tracks an index of US-listed companies involved in the rollout of connective technologies. Investments consist of 50 companies, selected and weighted based on market capitalization.

SIXG focuses on US-listed equities tied to the development and deployment of connective technologies, such as 5G or 6G networks. The portfolio consists of 50 securities deriving at least 50% of their revenues from activities, products, or services, such as core cellular network equipment, REITs and MNOs, service assurance and network optimization, and enhanced mobile broadband and related infrastructure. The fund uses a modified market cap-weighted approach with a max weight of 5% per security. The index only selects the largest three REITs and MNOs with a cap of 1.5%. Rebalancing and reconstitution are done semi-annually. SIXG was the first ETF to offer broad exposure to 5G-related opportunities, trading as Defiance Next Gen Connectivity ETF with the ticker FIVG, until it was changed on July 22, 2024. In addition, on Sep. 23, the index changed its name from BlueStar 5G Communications Index to better represent its updated exposure.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Bluestar ® Connective Technologies Index (the index). The fund uses a passive management approach to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is a rules-based index that consists of a tiered, modified market capitalization-weighted portfolio of the U.S.-listed equity securities, including depositary receipts, of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from business activities, products, or services.

name: Roundhill Magnificent Seven ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified exchange-traded fund aims for capital growth by providing concentrated exposure to a select group of approximately 5-10 of the largest U.S. companies operating within key technology and technology-related industries, such as technology hardware, e-commerce, internet media and services, and software. The fund's adviser selects constituents annually based on market capitalization, trading volume, and sector relevance, employing an equal-weighting strategy with quarterly rebalancing. Primarily utilizing swaps and forward contracts for investment exposure, though capable of holding common stocks and ADRs, the fund maintains full discretionary management, including the potential to temporarily allocate assets entirely to cash equivalents like U.S. Treasury securities or money market funds.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that pursues its investment objective by seeking investment exposure to the largest companies (“Underlying Issuers”) in one or more of the following industries, each of which is defined by an independent industry classification scheme: Technology Hardware Industry; E-Commerce Discretionary Industry; Internet Media & Services Industry; and Software Industry (collectively, the “Technology Industries”). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: MAGS, at the time of launch, is the first-ever FAAMG ETF in the US market space. The fund targets a narrow portfolio of 5-10 stocks publicly known as tech giants, aiming to capture the largest companies in social media, e-commerce, consumer discretionary, cloud computing, tech hardware, and software. On an annual basis, the adviser reviews the US tech universe to select the largest companies based on market cap, trading volume, and sector relevance. Holdings are equally weighted in the portfolio and rebalanced quarterly. As an actively managed fund, the adviser has full discretion in managing the portfolio. From time to time, 100% of the funds assets may be invested in US treasury securities, money market funds, and/or short-term bond ETFs. Holdings may include common stocks and ADRs, though the fund primarily gains exposure through the use of swaps and forward contracts. Prior to Nov. 9, 2023, the fund was called Roundhill BIG Tech ETF, trading under the ticker BIGT.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks growth of capital. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that pursues its investment objective by seeking investment exposure to the largest companies (“Underlying Issuers”) in one or more of the following industries, each of which is defined by an independent industry classification scheme: Technology Hardware Industry; E-Commerce Discretionary Industry; Internet Media & Services Industry; and Software Industry (collectively, the “Technology Industries”). The fund is non-diversified.

name: Nuveen ESG International Developed Markets Equity ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to companies in developed international markets, excluding the US and Canada, that demonstrate strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It seeks to track an index constructed from the MSCI EAFE universe by applying specific ESG criteria sourced from MSCI ESG Research. The process involves screening for positive ESG attributes like compliance, employee relations, and lower carbon emissions, while actively excluding companies involved in controversial sectors such as tobacco, alcohol, gambling, and weapons. Within each sector, only the top 50% of companies ranked by ESG score and market capitalization are selected for inclusion. The fund utilizes a replication strategy and employs a multifactor optimizer to weight holdings, aiming to minimize potential risk and return distortions arising from the ESG screening process, with the portfolio undergoing quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: In seeking to track the investment results of the index, the advisor attempts to replicate the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the securities represented in the index in approximately the same proportions as the index. The index identifies equity securities from the base index that satisfy certain ESG criteria, based on ESG performance data collected by MSCI ESG Research, Inc.
description_etfcom:
NUDM tracks an index of companies from developed countries, excluding the US and Canada, that align with various environmental, social, and governance principles.

NUDM screens for firms with positive ESG aspects in the developed markets ex-NA space. Index construction starts with a selection universe from its base index MSCI EAFE Index, which it trims down by applying a series of ESG screens. The screens attempt to capture different facets of ESG, such as compliance with international laws, relations with employees, and carbon emissions. The screens also exclude certain controversial businesses such as alcohol, tobacco, gambling, and weapons. The remaining firms are scored on ESG factors, and the top scoring firms within each sector (the top 50% by market cap) are selected for inclusion in the fund. NUDMs portfolio is weighted by a multifactor optimizer that tries to minimize any risk and return distortions created by the funds ESG screen. The portfolio is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. NUEM is a sibling fund with an emerging markets exposure.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results, before fees and expenses, of the TIAA ESG International Developed Markets Equity Index (the "index"). In seeking to track the investment results of the index, the advisor attempts to replicate the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the securities represented in the index in approximately the same proportions as the index. The index identifies equity securities from the base index that satisfy certain ESG criteria, based on ESG performance data collected by MSCI ESG Research, Inc.

name: KraneShares MSCI All China Health Care Index ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to mirror the performance of an index focused on the Chinese healthcare sector, investing at least 80% of its assets in index constituents or similar instruments. The underlying index captures the equity performance of large- and mid-cap Chinese companies classified within the healthcare sector according to the GICS standard, including various share types such as A-shares, H-shares, P-chips, and Red chips, provided they meet liquidity requirements. Its methodology uses free-float adjusted market capitalization weighting, adjusted for foreign ownership availability (with A-shares considered fully accessible), and applies a 10/40 capping constraint to manage concentration. Representing a specific segment of the Chinese market, the fund is non-diversified and rebalances quarterly.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float adjusted market capitalization weighted index, subject to the 10/40 Constraint, which is designed to measure the equity market performance of Chinese companies in the healthcare sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: KURE holds all types of publicly-issued shares (including A-shares, B-shares, H-shares, N-shares, P-chips, and Red chips) of large- and mid-cap Chinese companies in the healthcare sector. Stocks must meet minimum trading and liquidity requirements and be classified in the healthcare sector under MSCIs GICS standard. Holdings are market cap-weighted with an adjustment based on the proportion of shares available to foreign investorsexcept for A-shares, which are treated as 100% available. Weights are also modified using a 10/40 capping methodology. Overall, KURE provides exposure to a relatively small slice of the Chinese economy. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, track the price and yield performance of the MSCI China All Shares Health Care 10/40 Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float adjusted market capitalization weighted index, subject to the 10/40 Constraint, which is designed to measure the equity market performance of Chinese companies in the healthcare sector. The fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree Global High Dividend Fund
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of a fundamentally weighted index comprising high dividend-yielding companies selected from a global universe spanning U.S., developed, and emerging markets. The underlying index targets the top 30% of dividend-paying stocks ranked by yield, incorporating adjustments based on fundamental valuation, quality, and momentum factors. Constituents are weighted according to the total cash dividends paid over the past year, subject to 25% caps on both sector and country weights, and the index is reconstituted annually.
