The fund commits to investing at least 95% of its assets in the index's component securities or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 95% of its total assets in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of high dividend-yielding companies selected from the WisdomTree Global Dividend Index, which defines the dividend-paying universe of companies in the U.S., developed countries and emerging markets throughout the world. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DEW tracks an index of the top 30% of global dividend-paying stocks ranked by dividend yield and weighted by dividends.

DEW offers exposure to a global range of high dividend-yielding companies. The selection universe is drawn from the Wisdom Tree Global Dividend Index. The fund selects stocks by dividend yield, picking the top 30% from its universe, with some adjustments based on fundamental valuation, quality and momentum factors. It then weights the winners by total dividends paid out in cash over the past 12 months, capping sector and country weights at 25%. The resulting basket of stocks favors US stocks and the financial sector, but most peer funds share these traits. The index is reconstituted annually.
description_yahoo: The fund will invest at least 95% of its total assets in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of high dividend-yielding companies selected from the WisdomTree Global Dividend Index, which defines the dividend-paying universe of companies in the U.S., developed countries and emerging markets throughout the world. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance of the WisdomTree Global High Dividend Index. The fund will invest at least 95% of its total assets in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of high dividend-yielding companies selected from the WisdomTree Global Dividend Index, which defines the dividend-paying universe of companies in the U.S., developed countries and emerging markets throughout the world. The fund is non-diversified.

name: JPMorgan U.S. Minimum Volatility ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund concentrates on U.S. equity securities, following a strategy designed to achieve lower market volatility compared to the broader market. It invests predominantly (at least 80% of its assets) in the components of its underlying index, which utilizes a rules-based process to select U.S. stocks. The specific goal of this index construction is to target a portfolio volatility level below that of the Russell 1000 Index.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the underlying index. "Assets" means net assets, plus the amount of borrowing for investment purposes. The underlying index measures the performance of U.S. equity securities selected using a rules-based process that is designed so the underlying index targets lower volatility than the Russell 1000 Index.

name: Vanguard International High Dividend Yield Index Fund Admiral Shares
merged_description: This investment fund aims to track the performance of an index focused on non-U.S. companies characterized by high dividend yields. Utilizing an index sampling approach, it holds a broadly diversified collection of securities from developed and emerging markets outside the United States. The fund's strategy targets companies forecasted to offer above-average dividend yields, ensuring its holdings collectively approximate the key characteristics of the underlying high-yield, international equity index.
description_original: The fund invests by sampling the index, meaning that it holds a broadly diversified collection of securities that, in the aggregate, approximates the full index in terms of key characteristics. The index focuses on companies located in developed and emerging markets, excluding the United States, that are forecasted to have above-average dividend yields.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of FTSE All-World ex US High Dividend Yield Index that measures the investment return of non-U.S. companies that are characterized by high dividend yield. The fund invests by sampling the index, meaning that it holds a broadly diversified collection of securities that, in the aggregate, approximates the full index in terms of key characteristics. The index focuses on companies located in developed and emerging markets, excluding the United States, that are forecasted to have above-average dividend yields.

name: SPDR S&P Insurance ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to mirror the performance of the S&P Insurance Select Industry Index, which captures the insurance segment within the broader S&P Total Market Index. Employing a sampling strategy, it invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities, encompassing various sub-industries such as brokers, life & health, multi-line, property & casualty, and reinsurance. Its distinct characteristic is the use of a modified equal-weighting methodology across large, mid, and small-cap companies. This approach significantly reduces concentration risk compared to traditional market-cap weighted funds, offering investors potentially unconventional and more targeted exposure for strategic or tactical positioning within the insurance sector.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Insurance ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Insurance Select Industry Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the insurance segment of the S&P TMI, which comprises the following sub-industries: Insurance Brokers, Life & Health Insurance, Multi-Line Insurance, Property & Casualty Insurance, and ReinsuranceSeeks to track a modified equal weighted index which provides the potential for unconcentrated industry exposure across large, mid and small cap stocksAllows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional sector based investing
description_etfcom:
KIE tracks an equal-weighted-index of insurance companies, as defined by GICS.

While KIE stays true to the definition of an insurance company, its selection universe and equal-weighting scheme narrows its stock universe to make a very different portfolio from the other funds in the segment. The fund underweights property and casualty insurance in favor of a large overweighting to reinsurance companies. It also reduces its concentration risk-- good news in a top-heavy sector. Overall, this fund is for those looking for unconventional exposure to the insurance sector.
description_yahoo: In seeking to track the performance of the S&P Insurance Select Industry Index (the "index"), the fund employs a sampling strategy. It generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index represents the insurance segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of an index that tracks the performance of publicly traded companies in the insurance industry. In seeking to track the performance of the S&P Insurance Select Industry Index (the "index"), the fund employs a sampling strategy. It generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index represents the insurance segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").

name: SPDR S&P Global Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to mirror the total return performance of a global infrastructure index, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities or related depositary receipts. The underlying index comprises 75 of the largest publicly listed infrastructure companies meeting specific size and liquidity requirements, drawn from both developed and emerging markets (provided emerging market stocks trade on a developed exchange). Its construction features a distinct allocation strategy, specifically selecting 30 transportation, 30 utility, and 15 energy infrastructure companies. These sectors are assigned target weights of 40%, 40%, and 20%, respectively. Within these sector allocations, individual holdings are market-cap weighted, with a cap limiting any single security to a maximum of 5% of the index, ensuring diversified yet targeted exposure to key global infrastructure segments.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Global Infrastructure ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Infrastructure Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the 75 largest infrastructure-related stocks based on float-adjusted market cap and liquidityIndex is diversified across transportation, utilities, and energy infrastructure sub-industries
description_etfcom:
GII tracks a market-cap-weighted index of 75 infrastructure companies from developed and emerging markets engaged in the energy, transportation, or utility sectors.

GII tracks an index of 75 of the largest infrastructure firms globally, with constraints to ensure diversification between the energy, transportation, and utility sectors. The fund first selects the 15 largest emerging market companies from its eligible universe, limited to 10 per sector. These stocks must trade on a developed-market exchange. GII then rounds out its portfolio with the largest eligible developed-market companies such that the final portfolio consists of 30 transportation companies, 30 utility companies, and 15 energy companies. The transportation and utility sectors get 40% weight each, with energy getting 20%. Stocks are cap-weighted within each bucket, with no individual security having a weight greater than 5%. The funds small basket means that positions can change significantly at each semi-annual rebalance.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is comprised of 75 of the largest publicly listed infrastructure companies that meet specific investability requirements.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Infrastructure Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is comprised of 75 of the largest publicly listed infrastructure companies that meet specific investability requirements.

name: First Trust FTSE EPRA/NAREIT Developed Markets Real Estate Index Fund
merged_description: This passively managed fund invests heavily, typically at least 90% of its assets, in an index composed of global common stocks, REITs, and depositary receipts. Its core strategy focuses on real estate companies and REITs deriving significant revenue from owning, operating, or leasing properties crucial for modern digital infrastructure and e-commerce logistics. This includes assets supporting advanced wired and wireless communication, data storage and processing facilities, and e-commerce warehouses or fulfillment centers. Index components must meet specific listing, market capitalization, and liquidity standards, and are weighted based on their average daily trading values with a cap per holding, undergoing quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is modified market cap weighted based on free float market capitalization and includes the securities of real estate companies or REITs that are publicly traded on an official stock exchange located in North America, Europe or Asia and provides an audited annual report in English.
description_etfcom:
DTRE tracks an index of real estate stocks that support wired and wireless communication, data infrastructure, warehouses, and fulfillment centers. Selection and weighting of securities are based on three-month average trading values.

DTRE is a passively managed fund that provides exposure to real estate stocks perceived to support disruptive technology. It includes advanced wired and wireless communication, data storage and processing infrastructure, e-commerce warehouses, and fulfillment centers. The portfolio holds operating companies and REITs that derive at least 50% of revenues from owning, operating and/or leasing real estate that support rapid data transfer, distributed data handling, and e-commerce warehousing. Stocks must be listed on major globally recognized exchanges that meet sector, market-cap, and liquidity requirements. Holdings are weighted by their three-month average daily trading values, with a 10% single security cap. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Oct. 3, 2022, the fund was called First Trust FTSE EPRA/NAREIT Developed Markets Real Estate Index Fund, the first ETF to offer real estate exposure focused on developed markets worldwide, trading under the ticker FFR.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in the common stocks, real estate investment trusts (“REITs”) and depository receipts that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies that own, operate and/or lease real estate that supports advanced wired and wireless communication, data storage and processing infrastructure, e-commerce warehouses and fulfillment centers.

name: WisdomTree Europe Quality Dividend Growth Fund
merged_description: This fund invests primarily in dividend-paying common stocks of companies located in developed Europe, selected for possessing both growth potential and quality characteristics. Its underlying index screens eligible European stocks, ranking them based on factors like long-term earnings growth expectations and historical return on equity and assets. Uniquely, the index weights constituents according to the total cash dividends paid over the prior annual cycle, effectively emphasizing companies distributing more dividends. While issuer, sector, and country caps are applied, the fund maintains a non-diversified status and commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in securities reflecting the index's composition and economic characteristics, aiming to track its overall price and yield performance.
description_original: At least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks of companies with growth characteristics that are incorporated and listed on a stock exchange in one of the following countries: Germany, Switzerland, United Kingdom, etc. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
EUDG tracks an index of companies in developed Europe, selected for growth characteristics and weighted by total dividends paid.

EUDG screens 300 developed Europe stocks, based on combined ranking of growth and quality factors. Index selection starts with EUDGs parent index WisdomTree International Equity Index. Growth factor ranking uses long-term earnings growth expectations, while the quality factor ranking is based on three year historical averages for ROE and ROA. Index weighting is based on the total regular cash dividends paid by all the companies in the Index over the prior annual cycle, heavily weighting those paying more. Issuers are capped at 5% and the maximum weight of any one sector or country is capped at 20% and 25%, respectively. The index is reconstituted annually. Prior to August 31, 2015, the WisdomTree Europe Quality Dividend Growth Index was named the WisdomTree Europe Dividend Growth Index.
description_yahoo: At least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks of companies with growth characteristics that are incorporated and listed on a stock exchange in one of the following countries: Germany, Switzerland, United Kingdom, etc. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree Europe Quality Dividend Growth Index. At least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks of companies with growth characteristics that are incorporated and listed on a stock exchange in one of the following countries: Germany, Switzerland, United Kingdom, etc. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares ESG Aware Conservative Allocation ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund (ETF) operates as a fund of funds, designed for investors seeking a conservative risk profile combined with a focus on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors. It achieves this by investing exclusively in a portfolio of underlying ETFs, which themselves track indexes comprised of companies demonstrating positive ESG characteristics. The fund maintains a strategic target allocation, typically consisting of approximately 30% exposure to global equities (including developed and emerging markets) and 70% exposure to US investment-grade fixed income securities. This allocation is periodically rebalanced, usually semi-annually, to align with its conservative investment objective.
description_original: The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent a conservative risk profile.
description_etfcom:
EAOK is an index-tracking fund-of-funds that tactically allocates 30/70 global equites and US investment grade bonds with positive ESG characteristics.

EAOK is part of iShares suite of target-risk strategies that screens for positive ESG traits. The fund invests exclusively in iShares ETFs aiming for exposure that is consistent with conservative risk tolerance. The index allocates its assets to four equity ETFs (ESGU, ESML, ESGD, ESGE) and one fixed income ETF (EAGG). The equity basket has a fixed 30% allocation and provides an all-cap exposure to developed and emerging markets securities, while the fixed income basket has a fixed 70% allocation to broad US investment grade bonds. The index rebalances semi-annually to realign the allocations. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund name was iShares ESG Aware Conservative Allocation ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the BlackRock ESG Aware Conservative Allocation Index (the “underlying index”). The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account environmental, social and governance (“ESG”) characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent a conservative risk profile.

name: Roundhill Sports Betting & iGaming ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provides focused exposure to the global sports betting and iGaming industry by seeking to track the Morningstar® Sports Betting & iGaming Select IndexSM. It invests substantially all its assets, typically at least 80%, in securities of companies deriving revenue from sports wagering and online betting activities, which may include common stocks, depositary receipts (ADRs/GDRs), or other comparable investments offering similar exposure. The underlying index, developed by Morningstar, is designed to offer pure-play access to this specific theme, concentrating on companies significantly involved in the online sports and betting ecosystem.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) will be invested in securities issued by Sports Betting and iGaming Companies. The index tracks the performance of the common stock (or corresponding American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") or Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs")) of exchange-listed companies that earn revenue from online gaming ("iGaming"). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: BETZ is the second ETF by RoundHill investments and the first ETF to offer global passive exposure to sports betting and iGaming companies. This includes companies that are actively involved in analyzing sports events and wagering, as well as those involved with online betting. Eligible companies are scored from 1 to 4, depending on their involvement in the sports betting and iGaming industry, with companies deriving more than 50% of their revenue from the theme assigned the highest score of 4. Components are weighted in proportion to both their combined theme score and their free-float market capitalization, with higher theme scores receiving heavier tilt factors. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted annually in December. Prior to October 2, 2023, the fund tracked the Roundhill Sports Betting & iGaming Index.
description_yahoo: The index was developed by Morningstar, Inc. and is designed to provide pure exposure to sports and online betting themes. The fund will generally invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities of the index, but also may invest in investments that provide comparable exposure, including but not limited to depositary receipts representing Index components and investments in other ETFs. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Morningstar® Sports Betting & iGaming Select IndexSM. The index was developed by Morningstar, Inc. and is designed to provide pure exposure to sports and online betting themes. The fund will generally invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities of the index, but also may invest in investments that provide comparable exposure, including but not limited to depositary receipts representing Index components and investments in other ETFs. The fund is non-diversified.

name: FlexShares International Quality Dividend Defensive Index Fund
merged_description: This fund provides exposure to non-US companies from both developed and emerging markets, strategically selected to offer lower market risk, stable returns via quality attributes, and a consistent dividend stream. Primarily drawing constituents from a large-cap international index, though potentially including mid-caps, it invests at least 80% of its assets in the underlying index securities, including ADRs and GDRs. The methodology excludes non-dividend payers and the lowest-quality companies, assessing quality based on factors like management expertise, profitability, and cash flow. Holdings are weighted considering quality, dividend yield, and a lower beta relative to the parent index, aiming for enhanced financial strength and stability. The index reconstitutes quarterly. Importantly, this fund is scheduled for delisting, with its final day of trading anticipated to be January 21, 2025.
description_original: The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, possess greater financial strength and stability characteristics relative to the Northern Trust International Large Cap Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the underlying index.
description_etfcom:
IQDE tracks an index of non-US companies from developed and emerging markets, selected and weighted by dividend payments and various fundamentals. The index aims for lower market risk (beta).

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 21, 2025. IQDE delivers a safe and sound portfolio by combining three investment aims: lower market risk (the safe part), stable returns (quality), and a strong dividend stream (the sound part). The index has a bias on large-caps by selecting its constituents from its Parent Index, Northern Trust International Large Cap Index, but it may also invest in mid-cap stocks. Securities ranking in the lowest quintile of quality and non-dividend paying firms are excluded. Quality is scored using a proprietary methodology based on management expertise (e.g. corporate finance activities), profitability, and cash flow. The remaining securities are optimized and weighted based on quality, dividend yield, and lower beta (0.5-1x than the Parent index). The Index is reconstituted quarterly starting each February. The fund was anticipated to merge into ticker: IQDF in June of 2023 but plans were canceled.
description_yahoo: The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, provide exposure to a high-quality income-oriented universe of long-only international securities issued by non-U.S.-based companies. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the underlying index.

name: BondBloxx JP Morgan USD Emerging Markets 1-10 Year Bond ETF
merged_description: This fund offers focused exposure to U.S. dollar-denominated bonds from emerging market sovereign and quasi-sovereign issuers. It aims to track a market-value weighted index composed of these securities, which typically possess an average life between 1 and 10 years and span both investment-grade and high-yield credit ratings. Under normal conditions, at least 80% of its assets, including any borrowings, are invested directly or indirectly (potentially via derivatives) in these specific emerging market bonds. By concentrating on USD debt, the fund eliminates direct emerging market currency risk for U.S. investors but assumes credit risk associated with the issuers' capacity to repay in dollars. Characterized as non-diversified, it adheres to specific eligibility criteria for issuers and excludes instruments like convertible bonds.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in emerging markets bonds with an average life of 1-10 years denominated in U.S. dollars, either directly or indirectly (e.g., through derivatives). It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
XEMD tracks a market value-weighted index of USD-denominated debt issued by sovereign and quasi-sovereign issuers from emerging markets.

XEMD provides exposure to a basket of emerging market sovereign and quasi-sovereign bonds denominated in USD. The underlying index will include both investment-grade and high-yield securities with 1 to 10 years until maturity. Eligible countries must pass certain economic criteria. Convertible bonds are not eligible. By holding USD-denominated rather than local-currency debt, the fund eliminates direct currency risk for US investors but increases credit risk, as the strengthening dollar or weakening local currency could make debt harder to service. Each issuer must have at least USD 500 million outstanding, and bonds need at least 2.5 years remaining to maturity. The underlying index is market value-weighted and is rebalanced monthly on the last business day of the month.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in emerging markets bonds with an average life of 1-10 years denominated in U.S. dollars, either directly or indirectly. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the J.P. Morgan EMBI Global Diversified Liquid 1-10 Year Maturity Index composed of U.S. dollar-denominated emerging market bonds with an average life of below 10 years. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in emerging markets bonds with an average life of 1-10 years denominated in U.S. dollars, either directly or indirectly. It is non-diversified.

name: SoFi Smart Energy ETF
merged_description: This now-delisted fund, which last traded on February 20, 2024, provided exposure to a global portfolio of large-, mid-, and small-capitalization companies involved in distributed energy resources (DER), with a specific emphasis on renewable energy solutions. It tracked a rules-based index, selecting constituents based on criteria such as deriving a significant percentage of revenue from DER activities or demonstrating notable growth in that area, followed by screening against relevant sustainability and ESG standards. The non-diversified fund aimed to invest substantially all its assets in the index's components, which were equally weighted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The index follows a rules-based methodology that tracks the performance of the equity securities of publicly-traded large-, mid-, and small-capitalization U.S. and non-U.S. companies in developed and emerging markets that are selected based on a list of products and services that enable the practice of distributed energy generation. The fund will invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities that make up the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The fund was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is February 20, 2024. ENRG provides exposure to global companies that support distributed energy resources (DER). The fund focuses on renewable energy sources, a subset of all possible DER solutions. Firms are screened to determine the percentage of revenue each company receives from DER compared to its total revenue by analyzing financial and sustainability reports, along with other publicly available information. Companies with at least 20% DER revenue or have at least a 10% increase in DER revenue over the prior year are considered, as well as those that disclose DER as a key revenue source. Companies are then screened for relevant sustainability and ESG standards. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually, assigning each security an equal weight. Prior to February 14, 2022, the fund name was iClima Distributed Renewable Energy Transition Leaders ETF. Before August 9, 2022, the fund traded under the name iClima Distributed Smart Energy ETF and the ticker SHFT.

name: KraneShares Electric Vehicles and Future Mobility Index ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to mirror the performance of the Bloomberg Electric Vehicles Index, committing at least 80% of its assets to securities within the index or instruments with similar economic characteristics. The index focuses globally on companies central to the future of mobility, encompassing those involved in electric vehicle production and components, energy storage technologies, autonomous navigation, essential mining (lithium, copper), and hydrogen fuel cells. It typically holds a concentrated portfolio, selected based on significant revenue derivation from these themes and utilizing a modified market-capitalization weighting strategy with caps on individual securities, subject to quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The index is designed to track the equity market performance of companies engaged in the production of electric vehicles or their components or in other initiatives that may change the future of mobility, as determined by index provider.
description_etfcom:
KARS tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index of stocks that are involved in the production of electric vehicles or other initiatives that may enhance future mobility.

KARS holds globally-listed stocks of companies that derive significant revenues from electric vehicles, energy storage technologies, autonomous navigation technology, lithium and copper mining, and hydrogen fuel cells. An index committee determines portfolio inclusion by scraping filings of proposed companies for thematic key terms and then back-testing the resulting basket. This gives a concentrated portfolio of about 32 companies that are market-cap-weighted, with weights of the top 8 securities capped at 5% and other securities at 2.5%. However, if the holdings are less than 32, equal-weighting may be applied. KARS uses representative sampling to track its index, which is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to June 16, 2021, the fund tracked the Solactive Electric Vehicles and Future Mobility Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond to the price and yield performance of the Bloomberg Electric Vehicles Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The index is designed to track the equity market performance of companies engaged in the production of electric vehicles or their components or in other initiatives that may change the future of mobility, as determined by index provider.

name: Simplify Bitcoin Strategy PLUS Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks both income and capital appreciation by employing a multi-pronged approach. It primarily gains exposure to Bitcoin through futures contracts, often held via an offshore subsidiary, targeting approximately 100% economic exposure relative to its net assets. To support these futures positions, the fund holds a portfolio composed mainly of high-quality, short-term debt securities, such as U.S. Treasuries or similar ETFs, which also serve as a source of income; income may be further enhanced through tools like reverse repurchase agreements. Additionally, an active option overlay strategy is utilized, involving writing put and call option spreads on instruments correlated to Bitcoin futures, typically using up to 20% of assets and focusing on near-term expirations. The fund operates as a non-diversified investment.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (an "ETF"). The fund's adviser seeks to achieve its investment objective by using three strategies: (1) a Bitcoin futures strategy, (2) an income strategy, and (3) an option overlay strategy. Even though the adviser employs three strategies, the fund's portfolio is composed primarily of income producing securities. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: MAXI pursues three distinct strategies: long exposure to Bitcoin futures, collateral management via short-term debt securities, and income generation through active option overlay strategies. The funds adviser allocates the total economic value of Bitcoin exposure to be 100% of the funds net assets. A Cayman Island subsidiary is used to hold Bitcoin futures. High-quality, short-term US Treasury securities, or similar ETF exposure, serves as collateral for the futures positions. Reverse repurchase agreements may be entered into to potentially increase income. In addition, up to 20% of the funds assets will be used in option overlay strategies. The core of the option strategies consists of writing exchange-traded put and call option spreads on securities, index futures, or ETFs that the funds adviser believes to be sufficiently correlated to Bitcoin futures. Generally, the option spreads selected are close to expiration and positions are actively traded.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (an “ETF”). The fund’s adviser seeks to achieve its investment objective by using three strategies: (1) a Bitcoin strategy, (2) an income strategy, and (3) an option overlay strategy. Under normal market conditions, the adviser selects investments in Bitcoin related instruments so that the total value of economic Bitcoin exposure is approximately 50% to 200% of the net assets of the fund. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks income and capital appreciation. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (an “ETF”). The fund’s adviser seeks to achieve its investment objective by using three strategies: (1) a Bitcoin strategy, (2) an income strategy, and (3) an option overlay strategy. Under normal market conditions, the adviser selects investments in Bitcoin related instruments so that the total value of economic Bitcoin exposure is approximately 50% to 200% of the net assets of the fund. It is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard International Dividend Appreciation Index Fund Admiral Shares
merged_description: This investment fund aims to mirror the performance of the S&P Global Ex-U.S. Dividend Growers Index, targeting non-U.S. companies with a demonstrated history of increasing their dividends. It primarily invests in high-quality common stocks of companies located in both developed and emerging markets outside the United States, focusing specifically on those exhibiting both the capacity and commitment to sustained dividend growth over time. The fund utilizes a replication strategy, investing substantially all of its assets in the securities comprising the index and holding them in proportions closely aligned with their respective index weightings.
description_original: The index focuses on high-quality companies located in developed and emerging markets, excluding the U.S., that have both the ability and the commitment to grow their dividends over time. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the collection of securities that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_yahoo: The index focuses on common stocks of high-quality companies located in developed and emerging markets, excluding the U.S., that have both the ability and the commitment to grow their dividends over time. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the collection of securities that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of S&P Global Ex-U.S. Dividend Growers Index that measures the investment return of non-U.S. companies that have a history of increasing dividends. The index focuses on common stocks of high-quality companies located in developed and emerging markets, excluding the U.S., that have both the ability and the commitment to grow their dividends over time. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the collection of securities that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.

name: Invesco S&P SmallCap Utilities & Communication Services ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to replicate the performance of the S&P SmallCap 600® Capped Utilities & Communication Services Index, investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's component securities. The index itself comprises small-capitalization U.S. companies drawn from the S&P SmallCap 600 Index universe, specifically within the utilities and communication services sectors as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard. As a non-diversified fund, it provides highly concentrated exposure focused deliberately on the small-cap segment of these specific industries. This strategic focus often results in a portfolio that overweights smaller natural gas utilities and includes communication services firms, while underweighting the large-cap electric utilities typically dominant in broader utility benchmarks, creating a distinct investment profile compared to conventional utility ETFs.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the utilities and communication services sectors, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PSCU tracks a market-cap-weighted index of small-cap US utilities and telecom services companies, selected from the S&P small-cap 600 Index universe.

PSCU delivers concentrated exposure to small-cap utilities and telecommunication services. Its portfolio thus differs markedly from the broader utilities universe, even beyond the obvious size tilt. PSCU typically overweights small natural gas utilities and underweights electric utilities, which are dominated by large-caps. It also includes telecoms, which our all-cap benchmark excludes. The fund typically holds just a handful of names, and offers some of the segments most concentrated exposure all in small-caps of course. For these reasons, PSCUs performance has differed materially from those of the typical large-cap-dominated utility ETFs.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P SmallCap 600® Capped Utilities & Communication Services Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the utilities and communication services sectors, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust RBA American Industrial RenaissanceTM ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on small and mid-cap US companies positioned to capitalize on a potential American industrial renaissance, specifically targeting key industrial sectors alongside community banks operating within traditional manufacturing regions. It seeks to replicate the performance of an underlying index, normally investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's equities. The selection process favors companies with positive forward earnings estimates and significant US domestic sales, excluding banks outside specific Midwestern/industrial states and firms with over 25% non-US revenue. The portfolio utilizes a proprietary weighting approach, applying a 10% cap to the banking sector and a 4% limit to individual holdings, with quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing to maintain its strategic focus.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the equity securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of small and mid cap U.S. companies in the industrial and community banking sectors.
description_etfcom:
AIRR tracks a multifactor-selected index of equities that can benefit from potential regain in market share of US industrial and community banking sector.

AIRR is passively managed to select large- and midcap US companies from the Russel 2500 with the following industries: Commercial Services & Supplies, Construction & Engineering, Electrical Equipment, Machinery, and Banks. Firms must also have a positive 12-months forward earnings consensus estimate to be considered in the index. AIRR excludes community banks outside traditional mid-western manufacturing hubs, like Pennsylvania, Wisconsin, Michigan, Ohio, Illinois, Indiana and Iowa. Firms with non-US sales of more than 25% are also excluded. The index is weighted using proprietary portfolio optimization method and ensures that Banks will have a 10% sector cap and issuers will not exceed a 4% weight. The Index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an index called the Richard Bernstein Advisors American Industrial Renaissance ® Index (the "index"). The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the equity securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of small and mid cap U.S. companies in the industrial and community banking sectors.

name: First Trust NASDAQ ABA Community Bank Index Fund
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to replicate the performance of an index targeting the community banking sector, investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's component securities. The underlying index includes small, mid, and large-capitalization US banks and thrifts listed on NASDAQ. Its unique characteristic lies in specifically excluding the 50 largest banks by asset size, along with banks having significant international operations or a primary focus on credit cards, thereby aiming to capture the performance of traditional community banks while avoiding dominant mega-banks. The index employs a market-capitalization weighting methodology, subject to specific issuer caps, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of small, mid and large capitalization companies that comprise the community banking industry.
description_etfcom: QABA tracks an index of NASDAQ-listed US banks and thrifts while deliberately excluding the 50 largest based on asset size, according to Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) reports. QABA also excludes banks with an international specialization (assets greater than USD 10 billion and more than 25% of total assets in non-US offices) and banks with a credit card specialization (i.e. banks with credit card loans plus securitized receivables in excess of 50% of total assets plus securitized receivables). The result is an ETF that uniquely targets true community banks, avoiding the mega-money centers that tend to dominate this segment. The index is market-cap-weighted and undergoes quarterly rebalance and semi-annual reconstitution, subject to certain caps. The maximum weight of an issuer is capped at 25% and issuers weighting more than 5% in aggregate should not exceed 50% of the entire portfolio.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of small, mid and large capitalization companies that comprise the community banking industry.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the NASDAQ OMX® ABA Community Bank TM Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of small, mid and large capitalization companies that comprise the community banking industry.

name: Hartford Multifactor Low Volatility US Equity ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to replicate the total return performance of a specific US equity index, investing at least 80% of its assets in the constituent stocks of that index. The underlying index utilizes a multifactor construction methodology aimed at delivering outperformance relative to a broad US capitalization-weighted universe, while simultaneously targeting up to 25% lower volatility compared to that same universe over a complete market cycle.
description_original: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond to the total return performance of the Hartford Multifactor Low Volatility US Equity Index. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the equity securities that are components of the index. The index is designed to outperform a U.S. capitalization-weighted universe with up to 25% less volatility compared to that of the U.S. capitalization-weighted universe over a complete market cycle through the index construction process.
description_yahoo:
The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond to the total return performance of the Hartford Multifactor Low Volatility US Equity Index.
 The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the equity securities that are components of the index. The index is designed to outperform a U.S. capitalization-weighted universe with up to 25% less volatility compared to that of the U.S. capitalization-weighted universe over a complete market cycle through the index construction process.

name: Strive Mid-Cap ETF
merged_description: This fund provides market-capitalization-weighted exposure to the U.S. mid-cap equity sector by seeking to track the total return performance of an underlying index comprising 400 U.S. mid-cap stocks. The index selects constituents, including common stocks and Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs), based on their market capitalization rank (typically 501st to 900th largest within a broad U.S. market universe) and eligibility criteria like listing status and free float. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in these mid-cap companies, primarily aiming for full replication of the index, though a sampling strategy might be utilized. The index undergoes semi-annual rebalancing.
description_original: The index measures the performance of the mid-capitalization sector in the U.S. equity market as determined by Bloomberg. Under normal circumstances, substantially all, but at least 80%, of the fund’s total assets will be invested in mid-capitalization companies.
description_etfcom:
STXM tracks an index of 400 US mid-cap stocks selected and weighted based on market capitalization.

STXM provides exposure to the US mid-cap space. Starting with a broad, total market universe of 1500 US stocks, the index selects securities ranked 501 to 900 by market capitalization. Eligible securities must be listed on a US exchange and have a free float of at least 10% of its total shares outstanding. The index includes common stock and real estate investment trusts. Selected securities are weighted by market capitalization. The fund intends to utilize a replication strategy, which means it will invest all of its assets in the securities comprising the index. However, the adviser may use a sampling strategy if it is determined to be in the best interest of shareholders. The index rebalances semi-annually in January and July.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Bloomberg US 400 Index. The index measures the performance of the mid-capitalization sector in the U.S. equity market as determined by Bloomberg. Under normal circumstances, substantially all, but at least 80%, of the fund’s total assets will be invested in mid-capitalization companies.

name: First Trust Industrials/Producer Durables AlphaDEX Fund
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a smart beta strategy targeting the US industrials and producer durables sectors, aiming to generate positive alpha compared to traditional passive indices. It seeks to achieve this by tracking the StrataQuant® Industrials Index, which uses the quantitative AlphaDEX® methodology to select large- and mid-cap stocks from the Russell 1000® Index universe. The fund utilizes a modified equal-weighting approach, resulting in a tilt towards mid-cap companies and potentially different sector exposures than market-cap weighted benchmarks. Typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the constituent stocks of its underlying index, the portfolio undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the industrials and producer durables sectors that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
description_etfcom:
FXR tracks an index of large- and mid-cap US industrial firms. The underlying index uses multi-factor selection and tiered equal-weighting.

FXR uses a quant-based model to select industrial stocks it believes will outperform the broad industrials sector. The funds tiered equal-weighting scheme tilts the fund toward mid-cap companies. Aside from considerably less exposure to some of the segment giants, FXR also has pronounced sector bets. Overall, the fund offers a smart beta approach to the US industrials space, instead of providing market-like exposure. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the industrials and producer durables sectors that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the StrataQuant® Industrials Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the industrials and producer durables sectors that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.

name: QRAFT AI-Enhanced U.S. High Dividend ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund employs an investment strategy enhanced by artificial intelligence to select its holdings. It primarily invests, committing at least 80% of its assets, in dividend-paying securities of U.S.-listed companies. While its specific sector exposures may shift over time according to the AI model, it has shown the capacity to hold significant concentrations in areas such as consumer staples, information technology, and potentially others like healthcare or consumer discretionary. The fund operates as a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by utilizing an investment strategy enhanced by the use of artificial intelligence. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amounts of any borrowings for investment purposes, in dividend paying securities of U.S.-listed companies. A significant portion of the fund’s assets consisted of securities of companies in the consumer discretionary, consumer staples, and information technology sectors, although this may change from time to time. It is non-diversified.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by utilizing an investment strategy enhanced by the use of artificial intelligence. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amounts of any borrowings for investment purposes, in dividend paying securities of U.S.-listed companies. A significant portion of the fund’s assets consisted of securities of companies in the consumer staples sector, health care sector and information technology sector, although this may change from time to time. It is non-diversified.

name: Pacer BlueStar Engineering the Future ETF
merged_description: This passively managed ETF offers exposure to the future of engineering and manufacturing by tracking a rules-based index of globally listed stocks and depositary receipts. It focuses on companies significantly involved in key areas driving industrial advancement, specifically those generating at least 50% of their revenue from robotics and manufacturing automation, computer-aided design (CAD) software, or various aspects of 3D printing. The underlying index utilizes a modified market-capitalization approach with a tiered weighting structure: robotics and automation represent half the portfolio, while CAD and 3D printing each constitute a quarter. Weighting within tiers is based on market cap, subject to individual security caps. Employing a replication strategy, the fund invests in index components and is rebalanced semi-annually; it is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: A rules-based exchange traded fund (ETF) that aims to offer investors exposure to globally listed companies and depositary receipts that generate at least 50% of their revenues from robotics and manufacturing automation, 3D printing or computer aided design.
description_etfcom:
BULD tracks a modified market cap-weighted index of equities that provides global exposure to robotics and 3D printing.

BULD is passively managed to hold globally-listed stocks and depositary receipts of companies enabling the Fourth Industrial Revolution, particularly robotics and 3D printing. The index includes firms that derive at least 50% revenue from (i) robotics & manufacturing automation equipment, (ii) computer aided design (CAD) software, or (iii) 3D printing centers, hardware, software, and materials. The index selects at least 25 securities in the first sub-industry and at least 10 each in the other two sub-industries. The resulting portfolio is weighted in tiers, with robotics & manufacturing automation allocated 50% of the portfolio weight, while CAD and 3D printing are each given 25%. Securities are weighted by market capitalization within each tier, subject to an 8% single security capping. The aggregate weight of constituents with at least 5% weight is capped at 50%. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually
description_yahoo: The index is a rules-based index that consists of globally-listed stocks and depositary receipts of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from Robotics and 3D Printing Companies, as determined by the index provider. The fund adviser will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it will invest in all of the component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the BlueStar Robotics and 3D Printing Index (the “index”). The index is a rules-based index that consists of globally-listed stocks and depositary receipts of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from Robotics and 3D Printing Companies, as determined by the index provider. The fund adviser will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it will invest in all of the component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Utilities ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on providing exposure to the utilities sector by tracking an underlying index composed of companies from the S&P 500® classified within this sector, according to GICS standards. It generally invests at least 90% of its assets in these securities. A key characteristic is its equal-weighting methodology, which differentiates it from market-capitalization-weighted funds and influences its portfolio structure. Notably, the fund also incorporates a significant allocation to telecommunication stocks alongside traditional utilities, broadening its scope beyond pure-play utilities exposure. The underlying index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Utilities Plus Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the utilities sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_etfcom:
RSPU tracks an equal-weighted index of S&P 500 utilities companies.

RSPU tracks an equal-weighted index of large-cap utilities companies. Its equal-weighting scheme skews it away from a market-like portfolio. The fund also includes a significant allocation to telecom stocks, which are not included in some utilities fund. This is common, however, as many utilities ETFs combine the two sectors and telecom stocks may pay higher dividends than utilities. Still, investors looking for pure-play exposure should look elsewhere. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYU.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Utilities Plus Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the utilities sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: Goldman Sachs Dynamic California Municipal Income ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to provide a high level of current income exempt from both regular federal and California state personal income taxes. It primarily invests, under normal circumstances at least 80% of its assets, in U.S. dollar-denominated municipal bonds issued by the state of California and its political subdivisions, agencies, and instrumentalities. While focusing mainly on investment-grade securities with a portfolio duration typically ranging between two and eight years, the fund employs flexibility, allowing for investment of up to 30% in non-investment grade or defaulted bonds, and may hold private activity bonds whose interest could be subject to the alternative minimum tax. Utilizing a combination of top-down and bottom-up fundamental analysis, the investment advisor may integrate environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors, and the fund, which is non-diversified, might also invest through other investment companies, including ETFs.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in fixed income securities issued by or on behalf of the state of California and its political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities and other states, territories and possessions of the United States and the political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities thereof, the interest on which is exempt from regular federal income tax and California personal income tax. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GCAL seeks a high level of current income by investing in municipal securities exempt from federal and California state income tax. The actively managed fund mainly holds investment grade bonds with a two- to eight-year duration.

GCAL utilizes an active approach to a niche segment of the US muni bond space. The fund generally holds USD-denominated muni bonds issued by the state of California and its political subdivisions, seeking interest income exempt from federal and California state income tax. The fund may allocate its assets entirely to private activity bonds, whose interest may be a preference item for the federal alternative minimum tax. It may also get exposure through affiliated or unaffiliated investment companies, including other ETFs. Despite its focus on investment grade bonds, the fund can invest up to 30% in non-investment-grade bonds and may purchase securities of issuers in default. In constructing the portfolio, the fund adviser incorporates both a top-down approach and a bottom-up analysis. As part of its fundamental selection process, the adviser may integrate ESG factors alongside traditional fundamental metrics. Typically, the portfolio duration will range between two and eight years.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of current income that is exempt from regular federal income tax and California personal income tax. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes in fixed income securities issued by or on behalf of the state of California and its political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities and other states, territories and possessions of the United States and the political subdivisions, agencies and instrumentalities thereof, the interest on which is exempt from regular federal income tax and California personal income tax. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ProShares MSCI Europe Dividend Growers ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to track an index composed of developed European companies recognized for their history of stable dividend growth. Its core strategy selects firms from a broad European equity index that have consistently increased their cash dividends annually for at least ten consecutive years. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests a minimum of 80% of its assets in these component securities or in instruments offering similar economic exposure. The portfolio, consisting of at least 25 companies, employs an equal-weighting methodology and implements sector and country caps (30% and 50%, respectively) to mitigate concentration risk. The underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly to maintain its focus on qualifying dividend growers.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index, constructed and maintained by MSCI, targets companies that are currently members of the MSCI Europe Index ("MSCI Europe") and have increased dividend payments each year for at least 10 years.
description_etfcom:
EUDV tracks an index of developed European companies with a history of stable dividend growth.

EUDVs selection universe starts with a broad index representing the equity market performance of developed Europe. The fund selects at least 25 firms with a history of consistently increasing cash dividends for at least 10 years. In order to avoid large risk concentration in a small number of holdings, the portfolio is constructed with equal weights, subject to sector and country weight caps of 30% and 50%, respectively. The dividend growth screen coupled with a small, equal-weighted portfolio will likely produce exposure tilts. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the MSCI Europe index that have consistently increased dividends every year for at least 10 years. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the MSCI Europe Dividend Masters Index (the "index"). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the MSCI Europe index that have consistently increased dividends every year for at least 10 years. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics.

name: WisdomTree India ex-State-Owned Enterprises Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle focused on providing exposure to Indian companies, operating under the principle that private corporations tend to outperform state-controlled entities. Consequently, it systematically excluded state-owned enterprises, defined as companies with over 20% government ownership, from its portfolio. In addition to this core screen, the fund incorporated certain environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. It primarily invested (normally at least 80% of assets) in the components of its underlying modified float-adjusted market-capitalization weighted index. While employing caps to limit individual securities to 10% and sector weights to 30%, the fund was classified as non-diversified and underwent annual reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: Normally, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of companies incorporated and traded in India, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20, 2023. The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20, 2023. IXSE is designed around the premise that private corporations outperform firms controlled by governments. The fund aims to provide broad exposure to Indian companies, excluding state-owned enterprises (SOEs) that tend to dominate the telecommunications and transportation sectors. The fund defines an SOE as one with more than 20% government ownership. In addition, IXSE uses certain environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria to filter securities. Holdings are market-cap-weighted with single security and sector weight caps at 10% and 30%, respectively. Although, the resulting portfolio may have some sector biases, loose guardrails prevent extreme departures from market-like exposure to any sector. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced annually.

name: SPDR SSGA Multi-Asset Real Return ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to achieve real return, defined as returns exceeding inflation, through a combination of capital appreciation and current income. Primarily operating as a fund-of-funds, it typically invests at least 80% of its assets in exchange-traded products (ETPs) to gain diversified exposure to asset classes often associated with inflation protection. These core holdings span U.S. inflation-protected securities (TIPS), domestic and international real estate securities (including REITs), commodities (potentially accessed via derivatives), global infrastructure companies, and global companies engaged in natural resources or commodities businesses across sectors like energy, agriculture, and metals. The investment process utilizes both proprietary quantitative models and the adviser's fundamental analysis to determine allocations across these asset classes.
description_original: The SPDR SSGA Multi-Asset Real Return ETF seeks to achieve real return consisting of capital appreciation and current income. Seeks to provide exposure to domestic and international inflation protected securities, real estate securities, commodities, infrastructure companies, and companies in natural resources and/or commodity businesses which may include agriculture, energy, and metals and mining companies as well as industrial, and utility companies.The investment process relies on a proprietary quantitative model as well as fundamental views regarding factors that may not be captured by the quantitative model
description_etfcom:
RLY is an actively-managed fund that attempts to hedge against inflation by investing in funds with exposure to real estate, commodities, TIPS and natural resources companies.

RLY aims to achieve real return consisting of capital appreciation and current income through a fund-of funds structure. The funds active manager considers real return to be a rate of return above the rate of inflation. RLY uses a proprietary quantitative models as well the fund advisers fundamental views on qualitative factors to allocate exposure across asset classes via ETFs, including equities from developed and emerging markets, government bonds, TIPs, commodities (through the use of derivatives) and REITs. In the fund advisers view, the funds allocation among these asset classes should be consistent with its stated goal.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the Adviser invests at least 80% of the net assets of the fund among ETPs that provide exposure to the following primary asset classes: (i) inflation protected securities issued by the United States government; (ii) domestic and international real estate securities; (iii) commodities; (iv) publicly-traded domestic and international infrastructure companies; and (iv) publicly-traded companies in natural resources and/or commodities businesses.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve real return consisting of capital appreciation and current income. Under normal circumstances, the Adviser invests at least 80% of the net assets of the fund among ETPs that provide exposure to the following primary asset classes: (i) inflation protected securities issued by the United States government; (ii) domestic and international real estate securities; (iii) commodities; (iv) publicly-traded domestic and international infrastructure companies; and (iv) publicly-traded companies in natural resources and/or commodities businesses.

name: IQ Global Equity R&D Leaders ETF
merged_description: This investment fund concentrates on global large- and mid-cap companies demonstrating a strong commitment to innovation through substantial research and development (R&D) spending, targeting firms with attractive future growth potential. It seeks to track an underlying index comprising approximately 200 constituents selected from a broad global universe based on the highest reported one-year dollar amount of R&D expenditure. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its net assets in these index components, weighting them according to their R&D spending, subject to a 5% cap per individual company, and rebalances quarterly. Characterized as non-diversified, it ensures significant global reach by investing a minimum of 40% of its assets in companies located outside the United States.
description_original: The underlying index seeks to provide exposure to innovative companies by investing in the equities of companies that have high research and development (“R&D”) spending around the world. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the investments included in its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
WRND tracks an index that seeks to provide exposure to global large- and mid-cap companies that have high research and development spending, and attractive future growth potential.

WRND seeks exposure to innovative companies that are consistently reinvesting into their research and development activities, whilst exhibiting strong growth potential. It focuses on large- and mid-cap companies around the world, with at least 40% of its net assets invested in foreign countries. Selection begins with the components of the FTSE All-World Index, the parent index, which contains 200 constituents. These securities are those with the highest reported one-year dollar amount of research and development spending, intended for the innovation and expansion of present capabilities for revenue increase. Constituent weighting is also based on the same sense, highlighting actual fundamentals instead of future estimates, with individual capping at 5%. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. WRND launched alongside LRND and MRND to round out IndexIQs growth ETF equity suite. Prior to Aug. 28, 2024, the fund name was branded under IndexIQ.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks results that correspond (before fees and expenses) generally to the price and yield performance of its underlying index, the NYLI Global Equity R&D Leaders Index. The underlying index seeks to provide exposure to innovative companies by investing in the equities of companies that have high research and development (“R&D”) spending around the world. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the investments included in its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Advisorshares Msos 2x Daily ETF
