merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to deliver twice (2x) the daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of an affiliated underlying ETF focused on the U.S. cannabis and hemp industry. The underlying fund primarily invests in mid- and small-capitalization U.S. companies within this sector, utilizing both exchange-listed equity securities (such as common and preferred stocks) and total return swaps to gain exposure. To achieve its leveraged objective, this ETF employs swap agreements and may also hold cash equivalents or money market instruments as collateral. As a non-diversified, geared product featuring daily resets, it is intended as a short-term trading tool rather than a long-term investment vehicle; investors should be aware that daily compounding can cause long-term returns to significantly diverge from the underlying fund's performance, and the cannabis sector carries ongoing regulatory risks.
description_original: The fund will enter into one or more swap agreements intended to produce economically-leveraged investment results relative to the returns of the US Cannabis ETF. The US Cannabis ETF primarily invests in exchange-listed equity securities, including common and preferred stock, of mid- and small-capitalization companies, and in total return swaps intended to provide exposure to such companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: MSOX provides 2x leveraged exposure to the daily performance of MSOS, an affiliated exchange-traded fund that concentrates on mid- and small-cap US companies engaged in the cannabis and hemp industries. In addition to stocks, the underlying fund also uses total return swap contracts to gain such exposure. MSOX will enter into one or more swap agreements intended to produce leveraged investment results relative to the returns of MSOS. To achieve maximum results, the fund may also hold money market instruments or other cash equivalents as collateral. As a geared product with daily resets, MSOX is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. Long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying fund due to daily compounding. Investors also need to be aware of the ongoing regulatory risks on cannabis. Prior to Nov. 1, 2024 the fund name was MSOS 2x Daily ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond to approximately two times (2x) the daily total return of the U.S. Cannabis ETF. The fund will enter into one or more swap agreements intended to produce economically-leveraged investment results relative to the returns of the US Cannabis ETF. The US Cannabis ETF primarily invests in exchange-listed equity securities, including common and preferred stock, of mid- and small-capitalization companies, and in total return swaps intended to provide exposure to such companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: FIS Knights of Columbus Global Belief ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks income and long-term capital growth by primarily investing in a global portfolio of equity securities from companies of all market capitalizations, spanning both developed and emerging markets. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets are allocated to equities, including common stocks, ADRs, and GDRs. A distinctive feature is its adherence to the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops' Socially Responsible Investing Guidelines; the investment process combines quantitative and qualitative analysis to select companies with above-average potential while excluding those conflicting with these guidelines. The manager utilizes fundamental data and macroeconomic considerations to make investment decisions, aiming for diversification across sectors and regions.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in equity securities, including common stock and American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") of international and domestic companies. It may invest in companies of any market capitalization located anywhere in the world, including companies located in emerging markets. The fund will focus its investments in all capitalization companies. It seeks to outperform the FTSE All-World Index.
description_etfcom:
KOCG is an actively managed fund that invests in companies of any size across the world that meet certain Catholic investment guidelines.

KOCG provides exposure to companies from both developed and emerging markets that meet the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops Socially Responsible Investing Guidelines. The fund combines quantitative and qualitative analyses to select companies of any size with above-average investment potential. Stocks are then ranked using models that incorporate multiple fundamental factors. Highly ranked securities are evaluated based on fundamental data and macroeconomic considerations, while managing exposures to sectors and regions to ensure diversification. The fund excludes companies perceived to be in conflict with USCCB guidelines. As an actively managed fund, the portfolio manager can analyze market and financial data to make buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in equity securities, including common stock and American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") of international and domestic companies. It may invest in companies of any market capitalization located anywhere in the world, including companies located in emerging markets. The fund will focus its investments in all capitalization companies.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks income and long-term growth of capital. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in equity securities, including common stock and American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") of international and domestic companies. It may invest in companies of any market capitalization located anywhere in the world, including companies located in emerging markets. The fund will focus its investments in all capitalization companies.

name: Inspire Small/Mid Cap Impact ESG ETF
merged_description: This fund seeks to replicate an index comprising US small- and mid-capitalization equities, selected through a unique screening process based on alignment with biblical values. It invests primarily in companies scoring positively on these principles, after excluding those involved in specific activities such as abortion, gambling, alcohol, certain human rights violations, and promoting an LGBT lifestyle. Positive factors considered include community philanthropy, support for employee family time, and environmental stewardship. The resulting portfolio typically consists of the 500 highest-scoring firms, employing an equal-weighting strategy which may tilt the overall holdings towards smaller companies within the small- and mid-cap universe. The index components and their weights are rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects securities from a universe of publicly traded, domestic small and mid capitalization equity securities of companies with market capitalizations between $1 billion and $3.5 billion and which have an Inspire Impact Score® of zero or higher.
description_etfcom:
ISMD tracks an equal-weighted index of 500 small- and mid-cap US stocks that are screened for alignment with biblical values defined by the Issuer.

ISMD follows a principles-based, biblically responsible investing philosophy, screening for firms with products and policies aligned to evangelical Christian values. It screens out companies with any degree of involvement in certain activities: abortion, gambling, alcohol, human rights violations, and LGBT lifestyle. ISMD scores remaining firms by how well they align with its values, considering factors such as family time for employees, community philanthropy, environmental protection, or products that treat disease or support education. The 500 highest-scoring firms receive equal weights in the fund. The fund employs an equal-weighting scheme, which may cause a tilt toward smaller firms. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Between March 30 and August 19, 2022, the fund's name included a reference to 'ESG'. The name changes did not impact the fund strategy.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects securities from a universe of publicly traded, domestic small and mid capitalization equity securities of companies which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate investment results that generally correspond to the performance of the Inspire Small/Mid Cap Impact Equal Weight Index. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects securities from a universe of publicly traded, domestic small and mid capitalization equity securities of companies which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.

name: iShares Robotics and Artificial Intelligence Multisector ETF
merged_description: This global exchange-traded fund concentrates on companies across multiple sectors, drawn from both developed and emerging markets, that are significantly involved in the advancement of Artificial Intelligence. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index (or investments with similar economic characteristics), focusing on firms expected to contribute substantially to AI technologies through areas such as generative AI, AI data and infrastructure, AI software, and AI services. The index construction methodology scores and ranks potential companies based on their role in the AI value chain and the expected impact of AI exposure on their future revenue and profits, applying a preference towards smaller market capitalizations among the leading selections. The fund may allocate up to 20% of its assets to derivatives and cash equivalents, and its portfolio is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly to maintain alignment with its AI investment theme.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The underlying index measures the performance of equity securities across multiple sectors.
description_etfcom: ARTY is a global fund following the top 50 companies from both developed and emerging markets that are involved artificial intelligence (AI). The funds underlying index scores companies based on level of exposure to four subthemes: generative AI, AI data and infrastructure, AI software, and AI services. The scoring process takes into consideration the companys role in the AI value chain, expected net profit increase from the exposure to at least one of the AI subthemes, and the portion of revenue expected to be derived from each AI subtheme over the next five years. The index provider ranks companies into three tiers, emphasizing those with the greatest tie to the AI subthemes and current market capitalization. Preference is given to smaller market capitalization over larger. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to August 12, 2024, the fund ticker was IRBO and tracked the NYSE FactSet Global Robotics and Artificial Intelligence Index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index. The index is composed of U.S. and non-U.S. companies that provide products and services that are expected to contribute to artificial intelligence (“AI”) technologies in areas including generative AI, AI data and infrastructure, AI software, and AI services.

name: Vanguard ESG U.S. Corporate Bond ETF
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track an index of U.S. investment-grade corporate bonds selected based on specific environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria provided by an independent research firm. The underlying universe consists of U.S. dollar-denominated bonds with varying maturities, excluding those with less than one year remaining or under $750 million outstanding. The ESG screening process eliminates issuers involved in certain industries like fossil fuels, tobacco, controversial weapons, and others, as well as companies failing to meet standards related to diversity, controversy assessments, and adherence to the United Nations Global Compact principles. Employing a sampling strategy, the fund aims to invest at least 80% of its assets in bonds constituent within its target ESG-focused index, offering exposure to the U.S. corporate bond market while emphasizing issuers that meet defined sustainability criteria.
description_original: The index excludes bonds with maturities of less than 1 year and with less than $750 million outstanding, and is screened for certain environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria by the index provider, which is independent of Vanguard. All of the fund’s investments will be selected through the sampling process, and under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s assets will be invested in bonds included in the index.
description_etfcom:
VCEB tracks an index of US investment-grade corporate bonds of varying maturities, selected based on certain ESG traits provided by MSCI ESG research.

VCEB is Vanguards first move into the ESG fixed income markets. The fund includes USD-denominated bonds with various maturities. The funds parent index Bloomberg U.S. Corporate Index, represents the broad US investment-grade corporates, so expect similar exposure to VTC but with a positive ESG screen. MSCI will provide the ESG research and exclude firms that do not meet certain diversity criteria on their board and those that do not meet controversy assessment standards related to environmental, labor and human rights, as well as governance. Firms that derive threshold amounts of revenue from adult entertainment, alcohol, gambling, tobacco, nuclear power/weapons, civilian firearms, genetically modified organisms, thermal coal, oil, or gas are excluded. Moreover, firms must be adhering to the United Nations Global Compact Principles to be considered for inclusion.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the Bloomberg MSCI U.S. Corporate SRI Select Index (the “index”). The index excludes bonds with maturities of less than 1 year and with less than $750 million outstanding, and is screened for certain environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria by the index provider, which is independent of Vanguard. All of the fund’s investments will be selected through the sampling process, and under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s assets will be invested in bonds included in the index.

name: SPDR FactSet Innovative Technology ETF
merged_description: This ETF aims to track the performance of an index comprising innovative U.S.-listed technology and electronic media companies, identified through FactSet's methodology. Inclusion requires companies to generate at least half their revenue from specified technology or electronic media activities and operate within industries exhibiting top-quartile revenue growth over both one- and three-year periods. The strategy seeks broad exposure to firms potentially offering leading-edge products and services across the technology sector and electronic media sub-sector, rather than concentrating on narrow trends. Holdings within the index are equally weighted, potentially reducing single-stock risk, and the index is reconstituted annually; the fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in these underlying securities.
description_original: The SPDR FactSet Innovative Technology ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the FactSet Innovative Technology Index (the “Index”)Seeks to obtain exposure to companies within sub-sectors with robust revenue growth that may provide leading-edge products and servicesMay offer a way to capture innovation throughout the tech sector and electronic media sub-sector, and not just within one particular trendAs a result of equal weighted index methodology, may reduce stock-specific risk when attempting to overweight the more innovative areas of technology
description_etfcom:
XITK tracks an index composed of US-listed technology and electronic media companies deemed innovative or disruptive by FactSet.

XITK invests in US-listed technology and electronic media companies deemed innovative or disruptive by FactSet. Specifically, companies selected are required to derive at least 50% of their revenue from information technology services, hardware and software manufacturing, electronic components manufacturing, manufacturing equipment and services, and electronic media. Alongside the fund's sector qualification, the companies selected must exhibit innovation. To be considered innovative, the companies must belong to technology industries exhibiting top quartile revenue growth over 1-year and 3-year periods. Constituents are given equal weight within the fund. The index is reconstituted annually in December.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to represent the performance of U.S.-listed stock and American Depository Receipts of Technology companies and Technology-related companies within the most innovative segments of the Technology sector and Electronic Media sub-sector of the Media sector, as defined by FactSet Research Systems, Inc. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the FactSet Innovative Technology Index. The index is designed to represent the performance of U.S.-listed stock and American Depository Receipts of Technology companies and Technology-related companies within the most innovative segments of the Technology sector and Electronic Media sub-sector of the Media sector, as defined by FactSet Research Systems, Inc. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index.

name: Amplify High Income ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle operates as a "fund of funds," aiming to generate high income by investing primarily (at least 80% of its assets) in a portfolio tracking an index of U.S. exchange-listed closed-end funds (CEFs). Typically holding around 30 CEFs, its core strategy involves selecting and weighting these underlying funds based on criteria such as yield, discount to net asset value (NAV), and trading volume, seeking to capitalize on income potential and valuation discounts while maintaining liquidity. The fund places no restrictions on the asset classes or strategies employed by the CEFs it holds, allowing for broad exposure, and includes the expenses of these underlying funds within its overall fee structure.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of the index. Because the index is comprised of securities issued by other investment companies, the fund operates in a manner that is commonly referred to as a "fund of funds," meaning that it invests its assets in shares of funds that are included in the index. The index seeks to measure the performance of the top 45 U.S. exchange-listed closed-end funds.
description_etfcom:
YYY tracks an index of US-listed closed-end funds, weighted by yield, discount to NAV, and trading volume. There are no restrictions on the assets or strategies of the underlying funds.

YYY seeks yield using a basket of closed-end-funds (CEFs). The index-based fund typically holds about 30 CEFs, selected and weighted based on three criteria: yield, discount to NAV, and trading volume. The concept hinges on the success of buying discounted CEFs with big yields and enough liquidity to minimize trading costs within the basket. YYY can hold CEFs focused on any of the major asset classes, resetting the weight to a maximum of 4.25% each at rebalance. YYYs fee includes the expense of its constituent funds. On Oct. 7, 2019, YYY changed its name, primary advisor, issuer and trust to reflect complete integration with Amplify ETFs it was reorganized from the YieldShares High Income ETF. The fund did not make any changes to index or investment objectives. The previous issuer was white-label firm Exchange Traded Concepts. Prior to June 20, 2013, the fund tracked the SWM Index.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of the index. Because the index is comprised of securities issued by other investment companies, the fund operates in a manner that is commonly referred to as a "fund of funds," meaning that it invests its assets in shares of funds that are included in the index. The index seeks to measure the performance of the common stock of the top 60 U.S. exchange-listed closed-end funds.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that generally correspond to the price and yield of the ISE High Income™Index (the “index”). The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of the index. Because the index is comprised of securities issued by other investment companies, the fund operates in a manner that is commonly referred to as a "fund of funds," meaning that it invests its assets in shares of funds that are included in the index. The index seeks to measure the performance of the common stock of the top 60 U.S. exchange-listed closed-end funds.

name: Horizon Kinetics Energy Remediation ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified exchange-traded fund seeks long-term capital growth through concentrated investments in global companies of any capitalization. Employing a value-driven, bottom-up fundamental approach, the fund constructs a portfolio of 30 to 60 holdings primarily focused on two interconnected themes: companies involved in hydrocarbon-based energy production (such as oil and gas producers, exploration firms, and pipeline owners) and related remediation firms developing technologies to minimize the environmental impact of fossil fuels (like water treatment systems or carbon capture and storage). The strategy targets companies positioned to benefit from both the ongoing demand for traditional energy and the increasing focus on environmentally sensitive production methods, potentially holding common stock, preferred stock, or units of royalty trusts.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in securities of companies that are expected to benefit, either directly or indirectly, from the increasing focus on climate and environmentally sensitive carbon-based energy production. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
NVIR is actively managed to provide concentrated exposure to firms that are engaged in producing hydrocarbon-based energy or related remediation companies. Companies may be domiciled anywhere around the globe and of any capitalization.

NVIR seeks long-term capital growth through investments in a narrow basket of stocks focused on two main categories, energy companies and related remediation companies. Using a value-driven, bottom-up, fundamental approach, the fund adviser selects 30 to 60 stocks positioned to potentially benefit from the increasing demand for hydrocarbon-based energy production, as well as firms developing technologies that minimize the environmental impacts of fossil fuels. Such companies may include those engaged in the production of oil and gas, owners of pipeline networks, gas exploration firms, water treatment systems developers, technological developers of carbon dioxide capture and storage, and environmental-friendly carbon consumption and production. The fund may invest in common or preferred stock and units of royalty trusts. The adviser expects to sell securities when they no longer fit the investment thesis or no longer attractively valued.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in securities of companies that are expected to benefit, either directly or indirectly, from the increasing focus on climate and environmentally sensitive carbon-based energy production. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Dynamic Food & Beverage ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to track a specialized index comprising approximately 30 U.S. companies within the food and beverage sector, selected using a quantitative, multi-factor approach that evaluates criteria such as price and earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. The underlying index utilizes a tiered equal-weighting methodology, aiming to reduce concentration in mega-cap stocks and provide more balanced exposure across company sizes. Eligible companies span a broad definition, including those involved in the manufacture, sale, or distribution of food and beverage products, agricultural items, new food technologies, as well as food retailers and restaurants, though beverage stocks are significantly underweighted, and tobacco and pet supply companies are excluded. Consequently, the non-diversified portfolio typically exhibits concentrated exposure, distinct industry tilts, a lower average market capitalization compared to broader benchmarks, and aims to invest at least 90% of its assets in the index components, undergoing quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of U.S. food and beverage companies. These companies are engaged principally in the manufacture, sale or distribution of food and beverage products, agricultural products and products related to the development of new food technologies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PBJ tracks a multi-factor, tiered equal-weighted index of US food industry stocks.

PBJ offers a concentrated exposure to 30 US stocks in the food & beverage segment using quant screens based on five factors: price momentum, earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. The resulting portfolio provides significant industry tilts and a far lower average market cap compared to its benchmark. PBJ defines the segment broadly to include food retailers and restaurants, while severely underweighting beverage stocks, and ignoring tobacco and pet supplies stores entirely. Historically, around half of PBJ's portfolio is in its top ten holdings. The index tier weighting reduces concentrations in mega-caps and evenly weights the group of companies across size. The fund and the index are rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly in February, May, August and November. Prior to August 28, 2023, the fund traded under the name Invesco Dynamic Food & Beverage ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of U.S. food and beverage companies. These companies are engaged principally in the manufacture, sale or distribution of food and beverage products, agricultural products and products related to the development of new food technologies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dynamic Food & Beverage IntellidexSM Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of U.S. food and beverage companies. These companies are engaged principally in the manufacture, sale or distribution of food and beverage products, agricultural products and products related to the development of new food technologies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Hydrogen ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to track the performance of a global index focused on companies poised to benefit from advancements in hydrogen technology. It invests at least 80% of its assets, including potential borrowings, in the index's constituent securities, which may include American and Global Depositary Receipts. The underlying index provides exposure across the hydrogen economy, specifically targeting segments like production, fuel cells, technology, and integration. Employing a unique methodology, it uses natural language processing on public filings to identify and score companies based on their revenue exposure to the theme, categorizing them as pure-play, pre-revenue, or diversified. The fund typically holds a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio aiming for up to 40 pure-play companies, though pre-revenue and diversified firms may be included under specific conditions to reach a minimum holding count. Holdings are market-cap-weighted with caps on individual securities and aggregate weights for non-pure-play companies, and the index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets, plus borrowings for investments purposes (if any), in the securities of the index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to companies that are positioned to benefit from further advances in the field of hydrogen technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: HYDR is one of the few ETFs that capture the global hydrogen-based energy industry. It focuses on four segments of hydrogen economy: production, fuel cells, technology, and integration. The index uses a proprietary natural language processing (NLP) algorithm on public filings to score eligible companies for revenue-based thematic exposure. Companies are then divided into three buckets: pure-play, pre-revenue, and diversified. The index aims to hold a concentrated portfolio of up to 40 pure-play stocks. In the event that there are fewer than 25 pure-play companies, pre-revenue and diversified companies may be included until the holdings count reach 25. Holdings are market-cap-weighted, with single security weights capped at 12% (2% for pre-revenue or diversified). In addition, total weight allocation to diversified and pre-revenue companies cannot exceed 10%. The index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive Global Hydrogen Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets, plus borrowings for investments purposes (if any), in the securities of the index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to companies that are positioned to benefit from further advances in the field of hydrogen technology. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Tema Neuroscience and Mental Health ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks long-term capital growth by concentrating its investments within the neuroscience and mental health theme. It primarily invests at least 80% of its net assets, including borrowings, in companies deriving a significant portion (typically 50% or more) of their revenue from neuroscience, neurology-related diseases, or mental health activities. The portfolio usually holds between 15 and 100 global pure-play companies, potentially with significant exposure to the US and Europe, selected from sectors like pharmaceuticals, emerging biotech, medical devices, and healthcare services. Its strategy employs both top-down research (fundamental sector analysis and quantitative tools) and bottom-up security analysis, integrating ESG considerations to identify growth opportunities and manage risks.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the Tema Neuroscience and Mental Health ETF seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in neuroscience and mental health companies. A company is generally considered to be a neuroscience or mental health company that derives at least 50% of revenues from neuroscience or neurology-related diseases, or mental health. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: MNTL seeks long-term capital growth by targeting 15 to 100 pure-play companies contributing to neuroscience and mental health. This includes firms involved in pharmaceuticals, emerging biotech, medical devices, and healthcare services. The fund aims to identify growth opportunities within the thematic universe. It uses a two-fold strategy that includes both top-down fundamental sector research and quantitative tools, as well as bottom-up security analysis. As part of the strategy, ESG considerations are integrated to optimize profits and manage potential risks. Overall, the fund utilizes a comprehensive research and analysis approach that combines internal research, company disclosures, and publicly available sources to assess eligibility. While holdings may include global stocks, a significant portion is expected to be directed toward the US and Europe. The fund may engage in lending transactions.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term growth of capital. Under normal circumstances, the Tema Neuroscience and Mental Health ETF seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in neuroscience and mental health companies. A company is generally considered to be a neuroscience or mental health company that derives at least 50% of revenues from neuroscience or neurology-related diseases, or mental health. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily Latin America Bull 2X Shares
merged_description: This fund seeks amplified daily investment results, aiming for twice the daily performance of an underlying index focused on Latin American equities. Under normal conditions, it invests at least 80% of its assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities, and potentially other ETFs, that provide this leveraged daily exposure. The targeted index is float-adjusted and market-capitalization weighted, representing equity issuers from five major markets: Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Mexico, and Perú. Due to its use of leverage and specific daily targets, this non-diversified fund offers magnified short-term exposure to the movements within these Latin American markets.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, ETFs that track the index, securities of the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index is a float-adjusted market capitalization weighted equity index of issuers drawn from five major Latin American markets: Brazil, Chile, Columbia, Mexico, and PerÃº. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Strategas Macro Thematic Opportunities ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing principally in U.S. common stocks across various market capitalizations, provided they meet certain liquidity standards. Its investment approach centers on identifying companies highly correlated with specific macro-thematic trends, which involves top-down analysis encompassing economic conditions, policy shifts, socio-cultural developments, and global events to pinpoint prevailing market themes. The portfolio typically maintains exposure to three to five distinct, equally-weighted macro themes, selected through a research-driven process. A key characteristic is its dynamic management, allowing for active rotation among themes and individual securities in response to evolving macroeconomic landscapes and changing risk/return outlooks.
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its objective by investing principally in common stocks of U.S. companies that Strategas Asset Management, LLC (the “Adviser”) believes most highly correlate to macro-thematic trends. It may invest in securities of companies with any market capitalization, though certain liquidity parameters are required for a security to be considered.
description_etfcom:
SAMT is an actively managed fund of US stocks that seeks to outperform the broader market by providing exposure to multiple macro-thematic market trends.

SAMT seeks long-term capital appreciation through macro-thematic investing. The fund invests in US stocks of any size that are considered highly correlated to macro-thematic trends. The adviser defines macro as a top-down analysis which focuses on the overall economy, government fiscal and monetary policy changes, cultural and socioeconomic trends, and developments arising from global crises including pandemics, wars, or financial distress. Whereas, thematic refers to trends or views that are considered as, or likely to be prevalent in the market. The fund typically invests in three to five equally-weighted macro-thematic trends, identified using a research-driven approach. Individual securities for each determined trend are then selected based on various analytical tools. Investors should note that the funds active mandate allows it to rotate in and out of trends and securities over time, considering shifts in macro trends as well as their risk/return profiles.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its objective by investing principally in common stocks of U.S. companies that Strategas Asset Management, LLC (the “Adviser”) believes most highly correlate to macro-thematic trends. It may invest in securities of companies with any market capitalization, though certain liquidity parameters are required for a security to be considered.

name: iShares ESG Aware Growth Allocation ETF
merged_description: This fund is structured as a fund of funds, achieving its investment objective primarily by investing in underlying ETFs—predominantly from its own provider—that prioritize positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It follows a principles-based ESG selection process for its underlying holdings and seeks to track an index representing a specific target-risk strategy. The portfolio maintains a strategic, fixed allocation, weighted approximately 60% towards global equity ETFs and 40% towards US dollar-denominated, investment-grade fixed income ETFs, aiming for a moderately aggressive risk profile. This allocation is consistently upheld through semi-annual rebalancing, offering investors exposure built entirely on ESG-aware principles within a defined risk framework.
description_original: The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account ESG characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent a growth risk profile.
description_etfcom: EAOR is part of the ESG-oriented ETF suite with target-risk strategies offered by iShares. The fund invests in other ETFs, primarily of iShares, aiming for exposure that is consistent with the funds risk tolerance as determined by the BlackRock ESG Aware Balanced Allocation Index. The underlying ETFs are principles-based-selected, meaning equity and fixed income securities are evaluated based on their favorable ESG practices. The index uses a fixed allocation strategy of 40% to USD-denominated investment-grade fixed income ETFs and 60% to all-cap global equity ETFs, which aims to represent a risk profile that is moderately aggressive. The index rebalances semi-annually to maintain the exact same allocation. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund and index names were iShares ESG Aware Growth Allocation ETF and BlackRock ESG Aware Growth Allocation Index.
description_yahoo: The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account ESG characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent a balanced risk profile.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the BlackRock ESG Aware Balanced Allocation Index (the “underlying index”). The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account ESG characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent a balanced risk profile.

name: First Trust Dividend Strength ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund invests primarily in a focused selection of U.S. common stocks and REITs, aiming for exposure to well-capitalized companies with strong balance sheets, durable cash flow, profitability, and a history of increasing dividends. Its underlying index employs a rigorous, rules-based methodology, screening companies based on specific fundamental criteria including limits on debt-to-market cap and dividend payout ratios, alongside minimum requirements for return on equity and five-year dividend growth rate. Qualified securities are ranked by dividend yield within their industries, and the top 50 overall yield-ranked securities are selected for the portfolio. These final holdings are equally weighted and the index undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution, which can potentially lead to concentration in certain industries.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in the common stocks and real estate investment companies (“REITs”) that comprise the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to well-capitalized companies with a history of increasing their dividends. The term “well-capitalized” reflects companies that have strong balance sheets with durable cash flow and a record of profitability.
description_etfcom: FTDS tracks a narrow index of US securities selected based on several fundamental criteria and dividend yield. Securities selected must have a long-term debt to market-cap ratio less than 40%, ROE greater than 10%, a 5-year compounded dividend growth rate greater than 5%, and a dividend payout ratio less than 50%. Qualified stocks are then ranked within their respective industry by dividend yield. The top 15 stocks by dividend yield from each industry are evaluated and reranked as a group. The top 50 securities based on dividend yield are selected and equally-weighted. However, the portfolio can become concentrated in an industry or group. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. Prior to Apr. 29, 2022 the fund was called First Trust Total US Market AlphaDEX and traded under the ticker TUSA. The fund originally tracked the Value Line index. From Jan. 9, 2015 to Apr. 28, 2022, the fund tracked the NASDAQ AlphaDEX Total US Market Index before changing to the current index.

name: ALPS Medical Breakthroughs ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to mirror the performance of an index focused on small and mid-cap biotechnology companies. Its core strategy targets US-listed firms, typically with market capitalizations between $200 million and $5 billion, that possess at least one drug candidate currently undergoing Phase II or Phase III FDA clinical trials. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in these index constituents, which are also screened for financial sustainability, requiring enough cash reserves for approximately two years. The underlying market-cap weighted index employs capping rules, limiting the largest single stock position, leading to a concentrated portfolio characterized by a high-risk, high-reward profile tied to the success of clinical drug development.
description_original: The fund employs a "passive management" - or indexing - investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. It will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of small and mid-cap stocks of biotechnology companies that have one or more drugs in either Phase II or Phase III of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration clinical trials.
description_etfcom:
SBIO tracks, a market-cap weighted index comprising US-listed biotech companies with one or more drugs currently in either Phase II or Phase III FDA clinical trials.

SBIO invests in a concentrated portfolio of biotech companies with drugs in Phase II and Phase III of U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) clinical trials, and limits itself to US-listed firms with market caps between USD 200 million and USD 5 billion. SBIO also screens for sustainability, meaning constituent firms have enough cash on hand to last two years. Given the low historical success rates in clinical trials, the fund is a high-risk, high-reward bet on a small subset of biotech companies. The Underlying Index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalance subject to certain caps. The largest stock is capped at 4.5%, and the excess weight is redistributed proportionately over the remainder of the Underlying Index. Prior to July 9, 2019 the funds index was Poliwogg Medical Breakthroughs Index, which has the same strategies.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond (before fees and expenses) generally to the performance of its underlying index, the S-Network® Medical Breakthroughs Index. The fund employs a "passive management" - or indexing - investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. It will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of small and mid-cap stocks of biotechnology companies that have one or more drugs in either Phase II or Phase III of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration clinical trials.

name: Xtrackers S&P 500 ESG ETF
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to U.S. large-cap companies drawn from the S&P 500 index, selected based on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. It specifically excludes firms involved in tobacco and controversial weapons, those with low United Nations Global Compact rankings, and the bottom 25% of ESG scorers within their respective GICS industries. Companies passing these screens are included based on their ESG performance relative to sector peers and are weighted by market capitalization. A key feature is its design to maintain overall industry group weights similar to the standard S&P 500 index. The fund employs a full replication strategy to track its underlying index, is rebalanced annually, and is classified as non-diversified. Although the formal "ESG" naming was recently adjusted to "Scored and Screened," this change did not alter the fund's established investment strategy.
description_original: The index is a broad-based, market capitalization weighted index that provides exposure to companies with high environmental, social and governance ("ESG") performance relative to their sector peers, while maintaining similar overall industry group weights as the S&P 500 Index. The fund uses a full replication indexing strategy to seek to track the underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
SNPE tracks a principles-selected, market cap-weighted index of US large-cap securities.

SNPE is an ESG-focused fund that draws its universe from the S&P 500. The fund excludes companies involved in tobacco, controversial weapons, ranks low with the United Nations Global Compact (UNGC) score ranking, and score bottom 25% of GICS ESG ratings within its industry. After exclusions are applied, companies are selected by ESG score, while at the same time mirroring the industry weightings of the S&P 500. The fund uses a full replication method to track the Underlying Index. As such, the fund invests directly in the component securities of the Underlying Index in substantially the same weightings in which they are represented in the Underlying Index. Rebalancing occurs annually. On Feb. 10, 2025, both the fund and its index dropped and replaced ESG name claims with Scored and Screened. The change has no effect on the funds strategy.
description_yahoo: The index is a broad-based, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to measure the performance of companies meeting environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria, while maintaining similar overall industry group weights as the S&P 500 Index. The fund uses a full replication indexing strategy to seek to track the underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P 500 ESG Index. The index is a broad-based, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to measure the performance of companies meeting environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria, while maintaining similar overall industry group weights as the S&P 500 Index. The fund uses a full replication indexing strategy to seek to track the underlying index. It is non-diversified.

name: iShares MSCI USA ESG Select ETF
merged_description: This fund focuses on socially conscious investing by tracking an optimized index of U.S. large- and mid-cap companies selected for their high environmental, social, and governance (ESG) ratings. Its primary strategy is to maximize exposure to positive ESG characteristics while maintaining risk and return profiles similar to the broad MSCI USA Index. The index excludes companies involved in tobacco and civilian firearms or those with low controversy scores. Holdings are weighted according to their ESG scores, subject to diversification constraints including a 5% cap on individual securities and a 3% limit on sector deviations relative to the MSCI USA Index. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in these index components, with the remainder potentially allocated to derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents.
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is an optimized index designed to maximize exposure to positive environmental, social and governance ("ESG") characteristics, while exhibiting risk and return characteristics similar to the MSCI USA Index.
description_etfcom:
SUSA tracks an index of US companies with high environmental, social and governance (ESG) factor scores as calculated by MSCI.

SUSA offers socially conscious exposure to US large- and midcap equities. It holds MSCI USA companies with the highest ESG ratings, determined by the degree to which they reflect socially conscious values with regard to the environment, society, and corporate governance. As such, companies with tobacco and civilian firearms involvement as well as those with low MSCI ESG controversies score are excluded from the index. SUSA weights its holdings in proportion to their ESG scores. At the same time, the fund caps security weights at 5% and limits sector deviation from the broader MSCI USA index to 3%, ensuring that the fund doesn't deviate far from the equity market. Index constituents are reviewed on a quarterly basis. The fund traded under the ticker KLD until July 2017. Prior to June 1, 2018, the fund tracked the MSCI USA ESG Select Index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is an optimized index designed to maximize exposure to positive environmental, social and governance characteristics while exhibiting risk and return characteristics similar to the MSCI USA Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Extended ESG Select Index composed of U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance characteristics as identified by the index provider. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is an optimized index designed to maximize exposure to positive environmental, social and governance characteristics while exhibiting risk and return characteristics similar to the MSCI USA Index.

name: Revere Sector Opportunity ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund-of-funds ETF focused its investment strategy on ETFs representing the eleven sectors of the S&P 500 Index. Utilizing a proprietary sector selection model, the fund dynamically allocated assets by analyzing macroeconomic, financial, market data, and technical factors. The objective was to maximize returns by strategically overweighting, underweighting, or matching the benchmark weightings of various sectors relative to the S&P 500. While required to hold positions in at least five sector ETFs at all times, it did not necessarily maintain exposure to all eleven simultaneously. This active management approach could result in higher portfolio turnover costs, and the security has since been delisted from exchanges.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange traded fund ("ETF") that will primarily invest in ETFs that represent a sector of the S&P 500 Index. The S&P 500 Index is composed of the following eleven sectors: Information Technology, Health Care, Financials, Consumer Discretionary, Communication Services, Industrials, Consumer Staples, Energy, Utilities, Real Estate, and Materials. Under normal market conditions, the sub-adviser will invest the fund's assets in all eleven sectors that comprise the S&P 500 Index. The sub-adviser may adjust holdings based on changes in the S&P 500 economic sector weightings.
description_etfcom:
RSPY is an actively managed fund that invests in ETFs that represent the 11 sectors of the S&P 500. Holdings are selected and weighted using a proprietary sector selection model.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is July 28, 2023. RSPY is a fund-of-funds that actively invests in sector ETFs, or ETFs that focus on one of the 11 individual sectors of the S&P 500, namely information technology, health care, financials, consumer discretionary, communication services, industrials, consumer staples, energy, utilities, real estate, and materials. The sub-adviser uses a proprietary sector selection model that utilizes macroeconomic, financial and market data to select and allocate the funds resources to respective sector ETFs. In order to maximize returns, the model reviews technical factors to estimate which sectors should be overweighted, underweighted or weighted approximately the same as the S&P 500. The Fund may not always have complete exposure to all 11 sectors at the same moment, but it is required to be invested in at least five at all times. Additionally, actively managing a fund may result in high portfolio turnover costs.

name: iShares Lithium Miners and Producers ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers targeted exposure to the global lithium sector by tracking an index of companies primarily engaged in lithium ore mining and/or compound manufacturing worldwide. The underlying index selects constituents using a tiered approach based on revenue derived from lithium-related activities, prioritizing companies with higher exposure and aiming for approximately 50 holdings across various market capitalizations. This index is market-cap weighted but tilted towards firms with significant lithium revenue streams. Utilizing a representative sampling technique, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities mirroring the index, is considered non-diversified, and rebalances its portfolio quarterly.
description_original: iShares Trust - iShares Lithium Miners and Producers ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. The fund is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. It invests in public equity markets of global region. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across lithium ore mining and/or lithium compounds manufacturing sectors. The fund invests in growth and value stocks of companies across diversified market capitalization. It seeks to track the performance of the STOXX Global Lithium Miners and Producers Index, by using representative sampling technique. iShares Trust - iShares Lithium Miners and Producers ETF is domiciled in the United States.
description_etfcom: ILIT tracks an index comprised of lithium miners and compound manufacturers globally. The fund selects its stocks based on a two-tiered process. Tier 1 is divided into three, with Tier 1a being companies categorized as lithium ore miners. Tier 1b is for organizations classified as lithium compound manufacturers. Tier 1c are companies with more than 50% of their revenues tied with both lithium mining and lithium compound manufacturing, with the goal of having 50 stocks composing the index. In the occasion that less than 50 are eligible, Tier 2 constituents are considered. Tier 2 will be organizations with more than 25% but less than 50% of their revenues tied with both lithium industries. Companies are ranked and selected based on revenue exposure. The index is market-cap weighted with a tilt towards high-exposure (Tier 1 with top 20% of market share) companies. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the STOXX Global Lithium Miners and Producers Index composed of U.S. and non-U.S. equities of companies primarily engaged in lithium ore mining and/or lithium compounds manufacturing. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: JPMorgan Dividend Leaders ETF
merged_description: Aiming for long-term capital growth alongside current income, this investment vehicle primarily holds dividend-paying equity securities. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets are invested in companies identified by the manager as leaders, demonstrating a strong capacity for either sustained dividend growth or maintaining high dividend payouts relative to their global peers. The core concept emphasizes identifying robust dividend streams as key contributors to total return.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the underlying index. "Assets" means net assets, plus the amount of borrowing for investment purposes. The underlying index is comprised of higher yielding U.S. equity securities.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in dividend-paying equity securities and equity-related instruments of companies that the adviser believes are leaders in terms of their ability to, over time, (i) grow their dividends, and/or (ii) maintain high dividend payouts, in each case relative to the companies included in the fund’s benchmark, the MSCI ACWI Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital growth and current income. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in dividend-paying equity securities and equity-related instruments of companies that the adviser believes are leaders in terms of their ability to, over time, (i) grow their dividends, and/or (ii) maintain high dividend payouts, in each case relative to the companies included in the fund’s benchmark, the MSCI ACWI Index.

name: iShares U.S. Broker-Dealers & Securities Exchanges ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides targeted exposure to the U.S. investment services sector, concentrating specifically on broker-dealers and securities or commodities exchanges while excluding banks, investment management firms, and other broader financial institutions. It aims to replicate the performance of a market-cap-weighted index comprising U.S. equities from this sector, as defined by S&P Dow Jones Indices. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in its index components or economically similar investments, with the possibility of holding up to 20% in certain derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents. Characterized by high concentration and its non-diversified status, the fund employs market-capitalization weighting subject to specific constraints: individual holdings are capped at 22.5%, and the aggregate weight of companies exceeding 4.5% is capped at 45%. The portfolio undergoes quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The index measures the performance of the investment services sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by SPDJI. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IAI tracks a market-cap-weighted index of investment service providers as well as securities and commodities exchanges.

IAI delivers a tight focus on one subset of the financial industry, only capturing US broker-dealers while excluding other sectors like banks and other financial institutions. The fund bypasses investment management firms as it focuses squarely on broker-dealers and trading firms. While its selection universe is smaller than our benchmark, the fund avoids fancy methodology and simply weights the portfolio by market-cap. A concentrated fund to begin with well over half of IAI's assets are held in its top holdings. The fund uses a sampling method and caps each company to 22.5%, while the aggregate weight of companies with greater than 4.5% are capped at 45% of the funds value. The fund undergoes quarterly rebalancing.
description_yahoo: The index measures the performance of the investment services sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by SPDJI. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Investment Services Index composed of U.S. equities in the investment services sector. The index measures the performance of the investment services sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by SPDJI. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.

name: Alpha Architect High Inflation And Deflation ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term total return by dynamically allocating its assets across intermediate-term U.S. Treasury bonds, real estate (often via REITs), and commodities. Employing a quantitative investment model based on momentum and trend-following factors, which is updated periodically, the fund shifts its exposure between these asset classes to adapt to varying market conditions, with the sub-adviser retaining discretion over final decisions. While primarily investing through other ETFs or registered investment companies, the fund may also hold REITs and U.S. Treasury bonds directly. The strategy aims to leverage the different behaviors of these asset classes in diverse economic environments, and the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund primarily invests its assets in the shares of registered investment companies, including affiliated and non-affiliated ETFs, that emphasize investments in (i) intermediate-term U.S. Treasury bonds; (ii) real estate; and (iii) commodities. The Advisor expects to obtain its exposure to the Target Asset Classes primarily through its investments in underlying funds, but the fund also may invest directly in equity interests in real estate investment trusts (REITs) and in intermediate-term U.S. Treasury bonds. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
HIDE is an actively managed fund that dynamically allocates its assets to US Treasury bonds, real estate, and commodities. The fund shifts exposure based on momentum and trend-following factors.

HIDE dynamically allocates among asset classes that behave differently in various market conditions. The sub-adviser employs an investment model to determine asset allocations, retaining the discretion to modify. When all target asset classes have a buy signal, the fund invests 50% in intermediate-term US Treasury bonds, 25% in real estate, and 25% in commodities. These target weightings can change based on the analysis of current market conditions. While the fund invests in registered investment companies, such as ETFs, it may invest directly in REITs and US Treasurys. The investment model, which relies on past prices and return data, uses absolute momentum and trend-following factors to determine allocations and/or investments to cash and cash equivalents. The quantitative model is updated at least monthly. The sub-adviser may use a variety of lookbacks and formations, subject to change based on research efforts.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term total return. The fund primarily invests its assets in the shares of registered investment companies, including affiliated and non-affiliated ETFs, that emphasize investments in (i) intermediate-term U.S. Treasury bonds; (ii) real estate; and (iii) commodities. The Advisor expects to obtain its exposure to the Target Asset Classes primarily through its investments in underlying funds, but the fund also may invest directly in equity interests in real estate investment trusts (REITs) and in intermediate-term U.S. Treasury bonds. It is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Global Listed Private Equity ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to mirror the performance of a global index comprising publicly traded private equity companies, specifically focusing on up to 30 of the most actively traded firms primarily engaged in direct private equity investment strategies. Utilizing a market-capitalization weighting approach, the fund allocates at least 80% of its assets to component securities—predominantly common stocks of global firms of any size, including U.S. Business Development Companies (BDCs). Its investment profile reflects the index's potential concentration in particular industries or regions, and it is classified as non-diversified, offering focused exposure to the listed private equity sector.
description_original: The index consists of up to 30 qualifying listed private equity companies. The fund invests insecurities that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. It will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities. The fund will concentrate its investments in a particular industry or group of industries, country or region to approximately the same extent as the index is so concentrated. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PEX tracks a market-cap-weighted index of publicly traded private equity firms around the world.

PEX is the third launch in the Global Private Equity Segment and is a market-cap-selected and -weighted fund, thus offering plain vanilla exposure to investors. The underlying index tracks 30 qualifying listed private equity companies which were screened based on, among other things, greater relative trading volume. Generally, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index, and will primarily invest in common stocks of domestic and foreign companies (including in large part BDCs for US-domiciled companies) of any size.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the most actively traded listed private equity companies that mainly pursue a direct private equity investment strategy. It will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the LPX Direct Listed Private Equity Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the most actively traded listed private equity companies that mainly pursue a direct private equity investment strategy. It will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.

name: KraneShares Emerging Markets Healthcare Index ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to provide exposure to the healthcare sector within emerging markets by tracking a market-capitalization-weighted index. The portfolio encompasses companies across the full market-cap spectrum, including those engaged in pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, healthcare administration, medical equipment, and various health services, which must meet specific size, liquidity, and tradability requirements. Holdings are weighted by market capitalization and rebalanced semi-annually, with caps typically applied to individual security and country weights. Characterized as non-diversified, the fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in its underlying index components or economically similar instruments. Prospective investors should be aware that this fund is closing, with its final trading day set for October 18, 2023.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index includes companies that RBICS classifies as engaged in the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, medical specialties, managed health care, hospital/nursing management, medical/nursing services and services to the health industry businesses. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
KMED tracks a market-cap-weighted index of emerging market firms in the healthcare sector.

The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 18, 2023. KMED accurately represents the healthcare space within emerging markets. The funds holdings span the full market-cap spectrum, and include companies involved in pharmaceuticals, biotech, healthcare administration, and medical equipment. In addition, companies should meet size, liquidity, and tradability screens in order to be included in the portfolio. Selected securities are weighted according to market-cap and rebalanced semi-annually so that no individual security and country exceeds 4.5% and 45% weights respectively.

name: IndexIQ Active ETF Trust - IQ CBRE Real Assets ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks total return through both capital growth and current income by investing globally, primarily in the equity securities of real assets companies. Such companies are those deriving substantial revenue or holding significant assets in infrastructure—including transportation, utilities, energy, and communications sectors—or real estate, encompassing REITs, property owners/managers, and firms with extensive property holdings. The fund normally commits at least 80% of its assets to securities issued by these real asset companies, aiming for investments with attractive income growth, potential inflation protection, and long-term capital appreciation characteristics. While primarily investing in common stock, the portfolio may also incorporate preferred stock, convertible securities, MLPs, depositary receipts, rights, warrants, and potentially other ETFs with similar exposure, with up to 30% potentially allocated to emerging markets. Additionally, Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) criteria are considered within the investment selection process.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its assets (net assets plus borrowings for investment purposes) in securities issued by real assets companies. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests primarily in common stock, but may also invest in other equity securities including preferred stock, convertible securities, rights or warrants to buy common stocks, master limited partnerships (“MLPs”), and depositary receipts with characteristics similar to common stock.
description_etfcom:
IQRA is an actively managed equity strategy that invests globally in companies tied to real assets, such as infrastructure and real estate. The fund seeks total return through growth and income.

IQRA pursues a total return strategy through a targeted portfolio of common stocks tied to real asset companies. Such companies are those that derive most of their revenue or assets invested in infrastructure or real estate. Infrastructure companies are typically within the transportation, utility, energy, or communications industries. Real estate companies may include REITs, real estate owners or managers, and companies with substantial real estate holdings. Investments selected are considered to have attractive income growth, protection against inflation, and long-term capital appreciation. ESG criteria are also taken into consideration. Up to 30% of the portfolio may be in stocks from emerging markets. The fund may also hold MLPs, preferred stock, convertible securities, or ETFs that provide similar exposure to pursue the funds objective. Prior to Aug. 28, 2024, the fund name was branded under IndexIQ.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks total return through capital growth and current income. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its assets (net assets plus borrowings for investment purposes) in securities issued by real assets companies. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests primarily in common stock, but may also invest in other equity securities including preferred stock, convertible securities, rights or warrants to buy common stocks, master limited partnerships (“MLPs”), and depositary receipts with characteristics similar to common stock.

name: SPDR S&P Transportation ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to track the total return performance of the S&P Transportation Select Industry Index, which represents the U.S. transportation segment of the S&P Total Market Index. Employing a sampling strategy, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities comprising this index. Its distinct characteristic is the use of an equal-weighted methodology, which helps diversify exposure across large, mid, and small-cap stocks and reduces the concentration typical in market-cap weighted approaches to the transportation sector. It provides targeted exposure to various sub-industries, including air freight & logistics, airlines, railroads, trucking, marine transport, and related services, with the underlying index rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Transportation ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Transportation Select Industry Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the transportation segment of the S&P TMI, comprises the following sub-industries: Air Freight & Logistics, Airport Services, Cargo Ground Transportation, Highways & Rail Tracks, Marine Transportation, Marine Ports & Services,Passenger Airlines, Passenger Ground Transportation, and Rail TransportationSeeks to track a modified equal weighted index which provides the potential for unconcentrated industry exposure across large, mid and small cap stocksAllows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional sector based investing
description_etfcom:
XTN tracks a broad-based, equal-weighted index of US stocks in the transportation industry.

XTN offers a straightforward work-around for the transportation industry's high concentration by equal-weighting its holdings. That drastically cuts its weighted average market cap and introduces some sector biases. Eligible securities must be included in the S&P Total Market Index and must meet certain liquidity and capitalization thresholds.
