The index is an equal-weighted index composed of the securities comprising the NASDAQ-100 Index® that are classified as "technology" according to the Industry Classification Benchmark classification system.

name: Invesco DWA Industrials Momentum ETF
merged_description: This ETF focuses on the U.S. industrials sector, employing a strategy centered on momentum. It seeks to track a Dorsey Wright index composed of at least 30 industrial stocks demonstrating powerful relative strength, selecting and weighting them based on price momentum characteristics. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in these index constituents, utilizing a full replication approach. This methodology provides a distinct, growth-oriented perspective on industrial equities, with the underlying index being reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the industrials sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_etfcom:
PRN tracks an index of U.S. industrial firms selected and weighted by price momentum.

PRN changed its tune in February 2014 but continues to provide an alternate take on US industrial firms. The old version of the fund used a multi-factor selection method coupled with a tiered equal-weighting scheme that produced a vastly different portfolio than our neutral benchmark. Currently the fund follows a Dorsey-Wright relative strength index that selects and weights stocks by price momentum. The fund selects the top, at least 30 stocks, with the highest momentum scores in the industrial space. The fund uses a full replication indexing strategy, meaning PRN will generally invest in all of the stocks of the underlying index and in proportion to the weightings. Overall, PRN offers a different, growth-focused take on industrial stocks. Investors should consider all-in costs of holding the fund. The fund is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco DWA Industrials Momentum ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the industrials sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Industrials Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the industrials sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.

name: Invesco MSCI Global Timber ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides exposure to the global timber industry by tracking a market-capitalization weighted index of companies across developed and emerging markets. It invests at least 90% of its assets in index components, including ADRs and GDRs, targeting firms engaged in the ownership and management of forests and timberlands or the production of finished products using timber, such as those in the forest, paper, and packaging industries, along with specialized timber REITs. Although designed to cover the full market-cap spectrum and limit single stock concentrations to 5%, the fund is formally classified as non-diversified, reflecting the focused nature of the timber sector.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs") that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of equity securities of companies that are primarily engaged in the ownership and management of forests and timberlands and the production of finished products that use timber as a raw material. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CUT tracks a market cap-weighted index of global timber companies across the entire market-cap spectrum.

CUT offers plain-vanilla exposure to timber-related equities. The fund selects and weights stocks by market cap, and limits single-stock positions at 5%. The position limit matters in this highly concentrated space the fund caps its exposure to stay RIC-compliant, obtaining more diversification while reducing its pure play exposure. Its MSCI Index holds stocks in the forest, paper and paper packaging industries (per GICS) as well as specialized timber REITS to cover the likes of Weyerhaeuser. Prior to May 20, 2016, CUT tracked the Beacon Global Timber Index, an index with a multifactor selection process that aimed to pick winners rather than match the market. The change was material with respect to holdings, but the funds overall focus has not wavered from global timber exposure.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs") that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of equity securities of companies in both developed and emerging markets throughout the world that are engaged in the ownership and management of forests and timberlands and the production of finished products that use timber as a raw material. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI ACWI IMI Timber Select Capped Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs") that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of equity securities of companies in both developed and emerging markets throughout the world that are engaged in the ownership and management of forests and timberlands and the production of finished products that use timber as a raw material. The fund is non-diversified.

name: FT Energy Income Partners Strategy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks risk-adjusted total return by investing at least 80% of its assets in equity securities within the broader energy market. Its portfolio includes global companies of various market capitalizations classified under GICS energy and utilities (excluding water), as well as other firms deriving significant revenue (at least 50%) from activities across the energy value chain—such as exploration, production, transportation, processing, refining, distribution, or marketing of energy sources—and related services. The selection process emphasizes yield, growth, and valuation, targeting companies with stable cash flows, high and sustainable dividend payouts, potential for earnings growth, and value appreciation. To comply with tax regulations, the fund limits its holdings in Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs) and other entities taxed as partnerships, and it is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowing for investment purposes) in a portfolio of equity securities in the broader energy market ("Energy Companies"). The fund may invest in U.S. and non-U.S. companies with various market capitalizations. While the fund may invest in equity securities of MLPs, the fund will limit its investment in MLPs, or other companies taxed as partnerships in order to comply with applicable tax diversification rules. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: EIPX actively manages a portfolio of energy firms, stretching across multiple industries from the broadly defined energy space. The fund includes global companies classified under GICS energy, utilities (except water), and other sectors that derive at least 50% of their revenues from exploration, development, production, transportation, processing, storing, refining, distribution, or marketing of oil and gas, as well as other energy sources. Firms that derive at least half of their profits from engineering, consultation, and construction services are also eligible for inclusion. Holdings are selected by evaluating a companys yield, growth, and valuation. The sub-adviser looks for companies with stable cash flows, high and sustainable dividend payouts, increasing per share earnings, and the potential for positive changes in value. The fund limits its exposure to MLPs and other firms taxed as partnerships to comply with applicable tax diversification rules.
description_yahoo: Under normal market conditions, the fund will seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowing for investment purposes) in a portfolio of equity securities in the broader energy market (“Energy Companies”). The fund may invest in U.S. and non-U.S. companies with various market capitalizations. While the fund may invest in equity securities of MLPs, the fund will limit its investment in MLPs, or other companies taxed as partnerships in order to comply with applicable tax diversification rules. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks risk-adjusted total return. Under normal market conditions, the fund will seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowing for investment purposes) in a portfolio of equity securities in the broader energy market (“Energy Companies”). The fund may invest in U.S. and non-U.S. companies with various market capitalizations. While the fund may invest in equity securities of MLPs, the fund will limit its investment in MLPs, or other companies taxed as partnerships in order to comply with applicable tax diversification rules. It is non-diversified.

name: Defiance Hotel, Airline, and Cruise ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers concentrated exposure to the global travel sector by tracking a rules-based index focused specifically on the passenger airline, hotel/resort, and cruise industries. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 80% of its assets in globally-listed companies deriving a minimum of 50% of their revenue from these core travel segments, provided they meet specific market capitalization and liquidity standards. The underlying index utilizes a modified market-capitalization weighting approach, incorporating tiers, liquidity adjustments, caps on individual holdings, and constraints on the aggregate weight of each industry segment. Characterized as non-diversified, the fund's index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that consists of globally-listed stocks of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from the passenger airline, hotel and resort, or cruise industries (“Travel Companies”) as determined by MV Index Solutions. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in Travel Companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CRUZ tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index that gives global exposure to the airline, hotel and cruise industries.

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 28, 2025. CRUZ provides pure-play exposure to three segments of the travel and tourism businessairline, hotel and resort, and cruise. The fund holds at least 25 globally-listed stocks of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenue from the three business segments. Eligible companies must also meet investability and liquidity requirements, including a minimum market-cap of $150 million. Weighting is done in tiers, holdings are weighted by market-cap within each segment, subject to a liquidity overlay and an 8% single security cap. Each segment is also restricted to an aggregate portfolio weight of 1550%. The index is reconstituted semi-annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the BlueStar Global Hotels, Airlines, and Cruises Index (the “index”). The index is a rules-based index that consists of globally-listed stocks of companies that derive at least 50% of their revenues from the passenger airline, hotel and resort, or cruise industries (“Travel Companies”) as determined by MV Index Solutions. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in Travel Companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity MSCI Health Care Index ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to replicate the performance of a broad, market-capitalization-weighted index representing the U.S. health care sector. Investing at least 80% of its assets in securities from its underlying benchmark, the fund provides comprehensive exposure across large-, mid-, and small-cap companies spanning numerous health care subsectors. A key feature is the index's 25/50 capping methodology, which limits issuer concentration. Rather than holding every constituent security, the fund utilizes a representative sampling strategy to track the index, which is rebalanced quarterly. This approach offers diversified exposure within the health care space, potentially lessening the weight of dominant large pharmaceutical firms compared to uncapped strategies.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Health Care 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the health care sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Health Care 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FHLC tracks a market-cap-weighted index of stocks in the broad US health care sector.

FHLC casts a wide net across the entire health care market in the US, capturing over 300 large-, mid- and small-cap companies and spanning more than 10 subsectors. This diversification gives the vanilla fund less exposure to the big pharma companies that dominate the market, and more exposure to sectors like drug retailers and insurance. Prior to December 1, 2020, the fund tracked the MSCI USA IMI Health Care Index, an uncapped version of the present index. To meet diversification requirements, FHLC now uses a 25/50 capping methodology. Notably, instead of replicating the underlying index, the fund uses a representative sampling strategy. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Health Care 25/50 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Health Care 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the health care sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Health Care 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Themes US Small Cap Cash Flow Champions ETF
merged_description: This passively managed ETF focuses on U.S. small-capitalization companies selected for their strong cash flow characteristics. It aims to track an index constructed by first identifying small-cap U.S. companies with positive cash flow yields over the last three years, and then selecting the top 75 based on their estimated cash flow yield for the upcoming year. The underlying index weights these chosen companies by their free-float market capitalization, subject to a 5% cap per holding, and is rebalanced quarterly. The fund primarily uses a replication strategy, investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's components, but may utilize representative sampling if necessary. It is classified as non-diversified and may engage in securities lending up to one-third of its total assets.
description_original: The index is a free-float adjusted, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to small capitalization U.S. companies that have a high cash flow yield. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the securities that comprise the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SMCF is a passively managed ETF that tracks an index of small-cap US equities perceived to have high cash flow yield. From a universe of small-cap companies incorporated and listed in the US, the fund considers securities with positive cash flow yields over the last three years. Qualified companies are ranked according to the following years estimated cash flow yield. The fund then selects 75 of the top-ranked companies. The portfolio is weighted based on their free-float market capitalization, which is capped at 5%. The fund seeks to employ a replication strategy, meaning it will invest in all of the component securities in the same proportion as the index. However, the fund may still utilize a representative sampling strategy, when necessary, in which securities are chosen to provide the same investment characteristics as the index. The fund may engage in securities lending, up to one-third of its total assets. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive U.S. Small Cap Cash Flow Champions Index. The index is a free-float adjusted, market capitalization weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to small capitalization U.S. companies that have a high cash flow yield. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the securities that comprise the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares GSCI Commodity Dynamic Roll Strategy ETF
merged_description: This fund aims to achieve total return by tracking a broad commodity index that employs an enhanced, dynamic roll strategy for its futures contracts. Annually, the index selects 14 commodities from six major groups based on global production and price levels. Exposure to these commodities is gained primarily through derivatives such as exchange-traded futures, options, and swaps. A distinctive feature is its algorithm-based approach to optimize the monthly rolling of futures contracts, seeking better implied yields. The fund utilizes a wholly owned Cayman subsidiary to hold these commodity-linked investments, which allows for simplified tax reporting via a 1099 form rather than a K-1. Additionally, investment-grade fixed income instruments are held for cash and collateral management purposes.
description_original: The index measures the performance of futures contracts. In seeking to achieve its investment objective, the fund may invest in a combination of exchange-traded commodity futures contracts, exchange-traded options on commodity-related futures contracts and exchange-cleared commodity related swaps (together, “Commodity Linked Investments”), thereby obtaining exposure to the commodities markets.
description_etfcom: COMT provides exposure to six broad commodity groups selected from the S&P GSCI. In January of each year, the index selects 14 commodities from the broad groups based on global production levels and the price of the commodity. The fund gains its exposure through commodity-linked investments such as futures, options, and swaps. An algorithm identifies the optimum implied yields for a monthly roll strategy. In terms of commodity exposure, the fund offers some tax simplicity in the form of a 1099. COMT avoids issuing a K-1 by relying on a wholly owned Cayman subsidiary to access commodity derivatives. The funds investment grade fixed income investments are cash management tools focused on the cash or collateral portion of the portfolio with the objective to generate interest income and capital appreciation. Prior to March 1, 2021, the fund name was the iShares Commodities Select Strategy ETF. The fund was previously actively managed while aiming to mimic the underlying index.
description_yahoo: The index measures the performance of futures contracts. In seeking to achieve its investment objective, the fund may invest in a combination of exchange-traded commodity futures contracts, exchange-traded options on commodity-related futures contracts and exchange-cleared commodity related swaps (together, “Commodity-Linked Investments”), thereby obtaining exposure to the commodities markets.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P GSCI Dynamic Roll (USD) Total Return Index composed of a broad range of commodity exposures with enhanced roll selection, on a total return basis. The index measures the performance of futures contracts. In seeking to achieve its investment objective, the fund may invest in a combination of exchange-traded commodity futures contracts, exchange-traded options on commodity-related futures contracts and exchange-cleared commodity related swaps (together, “Commodity-Linked Investments”), thereby obtaining exposure to the commodities markets.

name: Amplify Lithium & Battery Technology ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to mirror the performance of a market-cap-weighted index focused on the global lithium battery technology sector. It primarily invests (at least 80% of assets) in companies deriving significant revenue from the development, production, use, mining, or processing of lithium and other key battery materials such as cobalt, nickel, manganese, and graphite, as well as those substantially involved in electric vehicle production. The underlying index employs specific revenue thresholds for company inclusion and incorporates weighting constraints, including caps on individual securities and the overall allocation to the automobile industry, while being classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to global companies deriving material revenue associated with the development, production and use of lithium battery technology. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
BATT tracks a market-cap-weighted index that invests in global advanced battery material companies such as those that mine or produce lithium, cobalt, nickel, manganese, and graphite.

BATT invests in advanced battery materials and technology companies globally. A committee selects the components of the fund from a pool of eligible companies. To qualify for inclusion in the selection pool, companies must generate at least 50% of their revenue from the mining, exploration, production, development, processing, or recycling of lithium, cobalt, nickel, manganese, or graphite. Also, companies that hold 10% or more of the global market share for advanced battery materials and report their primary source of revenue as such are also eligible. Alternatively, companies that derive 90% of their revenue from the development and production of electric vehicles can also be included. Index components are weighted by their market-cap, up to a maximum initial weight of 7%. Industry weight to automobiles and components cannot exceed 20% of the total index weight. Prior to October 12,2020, the fund was actively managed and was named Amplify Advanced Battery Metals and Materials ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that generally correspond to the price and yield of the EQM Lithium & Battery Technology Index. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to global companies deriving material revenue associated with the development, production and use of lithium battery technology. It is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Dynamic Media ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund invests at least 90% of its assets in securities comprising its underlying index, focusing on the theme of "future media." The index includes large- to small-cap companies from developed and emerging markets that derive at least 50% of their revenue from subsectors related to advancements in media technology and products. These component securities are weighted based on a combination of free-float market capitalization and their revenue exposure to these specific future media themes. The strategy aims to capture companies expected to benefit from long-term structural trends driven by technological and societal change, with the portfolio rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of U.S. media companies. These companies are principally engaged in the development, production, sale and distribution of goods or services used in the media industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: GGME seeks to track an index of large- to small-cap companies from developed and emerging markets that derive at least 50% of their revenue from subsectors that relate to future media. These component securities are expected to benefit from long-term structural trends driven by technological and societal change, which may have a substantial impact on their performance. Index securities are weighted proportionally to their free-float market capitalization, multiplied by aggregate revenue exposure to the applicable subsectors. Rebalancing is done quarterly starting in March, and reviewed annually in June. Prior to August 28, 2023, the fund was named Invesco Dynamic Media ETF, with ticker PBS, and tracked the Dynamic Media Intellidex Index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of securities of companies with significant exposure to technologies or products that contribute to future media through direct revenue. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Affinity World Leaders Equity ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a multi-factor strategy focused on identifying leading companies within global developed equity markets. Starting from a broad universe of large-cap developed market stocks, it selects approximately the top 10% from both U.S. and international regions based on a proprietary scoring system that evaluates valuation, analyst expectations (considering earnings quality and improving fundamentals), and stock price momentum. The resulting portfolio, typically comprising 150 to 250 holdings across the U.S. and potentially up to 20 international countries, utilizes a proprietary risk-management system for weighting. It aims for sector-neutral exposure relative to its selection universe, maintains significant geographic diversification, invests at least 80% of its assets in the targeted securities, and rebalances semi-annually.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities included in the index. The index is expected to consist of approximately 150 to 250 stocks of companies located in the U.S. and in at least three countries outside of the U.S. and may invest in up to 20 countries. It will be significantly invested in the securities of international companies in addition to securities of U.S. companies.
description_etfcom: WLDR provides a multi-factor take on developed market equities. The fund starts by selecting the securities that cover the top 85% of the Refinitiv Global Developed Equity Index by market-cap. These securities are divided into two regions (US and international), and scored based on: valuations, analyst expectations (includes earnings quality and improving fundamentals), and stock price momentum. The fund also applies a proprietary ranking system which considers the correlation between score components and subsequent long-term performance. WLDR selects the top 10% of firms within each region, which are then weighted using a proprietary risk-management system. The portfolio aims for sector-neutral exposure relative to the selection universe, with a similar geographic distribution. The index rebalances semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally, before fees and expenses, to the performance of the Thomson Reuters StarMine Affinity World Leaders Index (the "index"). The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities included in the index. The index is expected to consist of approximately 150 to 250 stocks of companies located in the U.S. and in at least three countries outside of the U.S. and may invest in up to 20 countries. It will be significantly invested in the securities of international companies in addition to securities of U.S. companies.

name: SPDR S&P Retail ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to mirror the performance of an index representing the U.S. retail sector, drawn from a broad total market index. Employing a sampling strategy, it invests substantially all, and at least 80%, of its assets in the securities composing its target index. A key feature is the index's equal-weighting methodology, which provides unconcentrated exposure across diverse retail sub-industries such as apparel, automotive, electronics, food, drug, and specialty retail. This equal-weighting approach notably results in significantly greater exposure to small- and micro-cap stocks compared to market-cap-weighted funds, offering investors a way to take targeted positions across the retail landscape, regardless of company size. The underlying index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Retail ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Retail Select Industry Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure the retail segment of the S&P TMI, which comprises the following sub-industries: Apparel Retail, Automotive Retail, Broadline Retail, Computer & Electronic Retail, Consumer Staples Merchandise Retail, Drug Retail, Food Retailers, and Other Specialty Retail.Seeks to track a modified equal weighted index which provides the potential for unconcentrated industry exposure across large, mid and small cap stocksAllows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional sector based investing
description_etfcom:
XRT tracks a broad-based, equal-weighted index of stocks in the US retail industry.

XRT uses equal-weighting rather than market-cap-weighting to make radical differences in exposure and performance than its peers. The effect of equal weighting is keener than some other equal-weighted funds because it draws retail stocks, as defined by GICS, from the broad S&P Total Market Index that include stocks of any capitalization. The result, XRT has an order of magnitude in greater small- and micro-cap exposure. The fund holds retail companies that stretch across multiple sub-industries that include apparel, automotive, computers and electronics, department stores, drugs, food, general merchandise stores, hypermarkets and super centers, internet and direct marketing retail, and specialty stores. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: In seeking to track the performance of the S&P Retail Select Industry Index (the "index"), the fund employs a sampling strategy. It generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index represents the retail segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of an index derived from the retail segment of a U.S. total market composite index. In seeking to track the performance of the S&P Retail Select Industry Index (the "index"), the fund employs a sampling strategy. It generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index represents the retail segment of the S&P Total Market Index ("S&P TMI").

name: Schwab Ariel ESG ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in U.S. small- and mid-capitalization equity securities, generally targeting companies within the size range of the Russell 2500™ Index at the time of purchase, although investments outside this range are permitted. The core investment process involves evaluating companies based on fundamental characteristics and valuation potential, followed by applying proprietary environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. This ESG screen includes excluding companies deriving significant revenue from controversial activities such as tobacco, fossil fuels, private prisons, firearms, and weapons. Operating under a non-transparent structure, the fund discloses its full holdings quarterly with a 60-day lag, providing a daily tracking basket in lieu of the actual portfolio; however, the fund adviser retains discretion to manage a portion of assets potentially without applying the sub-adviser's specific ESG risk rating system.
description_original: The fund invests primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of U.S. companies that have been evaluated based on certain environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria. It typically invests in exchange-traded securities of small- and mid-capitalization companies which are companies with capitalizations within the range of the Russell 2500™ Index, as measured at the time of purchase; however, the fund may invest in exchange-traded securities of companies outside the stated range.
description_etfcom:
SAEF is an actively-managed, non-transparent ETF that holds a portfolio of small- and mid-cap US firms screened for ESG criteria. The fund utilizes the Natixis/NYSE non-transparent model.

SAEF is the first active ETF and first ESG offering from Schwab. The fund uses the proprietary ESG research of its sub-adviser to build a portfolio of small- and mid-cap US stocks. The sub-adviser initially considers company valuation and screens for fundamental characteristics that enable capital appreciation. A proprietary risk-rating based on various ESG criteria is then assigned to each prospective holding. The sub-adviser screens out companies that derive significant revenue from controversial business activities such as those involving tobacco, fossil fuels, private prisons, firearms, and weapons. However, the fund adviser has the discretion to manage a portion of the assets, which may not utilize the sub-advisers ESG risk rating. SAEF only discloses its full holdings quarterly, with a 60-day lag. A tracking basket is published daily on its website, in place of the actual portfolio.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund invests primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of U.S. companies that have been evaluated based on certain environmental, social and governance (ESG) criteria. It typically invests in exchange-traded securities of small- and mid-capitalization companies which are companies with capitalizations within the range of the Russell 2500™ Index, as measured at the time of purchase; however, the fund may invest in exchange-traded securities of companies outside the stated range.

name: ALPS Equal Sector Weight ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle operates as a fund of funds, aiming to replicate the performance of an index that equally weights all active Select Sector SPDR® ETFs. By investing at least 90% of its assets into these underlying sector ETFs, it constructs a portfolio primarily composed of large-cap US stocks. The core strategy involves assigning equal importance to each major market sector, which contrasts with market-cap weighting by overweighting smaller sectors and underweighting larger ones. This equal-weighted portfolio undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: In order to track the underlying index, the fund will use a fund of funds approach, and seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 90% of its total assets in the shares of the Underlying Sector ETFs. The underlying index is an index of ETFs comprised of all active Select Sector SPDR® ETFs in an equal weighted portfolio. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
EQL tracks an equal-weighted index of all select sector SPDR ETFs.

EQL uses a fund of funds approach in investingit takes all major sectors that make up the S&P 500 index, and then weights each sector equally. The result is a portfolio of large-cap US stocks that underweights the largest sectors in the index, like technology and financials, and overweights the minor sectors, like basic materials and utilities. Proponents claim that the funds countercyclical rebalancing schedule will help it outperform the regular S&P 500 over time. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: In order to track the underlying index, the fund will use a "fund of funds" approach, and seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 90% of its total assets in the shares of the Underlying Sector ETFs. The underlying index is an index of ETFs comprised of all active Select Sector SPDR® ETFs in an equal weighted portfolio. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the performance of the NYSE® Equal Sector Weight Index (the "underlying index"). In order to track the underlying index, the fund will use a "fund of funds" approach, and seek to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 90% of its total assets in the shares of the Underlying Sector ETFs. The underlying index is an index of ETFs comprised of all active Select Sector SPDR® ETFs in an equal weighted portfolio. It is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard Dividend Growth Fund Investor Shares
merged_description: This investment focuses primarily on generating a growing stream of income over time, supported by secondary objectives of long-term capital appreciation and current income. It achieves this by investing mainly in stocks that currently pay dividends, specifically selecting high-quality companies with prospects for sustained earnings growth and a demonstrated willingness to increase their dividends consistently. While holdings are typically large-cap and potentially undervalued, the fund maintains diversification across various industry sectors, underscoring its core strategy centered on dividend growth.
description_original: The fund invests primarily in stocks that tend to offer current dividends. It focuses on high-quality companies that have prospects for long-term total returns as a result of their ability to grow earnings and their willingness to increase dividends over time. These stocks typically-but not always-will be large-cap, will be undervalued relative to the market, and will show potential for increasing dividends. The fund seeks to be diversified across industry sectors.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide, primarily, a growing stream of income over time and, secondarily, long-term capital appreciation and current income. The fund invests primarily in stocks that tend to offer current dividends. It focuses on high-quality companies that have prospects for long-term total returns as a result of their ability to grow earnings and their willingness to increase dividends over time. These stocks typically-but not always-will be large-cap, will be undervalued relative to the market, and will show potential for increasing dividends. The fund seeks to be diversified across industry sectors.

name: Strive U.S. Energy ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund passively tracks the Bloomberg US Energy Select Index, concentrating on U.S. oil and gas producers selected from the broader U.S. equity market. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in these energy companies, it employs a float-adjusted market-capitalization weighting methodology, subject to specific issuer and aggregate caps, with quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution. A key characteristic is its active use of shareholder engagement and proxy voting rights, aiming to influence portfolio companies to prioritize shareholder returns and core energy operations, potentially diverging from prevailing environmental, social, and governance (ESG) agendas.
description_original: The index is a subset of a float-adjusted capitalization weighted index of equity securities comprising the 1,000 largest companies from the U.S. stock market. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in U.S. energy companies. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DRLL tracks a market cap-weighted index of US-listed stocks in the energy sector. The fund aims to influence companies to prioritize returns through shareholder engagement and proxy voting, without regard to ESG agendas.

DRLL attempts to use the power of shareholder engagement and proxy voting to influence energy companies. The issuer believes there is an opportunity for energy companies to focus on solving global demand for energy and abandon political agendas, specifically ESG-imposed constraints. The fund is passively managed, providing exposure to oil and gas producers in the US equity market. From a starting universe of 1500 US-listed firms, the fund selects companies in the energy industry or sector specifically involved in oil and gas exploration, production, refinement, and marketing, including integrated oil companies. Constituents are free float-adjusted market cap-weighted with single issuers capped at 22.5%, and the aggregate weight of all issuers that individually exceed 4.5% of the portfolio capped at 45%. The index is reconstituted semi-annually and is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to April 11, 2024, the fund tracked the Solactive United States Energy Regulated Capped Index TR.
description_yahoo: The fund seeks to track the investment results of the Bloomberg US Energy Select Index, which measures the performance of U.S. oil and gas producers. The index is designed by Bloomberg Index Services Limited and consists of U.S. equity securities. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Bloomberg US Energy Select Index. The fund seeks to track the investment results of the Bloomberg US Energy Select Index, which measures the performance of U.S. oil and gas producers. The index is designed by Bloomberg Index Services Limited and consists of U.S. equity securities. It is non-diversified.

name: Dimensional - US Marketwide Value ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation, with consideration for maximizing after-tax returns. It invests in a broad and diverse portfolio of U.S. companies across all market capitalizations, specifically targeting those identified by the advisor as value stocks possessing lower relative prices and higher profitability potential. Stock selection incorporates fundamental factors, utilizing metrics such as price-to-cash flow and price-to-earnings ratios to assess relative price, alongside profitability measures like earnings relative to book value or assets. While holdings are typically market-cap weighted, the active approach allows for adjustments. The fund may also use futures contracts and options to manage overall equity market exposure related to portfolio cash flows.
description_original: The US Marketwide Value ETF is designed to purchase a broad and diverse group of securities of U.S. companies that the Advisor determines to be value stocks. The Advisor considers companies of all market capitalizations for purchase by the Portfolio. The Portfolio may purchase or sell futures contracts and options on futures contracts for U.S. equity securities and indices, to increase or decrease equity market exposure based on actual or expected cash inflows to or outflows from the Portfolio.
description_etfcom: DFUV is an actively managed fund that seeks long-term capital appreciation while maximizing after-tax returns. The fund holds US stocks that the funds advisor considers as having a lower relative price and higher profitability potential. Stocks are evaluated based on fundamental factors such as: price-to-cash flow or price-to-earnings ratios to assess relative price, as well as earnings or profits from operations relative to book value or assets to meausre profitability. In addition, ratios such as recent changes in assets divided by total assets are used to review a firms investment characteristics. Holdings are typically market-cap-weighted but with an active approach, weightings may fluctuate. DFUV launched from a mutual fund conversion, starting with $8.3 billion in assets.
description_yahoo: The ETF is designed to purchase a broad and diverse group of securities of U.S. companies that the Advisor determines to be value stocks. The Advisor considers companies of all market capitalizations for purchase by the Portfolio. The Portfolio may purchase or sell futures contracts and options on futures contracts for U.S. equity securities and indices, to increase or decrease equity market exposure based on actual or expected cash inflows to or outflows from the Portfolio.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. The ETF is designed to purchase a broad and diverse group of securities of U.S. companies that the Advisor determines to be value stocks. The Advisor considers companies of all market capitalizations for purchase by the Portfolio. The Portfolio may purchase or sell futures contracts and options on futures contracts for U.S. equity securities and indices, to increase or decrease equity market exposure based on actual or expected cash inflows to or outflows from the Portfolio.

name: Spear Alpha ETF
merged_description: This actively-managed exchange-traded fund seeks long-term capital growth by investing primarily in equity securities, including common stocks and ADRs, of companies believed poised to benefit from breakthrough innovations that are transforming or have the potential to transform the industrial sector. The investment strategy focuses on firms involved, directly or indirectly, in themes such as environmental focus and decarbonization, manufacturing digitalization, robotics and industrial automation, photonics and additive manufacturing, space exploration, and artificial intelligence. Utilizing a combination of top-down analysis, bottom-up research, ESG screening, and fundamental assessment, the adviser selects a high-conviction portfolio, which can be modified based on changing business drivers or valuations. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that will invest primarily in equity securities, including common stock or American depositary receipts (“ADRs”) of companies that Spear Advisors LLC (the “Adviser”) believes are poised to benefit from breakthrough innovation in industrial technology. The Adviser defines innovations in industrial technology as those technological developments that are transforming or have the potential to transform the industrial sector. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SPRXs active strategy aims to invest in companies it believes will benefit from technological advancements in the industrial sector. The fund targets companies in any part of the supply chain, directly or indirectly, related to one of the following themes: environmental focus and decarbonization, manufacturing digitalization, robotics and industrial automation, photonics and additive manufacturing, space exploration, and artificial intelligence. SPRXs adviser uses a combination of top-down analysis, bottom-up research, and an ESG screen before granting eligibility. Those eligible are then screened through a final fundamental research process and selected for inclusion. This process will theoretically produce a portfolio of thematic companies that have the highest conviction for investment as determined by the adviser. Holdings can be modified at any time if there are significant changes to a companys business drivers or valuation.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that will invest primarily in equity securities, including common stock or American depositary receipts (“ADRs”) of companies that Spear Advisors LLC (the “Adviser”) believes are poised to benefit from breakthrough innovation in industrial technology. The Adviser defines “innovation in industrial technology” as those technological developments that are transforming or have the potential to transform the industrial sector. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital growth. The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that will invest primarily in equity securities, including common stock or American depositary receipts (“ADRs”) of companies that Spear Advisors LLC (the “Adviser”) believes are poised to benefit from breakthrough innovation in industrial technology. The Adviser defines “innovation in industrial technology” as those technological developments that are transforming or have the potential to transform the industrial sector. It is non-diversified.

name: SPDR S&P Kensho Final Frontiers ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on companies driving innovation within the "final frontiers" of deep space and deep sea exploration. It seeks to track the performance of an index composed primarily of US-listed equities whose products and services are central to advancements in these areas, potentially including space travel, exploration technology, and various types of drones. The underlying index utilizes artificial intelligence and scans company documents to select constituents, employing a quantitative, tier-weighted methodology that gives greater emphasis to 'core' companies central to the theme, with semi-annual rebalancing. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in index securities, the fund may also hold non-index equities or cash equivalents and is considered non-diversified, aiming to capture long-term growth potential from the expansion of human activity and understanding in space and the oceans.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Kensho Final Frontiers ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Kensho Final Frontiers Index (the “Index”)Seeks to track an index utilizing artificial intelligence and a quantitative weighting methodology to capture companies whose products and services are driving innovation behind the exploration of the final frontiers, which includes the areas of outer space and the deep seaMay provide an effective way to pursue long-term growth potential by investing in a portfolio of companies involved in the expansion of human understanding and presence in outer space and in the oceans
description_etfcom:
ROKT tracks a tier-weighted index of US equities associated with space and deep sea exploration.

ROKT focuses on US-listed companies whose products and services are driving innovation behind the exploration of deep space and deep sea. The underlying index is a combination of two sub-indexes, one that follows space travel and exploration, and another that follows the remotely operated or unmanned aerial, underwater, and surface-level drones market. The methodology involves scanning company documents and SEC submissions for search terms to determine inclusion in the index. Selected stocks are deemed either core or non-core depending on whether one of ROKTs themes is a central focus of the company. Holdings are initially weighted equally, with an overweighting factor applied to core stocks. The index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_yahoo: Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index is designed to capture companies whose products and services are driving innovation behind the exploration of deep space and deep sea. The fund may invest in equity securities that are not included in the index, cash and cash equivalents or money market instruments. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Kensho Final Frontiers Index. Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index is designed to capture companies whose products and services are driving innovation behind the exploration of deep space and deep sea. The fund may invest in equity securities that are not included in the index, cash and cash equivalents or money market instruments. It is non-diversified.

name: Invesco DWA Developed Markets Momentum ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to capture momentum in developed equity markets outside the United States by tracking a specialized index. It invests at least 90% of its assets in approximately 100 large-capitalization stocks selected based on high relative strength scores, according to a Dorsey Wright trend-following methodology. Holdings are weighted based on these same relative strength scores, giving greater prominence to top-performing securities. The fund aims for outperformance, potentially with less volatility than some alpha-seeking strategies, features a liquid basket of holdings, and is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of equity securities of large capitalization companies classified as developed markets, excluding the United States.
description_etfcom:
PIZ tracks an index of stocks in developed markets outside the U.S. that exhibit high relative strength characteristics.

PIZ searches for outperformance in developed markets outside the US based on a trend-following index from Dorsey Wright. In its attempt to beat the market, the fund favors large cap securities, and those eligible for index inclusion are assigned a relative strength score. Approximately 100 of these securities with the greatest scores will form the Underlying Index. Component weights are also based on relative scores, wherein higher scoring-securities receive larger weights. PIZ is also less volatile than some alpha-seekers. Its liquid basket also allows for straightforward block execution. The Fund and the Index are rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the fund traded under the name Invesco DWA Developed Markets Momentum ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Developed Markets Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of equity securities of large capitalization companies classified as developed markets, excluding the United States.

name: Simplify Risk Parity Treasury ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks to provide total returns that match or outperform the ICE U.S. Treasury 20+ Year Index, specifically focusing on achieving this goal on a calendar quarter basis rather than over other periods. The underlying index comprises U.S. dollar-denominated Treasury securities with maturities exceeding 20 years. To pursue its quarterly objective, the fund primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in a combination of U.S. Treasury futures contracts, call and put options on these futures, direct U.S. government securities like bills, notes, and bonds, or fixed income ETFs holding U.S. Treasuries. It may also hold cash, equivalents, or short-term debt for collateral purposes and rebalances quarterly to maintain alignment with its time-specific performance target.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to provide total return that matches or outperforms the performance of the ICE US Treasury 20+ Year Index for a calendar quarter, not for any other period. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in futures contracts, call options, and put options on U.S. treasury futures, U.S. government securities, such as bills, notes and bonds issued by the U.S. Treasury or fixed income ETFs that invest in U.S. Treasuries.
description_etfcom:
TYA seeks to match or outperform a US Treasury 20+ year index for a calendar quarter. The portfolio utilizes futures, call, and put options on US Treasury futures, ETFs, and government securities.

TYA is actively managed, yet aims to either match or outperform an index - the ICE US Treasury 20+ Year Index. The index consists of only USD-denominated, Treasury securities with term to maturity of greater than 20 years. TYA gains its exposure primarily through the use of US Treasury futures, call options, and put options, Treasury ETFs, and other government securities. The fund may also hold cash and cash-like instruments or short-term investment-grade debt securities to collateralize its derivatives investment. TYA seeks to pursue its objective for just a calendar quarter, not for any other period. As such, the fund performs quarterly rebalancing.
description_yahoo: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to provide total return that matches or outperforms the performance of the ICE U.S. Treasury 20+ Year Index for a calendar quarter, not for any other period. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in futures contracts, call options, and put options on U.S. treasury futures, U.S. government securities, such as bills, notes and bonds issued by the U.S. Treasury or fixed income ETFs that invest in U.S. Treasuries.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide total return that matches or outperforms the performance of the ICE U.S. Treasury 20+ Year Index on a calendar quarter basis. The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to provide total return that matches or outperforms the performance of the ICE U.S. Treasury 20+ Year Index for a calendar quarter, not for any other period. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in futures contracts, call options, and put options on U.S. treasury futures, U.S. government securities, such as bills, notes and bonds issued by the U.S. Treasury or fixed income ETFs that invest in U.S. Treasuries.

name: iShares Gold Strategy ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified investment product, which was delisted with its final trading day on August 12, 2024, offered exposure to gold through a specific blend of assets. It primarily tracked an index composed mainly (around 76%) of liquid gold futures contracts, held via a subsidiary structure, while also allocating a significant portion (around 24%) to an exchange-traded product backed by physical gold, specifically the iShares Gold Trust. A key feature aimed to provide tax advantages over traditional commodity investments by issuing a 1099 form (instead of a K-1) and subjecting capital gains to standard rates rather than the higher collectibles tax rate associated with physical gold. The fund and its underlying index followed a quarterly rebalancing schedule.
description_original: The underlying index is composed of exchange-traded gold futures contracts and one or more ETPs backed by or linked to physical gold. The fund invests in a combination of exchange-traded gold futures contracts and other exchange-traded or OTC derivatives that correlate to the investment returns of physical gold, based on the notional value of such derivative instruments and ETPs backed by or linked to physical gold, which may include the iShares Gold Trust. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is August 12, 2024. IAUF provides exposure to gold with a few twists. The Underlying Index allocates 76% to Bloomberg Gold Tracker Total Return Index (Tracker Index) and 24% to iShares Gold Trust (IAU). The Tracker Index holds a long position on liquid gold futures contracts traded on the CME. To provide maximum liquidity, October gold contract is excluded due to its low trading volume and open interest . The gold futures are held via a Cayman Islands subsidiary. IAUFs structure addresses two of the sticking points associated with gold exposure. First, IAUF shareholders will receive a 1099 form at tax time, similar to other equity positions, not the K-1 typically associated with commodity pools. Second, capital gains in the fund are taxed at the usual rates, not the higher collectibles rate associated with physical gold investments. The Underlying Index and fund are rebalanced quarterly. Prior to March 1, 2021, the fund was actively managed, aiming to maximize correlation with the Underlying Index.

name: Simplify Volt Pop Culture Disruption ETF
merged_description: This investment fund primarily seeks exposure to U.S. and foreign equity securities of companies involved in its core theme of pop culture disruption. A distinguishing feature of its strategy is the application of an option overlay to its equity investments. Characterized by a focused approach on its specific investment theme, the fund operates as a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The adviser and sub-adviser seek to achieve the fund's investment objective by investing in U.S. and foreign equity securities and equity securities of companies that are consistent with the fund's investment theme of pop culture disruption. The adviser applies an option overlay strategy to the fund's equity investments. Under normal circumstances, the fund primarily invests in U.S. and foreign equity securities of companies that are engaged in the fund's investment theme. It is non-diversified.

name: Principal Millennial Global Growth ETF
merged_description: This actively managed ETF, which ceased trading on October 13, 2023, focused on global growth companies expected to benefit from the economic activity and spending patterns of the Millennial generation (defined as those born between 1980 and the mid-2000s). It employed a proprietary quantitative model to select growth-oriented equity securities across all market capitalizations. Under normal circumstances, the fund invested at least 40% of its assets in foreign and emerging markets and concentrated its holdings (over 25%) in industries within the consumer discretionary and communication services sectors. Characterized as non-diversified and rebalanced annually, the fund had previously tracked an index before transitioning to active management in July 2022.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund primarily invests in equity securities, focusing on growth equity securities. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 40% of its net assets in foreign and emerging market securities. The fund invests in equity securities of different market capitalizations (small, medium, or large). The fund will concentrate its investments (invest more than 25% of its assets) in one or more industries within the consumer discretionary sector and one or more industries within the communication services sector.
description_etfcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 13, 2023. GENY is actively managed and aims to provide exposure to growth companies around the world that are determined to have significant economic exposure to the spending habits of Millennials, which are those born between 1980 and the mid-2000s. The fund manager uses a proprietary quantitative model designed to identify and select equity securities with medium or high Millennial exposure, based on the materiality of the company's exposure to Millennial-related themes and the potential role of Millennials in driving long-term growth. Some segments with the most Millennial exposure are likely to be included but may change as the Millennial generation ages. Stocks may be of any market capitalization. Up to 40% of the funds assets may be in foreign and emerging market securities. The fund is non-diversified and is rebalanced annually. Prior to July 15, 2022, the fund tracked an index with similar exposure.

name: iShares Evolved U.S. Media and Entertainment ETF
merged_description: This investment fund concentrates its portfolio, under normal circumstances, by investing at least 80% of its net assets in U.S.-listed common stocks of media and entertainment companies spanning large, mid, and small capitalizations. Its distinct strategy relies on identifying companies within a proprietary "Media and Entertainment Evolved Sector," which groups businesses based on economic characteristics historically correlated with traditional firms in this industry. Notably, the fund is non-diversified, allowing for potentially larger allocations to individual holdings.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in U.S. listed common stock of large-, mid- and small-capitalization media and entertainment companies. It will hold common stock of those companies that fall into the Media and Entertainment Evolved Sector which have economic characteristics that have been historically correlated with companies traditionally defined as media and entertainment companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree International Quality Dividend Growth Fund
merged_description: This ETF provides targeted exposure to dividend-paying companies demonstrating quality and growth characteristics within developed markets, specifically excluding the US and Canada. It tracks an index constructed by screening stocks for factors like return on equity, return on assets, long-term earnings growth estimates, and dividend sustainability, selecting the top 300 qualifiers. These holdings are then weighted based on their total annual cash dividends paid, subject to caps on individual securities, countries, and sectors at rebalancing. Committing to invest at least 80% of its assets in index components or economically similar investments, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks with growth characteristics of companies in the industrialized world, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IQDG tracks an index of dividend-paying total market stocks from developed markets outside the US and Canada. The index is weighted by dividends paid.

IQDG offers an alternative, dividend-flavored take on total market stocks from developed countries outside the US and Canada. Like many WisdomTree ETFs, IQDG only holds dividend-paying stocks and deploys growth and quality screens. The fund ranks stocks by quality (3-year average ROE and ROA) and growth (long-term earnings growth estimates). Earnings yield must exceed dividend yield as well, a measure of dividend sustainability. The top 300 names make the cut and receive weight according to the total of their annual cash dividend payouts. Each constituent is capped at 5% weight and no single country or sector receives more than 20% weight at the annual rebalance. Sibling fund IHDG offers the same methodology with a currency-hedge overlay for USD investors.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks with growth characteristics of companies in the industrialized world, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree International Quality Dividend Growth Index. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index consists of dividend-paying common stocks with growth characteristics of companies in the industrialized world, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Cabana Target Leading Sector Moderate ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund-of-funds aims to achieve long-term growth while seeking a balance with capital preservation. It primarily allocates assets among other ETFs based on economic conditions and market outlook, utilizing a proprietary algorithm that combines fundamental and technical analysis to identify attractive market sectors. While focusing on sector rotation, its investment universe can span various asset classes, including global equities and fixed income without restrictions on maturity or quality, and may include allocations to less-correlated assets to manage volatility. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its investment objective primarily by allocating its assets among ETFs that invest in securities of companies in the various sectors of the U.S. market: communication services, consumer discretionary, consumer staples, energy, financials, health care, industrials, information technology, materials, real estate, and utilities. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: CLSM is an actively managed fund-of-funds that allocates its exposure based on economic conditions and market outlook for five broad asset classes: equities, fixed income, real estate, currencies, and commodities. Equities include both domestic and foreign companies, including emerging markets. Fixed income securities have no restrictions in maturity, quality, or duration. The sub-adviser uses a proprietary algorithm that combines fundamental economic and technical price data to identify investments in sectors that appear to be attractive. The fund can also allocate across less-/non-correlated assets to manage volatility or any potential market declines. The fund seeks a balance between capital preservation and growth. On January 8, 2024, the fund acquired all assets and liabilities of Cabana Target Leading Sector Aggressive ETF (ticker: CLSA) and Cabana Target Leading Sector Conservative ETF (ticker: CLSC), which had $39 million and $24 million in assets, respectively.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term growth. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its investment objective primarily by allocating its assets among ETFs that invest in securities of companies in the various sectors of the U.S. market: communication services, consumer discretionary, consumer staples, energy, financials, health care, industrials, information technology, materials, real estate, and utilities. It is non-diversified.

name: Xtrackers MSCI EAFE ESG Leaders Equity ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides exposure to large- and mid-capitalization companies located in developed equity markets, specifically excluding the United States and Canada. Its core investment strategy focuses on firms demonstrating leading Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) characteristics. The underlying index assesses companies based on ESG risk and opportunity management, requiring constituents to meet minimum scoring thresholds while screening out those involved in severe ESG controversies or certain controversial industries. Selection aims to cover approximately half the market capitalization within each sector, prioritizing higher-rated ESG performers, with holdings subsequently weighted by market capitalization within their respective sectors. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising its index, which may include depositary receipts.
description_original: The index consists of large- and medium-capitalization companies across developed markets countries, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities (including depositary receipts in respect of such securities) of the index.
description_etfcom:
EASG tracks a principles-based, market-cap-weighted index of stocks from developed markets outside of the US and Canada.

EASG is an ESG-focused fund of large- and midcap stocks from developed economies outside North America. The funds index scores each security for ESG risk and opportunity management. Holdings must meet a minimum score threshold, and the index also screens out companies involved in severe ESG controversies or specific controversial industries. After this initial screening, the index uses the following process to select securities until it covers 50% of the market cap in each sector: 1) eligible securities in the top 35% of market cap, 2) highly-rated securities in the top 50%, 3) current holdings in the top 65%, 4) other eligible securities. At each step, higher rated firms are selected first. Holdings are market-cap-weighted within their respective sector. The index undergoes reconstitution in May and rebalancing in August, November and February. Prior to Feb. 3, 2025, the fund was named Xtrackers MSCI EAFE ESG Leaders Equity ETF, and tracked MSCI EAFE ESG Leaders Index.
description_yahoo: The underlying index consists of large- and medium-capitalization companies across developed markets countries, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities (including depositary receipts in respect of such securities) of the underlying index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the MSCI EAFE Selection Index,. The underlying index consists of large- and medium-capitalization companies across developed markets countries, excluding Canada and the United States. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities (including depositary receipts in respect of such securities) of the underlying index.

name: Merlyn.AI SectorSurfer Momentum ETF
merged_description: This fund is closing, with its last trading day scheduled for November 10, 2023. It employed a dynamic investment strategy driven by a proprietary algorithmic indicator designed to identify market conditions as either 'Bull' or 'Bear,' utilizing inputs such as price trends, market momentum, sentiment, and volatility. In perceived bull markets, the portfolio targeted six thematic equity ETFs (a mix of sector and geopolitical exposures) aiming for an aggressive 70/30 domestic/foreign allocation. During identified bear markets, the strategy shifted defensively, selecting at least four momentum-leading safe-haven ETFs from asset classes like bonds, treasuries, and gold. The fund explicitly avoided inverse and leveraged instruments, was classified as non-diversified, and while its index was typically evaluated monthly, the core indicator could react to significant market volatility at any time.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in the component securities of the index. The index seeks to determine whether U.S. equity markets appear to be in an advancing market (a "Bull" indicator) or appear to have an elevated risk of market decline (a "Bear" indicator). The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: This fund is closing. The last day of trading is November 10, 2023. DUDE tracks an index that shifts its investment strategies during times of market decline. The fund uses their algorithmic Bull/Bear indicator that utilizes price-trend, market momentum, value sentiment, and market volatility to assess market conditions. It maintains the bull condition during times of advancing markets, and the bear condition during decline. During bull markets, the index selects six thematic ETFs (four sectors and two geopolitical sectors) that approximate the 70/30 domestic/foreign equities ratio of an aggressive portfolio. In bear markets, the fund selects at least four momentum leaders from among a broad selection of bond, treasury, and gold safe-harbor ETFs. The fund does not use inverse and leveraged ETFs. The index is normally evaluated monthly, but the bull/bear indicator can be activated anytime when excess market volatility is experienced. Prior to June 1, 2022, the index name was MAI SectorSurfer Momentum Index.

name: Global X Autonomous & Electric Vehicles ETF
merged_description: This fund aims to mirror the performance of an index focused on the autonomous and electric vehicle industries. It allocates at least 80% of its assets to a global portfolio of companies involved in areas such as electric/hybrid vehicle production, related components and materials, autonomous driving technology, and connected transportation services. Utilizing a proprietary natural language processing algorithm, the index identifies relevant companies across various market capitalizations, including those in emerging markets, by scoring their exposure based on keyword frequency in public documents across distinct segments like EV production, components, and autonomous tech.
