name: Janus Henderson U.S. Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks total return through a combination of capital appreciation and current income. Its core strategy involves investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities—including common stocks, preferred stocks, and REITs or similar entities—of U.S. companies operating within the real estate industry or related sectors. Eligible companies generally derive a significant portion (typically over 50%) of their revenue, asset value, or overall company value from real estate activities. The portfolio manager employs a bottom-up security selection process, analyzing individual company fundamentals, valuation, management strength, and risk-adjusted return potential. While primarily focused on the U.S., the fund maintains the flexibility to invest up to 15% of its assets in Canadian issuers and may participate in initial public offerings. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund pursues its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of U.S. real estate-related companies. Such companies may include those in the real estate industry or real estate-related industries. It may also invest up to 15% of its net assets in securities of Canadian issuers. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
JRE is an actively managed fund of real-estate and real estate-related companies in the United States.

JRE actively invests in the US real estate industry and real estate-related industries. The fundprovides exposure through common stocks, preferred stocks, and other equity securities like REITs and REIT-like entities (such as real estate operating companies). To be included in the fund, constituents must (i) derive 50% of their revenue from real estate activities (ii) have at least 50% of their book value in real estate assets, or (iii) have real estate holdings that account for more than 50% of the companys value. The portfolio manager selects securities using a bottom-up approach, utilizingknowledge of issuers, and other factors like companys balance sheet, valuation, strength of management, and risk-adjusted returns. JRE may invest up to 15% in Canadian issuers and may also invest in companies through IPOs.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks total return through a combination of capital appreciation and current income. The fund pursues its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of U.S. real estate-related companies. Such companies may include those in the real estate industry or real estate-related industries. It may also invest up to 15% of its net assets in securities of Canadian issuers. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares U.S. Utilities ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to track the performance of the Russell 1000 Utilities RIC 22.5/45 Capped Index, providing focused exposure to the U.S. utilities equity sector. Primarily holding large-cap U.S. utilities firms, the fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or economically similar investments, potentially utilizing a representative sampling approach rather than holding every security. Its portfolio construction employs a float-adjusted market-capitalization weighting, subject to regulatory capping rules applied quarterly: individual issuers are limited to 22.5%, and the aggregate weight of issuers exceeding 4.5% is capped at 45%. While classified as non-diversified, these constraints manage concentration within the sector focus. The fund retains flexibility to hold up to 20% in cash, money market funds, and derivatives like futures, options, and swaps to manage its portfolio and achieve its objective.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the utilities sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: IDU holds a float-adjusted market-cap-weighted portfolio of large-cap US utilities firms. The funds advisor uses a representative sampling approach to indexing, meaning the fund may not hold all of the underlying in the index but a sample of securities that provide the same investment profile. Regulatory capping targets are also applied at each quarterly rebalance such that single issuer weights are capped at 22.5% and the aggregate weight of all companies exceeding 4.5% weight is capped at 45%. Additionally, the fund may hold cash and cash equivalents, money market funds, and derivatives including futures, options and swap contracts up to 20% of the portfolio to maximize investment. In all, it's a good choice for investors looking for a diversified, broad exposure to the segment. Prior to September 20, 2021, the fund tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Utilities Index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the utilities sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Russell 1000 Utilities RIC 22.5/45 Capped Index. name: ProShares Smart Materials ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to mirror the performance of an index composed of global companies significantly engaged in the smart materials field. These companies are involved in the development, research, production, or application of advanced, responsive, or intelligent materials—substances whose properties can adapt to external stimuli such as temperature or electrical impulses—driving industrial innovation and enhancing products or processes. Utilizing a natural language processing algorithm to screen public data, the underlying index selects the top 30 companies based on their thematic exposure, weighting them by market capitalization with a 4.5% cap per constituent, and reconstitutes semi-annually. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities tracking the index, seeks to remain fully invested regardless of market conditions, and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The index selects companies focused on making or applying industrial innovations which allow for improved products, processes, or techniques through advanced, responsive, or intelligent materials. The fund adviser seeks to remain fully invested at all times in securities and/or financial instruments that, in combination, provide exposure to the returns of the index without regard to market conditions, trends or direction. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
TINT tracks a market-cap weighted index of global companies that have significant exposure to smart materials, also known as intelligent or responsive materials.

TINT tracks an index that invests in global companies within the smart materials space. These are companies that develop, research or produce materials with properties that can adapt to external stimuli, or that have disruptive or pioneering properties. Examples of which are materials that change color when subject to a certain temperature, or those that change shape in response to an electrical impulse. In selecting components for the index, a natural language processing algorithm is used to screen publicly available information such as financial news, business profiles, and company publications. Companies are then ranked based on their exposure to the smart materials theme, and those who do not meet the minimum threshold are excluded from the index. The top 30 companies are selected for inclusion and are weighted using market capitalization, with a weight cap of 4.5% per company. Reconstitution and rebalancing occurs semi-annually, every May and November
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies that have business operations in the field of smart materials. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the Solactive Smart Materials Index (the “index”). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ALPS Clean Energy ETF
merged_description: This investment fund offers focused exposure to the North American clean energy sector by tracking a rules-based index composed of U.S. and Canadian companies. It invests at least 80% of its assets in securities comprising this underlying index, which targets firms involved in renewable energy sources (like solar, wind, and hydropower) and clean technologies (such as electric vehicles, battery storage, fuel cells, and smart grids), aiming to capture businesses enabling a more sustainable energy future. The index employs a market-capitalization weighting methodology, subject to a cap on individual stock weights, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution. The fund itself is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index utilizes a rules-based methodology developed by CIBC National Trust Company (the "index provider"), which is designed to provide exposure to a diverse set of U.S. and Canadian companies involved in the clean energy sector including renewables and clean technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ACES tracks a market-cap-weighted index of North American companies involved in the clean energy industry. The index provider targets companies that enable the evolution of a more sustainable energy sector, and includes activities such as renewable energy sources (solar, wind, hydropower, biofuels), clean technologies (electric vehicles, battery technology, fuel cells, smart grids), and any other emerging clean energy technology. All companies involved in clean energy businesses and listed in the US or Canada are eligible for inclusion. Constituents are market-cap-weighted, subject to a 5% cap on individual stocks. The underlying index undergoes a quarterly rebalance and reconstitution.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond (before fees and expenses) generally to the performance of its underlying index, the CIBC Atlas Clean Energy Index (ticker symbol NACEX) (the "underlying index"). The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index utilizes a rules-based methodology developed by CIBC National Trust Company (the "index provider"), which is designed to provide exposure to a diverse set of U.S. and Canadian companies involved in the clean energy sector including renewables and clean technology. The fund is non-diversified.

name: abrdn Bloomberg All Commodity Longer Dated Strategy K-1 Free ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified exchange-traded fund seeks to mirror the performance of the Bloomberg Commodity Index 3 Month Forward Total Return. This index represents a fully collateralized, forward-looking version of the broader Bloomberg Commodity Index, which comprises futures contracts across diverse sectors including agriculture, energy, livestock, and metals, weighted using trading volume and world production data, and rebalanced periodically with sector caps. To achieve its objective, the fund invests in exchange-traded commodity futures contracts, specifically focusing on longer-dated contracts selected several months out on the futures curve, managed through a wholly-owned Cayman Islands subsidiary—a structure commonly used to avoid issuing K-1 tax forms to investors.
description_original: The index is a three-month forward version of the Bloomberg Commodity Index Total ReturnSM (“BCOMTR”), which reflects the return on a fully collateralized investment in the Bloomberg Commodity IndexSM (“BCOM”). The fund invests in exchange-traded commodity futures contracts through a wholly-owned subsidiary of the fund organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands (the “Subsidiary”). It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: BCD is an index-tracking fund- the Bloomberg Commodity Index. The index includes the following commodity futures contracts: agriculture, energy, livestock, and metals sectors, there are 25 eligible commodities but may vary. Futures positions are weighted 2/3 by trading volume and 1/3 by world production. The index rebalances each January, with weight-caps applied at the sector level. Contracts are selected several months out on the futures curve and held for 2-4 months, according to a set roll schedule that varies by commodity. The fund manages its commodity exposure through a wholly owned Cayman Islands subsidiary, a common structure in the commodity ETF space which allows the fund to avoid issuing k-1 tax forms each year.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that closely correspond, before fees and expenses, to the performance of the Bloomberg Commodity Index 3 Month Forward Total ReturnSM. The index is a three-month forward version of the Bloomberg Commodity Index Total ReturnSM (“BCOMTR”), which reflects the return on a fully collateralized investment in the Bloomberg Commodity IndexSM (“BCOM”). The fund invests in exchange-traded commodity futures contracts through a wholly-owned subsidiary of the fund organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands (the “Subsidiary”). It is non-diversified.

name: JPMorgan U.S. Momentum Factor ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to U.S. large-cap equities demonstrating strong momentum characteristics, selecting constituents from the Russell 1000 Index. It specifically targets companies with high risk-adjusted total returns over the preceding 12 months. While holdings are market-cap weighted with optimizations intended to align sector exposures with the broader market, the strategy's focus on momentum can result in significant sector tilts. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying U.S. momentum factor index, which includes common stocks, REITs, and preferreds, and is reviewed quarterly.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the underlying index. "Assets" means net assets, plus the amount of borrowing for investment purposes. The underlying index is comprised of U.S. equity securities selected to represent positive momentum factor characteristics.
description_etfcom:
JMOM tracks an index of US large-cap companies with strong momentum, weighted by optimized market-cap.

JMOM selects companies from the Russell 1000 Index that have had high risk-adjusted total returns over the past 12 months. The momentum score considers the 12-month returns divided by the 12-month volatility of the returns to get the risk-adjusted returns. Companies are market cap-weighted, optimized to match the sector weights of the Russell 1000 Index. JMOM does not constrain sector or industry exposure, so investors could experience significant portfolio tilts towards one sector or another depending on the market environment. Holdings include common stock, REITs, and preferreds. The underlying index undergoes quarterly review.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that closely correspond, before fees and expenses, to the performance of the JP Morgan US Momentum Factor Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the underlying index. "Assets" means net assets, plus the amount of borrowing for investment purposes. The underlying index is comprised of U.S. equity securities selected to represent positive momentum factor characteristics.

name: Direxion Auspice Broad Commodity Strategy ETF
merged_description: This ETF tracks a rules-based commodity index designed to capture upward market trends while minimizing risk during downturns. Employing a quantitative methodology, the index follows 12 commodity futures contracts across the agriculture, energy, and metals sectors. Positions are weighted by historical volatility and can dynamically toggle between long exposure and cash (flat) based on momentum or prevailing price trends, with contract selection guided by an optimized process. The fund achieves its exposure indirectly through a wholly-owned Cayman Islands subsidiary, holding collateral in short-term fixed income securities such as T-bills and money market funds. This structure helps taxable investors avoid K-1 forms, though the fund itself is considered non-diversified.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that attempts to capture upward trends in the commodity markets while minimizing risk during downtrends by tracking a portfolio of commodity futures contracts. The index uses a quantitative methodology to track a diversified portfolio of 12 different commodity futures contracts, or “components.” The fund generally will not invest directly in the 12 commodity futures contracts that comprise the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
COM tracks a broad-market index consisting of 12 commodity futures contracts, weighted by historical volatility, which can toggle to cash based on momentum. The fund will also hold short-term fixed income securities as collateral.

COM tracks a broad commodity index that considers 12 different commodity futures contracts in the agriculture, energy, and metals sectors. Futures positions are weighted by historical volatility and each position can be either long or flat (i.e. moved to cash) based on prevailing price trends in the contract. Contract tenor is determined by an optimized, rules-based process that selects contracts within the next 13-month period. The adviser also invests COMs collateral in T-bills, money market funds, cash, and other short-term, highly rated corporate and government debt. Rather than a commodity pool, the fund uses a Cayman structure (getting exposure through a wholly-owned Cayman Islands subsidiary). As such, taxable investors avoids a K-1 form at tax time. Prior to August 31, 2021, COM was thought of as an index-tracking fund with an active overlay.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the Auspice Broad Commodity Index. The index is a rules-based index that attempts to capture upward trends in the commodity markets while minimizing risk during downtrends by tracking a portfolio of commodity futures contracts. The index uses a quantitative methodology to track a diversified portfolio of 12 different commodity futures contracts, or “components.” The fund generally will not invest directly in the 12 commodity futures contracts that comprise the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion mRNA ETF
merged_description: This passively managed, non-diversified fund concentrated on the niche healthcare segment of messenger RNA (mRNA) technology. It sought to track a market-capitalization-weighted index comprising companies primarily from the US, Canada, and Europe identified as leaders in developing and applying mRNA technology. Inclusion criteria involved commercialization, clinical trials, patents related to mRNA, or a specific clinical-stage focus on the technology, with constituents screened for significant thematic exposure. The underlying index underwent quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing. This security was subsequently delisted, with its final trading day on April 21, 2023.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities that comprise the index or investments with economic characteristics similar to the securities included in the index. The index provides exposure to the performance of companies, publicly listed in the United States, Canada and Europe, that are leading the development and application of messenger RNA (“mRNA”) technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
MSGR tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies from the US, Canada, and Europe that contribute to the development and application of messenger RNA (mRNA) technology.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 21, 2023. MSGR targets a very niche segment of the healthcare sector. The fund is passively managed to look for firms listed in the US, Canada, and Europe that are believed to be in the forefront of mRNA technology. To be included in the index, a company must be either (i) involved in the commercialization of mRNA-based (or sister RNA-based) products and therapies, (ii) classified as a clinical stage biotech company with a focus on mRNA technology, (iii) have mRNA-focused clinical trials, or (iv) have patents involving mRNA technology. Eligible companies are screened for significant thematic exposure, which is scored according to revenue, declared focus, or clinical trials on mRNA-based products and therapies. The index weights the resulting portfolio by market capitalization and undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.

name: VictoryShares ESG Core Plus Bond ETF
merged_description: This actively managed bond fund seeks high current income without undue risk by investing primarily in intermediate-term fixed income securities demonstrating positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets are held in debt securities or instruments with similar economic features, maintaining a dollar-weighted average portfolio maturity typically between three and ten years. While focusing on investment-grade debt across various types (including corporate, government, mortgage-backed, and asset-backed securities), the fund may allocate up to 20% to below-investment-grade bonds to potentially enhance income. Security selection relies on a proprietary methodology integrating ESG scoring with credit analysis, and the fund may engage in relative value trading.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in debt securities and in derivatives and other instruments that have economic characteristics similar to such securities. The fund primarily invests in securities that have a dollar-weighted average portfolio maturity between three to 10 years. The fund will invest primarily in investment-grade securities, but may invest up to 20% of its net assets in below-investment-grade securities which are sometimes referred to as high-yield or “junk” bonds.
description_etfcom:
UBND is an actively managed fund that holds intermediate-term bonds of any type and rating that exhibit positive ESG characteristics.

UBND actively invests primarily in a wide range of intermediate-term fixed income securities including investment grade corporate bonds, US government debt, mortgage- and asset-backed securities, repurchase agreements, and USD-denominated securities of foreign issuers that exhibit strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. In seeking above-average income, the fund may also hold up to 20% of its portfolio in high-yield bonds. The adviser combines an ESG scoring methodology with a proprietary credit rating methodology, and uses ESG factors, as well as industry-specific models to conclude an internal ESG score and internal credit rating assessment to determine the securities to be included in the fund. UBND may also engage in relative value trading to enhance the funds returns - with the risk of a higher portfolio turnover rate. Prior to April 24, 2023, the fund was named VictoryShares ESG Core Plus Bond ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks high current income without undue risk to principal. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in debt securities and in derivatives and other instruments that have economic characteristics similar to such securities. The fund primarily invests in securities that have a dollar-weighted average portfolio maturity between three to 10 years. The fund will invest primarily in investment-grade securities, but may invest up to 20% of its net assets in below-investment-grade securities which are sometimes referred to as high-yield or “junk” bonds.

name: Invesco China Technology ETF
merged_description: This fund aims to offer broad exposure to the Chinese technology sector by tracking the investment results of the FTSE China Incl A 25% Technology Capped Index. Its portfolio encompasses a wide range of Chinese share classes, including mainland-listed A-shares and internationally-listed N-shares crucial for tech coverage, selected based on an industry classification system without applying factor screens. Constituents are market-capitalization weighted, subject to specific caps on larger individual holdings to manage concentration. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in securities comprising the index, including ADRs and GDRs, rebalances quarterly, and operates as a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that represent securities in the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, the index provider compiles, maintains, and calculates the underlying index. The underlying index may include China A-Shares, B Shares, H Shares, N Shares, Red Chips, P Chips and S Chips. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: CQQQ provides broad, vanilla exposure to Chinese tech firms. It includes A-shares (firms listed on the mainland), N-shares (firms with primary listings in New York) and other share classes. N-share coverage is particularly helpful in the tech space. The index includes all companies in the tech sector based on its underlying ICB industry classification system, which can vary materially from its main sector scheme rival, GICS. The selection process does not apply any factor-based screens. Stocks are market-cap weighted, subject to some position limits. Individual positions are capped at 10% for largest stock, 9% for second, etc. on through the top six names, subject to a cap of 40% total for individual positions greater than 5%. Prior to June 24, 2019, the fund tracked an AlphaShares China tech index. The fund and index are rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the FTSE China Incl A 25% Technology Capped Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that represent securities in the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, the index provider compiles, maintains, and calculates the underlying index. The underlying index may include China A-Shares, B Shares, H Shares, N Shares, Red Chips, P Chips and S Chips. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Tema ETF Trust - Tema Monopolies and Oligopolies ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term growth by investing globally in companies operating within monopolistic or oligopolistic market structures, characterized by strong competitive advantages and high barriers to entry. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 80% of its net assets (including borrowings) primarily in domestic and foreign common and preferred stocks where the company derives over half its revenue from markets with a Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI) exceeding 2,500, signifying high concentration. The investment process combines top-down thematic screening with bottom-up fundamental analysis focused on valuation, integrating ESG considerations. The resulting non-diversified portfolio typically holds 15-100 stocks, potentially including up to 25% in emerging markets, with the manager actively making buy, hold, and sell decisions.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in domestic and foreign, common and preferred stocks of publicly listed companies where the Herfindahl–Hirschman (HHI) index of the market of operation representing more than 50% of the company’s revenue is above 2,500. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
TOLL is an actively managed fund that invests in companies perceived as monopolies or oligopolies. The fund aims to identify quality companies from around the world characterized by their strong competitive advantage and high barriers to entry.

TOLL targets companies with monopolistic or oligopolistic industry structures that have strong competitive advantage and little or no competition. The broad portfolio may include infrastructures such as toll roads, stock exchanges, data, payments, healthcare and patented pharmaceutical companies. The fund selects 15-100 stocks considered highly concentrated by using the Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI), a well-known measure of market concentration that calculates a companys relative size compared to the industry. The fund aims for an attractively valued portfolio through both a top-down approach that narrows down the thematic universe and a bottom-up security analysis focused on valuation multiples and fundamentals. ESG considerations are also integrated with the investment analysis. Securities could be from around the world with up to 25% invested in emerging markets. As an actively managed ETF, the fund manager may make buy, hold or sell decisions at any time at their discretion.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term growth. Under normal circumstances, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in domestic and foreign, common and preferred stocks of publicly listed companies where the Herfindahl–Hirschman (HHI) index of the market of operation representing more than 50% of the company’s revenue is above 2,500. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Inspire International ESG ETF
merged_description: This fund provides exposure to large-capitalization international stocks from developed and emerging markets outside the U.S., selected according to specific ethical criteria defined by its index provider. Aiming to track an index reflecting these standards, the fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in constituent securities. The selection methodology employs screening based on "biblical values," excluding companies involved in activities such as abortion, gambling, alcohol, tobacco, pornography, specific LGBT lifestyle criteria, and human rights violations. Concurrently, firms are positively assessed using a proprietary "Inspire Impact Score," requiring a minimum score based on factors related to customers, community, workforce, and environmental stewardship. The resulting portfolio generally comprises around 200 equally weighted securities from companies, often with market capitalizations exceeding $5 billion, that meet these combined criteria.
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the Inspire Global Hope ex-US Index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of foreign and emerging market companies with a market capitalization of $5 billion (U.S. Dollars) or greater and which have an Inspire Impact Score® of zero or higher.
description_etfcom:
WWJD offers exposure to equity in large firms outside the US, screened for biblical values per the index provider and weighted equally.

WWJD holds large-cap stocks in firms from developed and emerging economies outside the US. The index selects stocks using biblical values defined by the index provider. The index removes firms related to abortion, gambling, alcohol, tobacco, pornography, LGBT lifestyle, and human rights violations. Remaining firms are scored on 4 themes: customers (including business model & innovation), community (impact & giving), workforce (governance), and world (environment and sustainability). The 200 stocks with the highest score make the cut and receive equal weight. Fund documents cite an unremarkable expectation of about 80% to 20% split of developed and emerging firms. For similar funds outside the segment, see Developed Markets Ex-U.S. Large-cap or Global Ex-U.S. Total Market segments. Between March 30 and August 19, 2022, the fund's name included a reference to 'ESG'. The name changes did not impact the fund strategy.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of large capitalization foreign and emerging market companies which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate investment results that generally correspond, before fees and expenses, to the performance of the Inspire International Index. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects foreign (including emerging markets) equity securities from a global universe of publicly traded equity securities of large capitalization foreign and emerging market companies which have an Inspire Impact Score™ of zero or higher.

name: SPDR Portfolio S&P 500 Growth ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to provide investment results corresponding generally to the total return performance of the S&P 500 Growth Index, before fees and expenses. It primarily invests in large-capitalization U.S. equity securities selected from the S&P 500 Index that exhibit strong growth characteristics, based specifically on sales growth, the ratio of earnings change to price, and momentum. Holding roughly 300 stocks, the fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising its target index. The portfolio is market-capitalization weighted, rebalanced annually, and is considered non-diversified, potentially including some mid-cap exposure and making significant sector bets at times due to its S&P 500 origins. Positioned as a low-cost option, it serves as a core building block for exposure to the large-cap growth segment of the U.S. equity market.
description_original: The SPDR Portfolio S&P 500 Growth ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P 500 Growth Index (the “Index”)A low cost ETF that seeks to offer exposure to S&P 500 companies that display the strongest growth characteristicsThe Index contains stocks that exhibit the strongest growth characteristics based on: sales growth, earnings change to price ratio, and momentumOne of the low cost core SPDR Portfolio ETFs, a suite of portfolio building blocks designed to provide broad, diversified exposure to core asset classes
description_etfcom:
SPYG tracks an index of primarily large-cap growth stocks. The index selects companies from the S&P 500 Index based on three growth factors.

SPYG is a large-cap growth fund, holding roughly 300 companies selected from the well-known S&P 500 Index based on three growth factors: sales growth, the ratio of earnings change to price, and momentum. Eligible securities are those that meet certain liquidity and size requirements and have positive reported earnings in the most recent quarters. At times, given the limited number of holdings to reflect sector representation, securities meeting these criteria do not guarantee automatic index inclusion. The fund competes directly with iShares' IVW and Vanguard's VOOG, and its portfolio looks much like theirs. Compared with our neutral growth benchmark, SPYG makes sizable sector bets at times. Because it pulls from the S&P 500, SPYG also carries some midcap exposure that our narrower benchmark excludes. The Index is weighted by market-cap and rebalanced annually. Prior to October 16, 2017 the fund traded under name SPDR S&P 500 Growth ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P 500 Growth Index that tracks the performance of large capitalization exchange traded U.S. equity securities exhibiting "growth" characteristics. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market. It is non-diversified.

name: Janus Henderson International Sustainable Equity ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund, which was delisted with a final trading date of October 10, 2024, pursued long-term capital growth by integrating thematic investing with ESG principles. It focused on international equity securities, including those in emerging markets, selecting companies deemed to make positive contributions to sustainable economic development. The investment process involved identifying firms aligned with environmental and social themes (such as cleaner energy, water management, health, and technology) driven by global megatrends like climate change and population growth, applying exclusionary screens to remove harmful industries, and utilizing fundamental bottom-up analysis alongside ESG assessments. The fund typically held a concentrated portfolio of 30-50 securities, primarily common stocks but potentially including depository receipts and warrants across various market capitalizations, while committing to invest at least 80% of its net assets in equity securities under normal circumstances.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities. The fund primarily invests in equity securities of companies that are economically tied to countries outside of the United States, including investments in emerging markets. The fund generally invests in a core group of 30-50 equity securities, which consist primarily of common stocks, but may also include other types of instruments, such as depository receipts and warrants.
description_etfcom: The security Was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 10, 2024.SXUS is an actively managed fund that incorporates thematic investing with ESG factors. It seeks long-term capital growth by selecting international stocks with positive contributions to sustainable economic development and are classified under environmental (efficiency, cleaner energy, water management, environmental services, and sustainable transport) and social (sustainable property & finance, safety, quality of life, knowledge & technology, and health) themes, all of which aligns with four megatrends: population growth, resource constraints, climate change, and aging population. Constituent selection starts with an exclusionary screen which removes firms engaged in industries with negative impact on society or the environment. Companies are then assessed using a fundamental bottom-up approach and various ESG factors. The funds concentrated portfolio typically holds 30 to 50 securities which may include large-, mid and small-caps.
description_yahoo: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities. The fund primarily invests in equity securities of companies that are economically tied to countries outside of the United States, including investments in emerging markets. The fund generally invests in a core group of 30-50 equity securities, which consist primarily of common stocks, but may also include other types of instruments, such as warrants.

name: SPDR S&P 600™ Small Cap Growth ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund aims to replicate the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of an index tracking the U.S. small-capitalization growth equity market segment. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities, potentially using a representative sampling approach to achieve similar risk and return profiles. The underlying portfolio comprises U.S. small-cap stocks selected based on strong growth characteristics, including sales growth, earnings change relative to price, and momentum. Additionally, constituents are screened for liquidity, free float availability, and a history of positive earnings over the previous four consecutive quarters, with holdings weighted by market capitalization and rebalanced annually across various sectors.
description_original: The SPDR S&P 600 Small Cap Growth ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of The S&P SmallCap 600 Growth Index (the “Index”)The Index includes stocks that exhibit the strongest growth characteristics based on: sales growth; earnings change to price; and momentum
description_etfcom:
SLYG tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US small-cap securities exhibiting growth characteristics.

SLYGs portfolio consists of US small-cap equities having strong growth characteristics measured by sales growth, earnings change to price ratio, and momentum. In addition, the indexs constituents are also screened for liquidity based on annual traded value ratio and number of shares traded, while at the same time considering the free float percentage, and positive earnings reported by the company for the previous four consecutive quarters. The fund may invest in securities of companies across various sectors. Holdings are weighted by market capitalization, with annual rebalance.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the small-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market. It may purchase a subset of the securities in the index in an effort to hold a portfolio of securities with generally the same risk and return characteristics of the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P SmallCap 600 Growth Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the small-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market. It may purchase a subset of the securities in the index in an effort to hold a portfolio of securities with generally the same risk and return characteristics of the index.

name: Invesco S&P SmallCap Materials ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers focused exposure to the U.S. small-cap basic materials sector by tracking a specialized index derived from the S&P SmallCap 600. Investing at least 90% of its assets in index components, the fund holds companies principally engaged in producing raw materials, encompassing sectors like chemicals, construction materials, containers and packaging, metals and mining, and paper and forest products. These small-cap constituents, initially screened for size, liquidity, and financial viability, are market-cap weighted within the portfolio but subject to specific constraints: individual holdings are capped at 22.5%, and the total weight of holdings exceeding 4.5% is limited to 45%. The underlying index undergoes quarterly rebalancing, and the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. These companies are principally engaged in the business of producing raw materials, including producing and manufacturing chemical products; manufacturing construction materials, containers, and packaging; mining metals and the production of related products; and manufacturing paper and forest products. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: PSCM focuses exclusively on US small-cap basic materials companies. The fund pulls from the S&P SmallCap 600, a market-cap-weighted index that consists of US small-cap companies screened for size, liquidity, and financial viability. It specifically holds a concentrated portfolio of companies engaged in producing raw materials, including paper or wood products, mining and metals, chemicals, and construction materials. Selected securities are weighted by market cap and are constrained, such that individual securities will not exceed 22.5% weight and the aggregate weight of securities with over 4.5% allocation is capped at 45% weight of the portfolio. The index rebalances quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P SmallCap 600 ® Capped Materials Index (the “underlying index”). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. These companies are principally engaged in the business of producing raw materials, including producing and manufacturing chemical products; manufacturing construction materials, containers, and packaging; mining metals and the production of related products; and manufacturing paper and forest products. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Aerospace & Defense ETF
merged_description: This ETF provides concentrated exposure primarily targeting companies deemed systematically important to the U.S. defense, military, homeland security, and government space sectors. It seeks to replicate the performance of an underlying index composed of common stocks involved in the development, manufacture, operation, and support within these critical areas, listed on major US exchanges. Investing substantially all (at least 90%) of its assets in the index constituents, the fund utilizes a market-capitalization weighting approach with quarterly rebalancing. While the index methodology incorporates a 10% weighting cap per individual security, the fund maintains a non-diversified classification due to its focused investment scope within this specific industry.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of companies that are systematically important to the defense sector and are involved with the development, manufacture, operation and support of U.S. defense, military, national/homeland security, and government space operations. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: PPA aims to provide broadly defined exposure to the aerospace & defense industry, which may also include firms in non-defense industries. The fund specifically includes NYSE- or NASDAQ-listed companies engaged in operations supporting the US defense, military, homeland security, and space operations. In this narrow, highly concentrated space, the fund managers use size, liquidity, and revenue screens in selecting its constituents. In addition, the fund managers have discretion on any addition or deletions of holdings at any time if they believe such securities no longer represent the funds industry focus. Selected securities are weighted by market-cap and are rebalanced quarterly, employing 10% weight constraints on each individual constituent in an effort to diversify its portfolio.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of companies that are systematically important to the defense sector and are involved with the development, manufacture, operation and support of U.S. defense, military, national/homeland security, and government space operations. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the SPADE® Defense Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of common stocks of companies that are systematically important to the defense sector and are involved with the development, manufacture, operation and support of U.S. defense, military, national/homeland security, and government space operations. The fund is non-diversified.

name: FlexShares STOXX Global ESG Select Index Fund
merged_description: This fund aims to mirror the performance of a global index composed of companies demonstrating strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. The index selects constituents based on specific positive ESG metrics, including low emissions, board independence, and gender diversity, while excluding companies involved in controversial weapons, coal mining, or those violating UN Global Compact principles. Designed to identify companies scoring collectively better on these ESG key performance indicators relative to a broad global market benchmark, the index weights its holdings based on aggregated ESG scores. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising this index, including ADRs and GDRs, and undergoes quarterly reconstitution.
description_original: The index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, score better with respect to a set of ESG KPIs relative to the STOXX® Global 1800 Index, a float-adjusted market-capitalization weighted index of companies incorporated in the U.S. and in developed international markets. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.
description_etfcom:
ESGG follows a principles-based global index composed of companies that exhibit environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) characteristics.

ESGG follows an index designed to provide global exposure to companies that exhibit several specific environmental, social, and corporate governance attributes. These factors include low emissions, percentage of independent board members, percentage of women board members, policies against child labor, and non-use of golden parachute agreements. Disqualifying characteristics include non-adherence to UN Global compact principles, involvement in controversial weapons, or coal mining. All qualifying constituents are weighted based on an aggregated ESG score, derived from the factors mentioned above. The index is reconstituted on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 1, 2021, the fund was named FlexShares STOXX Global ESG Impact Index Fund and tracked the STOXX Global ESG Impact Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the STOXX® Global ESG Select KPIs IndexSM. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that, in aggregate, score better with respect to a set of ESG KPIs relative to the STOXX® Global 1800 Index, a float-adjusted market-capitalization weighted index of companies incorporated in the U.S. and in developed international markets. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.

name: Fidelity Stocks for Inflation ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to U.S. large and mid-cap equities selected for their potential to outperform in inflationary environments. It tracks a factor-based index, choosing stocks from the largest 1000 U.S. companies based on criteria including attractive valuations, high quality profiles, and positive momentum signals. The resulting portfolio, typically holding around 100 stocks, structurally emphasizes sectors historically resilient to inflation—such as energy, materials, and real assets—by applying specific overweight adjustments to these industries on top of an otherwise equal weighting approach for constituents. The fund aims to invest at least 80% of its assets in securities matching its target index, which undergoes semi-annual rebalancing.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the Fidelity Stocks for Inflation Factor Index?, which is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization U.S. companies with attractive valuations, high quality profiles and positive momentum signals, emphasizing industries that tend to outperform in inflationary environments.
description_etfcom:
FCPI tracks an index of U.S. large- and mid-cap stocks based on multi-factor criteria with structural tilts towards inflation-sensitive sectors and industries. The index is weighted based on market capitalization.

FCPI providesexposure tolarge-and mid-cap US equities that tend tooutperform in inflationary environments. Theindexstarts with the top 1000 US companies by market cap,each are rankedand scoredbased onvalue, momentum and quality factors.Thefinal selection being approximately 100 stocks, based on market cap within each sector. Each stock isequally weighted plusan overweight adjustment depending onitssector.Sectors such as energy, materials, consumer staples, health care,real assets and infrastructure receive+5% overweight in the portfolio. The index is rebalanced semi-annually, on the third Friday in February and August.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity Stocks for Inflation Factor Index℠. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the Fidelity Stocks for Inflation Factor Index℠, which is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization U.S. companies with attractive valuations, high quality profiles and positive momentum signals, emphasizing industries that tend to outperform in inflationary environments.

name: First Trust Exchange -Traded Fund Vi - First Trust S&P 500 Diversified Free Cash Flow Etf
merged_description: This investment fund targets U.S. large-cap equities selected from the S&P 500 Index, focusing specifically on companies exhibiting high free cash flow (FCF) yields relative to peers within their respective GICS sectors. The strategy aims for sector neutrality by selecting the top eligible companies (approximately 20%) based on FCF yield within each sector, including those in Financials and Real Estate, while typically excluding negative yielders. Holdings are subsequently weighted by their FCF yield, subject to minimum and maximum constraints, ensuring diversification across the selected stocks. The underlying index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and rebalancing, and the fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in these component securities to track its performance.
description_original: Under normal conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index measures the performance of companies within the S&P 500® Index that have the highest relative FCF Yield within each GICS® sector represented in the S&P 500® Index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FCFY is designed to mirror a broad US sector-neutral index comprising of firms perceived to have strong free cash flow yields in their respective GICS sectors. The fund follows a model akin to the Pacer's Cash Cows line-up in screening for companies with the highest free cash flow yields, but includes those in Financials and Real Estate. Free cash flow yield, a measure of an organizations cash flow generated from operations after expenses, guides the selection process from the S&P 500, with the top 20% within each sector chosen. Non-positive yielding companies are excluded for diversity until sector count meets a threshold. Firms are then weighted by free cash flow yield, each capped between 0.25% and 5% within their sector. The index undergoes semi-annual rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield, before fees and expenses, of an equity index called the S&P 500 Sector-Neutral FCF Index. Under normal conditions, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index measures the performance of companies within the S&P 500® Index that have the highest relative FCF Yield within each GICS® sector represented in the S&P 500® Index. It is non-diversified.

name: iShares Global Utilities ETF
merged_description: This fund aims to mirror the performance of the S&P Global 1200 Utilities (Sector) Capped Index™, providing concentrated exposure to the worldwide utilities sector. It primarily invests in global utility companies, drawn from the S&P 1200 index and classified under GICS, employing a market-capitalization weighting strategy with a 10% cap per issuer and quarterly rebalancing. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities or economically similar investments, potentially using a sampling strategy to achieve this, while allowing up to 20% allocation to certain derivatives, cash, and cash equivalents.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
JXI tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies involved in the utilities industry worldwide.

JXI is a concentrated play on global utilities. Although the sector might be dominated by a few regions, the fund does not limit itself geographically and will invest in companies from around the world. JXI holds committee-picked companies from the S&P 1200 classified by GICS as utilities. The fund also uses a sampling method, which means it will invest in a sample of securities that collectively have an investment profile similar to that of the underlying index. The index is market-cap-weighted, with a cap of 10% per issuer, and is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to May 3, 2021, the fund tracked an uncapped version of its index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Global 1200 Utilities (Sector) Capped IndexTM composed of global equities in the utilities sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.

name: Fidelity Covington Trust - Disruptive Medicine ETF
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks long-term capital growth by investing primarily in companies pioneering disruptive innovations within the global healthcare sector. Normally allocating at least 80% of its assets to securities of these "disruptive medicine" firms, the fund targets businesses developing unconventional products, services, or technologies—such as robotic surgery, cell and gene therapy, genomics, and advanced diagnostics—that possess the potential to reshape the industry and displace incumbents. Employing fundamental analysis and considering economic conditions, the adviser selects primarily growth and value stocks, operating with a non-diversified portfolio structure.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of disruptive medicine companies. Fidelity's disruptive strategies seek to identify innovative developments that could signal new directions for delivering products and services to customers. Generally, these companies have or are developing new or unconventional ways of doing business that could disrupt and displace incumbents over time. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FMED seeks long-term capital appreciation by utilizing proprietary disruptive strategies in identifying companies involved in disruptive technologies for its portfolio. Disruptive technologies are innovations that may reshape how businesses currently deliver their services and operate, potentially displacing industry leaders over time. The fund primarily invests in growth and value stocks of companies tied with disruptive innovation in health care globally. This includes robotic surgery, cell and gene therapy, genomics, rare diseases, medical devices and equipment, immunotherapy, technology-based healthcare platforms, advanced diagnostics, and consumer wellness. The adviser uses fundamental analysis, as well as economic and market conditions for its portfolio construction. The adviser may buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion. FMED converted from a mutual fund to an actively managed ETF, with $44 million in assets.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of disruptive medicine companies. Fidelity's disruptive strategies seek to identify innovative developments that could signal new directions for delivering products and services to customers. Generally, these companies have or are developing new or unconventional ways of doing business that could disrupt and displace incumbents over time. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco MSCI Green Building ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides targeted exposure to the global green building ecosystem by seeking to track a market-capitalization weighted index. The underlying index sources components from a broad global universe, including large-, mid-, and small-cap companies across developed and emerging markets. Eligible companies must derive a significant portion of their revenue (initially at least 50%) from activities central to the sustainable building value chain—such as construction, redevelopment, or retrofitting of green-certified properties—and are also screened based on relevant ESG criteria assessing their commitment to this theme. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in these index constituents, is considered non-diversified, and its underlying index undergoes quarterly reviews.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of securities that are also components of the MSCI ACWI Investable Market Index (the "Parent Index"), an equity index composed of more than 9,300 securities of large-, mid- and small-capitalization companies located in both developed and emerging market countries around the world. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GBLD is a market-cap-weighted index of global companies focused on the sustainability of the worlds green building ecosystem.

GBLD offers pure-play exposure to the global green building industry by investing in companies of all capitalization sizes involved in the construction, redevelopment, and retrofitting of green-certified properties. The fund is the first of its kind to focus specifically on the efficiency of the entire sustainable building value chain which is one of the five MSCI environmental themes. Potential firms must derive at least 50% of their revenue from green building activities which revolves around conserving natural resources and creating a safe and healthy environment, and must be screened based on their commitment and contribution to the impact theme using an ESG rating and score data. Constituents are then weighted by market-cap and may remain in the fund as long as the revenue they derive does not fall under 40%. The index is reviewed quarterly
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the MSCI Global Green Building Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of securities that are also components of the MSCI ACWI Investable Market Index (the "Parent Index"), an equity index composed of more than 9,300 securities of large-, mid- and small-capitalization companies located in both developed and emerging market countries around the world. It is non-diversified.

name: iShares MSCI USA Min Vol Factor ETF
merged_description: This investment fund offers exposure to U.S. large- and mid-capitalization equity securities, specifically targeting lower aggregate volatility compared to the broader market. It achieves this by tracking an index constructed using an optimization algorithm designed to build a minimum variance portfolio; this process considers correlations between stocks, not just individual security volatility, and operates under various constraints, including sector limits. While the strategy aims to keep other risk factors relatively marketlike, it often results in overweighting defensive, dividend-paying sectors and typically exhibits substantially lower market risk (beta). The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index or investments with economically similar characteristics.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index measures the performance of large and mid-capitalization equity securities listed on stock exchanges in the U.S. that, in the aggregate, have lower volatility relative to the large- and mid-cap U.S. equity market.
description_etfcom:
USMV tracks an index of US-listed firms selected and weighted to create a low-volatility portfolio subject to various constraints.

USMV offers a minimum-volatility portfolio of US stocks. The fund's index uses an optimization algorithm to build a minimum variance portfolio, one that considers correlation between stocks rather than simply holding a basket of low-vol stocks. While USMV applies sector constraints in its optimizer, sector bets can be substantial, if unsurprising. The fund typically overweights defensive, dividend-paying sectors. USMV`s optimizer also aims to keep other risk factors marketlike as it dials back on volatility. The ETF takes substantially less risk than the market portfolio as shown by low beta.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks the investment results of the MSCI USA Minimum Volatility (USD) Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index measures the performance of large and mid-capitalization equity securities listed on stock exchanges in the U.S. that, in the aggregate, have lower volatility relative to the large- and mid-cap U.S. equity market.

name: Invesco Water Resources ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to track the performance of an index focused on US-listed companies that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries. To be included, these companies must also participate in the Green Economy. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the index's constituent securities, which may encompass various equity types. The underlying index employs a modified liquidity-weighting methodology, capping the five largest holdings at 8% each while distributing the remaining weight equally among other components, and is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. The fund operates as a non-diversified investment vehicle, concentrating its holdings within the water resources sector.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index seeks to track the performance of companies that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. The underlying index may include common stocks, ordinary shares, American depositary receipts ("ADRs"), shares of beneficial interest and tracking stocks. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PHO tracks a modified liquidity-weighted index of US-listed companies that create products to conserve and purify water.

PHO is a water-themed fund of US companies that create products that conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries. Securities should also participate in the Green Economy, as determined by SustainableBusiness.com LLC. Holdings are weighted by liquidity, with no more than five companies capped at 8% and with the rest distributed equally. The index is reconstituted annually in April and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index seeks to track the performance of companies that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. The underlying index may include common stocks, ordinary shares, American depositary receipts ("ADRs"), shares of beneficial interest and tracking stocks. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the NASDAQ OMX U.S. Water IndexSM (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index seeks to track the performance of companies that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. The underlying index may include common stocks, ordinary shares, American depositary receipts ("ADRs"), shares of beneficial interest and tracking stocks. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Ultra Basic Materials
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, equivalent to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Materials Select Sector Index. Managed by ProShare Advisors, it employs financial instruments to achieve this leveraged objective, normally obtaining leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its assets in the index's components or similar instruments. The underlying market-cap weighted index tracks basic materials companies from the S&P 500, covering areas like metals, chemicals, and paper products. Due to its daily leverage reset mechanism, the fund's returns over periods exceeding one day can significantly deviate from twice the index's performance because of compounding effects, making it primarily suitable as a short-term trading tool rather than a long-term investment.
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the basic materials industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
UYM provides 2x leveraged exposure to a market-cap-weighted index of companies in the basic materials sector that includes production of certain metals, chemicals and paper products.

UYM provides 2x leveraged exposure on a daily basis to the S&P Materials Select Sector Index, a market cap-weighted index that could include companies involved in the production of aluminum, steel, non-ferrous metals, commodity and specialty chemicals, forest and paper products, as well as the mining of precious metals and coal. The daily distinction is critical, since the fund will start to drift from its 2x target returns over periods of greater than one day. Because of that, the fund's return for periods longer than a day becomes path-dependent and is likely to be different from 2x the return of the index for the same period. As a geared product with daily resets, UYM is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. Long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to Mar. 20, 2023, the fund was called ProShares Ultra Basic Materials ETF that tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Basic Materials Index.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is designed to measure the performance of materials companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Materials Select Sector Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is designed to measure the performance of materials companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: SPDR MSCI USA Gender Diversity ETF
merged_description: This ETF aims to track an index composed of U.S. large- and mid-cap companies recognized for leading their sectors in gender diversity. It invests in firms demonstrating high levels of women's representation throughout the organization and promoting advancement through effective diversity policies and programs. The underlying index construction involves screening the broad U.S. large/mid-cap universe, excluding companies with significant ESG-related controversies, and then selecting constituents based on their gender diversity performance and sector. Holdings are weighted by a combination of market capitalization and a gender diversity score, subject to an individual security cap, and the portfolio is rebalanced quarterly. While typically investing at least 80% of its assets in index components, the fund retains flexibility to hold non-index securities or cash equivalents.
description_original: The SPDR MSCI USA Gender Diversity ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the MSCI USA Gender Diversity Select (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to US companies that lead their sector in demonstrating a commitment towards promoting and supporting gender diversity throughout all levels of the organizationCompanies are also evaluated on promoting advancement through their diversity policies and programsCompanies are weighted according to their market capitalization and Gender Diversity Score, a measure of a company’s women representation and diversity management
description_etfcom: SHE seeks out companies that support and maintain a high level of gender diversity and promote women's representation within their organization. Index construction begins with all the components of the MSCI USA Index, capturing the large- and mid-cap segments of the US equity market. The fund utilizes ESG metrics with each company initially assigned a score based on related controversies causing negative ESG impacts. Those with a score of zero or no score at all due to the severity of controversies are excluded. The remaining securities are given a new score reflecting the ratio of women in their organization and the effectiveness of their implementation of various diversity policies and programs. Final constituents are selected by sector and weighted by market cap, with an individual capping weight of 4.5%. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Dec. 8, 2022, the fund tracked the SSGA Gender Diversity Index and was named SPDR SSGA Gender Diversity Index ETF.
description_yahoo: Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. In addition, it may invest in equity securities that are not included in the index, cash and cash equivalents or money market instruments.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the MSCI USA Gender Diversity Select Index that tracks U.S. large- and mid-cap companies exhibiting certain gender diversity and diversity management characteristics. Under normal market conditions, the fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. In addition, it may invest in equity securities that are not included in the index, cash and cash equivalents or money market instruments.

name: MicroSectors FANG+ ETN
merged_description: This exchange-traded note, issued by Bank of Montreal as an unsecured and unsubordinated obligation, aims to mirror the gross total return performance of an equal-dollar weighted index. The index provides concentrated exposure to a select group, typically comprising at least ten highly-traded growth stocks, representing leading technology and tech-enabled companies within the technology and consumer discretionary sectors listed on US exchanges (including ADRs).
