FXH tracks a tiered, equal-weighted index of large- and mid-cap US health care companies. Holdings are selected and weighted based on various growth and value criteria.

FXH tracks a quant-driven index that attempts to achieve excess returns by selecting health care stocks based on growth and value factors, and equal-weighting them in tiers. The portfolio offers noteworthy mid-cap exposure, downplaying familiar large-cap names relative to cap-weighted peer funds. Additionally, FXH underweights pharmaceuticals relative to the market, but allows a significant exposure to biotechnology and healthcare providers. Overall, this fund offers a smart beta approach to the US health care space, tilting away from big pharma and towards other facets of health care. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the health care sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the StrataQuant® Health Care Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the health care sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.

name: Fidelity Real Estate Investment ETF
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified exchange-traded fund aims for above-average income and long-term capital growth by investing primarily in the global real estate sector. It normally allocates at least 80% of its assets to securities of domestic and foreign companies engaged in the real estate industry and related investments, selecting them through fundamental analysis of company financials, industry standing, and market conditions. Operating under an SEC exemptive order, the fund features a non-transparent structure; it does not disclose its full holdings daily but instead publishes a daily tracking basket designed to closely approximate performance, with complete portfolio details revealed monthly on a 30-day lag.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that operates pursuant to an exemptive order from the Securities and Exchange Commission (Order) and is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of companies principally engaged in the real estate industry and other real estate related investments. It invests in domestic and foreign issuers. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FPRO provides exposure to companies that engage in the real estate industry and other related investments. The fund selects securities perceived to have above-average income and long-term capital growth, using fundamental analyses of factors such as each companys financial condition and industry position, as well as market and economic conditions. As an actively managed fund, FPRO is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day, but instead publishes its Tracking Basket and Tracking Basket Weight Overlap daily, which are designed to closely track the daily performance of the fund without disclosing the actual portfolio and how similar they are in percentage terms. The fund only discloses its complete holdings monthly with a 30-day lag.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks above-average income and long-term capital growth, consistent with reasonable investment risk. The fund is an actively managed ETF that operates pursuant to an exemptive order from the Securities and Exchange Commission (Order) and is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of companies principally engaged in the real estate industry and other real estate related investments. It invests in domestic and foreign issuers. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Emerging Markets Dividend ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on providing exposure to high-dividend-paying equities within emerging markets. It aims to track an index comprising 100 leading companies selected primarily based on their indicated annual dividend yield, subject to various screening and buffering criteria. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities constituting its underlying index or investments with similar economic characteristics. Holdings are weighted according to their indicated annual dividends, incorporating constraints such as a maximum 25% allocation to any single country. The index methodology involves annual reconstitution and quarterly reviews to maintain its dividend-focused objective.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index measures the performance of 100 leading dividend-paying emerging-market companies, selected by dividend yield subject to screening and buffering criteria.
description_etfcom:
DVYE tracks a dividend-weighted index of high-dividend-paying emerging markets companies.

DVYE has a somewhat narrow focus, holding 100 of the highest-yielding stocks from emerging markets. Selecting and weighting constituents are primarily based on dividend yield, subject to screening and buffering criteria. It delivers some extra yield, but in terms of total return, the case for DVYE is somewhat less clear. The universe begins with the S&P Emerging BMI, excluding real estate investment trusts. Stocks are then screened largely for dividend yield along with other fundamental factors. Stocks are weighted based on indicated annual dividend, with no single country going above 25%. The index is reconstituted annually, subject to quarterly reviews.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index measures the performance of 100 leading dividend-paying emerging market companies, selected according to indicated annual dividend yield, subject to screening and buffering criteria and weighting constraints.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones Emerging Markets Select Dividend Index composed of relatively high dividend paying equities in emerging markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index measures the performance of 100 leading dividend-paying emerging market companies, selected according to indicated annual dividend yield, subject to screening and buffering criteria and weighting constraints.

name: YieldMax COIN Option Income Strategy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily seeks to generate current income, with a secondary objective of providing exposure to the share price movements of a specific underlying technology stock involved in the digital asset ecosystem, subject to a cap on potential gains. It employs a synthetic covered call strategy, utilizing both standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options, and collateralizes its positions primarily with cash and US Treasurys. The strategy aims to replicate the underlying stock's price movements while generating income, typically monthly, by writing short-term call options, which limits participation in the stock's potential appreciation but fully exposes investors to downside risk. Importantly, the fund does not invest directly in the underlying company's shares, meaning investors are not entitled to dividends. It operates as a non-diversified fund and maintains its investment approach regardless of adverse market or economic conditions, without taking temporary defensive positions.
description_original: The fund will seek to employ its investment strategy as it relates to COIN regardless of whether there are periods adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CONY seeks to provide current income and capped gains on the Coinbase Global Inc. stock (COIN) through a synthetic covered call strategy, collateralized by cash and US Treasurys. The actively managed fund uses both standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options.

CONY aims to generate monthly income while providing exposure to the price returns of Coinbase Global Inc. stock (COIN), subject to a cap on potential gains. The fund utilizes a synthetic covered call strategy via standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options, which consists of three elements: i) synthetic long exposure, ii) covered call writing, and iii) US Treasurys for collateral. The synthetic long exposure seeks to replicate the price movements of COIN by purchasing and selling at-the-money calls and puts that have one- to six-month terms. To generate income, the fund writes call options with an expiration of one month or less and a strike price of approximately 0%-15% above COIN's current share price. This limits participation in potential gains if COIN shares increase in value. The short put positions fully expose investors to the downside of the stock. Note: the fund does not invest directly in COIN stocks. Thus, investors are not entitled to any COIN dividends.
description_yahoo: The fund will employ its investment strategy as it relates to COIN regardless of whether there are periods of adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks current income; the secondary investment objective is to seek exposure to the share price of the common stock of Coinbase Global, Inc. (“COIN”), subject to a limit on potential investment gains. The fund will employ its investment strategy as it relates to COIN regardless of whether there are periods of adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco DWA Consumer Staples Momentum ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a momentum-driven strategy within the US consumer staples sector, aiming to track the investment results of the Dorsey Wright® Consumer Staples Technical Leaders Index. Investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's holdings, the fund focuses on a minimum of 30 consumer staples companies selected from a broad universe of large-cap US stocks based on powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics. Its unique approach uses a quantitative, momentum-focused scoring system not only for security selection but also for weighting, giving greater allocation to stocks demonstrating the strongest relative performance. This strategy seeks to capture intermediate and long-term upward price trends relative to a market benchmark, with the underlying index rebalancing and reconstituting quarterly.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the consumer staples sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_etfcom: PSL provides an alternate take on US consumer staples firms. It starts its selection universe covering about 2,000 of the largest companies by market cap within the NASDAQ US Benchmark Index. The fund then follows the Dorsey-Wright Technical Leaders Indexs momentum-focused scoring scheme to narrow down its constituents to a minimum of 30. At the same time, this momentum score will also be the basis of their respective weightings. Meaning, securities that scored the highest receives greater weight in the index. This relative strength strategy aims to focus on securities performance when it comes to intermediate and long-term upward price movements as compared to a market benchmark. Index rebalancing and reconstitution occurs quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco DWA Consumer Staples Momentum ETF.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the consumer staples sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Consumer Staples Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the consumer staples sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.

name: Strive Emerging Markets Ex-China ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to track the total return performance of a market-capitalization-weighted index focused on large and mid-cap companies across 24 emerging market economies, distinguished by its specific exclusion of China. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in these emerging market securities, which include common stocks, real estate investment trusts (REITs), and potentially depositary receipts (ADRs/GDRs). The underlying index constituents are selected based on criteria like free-float market capitalization and liquidity, and the index undergoes quarterly rebalancing and semi-annual reconstitution, offering diversified exposure to emerging markets beyond China.
description_original: The index tracks large and mid-capitalization equity securities across 24 emerging market economies, excluding China. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in the emerging market securities, which may include depositary receipts (including American Depository Receipts (“ADRs”) or Global Depository Receipts (“GDRs”) representing securities included in the index.
description_etfcom:
STXE tracks a market cap-weighted index of mid and large cap companies in emerging markets, excluding China.

STXE is designed to track an index of mid and large cap companies in emerging markets, excluding China. Securities eligible for inclusion in the index are screened based on factors such as free float market capitalization, trading volume thresholds, and market price cap levels. Constituents are then sorted by emerging markets country based on market size, liquidity, and capital market structure. Each security selected for the index is market cap-weighted. It includes both common stocks and real estate investment trusts. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted on a semi-annual basis in March and September.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Bloomberg Emerging Markets ex China Large & Mid Cap Index composed of emerging market, ex-China securities. The index tracks large and mid-capitalization equity securities across 24 emerging market economies, excluding China. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in the emerging market securities, which may include depositary receipts (including American Depository Receipts (“ADRs”) or Global Depository Receipts (“GDRs”) representing securities included in the index.

name: First Trust Morningstar Dividend Leaders Index Fund
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of an equity index focused on high dividend yields. It invests at least 90% of its assets in the index's 100 constituent common stocks, selected based on having the highest yields combined with a consistent record and perceived ability to sustain dividend payments. Specific criteria include requiring dividend growth over the preceding five years and ensuring the current dividend is below forward earnings per share estimates. The portfolio is weighted based on the total dollar amount of dividends paid, subject to caps limiting individual securities to 10% and ensuring that holdings exceeding 5% do not collectively represent more than 50% of the portfolio. This non-diversified fund rebalances quarterly and reconstitutes annually, emphasizing companies with robust and growing dividend characteristics.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the 100 highest-yielding stocks that have a consistent record of dividend payment and have the ability to sustain their dividend payments. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FDL tries to generate a greater dividend yield by building its portfolio on the basis of historical yield performance and the ability to sustain dividend payments. Its rule set requires a company's current dividend to be higher than it was five years ago, and less than its forward EPS estimates. Eligible securities are ranked by dividend yield and the top 100 securities are selected for index inclusion. Its weighting scheme is also dividend dollar-weighted. Adjustments occur so that each security has a maximum weight of 10% and those securities weighing more than 5% do not collectively exceed 50% of the entire portfolio. This approach causes FDL to diverge from its Base Index. The Index undergoes quarterly rebalance and annual reconstitution.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the 100 highest-yielding stocks that have a consistent record of dividend payment and have the ability to sustain their dividend payments. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the Morningstar® Dividend Leaders IndexSM. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of the 100 highest-yielding stocks that have a consistent record of dividend payment and have the ability to sustain their dividend payments. It is non-diversified.

name: LifeGoal Home Down Payment Investment ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aimed to generate current income and capital appreciation, primarily allocating 60-95% of its assets to fixed income and cash equivalents to manage return volatility. Complementing this core holding, it invested 5-35% in global equities across various market caps and geographies, and potentially 0-35% in underlying funds providing exposure to commodities, REITs, and high-yield debt securities. The advisor employed proprietary research to select underlying mutual funds and ETFs, allowing for broad flexibility in fixed income types (including domestic/international, convertibles, inflation-linked, and varying maturities) and equity exposures. A unique feature was the potential to tilt 5-15% of the portfolio towards housing-related industries. Originally designed to assist investors saving for home-related expenses like down payments or rent, the fund did not target a specific investment time horizon and has since been delisted, with its last trading day on June 12, 2023.
description_original: The fund is designed to assist investors in saving for a home down payment. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest its assets within the following ranges: 60-95% of its assets in fixed income and cash and cash equivalents, 5-35% of its assets in equities, and 0-35% of its assets in a combination of underlying funds providing exposure to commodities, REITs and high yield debt securities. The adviser seeks to emphasize exposure to fixed income, in order to avoid excessive volatility of returns.
description_etfcom: The fund is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is June 12, 2023. HOM aims to attract investors interested in housing. Note the fund does not target a specific investment time horizon, which is important when considering investing in a home, obtaining a mortgage or renting. The fund seeks to generate current income and capital appreciation by allocating 60-95% of its assets to fixed income, 5-35% to equities, and 0-20% to commodities, REITs and high yield bonds. The fund may tilt 5-15% of the portfolio to housing related industries such as home furnishings, home builders, lumber and precious metals. The funds advisor uses their own proprietary research to select and allocate, with very few limitations, to mutual funds and ETFs to provide such exposure. Fixed income securities may be from issuers both domestic and international, public and private, including convertibles and inflation-linked, and of any maturity. Equity exposure as well may be US or international including developed and emerging markets, and of any market capitalization.
description_yahoo: The fund is designed to assist investors in saving for a home down payment, mortgage or rent budget or general home-related expenses or costs. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest its assets within the following ranges: 60-95% of its assets in fixed income and cash and cash equivalents, 5-35% of its assets in equities, and 0-35% of its assets in a combination of underlying funds providing exposure to commodities, REITs and high yield debt securities. The adviser seeks to emphasize exposure to fixed income, in order to avoid excessive volatility of returns.

name: Virtus Private Credit ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to the private credit market by operating as a fund of funds, seeking investment results that correspond to the performance of an underlying index. Under normal conditions, it invests primarily in the index's components, which consist of U.S.-listed closed-end funds (CEFs), including both business development companies (BDCs) and non-BDC CEFs focused on private credit instruments like loans and CLOs. BDCs within the portfolio typically invest in middle-market companies. A key feature is its index methodology, which weights constituents by dividend yield and employs screens for steady historical dividend payments and, for non-BDC CEFs, significant deviations between market price and net asset value. Due to its fund-of-funds structure, investors may incur compounded expenses.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its assets in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of U.S.-listed, registered closed-end investment companies that have elected to be regulated as "business development companies" under the Investment Company Act of 1940, as well as U.S.-listed, non-BDC registered closed-end funds.
description_etfcom:
VPC tracks an index of closed-end funds focused on the private credit market, including business development companies. The index is weighted by dividend yield.

VPC is a fund of funds that aims for income from private credit markets via exposure to US-listed closed-end funds (CEFs). It holds 2 main types: CEFs regulated as business development companies (BDCs) and non-BDC CEFs that focus on private credit. The BDCs invest in middle market firms with below-investment grade ratings using a variety of debt and equity vehicles. The non-BDC CEFs invest in loans, CLOs and senior loans. VPCs index screens for steady dividend payments over the past 3 years. The non-BDC CEFs are further screened to weed out large premiums or discounts of price vs. NAV. Securities are weighted by dividend yield. Structured as a fund-of-funds, investors should expect to pay double because of costs compounding. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond the price and yield performance of the Indxx Private Credit Index (the "underlying index"). Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its assets in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of U.S.-listed, registered closed-end investment companies that have elected to be regulated as "business development companies" under the Investment Company Act of 1940, as well as U.S.-listed, non-BDC registered closed-end funds.

name: Invesco S&P SmallCap Information Technology ETF
merged_description: This fund provides targeted exposure to the U.S. small-cap information technology sector by seeking to replicate the performance of a specific market-capitalization-weighted index. Investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's constituents, it draws companies from the S&P SmallCap 600 index, which screens potential holdings for size, liquidity, and financial viability. Technology firms are identified using the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) and include various sub-sectors like hardware, software, and semiconductors. To manage concentration risk, the underlying index applies capping rules that limit the weight of individual securities and the aggregate weight of the largest positions. The portfolio composition is updated through quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the information technology sector, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard.
description_etfcom:
PSCT tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US small-cap technology companies. Its selection universe is limited to the S&P SmallCap 600 Index.

PSCT offers targeted exposure to US small-cap technology companies selected from the S&P SmallCap 600, a market-cap-weighted index that consists of US small-caps screened for size, liquidity, and financial viability. The fund uses GICS in identifying technology firms, which may include those engaged in computer hardware and software, internet services and infrastructure, electronics and semiconductors, and communication technologies. Selected securities are weighted by market cap and are constrained, such that individual securities will not exceed 22.5% weight and the aggregate weight of securities with over 4.5% allocation is capped at 45% weight of the portfolio. The index rebalances quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P SmallCap 600® Capped Information Technology Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the information technology sector, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard.

name: Global X MLP & Energy Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides exposure to the midstream energy infrastructure sector by tracking an index composed of both Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs) and corporations. It invests at least 80% of its assets in these index securities. Structured as an open-ended fund under the 1940 Act (RIC compliant), its ability to hold MLPs is capped, typically around 24% of the portfolio following rebalances. The remainder is invested primarily in energy infrastructure corporations, often market-cap weighted with specific capping constraints. Consequently, while offering access to the sector, this non-diversified fund provides diluted MLP exposure compared to funds structured differently, blending MLPs with broader energy infrastructure corporate holdings.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index. It also invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of master limited partnerships and energy infrastructure corporations. The fund's 80% investment policies are non-fundamental and require 60 days prior written notice to shareholders before they can be changed. The index tracks the performance of midstream energy infrastructure MLPs and corporations. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
MLPX tracks an index of MLPs and companies engaged in energy infrastructure. The ETF is structured as an open-ended fund.

MLPX's seemingly vanilla structure comes with important trade-offs on how it plays the space. Unlike most existing MLP ETPs that are structured as C-corporations, MLPX is regulated as a classic 1940 Act fund. While this eliminates the downsides of the other structures, it also means the fund offers diluted exposure to MLPs. The fund intends to hold at least 20 US-listed midstream energy infrastructure MLPs and corporations. Since MLPX must be RIC compliant, it may only allocate 24% of its portfolio to MLPs at each quarterly rebalance, with the rest going to infrastructure firms which on the other hand are market-cap-weighted. Holdings are subjected to various capping constraints.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive MLP & Energy Infrastructure Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index. It also invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of master limited partnerships and energy infrastructure corporations. The fund's 80% investment policies are non-fundamental and require 60 days prior written notice to shareholders before they can be changed. The index tracks the performance of midstream energy infrastructure MLPs and corporations. It is non-diversified.

name: ETFMG Treatments, Testing and Advancements ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provided targeted exposure to a specific healthcare subsector by investing at least 80% of its assets in U.S.-listed equity securities or ADRs of companies focused on combating infectious diseases. It tracked a passively managed, tier-weighted index composed of firms engaged in the research, development, and commercialization of treatments or vaccines, as well as those involved in advancing, manufacturing, and providing biological tests. Holdings, selected based on criteria including market capitalization and liquidity, were subject to a unique weighting scheme and quarterly reconstitution. Having previously acquired the assets of another ETF with an identical strategy, this fund was subsequently delisted, with its final trading day on September 5, 2024.
description_original: The index tracks the performance of U.S.-listed equity securities or depositary receipts of companies that (i) perform research, development, and commercialization of treatments or vaccines for infectious diseases or (ii) engage in the research, development, manufacturing, and provision of biological tests for patients. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GERM tracks a tier-weighted index of US-listed healthcare companies engaged in treatments, testing, and other medical advancements. Holdings are selected by the index committee.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is September 5, 2024. GERM provides targeted exposure to a subsector of the healthcare industry. The passively managed fund holds firms that research, develop, and commercialize treatments or vaccines against infectious diseases, as well as companies involved in the research, development, manufacturing, and provision of biological tests for patients. Firms must meet market-cap and liquidity requirements, and have an operating company structure. Stocks are weighted in tiers: mega-caps or firms with market-cap of $15 billion or more are equally weighted within an aggregate allocation of 10%, the top 5 after excluding mega-caps receive 6% weights, and the remaining stocks are market cap-weighted, subject to a 4% cap. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. On Jan. 29, 2024, the fund acquired all assets and liabilities of the ETFMG Treatments Testing and Advancements ETF, to become a new ETF employing the same strategy.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in U.S.-listed equity securities or ADRs of Treatments, Testing and Advancements Companies. In general, the index seeks to be comprised of companies performing advancements in research, development, and commercialization of treatments or vaccines for infectious diseases, or engaged in the advancement of research, development, manufacturing, and provision of biological tests for patients. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Artificial Intelligence & Technology ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to mirror the performance of an index focused on developed-market companies significantly involved in the artificial intelligence (AI) and big data sectors. Constituents are selected based on their engagement in the development or utilization of AI and big data, encompassing analysis for internal operations, providing related services, or producing relevant hardware. The fund invests primarily (at least 80% of its assets) in the securities of its market-cap weighted underlying index, which is reconstituted annually and reweighted semi-annually. As a focused investment vehicle targeting this specific technological theme, it is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of companies involved in the development and utilization of artificial intelligence ("AI") and big data. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
AIQ tracks a market-cap-weighted index of developed-market equities involved in artificial intelligence & big data.

AIQ is passively managed to invest in developed market companies that are involved in the use of artificial intelligence to analyze big data, whether for their own operations, as a service to other companies, or through the production of related hardware. The fund determines this classification based on a composite analysis of public filings, products and services, official company statements, and other information regarding direct involvement in the artificial intelligence and big data categories. AIQs constituents are market cap weighted with a semi-annual re-weighting and are reconstituted annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx Artificial Intelligence & Big Data Index ("underlying index"). The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of companies involved in the development and utilization of artificial intelligence ("AI") and big data. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco KBW Bank ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provides focused exposure to the U.S. banking sector by seeking to track a modified market-capitalization weighted index. It generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the index's constituent securities, which are primarily U.S.-traded large national money centers, regional banks, and thrift institutions. The underlying index employs a capped weighting methodology intended to reflect the sector's market characteristics, is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly, and while predominantly focused on banking activities, may also include some firms from closely related industries.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index of companies primarily engaged in U.S. banking activities, as determined by the index provider. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of large national U.S. money centers, regional banks, and thrift institutions that are publicly traded in the U.S. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
KBWB tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index of US banking firms.

KBWB provides good exposure to the broad US banking market. Its portfolio includes large national money centers, regional banks and thrift institutions that are traded in the US. An index committee determines the funds holdings, while attempting to maintain a market-like exposure. KBWB uses a capped, modified market-cap-weighting strategy that comes close to matching the top-heavy nature of the segment. By industry, the fund strays a bit by including investment management & fund operators, and firms from other industries. Still, KBWB is a nice proxy for the broad industry. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted on a quarterly basis.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the KBW Nasdaq BankTM Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index of companies primarily engaged in U.S. banking activities, as determined by the index provider. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of large national U.S. money centers, regional banks, and thrift institutions that are publicly traded in the U.S. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Ultra Nasdaq Biotechnology
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to provide investment results corresponding to two times (2x) the daily performance of the Nasdaq Biotechnology Index®. It utilizes a combination of financial instruments, such as equity securities, derivatives, and money market instruments, to achieve this leveraged daily target. The underlying index is modified capitalization-weighted, includes Nasdaq-listed biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies, and exhibits a large-cap bias. As a non-diversified fund that rebalances its exposure daily, it is designed primarily for short-term trading, as compounding effects over longer periods can cause returns to differ significantly from the stated daily objective.
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is a modified capitalization weighted index that includes securities of Nasdaq listed companies that are classified as either biotechnology or pharmaceutical. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: BIB, having been around since 2010, is a leveraged play on the NASDAQ Biotechnology Index (which is also tracked in unlevered form by iShares' IBB), and is heavily focused on NASDAQs biotechnology and pharmaceutical firms with a large-cap bias. The fund gains its 2x leveraged exposure to the index through several financial instruments (i.e. equity securities, derivatives and money-market instruments), and rebalances its exposure daily. Like all geared funds that rebalance daily, BIB is meant for short-term trading since compounding effects over the long-term could create vast differences from expected returnsfor good or for ill.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is a modified capitalization weighted index that includes securities of Nasdaq listed companies that are classified as either biotechnology or pharmaceutical. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the Nasdaq Biotechnology Index®. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is a modified capitalization weighted index that includes securities of Nasdaq listed companies that are classified as either biotechnology or pharmaceutical. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares U.S. Medical Devices ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers targeted exposure to the U.S. medical equipment sector by seeking to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Medical Equipment Index. It invests primarily in domestic companies involved in the manufacturing and distribution of medical devices, including items such as MRI scanners, prosthetics, pacemakers, and X-ray machines. The underlying index employs a float-adjusted market-capitalization weighting methodology, incorporating caps on individual security weights. While aiming to hold index constituents, often investing at least 80% of its assets in them, the fund may use a sampling approach and is classified as non-diversified, concentrating its investments within this specific healthcare industry segment.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index, but which BFA believes will help the fund track the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IHI tracks a market-cap-weighted index of manufacturers and distributors of medical devices in the US.

IHI is a niche sector fund that specifically targets domestic companies engaged in the medical devices portion of the broader health care space. It aims to invest in companies that manufacture and distribute medical devices such as magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scanners, prosthetics, pacemakers, X-Ray machines, and other non-disposable medical devices. The fund is rebalanced quarterly and weighted by float-adjusted market cap, subject to capping restraints of 22.5% for any individual company. The fund uses a sampling method, and may not hold all of the securities in the index.
description_yahoo: The fund seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Medical Equipment Index, which measures the performance of the medical equipment sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. The index includes medical equipment companies, including manufacturers and distributors of medical devices such as magnetic resonance imaging scanners, prosthetics, pacemakers, X-ray machines, and other non-disposable medical devices. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Medical Equipment Index composed of U.S. equities in the medical devices sector. The fund seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Medical Equipment Index, which measures the performance of the medical equipment sector of the U.S. equity market, as defined by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. The index includes medical equipment companies, including manufacturers and distributors of medical devices such as magnetic resonance imaging scanners, prosthetics, pacemakers, X-ray machines, and other non-disposable medical devices. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Revenue ETF
merged_description: This investment fund seeks to track a revenue-weighted index composed of positive revenue-producing companies from the S&P 500®. Rather than weighting constituents by market capitalization, this strategy weights large-cap US companies based on their top-line revenue, typically investing at least 90% of its assets in these securities. Consequently, the portfolio often favors companies with significant sales figures, such as consumer firms, potentially underweighting sectors like technology, and notably disregards profit margins in its weighting methodology. The holdings are rebalanced quarterly, offering investors exposure to the large-cap US market through a distinct revenue-focused lens.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index includes positive revenue-producing constituent securities of the S&P 500® Index.
description_etfcom:
RWL tracks a revenue-weighted index of S&P 500 stocks.

RWL takes the securities of the S&P 500 Index, an index consisting of 500 large-cap US companies across various industry groups. The fund reweights each company by its revenue rather than its market cap. It follows that RWL underweights technology in favor of consumer firms, which generate large sales, but unlike some other fundamentally-weighted funds, it ignores profit margins. Overall, RWL delivers a decent, if revenue-biased, approximation of the market. The index constituents are rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 4, 2018, the funds underlying index was called OFI Revenue Weighted Large Cap Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P 500® Revenue-Weighted Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index includes positive revenue-producing constituent securities of the S&P 500® Index.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Materials ETF
merged_description: This investment fund tracks an equal-weighted index composed of materials sector companies included in the S&P 500. Its distinctive strategy assigns the same significance to each stock, regardless of market capitalization, thereby mitigating concentration in the largest firms and introducing a tilt towards mid-cap stocks compared to traditional market-cap weighted benchmarks. The fund commits to investing at least 90% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index, which rebalances on a quarterly basis. This approach offers investors less concentrated exposure to liquid U.S. materials companies, potentially without increasing overall portfolio volatility.
description_original: RSPM differentiates itself by using an equal-weighting strategy, which only includes basic materials companies in the S&P 500. Smaller companies have the same weighting as giants, tilting the whole fund to midcaps. Perhaps surprisingly, this does not increase RSPM's portfolio volatility. In short, investors who want to make a less-concentrated bet on the most liquid basic materials firms can do so with confidence in RSPM. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 7, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker RTM.
description_etfcom:
RSPM tracks an equal-weighted index of US materials companies in the S&P 500.

RSPM differentiates itself by using an equal-weighting strategy, which only includes basic materials companies in the S&P 500. Smaller companies have the same weighting as giants, tilting the whole fund to midcaps. Perhaps surprisingly, this does not increase RSPM's portfolio volatility. In short, investors who want to make a less-concentrated bet on the most liquid basic materials firms can do so with confidence in RSPM. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 7, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker RTM.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Materials Index. The Parent index is designed to measure the performance of common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the materials sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P 500® Equal Weight Materials Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Materials Index. The Parent index is designed to measure the performance of common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the materials sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: SPDR S&P 400™ Mid Cap Growth ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to replicate the performance of an index representing the mid-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market, drawn from the S&P 400 index. Investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities, typically using a sampling strategy, the fund focuses on companies demonstrating strong growth characteristics based on sales growth, earnings change relative to price, and momentum. The underlying index is float-adjusted market-cap weighted and rebalanced quarterly. Its selection process may result in a portfolio with a lower average market capitalization, including some small-cap exposure, compared to typical mid-cap funds. Importantly, the methodology allows for securities to fit multiple classifications, meaning its holdings might overlap with core or even value strategies, and it could exhibit notable sector tilts, such as overweighting financials.
description_original: The SPDR S&P 400 Mid Cap Growth ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P MidCap 400 Growth Index (the “Index”)The Index contains stocks that exhibit the strongest growth characteristics based on: sales growth, earnings change to price ratio, and momentum
description_etfcom:
MDYG tracks a market-cap-weighted index of growth companies selected from the S&P 400.

MDYG curates a portfolio of S&P MidCap 400 (commonly known as S&P 400) companies with high sales growth, high valuations and momentum. It starts selecting constituents further down the market-cap spectrum, leading to a lower than usual average market-cap and even some exposure to small-caps. Unlike some of its peers, MDYG isn't a pure growth fundits methodology allows securities to be classified into multiple categories. As such, its holdings could overlap with so-called core funds or even value funds. The fund may also heavily overweight financials, while underweighting other sectors such as consumer cyclicals. Additionally, instead of replicating the index, MDYG uses sampling indexing. The index is weighted by float-adjusted market-cap and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the mid-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P MidCap 400 Growth Index that tracks the performance of medium capitalization exchange traded U.S. equity securities exhibiting "growth" characteristics. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index measures the performance of the mid-capitalization growth segment of the U.S. equity market.

name: Invesco Global Clean Energy ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides global exposure to the clean energy sector by tracking an index comprising companies focused on cleaner energy generation and usage, conservation, efficiency, and the advancement of renewable energy technologies. Typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's securities, including ADRs and GDRs, the fund employs a unique index methodology where constituents are selected based on the index provider's assessment of their potential for capital appreciation, adding an element often associated with active management. While capable of holding large-cap firms, the portfolio exhibits a bias towards pure-play small- and mid-cap companies within the clean energy space. Diversification is maintained through quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution, a 5% cap on individual holdings, and a requirement to invest at least half of its assets internationally.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs") that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised primarily of companies whose technologies focus on the generation and use of cleaner energy, conservation and efficiency, and the advancement of renewable energy in general, as determined by the index provider.
description_etfcom: PBD is passively managed to invest in a wide array of global renewable energy companies, including those involved in conservation, improving energy efficiency and advancing renewable energy. The index may invest in large cap firms and those that derives at least 10% of its market value from clean energy activities, but has bias on pure-play, small- and midcap companies. Importantly, PBDs portfolio companies are selected based on the index providers opinion of their potential for capital appreciation. In that sense, PBD is more akin to an actively managed strategy than other funds in the segment. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. For diversification, the fund caps its largest holdings at 5% and is required to invest half its assets internationally.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the WilderHill New Energy Global Innovation Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as American depositary receipts ("ADRs") and global depositary receipts ("GDRs") that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised primarily of companies whose technologies focus on the generation and use of cleaner energy, conservation and efficiency, and the advancement of renewable energy in general, as determined by the index provider.

name: Defiance Next Gen Altered Experience ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund employs a replication strategy, aiming to mirror the performance of a rules-based index. Its portfolio consists of companies involved in legally compliant activities within the medical psychedelics, medical cannabis, cannabis pharmaceuticals, cannabidiol derivatives, and ketamine sectors, adhering strictly to applicable national laws. By investing in nearly all component securities in proportions similar to the index, the fund provides focused exposure to businesses operating within the emerging field of therapeutic and medically sanctioned altered experiences.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that tracks the performance of a portfolio of companies conducting legal activities under the national laws of the applicable country related to medical psychedelics, medical cannabis, cannabis pharmaceuticals and cannabidiol derivatives, and ketamine. The fund uses a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, it will invest in all of the component securities of the index in the same approximate proportions as in the index. It is non-diversified.

name: IQ Global Resources ETF
merged_description: This passively managed fund provided exposure to large global companies, primarily from developed markets, engaged in the production and distribution of commodities and related services. It tracked an index featuring stocks across key natural resource sectors: Energy, Metals (Industrial and Precious), and Agriculture (Grains, Food & Fiber, Livestock), supplemented by Timber and Water. A distinct, tiered weighting methodology allocated roughly 30% each to the broad Energy, Metals, and Agricultural categories, with the remaining 10% split equally between Timber and Water. Characterized as non-diversified, this investment vehicle ceased trading in December 2023.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, in the investments included in its underlying index. The underlying index seeks to employ a tiered sector weighting approach designed to provide exposure to developed market companies involved in the production and distribution of commodities and commodities-related products and services across the Precious Metals, Grains, Food and Fiber, Energy, Industrial Metals, Timber and Water sectors. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GRES is passively managed to provide exposure to the largest stocks from developed markets that are involved in commodities and commodities-related products and services.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 12, 2023. GRES tracks an index of natural resources stocks that are headquartered in developed markets. The largest companies from each of seven SICS sub-sectors are selected: 15 from Livestock, Timber, and Water companies and 40 from Industrial Metals, Energy, Grains, Food & Fiber, and Precious Metals. Using a tiered weighting approach, 30% is each allocated to Energy, Metals (Industrial and Precious) and Agricultural (Grains, Food & Fiber and Livestock) sectors. Timber and Water are both set at 5%. The sub-sectors under Metals and Agricultural are weighted using the pro-rata split based on market cap. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Sep. 1, 2021, the fund had additional exposure to the coal sector, employed an equity hedge overlay, used a momentum and valuation-based weighting scheme, and rebalanced monthly.

name: LGBTQ100 ESG ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund primarily invests in companies selected for an underlying index based on their demonstrated support for LGBTQ equality or adherence to broader Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) principles. Typically, the fund allocates at least 80% of its net assets to the securities comprising this index. To aid in tracking the index or for liquidity purposes, up to 20% of its assets may be held in other instruments, including cash, shares of other investment companies, or securities not included in the primary index.
description_original: Normally, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets in components of the underlying index. The index is comprised of securities screened to support LGBTQ or ESG positions. It also may invest up to 20% of its assets in instruments other than the components of the index, including shares of other investment companies, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index, but which the adviser believes will help the fund track the underlying index.

name: Fidelity MSCI Materials Index ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides focused exposure to the U.S. materials sector by aiming to track the performance of a market-capitalization-weighted index covering companies across the entire market-cap spectrum within this sector. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities included in its underlying benchmark, the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index, potentially utilizing a representative sampling strategy rather than holding every constituent. A defining characteristic of the index is its 25/50 capping methodology, which limits the weight of any single group entity to 25% and caps the aggregate weight of issuers exceeding 5% at 50%, designed to meet diversification requirements. Despite this index capping, the fund itself is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the materials sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FMAT tracks a market-cap-weighted index of stocks in the US basic materials sector across the entire market-cap spectrum.

FMAT is one of ten Fidelity ETFs that track MSCI sector indexes. The fund targets the US basic materials sector as defined by the GICS sector classification scheme. To meet diversification requirements, the funds underlying index employs a capping methodology, such that no group entity exceeds 25% of index weight and the aggregate weight of issuers with over 5% weight in the index are capped at 50% weight of the portfolio. The fund is both broad and representative, carrying only a few minor definitional differences from our benchmark. Prior to December 1, 2020, FMAT tracked the unconstrained MSCI USA IMI Materials index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index. The fund invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the fund's underlying index. The fund's underlying index is the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index, which represents the performance of the materials sector in the U.S. equity market. It may or may not hold all of the securities in the MSCI USA IMI Materials 25/50 Index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard FTSE Social Index Fund Institutional Shs
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to track the performance of a market-capitalization weighted benchmark index composed of large- and mid-capitalization stocks. Its core strategy focuses on companies screened by the index provider for specific environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) criteria. Employing a replication approach, the fund aims to invest substantially all its assets in the constituent stocks of the underlying ESG-focused index, holding them in approximately the same proportions as their index weighting. Notably, this fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The investment seeks to track the performance of a benchmark index that measures the investment return of large- and mid-capitalization stocks. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the FTSE4Good US Select Index. The index, which is market-capitalization weighted, is composed of large- and mid-cap stocks of companies that are screened for certain ESG criteria by the index sponsor. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_yahoo: The index is composed of large- and mid-cap stocks of companies that are screened for certain environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) criteria by the index provider. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the FTSE U.S. Choice Index Index that measures the investment return of large- and mid-capitalization stocks. The index is composed of large- and mid-cap stocks of companies that are screened for certain environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) criteria by the index provider. The manager attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. It is non-diversified.

name: iShares International Developed Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This investment provides targeted exposure to the international developed real estate market, specifically excluding the United States. It seeks to replicate the performance of a market-capitalization-weighted index, defined by FTSE EPRA Nareit, composed of companies engaged in the ownership, development, and trading of income-producing real estate within these developed non-US markets. Utilizing size, liquidity, and revenue screens for constituent selection, the portfolio primarily holds real estate developers, commercial property firms, and Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs). Adhering to its strategy, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or economically similar securities and notably excludes exposure to China's real estate market. Holdings are reviewed on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the stock performance of companies engaged in the ownership and development of real estate markets in developed countries (except for the United States) as defined by FTSE EPRA/NAREIT.
description_etfcom:
IFGL tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies that own or develop real estate throughout the developed world, excluding the United States.

IFGL offers an international view on the real estate industry. The funds underlying index represents the developed markets ex-US segment of the FTSE EPRA Nareit Global Real Estate Index Series. As such, investors should note that the fund does not provide any exposure to China or its massive real estate market. The fund uses size, liquidity, and revenue screens in selecting its constituents which mainly comprises of real estate developers, commercial real estate, as well as real estate investment trusts (REITs). Holdings are weighted by market-cap and reviewed quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of companies engaged in the ownership, trading and development of income-producing real estate in the developed real estate markets (except for the U.S.) as defined by FTSE EPRA Nareit.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the FTSE EPRA Nareit Developed ex US Index composed of real estate equities in developed non-U.S. markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of companies engaged in the ownership, trading and development of income-producing real estate in the developed real estate markets (except for the U.S.) as defined by FTSE EPRA Nareit.

name: Democracy International Fund
merged_description: This investment fund aims to track the total return performance of an international index emphasizing companies based on the democratic standing of their home countries. Starting with a universe of large and mid-cap companies from global markets outside the United States, the underlying index employs a unique weighting methodology. Companies are reweighted based on the product of their market capitalization and their country's "Democracy Score," as determined by The Economist Group's assessment across criteria like electoral process, civil liberties, and political culture. This process results in a portfolio that typically overweights larger companies located in countries with higher democracy scores, though significant market capitalization can still lead to the inclusion of some firms from less democratic nations. The fund generally utilizes a representative sampling approach to achieve its investment objective, and its underlying index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly.
description_original: The index construction process begins with the universe of companies that are current members of the Solactive GBS Global Markets ex United States Large & Mid Cap USD Index NTR. In constructing the fund's portfolio, the Adviser generally will use a representative sampling investment approach designed to achieve the fund's investment objective.
description_etfcom: DMCYs underlying index aims to invest heavily in companies located in democratic countries, and less heavily in authoritarian countries. Index construction begins by utilizing the Democracy Score assigned to each country by The Economist Group. This score is a composite of 60 different criteria from five categories of: electoral process and pluralism, civil liberties, functioning of government, political participation, and political culture. Using the holdings from the Solactive GBS Global Markets ex-United States Large & Mid Cap USD Index, companies are reweighted based on the product of the companys market-cap and Democracy Score. This results in a portfolio that overweights large companies from countries with higher Democracy Scores. Do note that certain companies from authoritarian countries may be overweighted if they have a sufficiently large market capitalization. Rebalancing and reconstitution of the underlying index is done quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Democracy Investments International Index. The index construction process begins with the universe of companies that are current members of the Solactive GBS Global Markets ex United States Large & Mid Cap USD Index NTR. In constructing the fund's portfolio, the Adviser generally will use a representative sampling investment approach designed to achieve the fund's investment objective.

name: SPDR SSGA US Sector Rotation ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks capital appreciation by investing in a portfolio of underlying ETFs, each tracking a specific GICS-defined sector of the S&P 500. Its core strategy involves tactical sector rotation, dynamically adjusting allocations based on a proprietary approach that combines quantitative modeling (forecasting sector returns using economic and market data) and qualitative analysis. This method aims to maximize expected returns while managing risk relative to the benchmark, with portfolio adjustments typically made monthly but adaptable to changing market conditions.
description_original: The SPDR SSGA US Sector Rotation ETF seeks to provide capital appreciation by tactically allocating among the GICS-defined sectors of the S&P 500 IndexThe investment approach combines quantitative and qualitative analysis and dynamically adjusts active risk budgets relative to the benchmarkTypically rebalanced monthly, but rebalancing may occur more or less frequently depending on market conditions
description_etfcom:
XLSR is an actively-managed portfolio of companies classified within favorable sectors of the S&P 500.

XLSR is a fund of funds that each focus on equities within the individual sector of the S&P 500 Index. The fund employs their own selection model which incorporates macroeconomic, financial and market data to project sector returns. Using these forecasts, the model then allocates the weightings of each equity sector to construct a portfolio that seeks to maximize expected return. Included sectors are communication services, consumer discretionary, consumer staples, energy, financials, healthcare, industrials, materials, real estate, information technology, and utilities. Although XLSR employs a model, the fund is actively managed.
description_yahoo: The fund is a "fund of funds," meaning that it primarily invests its assets in securities of other exchange-traded funds ("ETFs"). In particular, it allocates its assets among ETFs that each focus on common stocks of companies included in an individual sector of the S&P 500® Index, as determined by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS®). Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of borrowings for investments purposes) directly or indirectly through the underlying ETFs, in securities of U.S. companies.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide capital appreciation. The fund is a "fund of funds," meaning that it primarily invests its assets in securities of other exchange-traded funds ("ETFs"). In particular, it allocates its assets among ETFs that each focus on common stocks of companies included in an individual sector of the S&P 500® Index, as determined by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS®). Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of borrowings for investments purposes) directly or indirectly through the underlying ETFs, in securities of U.S. companies.

name: Nuveen ESG Mid-Cap Value ETF
merged_description: This fund provides focused exposure to U.S. mid-capitalization companies selected for both value characteristics and strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) performance, seeking to track the results of a corresponding index. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities under normal conditions. The underlying index methodology begins with a broad mid-cap value universe, then applies exclusionary screens to remove firms involved in controversial businesses (like alcohol, weapons, gambling, and nuclear power) and those exceeding carbon emission thresholds. From the eligible companies, it selects the highest-scoring ESG performers within each sector. A multi-factor optimization algorithm is used to weight the holdings, aiming to maintain exposure similar to a traditional mid-cap value benchmark while emphasizing the selected ESG leaders, with the portfolio undergoing quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index. The index is comprised of equity securities with value characteristics issued by mid-capitalization companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") criteria.
description_etfcom:
NUMV tracks an index of US mid-cap value stocks that score highly on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. The fund weighting uses a multi-factor optimizer.

NUMV aims to invest in the most socially responsible companies while still providing reasonably market-like exposure to mid-cap value stocks. The index takes its holdings from the MSCI USA Mid-Cap Value Index (the parent index), which selects value stocks according to price/book, forward price/earnings, and dividend yield. From there, NUMV screens out companies involved in controversial businesses, such as alcohol, weapons, nuclear power, and gambling. Companies that exceed carbon emissions thresholds are also excluded. The remaining firms are scored on ESG factors, and the highest scoring firms within each sector (top 50% by market cap) are selected for inclusion in the index. The portfolio is weighted according to a multi-factor optimization algorithm that aims to keep holdings and performance similar to the parent index. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly starting each February. Sibling fund NULV applies the same strategy to US large caps.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results, before fees and expenses, of the TIAA ESG USA Mid-Cap Value Index (the "index"). Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index. The index is comprised of equity securities with value characteristics issued by mid-capitalization companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") criteria.

name: Global X Funds - Global X Emerging Markets ETF
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital growth, this actively managed ETF invests primarily (at least 80% of its assets) in equity securities linked to emerging markets, specifically excluding China. It employs an opportunistic, bottom-up fundamental analysis approach to identify companies considered well-positioned leaders within their respective country, region, or industry, aiming to capitalize on the growth potential driven by socio-economic changes in these markets. The selection process emphasizes advantageous competitive strategies and shareholder-beneficial practices, potentially involving active and frequent trading within its defined investment universe.
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF advised by the Adviser and sub-advised by the Sub-Adviser that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, measured at the time of purchase, in equity securities: (i) of issuers in emerging markets; and/or (ii) that are tied economically to emerging markets.
description_etfcom: EMM invests in companies believed to achieve and maintain a leading position within their respective country, region, industry, products produced, or services provided.
