The belief is that emerging markets have the potential for higher levels of growth based on socio-economic changes. The fund uses an opportunistic approach targeting companies considered best positioned to benefit from these changes. The investable universe is limited to emerging market stocks, excluding China, that meet minimum market cap and liquidity requirements. The process also considers advantageous competitive strategies and shareholder-beneficial practices and philosophies. The portfolio is constructed using a bottom-up fundamental analysis, subject to a risk management framework. The fund may engage in active and frequent trading. On May 15, 2023, EMM converted from a mutual fund to an actively managed ETF, with $18 million in assets. Before April 1, 2024, the fund appended 'ex-China' to its fund name.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital growth. The fund is an actively managed ETF advised by the Adviser and sub-advised by the Sub-Adviser that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, measured at the time of purchase, in equity securities: (i) of issuers in emerging markets; and/or (ii) that are tied economically to emerging markets.

name: iShares ESG Screened S&P Mid-Cap ETF
merged_description: This investment fund offers exposure to the U.S. mid-capitalization equity market by tracking a market-cap weighted index that applies specific sustainability screens. Based on the S&P MidCap 400, the index excludes companies significantly involved in controversial business activities, such as tobacco, controversial weapons, and fossil fuels (including reserves). It also screens out firms deemed non-compliant with UN Global Compact principles or flagged for major governance controversies like economic crime, human rights abuses, or environmental disasters. The fund utilizes a representative sampling indexing strategy to achieve its objective of tracking the performance of these screened mid-cap equities and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund seeks to track the investment results of the S&P MidCap 400 Sustainability Screened Index, which measures the performance of the mid-capitalization sector of the U.S. equity market while excluding companies involved in controversial business activities and controversies, as determined by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. BFA uses a representative sampling indexing strategy to manage the fund. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
XJH tracks a market cap-weighted index of US mid-caps screened for sustainability and excluding those with exposure to certain controversial business activities.

XJH is part of an iShares suite that offers ESG take on S&P indices. It starts with the S&P MidCap 400 and screens out companies over a certain threshold level of involvement in tobacco, controversial weapons, and involvement with fossil-fuels. Companies are evaluated based on their involvement in certain controversial business activities. Excluded are those holding reserves of coal, oil, natural gas or shale, and companies deemed non-compliant with the UNGC principles. Companies are also evaluated for governance controversies, such as economic crime, corruption, fraud, human rights abuses, labor disputes, workplace safety, catastrophic accidents, and environmental disasters. Those flagged on any of these issues may be removed from the index and remain ineligible for reentry for up to one year. Exclusions are reviewed at each quarterly rebalance. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund name was iShares ESG Screened S&P Mid-Cap ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of an index composed of mid-capitalization U.S. equities while applying screens for company involvement in controversies and controversial business activities. The fund seeks to track the investment results of the S&P MidCap 400 Sustainability Screened Index, which measures the performance of the mid-capitalization sector of the U.S. equity market while excluding companies involved in controversial business activities and controversies, as determined by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC. BFA uses a representative sampling indexing strategy to manage the fund. It is non-diversified.

name: FlexShares ESG & Climate Developed Markets ex-US Core Index Fund
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks to mirror the performance of a principles-based index offering core exposure primarily to large-cap equities from developed markets outside the United States. The underlying index selects companies demonstrating specific positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics, evaluating their ability to manage material ESG risks and maintain good corporate governance. It distinctly incorporates carbon-related risk metrics, assessing factors like emissions intensity, carbon reserves, and overall carbon risk exposure, while also screening out companies involved in activities with negative environmental impacts. The index methodology includes optimization constraints to manage systematic risks and undergoes quarterly reconstitution. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the constituent securities of the index, including corresponding ADRs and GDRs.
description_original: The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that exhibit certain ESG characteristics, while also seeking to provide broad-market, core exposure to publicly traded equity securities issued by companies domiciled in developed market countries, excluding the U.S. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FEDM tracks a principles-based index of large-cap companies from the developed markets outside the US that exhibit environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) characteristics.

FEDM follows an index designed to provide a broad exposure to developed market companies outside the US that exhibit several specific environmental, social, and corporate governance attributes. Selection begins with the constituents of the NorthernTrust Developed Markets ex-US Large Cap Index. Each eligible company is ranked based on their ESG scores as measured by their ability to manage risks associated with material ESG issues and their good corporate governance. Moreover, the fund also utilizes carbon-related risk metrics to assess the carbon emissions intensity, carbon reserves, and carbon risk exposure for each firm. Companies are also screened and excluded based on business activities that produce negative impacts in the environment. Additional optimization is also done to minimize systematic risk including constituent, liquidity, absolute weight, sector, industry group, and turnover constraints. The index is reconstituted on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that exhibit certain ESG characteristics in the aggregate, while also seeking to provide broad-market, core exposure to publicly traded equity securities issued by companies domiciled in developed market countries, excluding the U.S. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance of the Northern Trust® ESG & Climate Developed Markets ex‑US Core IndexSM. The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of a selection of companies that exhibit certain ESG characteristics in the aggregate, while also seeking to provide broad-market, core exposure to publicly traded equity securities issued by companies domiciled in developed market countries, excluding the U.S. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ETFMG Travel Tech ETF
merged_description: Focusing on the intersection of technology and global travel, this passively managed fund aims to mirror the performance of an index comprising companies engaged in the "Travel Technology Business." It invests heavily (at least 80% of net assets plus borrowings) in the index's components—globally listed equities, American Depositary Receipts (ADRs), and Global Depositary Receipts (GDRs). To qualify for the index, companies must primarily focus on and derive a majority of their revenue from providing travel-related services via the internet and connected devices, such as booking and reservation platforms, ride-sharing apps, price comparison tools, and online travel advice. The index weights its holdings based on market capitalization and liquidity (average daily value traded), undergoing quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing. Notably, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets, exclusive of collateral held from securities lending, in the component securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the component securities in the index. The index tracks the performance of globally exchange-listed equity securities of companies across the globe that are engaged in "Travel Technology Business" which is defined as providing technology, via the internet and internet-connected devices.
description_etfcom:
AWAY tracks an index of committee-selected travel technology companies from around the globe. Holdings are weighted based on market cap and liquidity.

AWAY is the first ETF to provide access to the technology-focused global travel and tourism industry. It is a passively managed portfolio of companies that, via the internet and internet-connected devices, facilitates travel bookings and reservations, ride sharing and hailing, travel price comparison, and travel advice. To be eligible for inclusion, descriptions of a companys primary business activities in its regulatory filings must be related to travel tech, and the majority of its revenue, according to its financial reports and other filings, must be derived from travel technology business activities. Index constituents are weighted based on market capitalization and average daily value traded, in which larger and more frequently traded companies receive greater weights. The index reconstitutes and rebalances quarterly. On January 29, 2024, the fund acquired all assets and liabilities of the ETFMG Travel Tech ETF, morphing into a new ETF that employs the same strategy.
description_yahoo: The index tracks the performance of globally exchange-listed equity securities (or corresponding American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) or Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”)) of companies across the globe that are engaged in “Travel Technology Business”. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the component securities of the index and in ADRs or GDRs based on the component securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks that generally correlate (before fees and expenses) to the total return performance of the Prime Travel Technology Index NTR. The index tracks the performance of globally exchange-listed equity securities (or corresponding American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) or Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”)) of companies across the globe that are engaged in “Travel Technology Business”. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the component securities of the index and in ADRs or GDRs based on the component securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a 'Growth at a Reasonable Price' (GARP) strategy, targeting large- and mid-cap US equities selected from the MSCI USA Index universe. It initially identifies stocks based on strong growth characteristics using criteria such as earnings growth trends and internal growth rates. The portfolio construction then incorporates a tilt towards securities that also exhibit favorable value (e.g., P/B, forward P/E) and quality (e.g., ROE, D/E) metrics relative to their respective sectors. Committing to invest at least 80% of its assets in the components of its underlying index, the fund may utilize the remaining portion for investments in derivatives, cash, or cash equivalents. The fund is classified as non-diversified and rebalances its holdings on a quarterly basis.
description_original: The underlying index is designed to select equity securities from the Russell 1000® Growth Index, which in turn is a subset of the Russell 1000® Index. It generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: GARP focuses on large- and mid-cap US growth stocks that exhibit value and quality traits, or growth at a reasonable price. The selection process begins with the MSCI USA Index, where each stock is assigned a growth score based on five criteria: long-term and short-term forward EPS growth rates, historical EPS and sales per share growth trends, and current internal growth rate. Stocks with higher growth scores are selected until they represent approximately 50% of the parent index. Each stock receives a tilt score, which considers value (P/B, forward P/E, and EV/CFO) and quality (ROE, D/E, and earnings variability) metrics relative to its sector. The portfolio is then tilted toward securities that score favorably on both metrics, with weights adjusted for portfolio diversification. Index rebalancing is done quarterly. Before June 3, 2024, the fund was named iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF under the ticker STLG and tracked the Russell US Large Cap Factors Growth Style Index.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily Aerospace & Defense Bull 3X Shares
merged_description: This non-diversified exchange-traded fund seeks to achieve daily investment results, before fees and expenses, equivalent to 300% of the daily performance of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace & Defense Index, which tracks the market-cap-weighted performance of the U.S. aerospace and defense industry. To obtain this 3x daily leveraged exposure, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, including borrowings, primarily in financial instruments like swap agreements, index securities, and related ETFs. Due to the effects of daily compounding and reset mechanisms, its performance over longer periods can significantly diverge from 300% of the index's cumulative return, making it principally designed as a short-term trading vehicle rather than a long-term investment strategy.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, and securities of the index, ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or ETFs that track the index. The index attempts to measure the performance of the aerospace and defense industry of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: DFEN is a daily 3x leveraged bet on the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace and Defense Index, a market-cap-weighted index of US-listed aerospace and defense stocks. Unleveraged exposure to the same index can be found in ITA a fund from BlackRock. The geared 3x nature of DFEN is designed to magnify the daily performance of the index, not to return 300% of the index performance over extended periods of time. Due to compounding and the daily reset function, the fund is meant to be a trading vehicle for investors to make short-term bets on the direction of the aerospace and defense industry and not a long-term investment strategy. Compounding becomes more pronounced and more of a concern as holding periods increase, and the fund is likely to stray from the returns of the underlying index in such cases. Due to the fund`s day trading personality, trading volume and bid/ask spread are more important cost considerations than expense ratio.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index attempts to measure the performance of the aerospace and defense industry of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace & Defense Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index attempts to measure the performance of the aerospace and defense industry of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Utilities ETF
merged_description: This investment fund concentrates on large-cap companies from the S&P 500® Index classified within the utilities and telecommunications sectors. Utilizing an equal-weighting methodology, it allocates a similar weight to each constituent stock, diverging significantly from traditional market-capitalization weighted strategies. The fund aims to mirror the performance of its underlying index by investing substantially all (typically at least 90%) of its assets in the index's securities, with the portfolio undergoing quarterly rebalancing. Due to the notable inclusion of telecommunications stocks alongside utilities, it does not provide pure-play exposure exclusively to the utilities sector.
description_original: RSPU tracks an equal-weighted index of large-cap utilities companies. Its equal-weighting scheme skews it away from a market-like portfolio. The fund also includes a significant allocation to telecom stocks, which are not included in some utilities fund. This is common, however, as many utilities ETFs combine the two sectors and telecom stocks may pay higher dividends than utilities. Still, investors looking for pure-play exposure should look elsewhere. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYU.
description_etfcom:
RSPU tracks an equal-weighted index of S&P 500 utilities companies.

RSPU tracks an equal-weighted index of large-cap utilities companies. Its equal-weighting scheme skews it away from a market-like portfolio. The fund also includes a significant allocation to telecom stocks, which are not included in some utilities fund. This is common, however, as many utilities ETFs combine the two sectors and telecom stocks may pay higher dividends than utilities. Still, investors looking for pure-play exposure should look elsewhere. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYU.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Utilities Plus Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the utilities sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P 500® Equal Weight Utilities Plus Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Utilities Plus Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the utilities sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: Cabana Target Leading Sector Conservative ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund-of-funds employed a proprietary algorithm, combining fundamental economic and technical data, to dynamically allocate assets based on the business cycle and market outlook. It invested primarily in other ETFs across diverse asset classes including equities (domestic, foreign, and emerging markets), fixed income (without restrictions on maturity, quality, or duration), real estate, currencies, and commodities, though it could also invest directly in securities. The strategy aimed for a conservative investment style, seeking to minimize volatility in bearish markets while allocating to leading sectors anticipated to outperform during bullish periods. Operating as a non-diversified fund, the sub-adviser had discretionary authority to override the algorithm if necessary. Trading for this security ceased, and it was delisted in early January 2024.
description_original: The manager seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective primarily by allocating its assets among ETFs that invest in securities of companies in the various sectors of the U.S. market. It operates in a manner that is commonly referred to as a "fund of funds," meaning that it primarily invests in other ETFs. The ETFs may invest in any of the five major asset classes - equities, fixed income, real estate, currencies, and commodities. It may invest directly in securities and other instruments to obtain the desired exposure to a specific sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CLSC is an actively managed fund-of-funds which aims to provide long-term growth. The fund uses a proprietary algo to identify attractive sectors at any given time in the business cycle.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 05, 2024.CLSC is an actively-managed fund-of-funds that shifts its allocation based on the economic conditions and market outlook for variety of asset classes: equities, fixed income, real estate, currencies and commodities. Equities will include both domestic and foreign companies, including emerging markets. Fixed Income securities have no restrictions in terms of maturity, quality or duration. The Sub-Adviser utilizes a proprietary algorithm that combines fundamental economic and technical price data to identify assets that appear to be attractive based on the current business cycle. The fund claims a conservative investment style, it optimizes the portfolio to target minimum volatility in bearish markets and allocates to leading sectors that are believed to outperform during bullish markets. The Sub-Advisor has full discretion to override the algo if a perceived breakdown or systemic change has occurred.

name: Defiance Next Gen H2 ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund is scheduled for delisting, with its final day of trading set for April 28, 2025. It was structured to track a rules-based index of global companies involved in developing hydrogen-based energy sources and fuel cell technologies, representing one of the initial offerings focused on this specific industry. The strategy prioritized investment in pure-play companies generating substantial revenue from these activities, aiming for a minimum of 25 constituents and dedicating at least 85% aggregate portfolio weight to them. Under normal conditions, at least 80% of the fund's assets were invested in such hydrogen-related firms. This non-diversified fund employed a tiered, market-capitalization-based weighting system with individual security caps and liquidity adjustments, undergoing quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing. Provisions allowed for including select non-pure-play companies if insufficient pure-play options were available.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that tracks the performance of a group of globally listed equity securities of companies involved in the development of hydrogen-based energy sources and fuel cell technologies. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) will be invested in H2 Companies. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 28, 2025. HDRO is one of the first ETFs that capture the global hydrogen-based energy industry. The fund mainly focuses on pure-play companiesthose that derive at least 50% of their revenue from hydrogen-based energy sources and fuel cell technologies. HDRO selects stocks by market-cap to construct its narrow portfolio, holding at least 25 constituents. In the event that fewer than 25 eligible pure-play stocks are included, non-pure-play companies, excluding vehicle manufacturers, may be selected. Holdings are weighted in tiersfirst by market-cap, with a minimum aggregate weight of 85% for pure-play companies and a single security weight cap of 10% (4% for industrial gas). Weights are then adjusted using a liquidity overlay. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the BlueStar Hydrogen & NextGen Fuel Cell Index. The index is a rules-based index that tracks the performance of a group of globally listed equity securities of companies involved in the development of hydrogen-based energy sources and fuel cell technologies. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) will be invested in H2 Companies. It is non-diversified.

name: IQ Clean Oceans ETF
merged_description: This now-delisted ETF (last traded April 9, 2025) employed a passive management approach, tracking a thematic index focused on global companies contributing to cleaner oceans through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency. The index selected approximately 50 to 80 companies based on their positive environmental impact and revenue derived from relevant sectors such as the circular economy, clean energy, water treatment, and sustainable packaging, while excluding firms failing sustainability standards, UN Global Compact principles, or involved in controversies. Holdings were market-cap weighted, subject to a 3% cap on individual securities, and rebalanced quarterly; the fund operated as a non-diversified investment.
description_original: The manager employs a “passive management” — or indexing — investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index incorporates thematic selection criteria designed to provide exposure to equity securities of companies that help to protect and/or achieve a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
OCEN tracks a market-cap-weighted index of globally-listed companies that are believed to contribute in achieving a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 9, 2025. OCEN is passively managed, holding a portfolio of companies engaged in ocean-related sustainability. The portfolio aims to cast a wide net, selecting from a universe of companies involved in a circular economy, clean energy, water and waste treatment, electronic components, energy-efficient economy, seafood and alternatives, shipping and ports, and sustainable packaging. Companies not meeting globally sustainability trends, non-compliant with the UN Global Compact, or engaged in controversial activities are excluded. Eligible companies are given a score based on revenue generated from thematic exposure and impact on the environment. The top 50 to 80 companies are selected and the resulting portfolio is market-cap-weighted, with single security weights capped at 3%. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Aug. 28, 2024, the fund name was branded under IndexIQ.
description_yahoo: The underlying index incorporates thematic selection criteria designed to provide exposure to equity securities of companies that help to protect and/or achieve a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard U.S. Liquidity Factor ETF
merged_description: This fund primarily invests in U.S. common stocks, aiming to outperform the broad U.S. equity market by strategically selecting stocks characterized by lower measures of trading liquidity, as determined by its advisor. It maintains a diversified portfolio, incorporating a wide mix of companies from numerous market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, the fund commits at least 80% of its assets to securities issued by U.S. companies, emphasizing its focus on the domestic market while leveraging the potential return premium associated with less liquid stocks.
description_original: The fund invests primarily in U.S. common stocks with the potential to generate higher returns relative to the broad U.S. equity market by investing in stocks with lower measures of trading liquidity as determined by the advisor. The portfolio will include a diverse mix of companies representing many different market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies.

name: FlexShares Real Assets Allocation Index Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle operates as a fund-of-funds, providing diversified global exposure to real assets through investments in underlying ETFs focused on natural resources, infrastructure, and real estate. It is designed to serve as a core real asset holding, seeking to track an index that employs an optimized allocation methodology across these underlying funds with the primary objective of minimizing overall portfolio volatility. This strategy aims to provide investors with potential inflation hedging and income characteristics inherent in real assets. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the components of its target index, which undergoes reconstitution and rebalancing at least annually.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of an optimized allocation to the underlying funds that is intended to provide exposures to certain real assets and minimize overall volatility of investment in the underlying funds.
description_etfcom:
ASET is a fund-of-funds that gives investors diversified global exposure to real assets.

ASET is designed to serve as a core real asset allocation by investing in three of FlexShares ETFs: FlexShares Morningstar Global Upstream Natural Resources Index Fund (GUNR), FlexShares STOXX Global Broad Infrastructure Index Fund (NFRA) and FlexShares Global Quality Real Estate Index Fund (GQRE). The portfolio managers use a proprietary optimization methodology to allocate between these three funds with the goal of minimizing overall return volatility. This fund is meant as an all-in-one product addressing investors need for both inflation-hedging and income. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced at least annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Northern Trust Real Assets Allocation IndexSM. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of an optimized allocation to the underlying funds that is intended to provide exposures to certain real assets and minimize overall volatility of investment in the underlying funds.

name: iShares S&P 500 Growth ETF
merged_description: This investment fund tracks an index composed of large-capitalization U.S. stocks drawn from the S&P 500 that exhibit growth characteristics. Selection for the index is based on three factors: sales growth, earnings growth, and price momentum. The fund primarily invests, committing at least 80% of its assets, in the component securities of this underlying index or in investments with substantially identical economic characteristics. It may allocate up to 20% to derivatives like futures and options, along with cash equivalents. Considered an established and inexpensive option, it offers balanced exposure to the large-cap growth sector, potentially showing modest sector tilts and a slight mid-cap bias compared to broader benchmarks, and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
IVW tracks an index of large-cap US stocks. The index selects stocks with growth characteristics from the S&P 500 Index, based on three growth factors.

IVW is one of the most established and popular growth-focused ETFs, holding firms with growth characteristics from the S&P 500 Index. S&P's style methodology selects companies based on three growth factors: sales growth, earnings growth, and momentum. IVW was one of the first growth-focused ETFs to launch. The portfolio shows only modest sector tilts compared to our large-cap-growth benchmark, with a small but persistent bias toward midcaps. VOOG and SPYG track the same index with similarly low holdings cost. Overall, the fund is inexpensive and provides balanced exposure to large-cap-growth firms.
description_yahoo: The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P 500 Growth IndexTM composed of large-capitalization U.S. equities that exhibit growth characteristics. The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Supply Chain Logistics ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund aims to track the performance of an index representing companies central to the global supply chain logistics sector, which includes the movement of raw materials, intermediate goods, and finished products. The index methodology generally selects the 40 largest global companies by market capitalization that generate at least 75% of their revenue from relevant logistics activities such as support services, software, rail, air freight, trucking, and sea shipping, with provisions to adjust the revenue threshold to ensure a minimum number of holdings. Constituents are market-cap weighted with a cap on individual issuer weights, and the fund invests primarily in global common stocks, ADRs, and GDRs comprising the index, committing at least 80% of its assets to these or similar instruments, while undergoing semi-annual reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund invests in securities that ProShare Advisors believes should track the performance of the index. The index provider then selects into the index the 40 largest companies, by market capitalization, that generate 75% or more of their revenue from products or services produced or provided by one or more of the applicable RBICS Sub-Industries. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: SUPL tracks an index of companies primarily involved in the logistics of moving raw materials, intermediate goods, and finished products around the globe. Eligible companies must be included in at least one of 17 RBICS Sub-Industries related to the supply chain logistics industry, which encompasses logistics support and software, rail and air freight, trucking, and sea shipping. The index selects the 40 largest companies that generate at least 75% of their revenue from the related industry. If less than 25 companies are selected, the revenue threshold is decreased to 50% and companies with the highest percentage revenue related to the industry are added until the portfolio reaches 25 constituents. Weightings are based on market-cap, with a limit of 4.5% per issuer. The index will principally invest in common shares, ADRs and GDRs listed for trading on a stock exchange globally. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually in June and December.
description_yahoo: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies focused on raw materials and merchandise shipping and delivery. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the FactSet Supply Chain Logistics Index (the “Index”). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies focused on raw materials and merchandise shipping and delivery. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Ultra Oil & Gas
merged_description: This non-diversified fund seeks to provide twice (2x) the daily investment results of the S&P Energy Select Sector Index. The index itself measures the performance of market-capitalization-weighted US energy companies found within the S&P 500, concentrating particularly on industry giants engaged in areas like oil and gas exploration, production, integrated operations, equipment, pipelines, and alternative fuels. To achieve its objective, the fund invests in financial instruments providing leveraged exposure covering at least 80% of its assets. Due to the daily reset mechanism inherent in its leveraged strategy, this product is designed primarily as a short-term trading tool, as long-term returns can significantly diverge from the underlying index's cumulative performance due to the effects of daily compounding.
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index measures the performance of certain companies in the oil and gas sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: DIG provides 2x leveraged exposure to the S&P Energy Select Sector Index, a market-cap-weighted index of US oil and gas companies. This is a concentrated market that especially captures industry giants. Specifically, the fund typically includes firms involved in oil and gas exploration and production, integrated oil and gas, equipment for oil as well as renewable energy, pipelines, and alternative fuel producers. As a geared product with daily resets, DIG is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. Long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to Mar. 20, 2023, the fund was called ProShares Ultra Energy that tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Oil & Gas Index.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to measure the performance of energy companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Energy Select Sector Index. The index is designed to measure the performance of energy companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: VanEck Digital Transformation ETF
merged_description: This investment fund provides focused equity exposure to global companies driving the digital transformation of the economy, particularly those deriving significant revenue (typically at least 50%) from digital asset projects such as exchanges, mining operations, payment gateways, and related technology or infrastructure services. It seeks to track a market-cap-weighted index representing these innovators, normally investing at least 80% of its assets in such securities. The portfolio often consists of a limited number of top-ranking companies in this space, subject to single-security weighting caps and quarterly rebalancing. Crucially, the fund does not invest directly or indirectly (via derivatives) in cryptocurrencies or other digital assets, nor does it participate in initial coin offerings, positioning itself as a non-diversified vehicle for accessing the growth of the digital asset ecosystem through traditional equities.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of Digital Transformation Companies. The index is a global index that tracks the performance of Digital Transformation Companies. The fund will not invest in digital assets (including cryptocurrencies) (i) directly or (ii) indirectly through the use of digital asset derivatives. It also will not invest in initial coin offerings. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
DAPP tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global innovative companies that are involved in the digitalization of the worlds economy through a diverse range of digital assets.

DAPP offers pure-play exposure to companies leading the digital transformation of the economy through digital assets without geo constraints. The funds underlying index is composed of diversified companies of all capitalization defined as Digital Assets Stocks which derive at least 50% of their revenue from digital assets projects. These companies include digital asset exchanges, payment gateways, miners, equipment, technology, and service providers, digital asset infrastructure businesses, and e-commerce. Eligible securities are ranked in terms of market-cap with the top 85% qualified for inclusion. The largest 25 ranking companies are chosen as index constituents and are then weighted by market-cap with single security capping at 8%. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® Global Digital Assets Equity Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of Digital Transformation Companies. The index is a global index that tracks the performance of Digital Transformation Companies. The fund will not invest in digital assets (including cryptocurrencies) (i) directly or (ii) indirectly through the use of digital asset derivatives. It also will not invest in initial coin offerings. The fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Fund
merged_description: This actively managed fund focuses on U.S. value stocks, employing a proprietary quantitative AI model for security selection. The model analyzes diverse inputs, including company fundamentals and market sentiment, to construct a portfolio typically consisting of 60 to 190 stocks demonstrating value characteristics. Holdings are weighted based on the AI model's scores, with individual security weights capped at 6%. The portfolio is generally re-evaluated and adjusted monthly according to the AI's recommendations, guided by the discretion of the fund managers.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 95% of its total assets will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is comprised of the 10 highest dividend-yielding companies in each sector, selected from the 300 largest companies by market value in the WisdomTree U.S. Dividend Index outside the financials sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
AIVL is an actively managed fund that provides exposure to US value stocks from developed markets.

AIVL invests in US value stocks by employing a proprietary, quantitative AI model that analyzes various inputs, including company fundamentals and market sentiment, to select 60-190 stocks that exhibit value characteristics. The AI model weights stocks based on their overall model scores, capped at 6% per individual security. The sub-adviser generally buys and sells stocks monthly based on the AI models updated recommendations. As an actively managed fund, the portfolio managers can analyze market and financial data to make buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion. Prior to Jan. 18, 2022, the fund was called WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Fund, which traded under the ticker DTN, and tracked the WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Index.

name: John Hancock Multifactor Consumer Staples ETF
merged_description: This fund employs a multifactor investment strategy focused on the U.S. consumer staples sector. It aims to invest at least 80% of its assets in securities that constitute its underlying index, which targets U.S. consumer staples companies with market capitalizations larger than the 1001st largest U.S. company at the time of index reconstitution, thereby focusing on the larger end of the market spectrum within the sector. Characterized as non-diversified, the fund may hold more concentrated positions than a diversified fund.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities that compose the fund's index. The index is designed to comprise securities in the consumer staples sector within the U.S. Universe whose market capitalizations are larger than that of the 1001st largest U.S. company at the time of reconstitution. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Pacer American Energy Independence ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to track a rules-based index focused on U.S. and Canadian midstream energy infrastructure companies, specifically those deriving the majority of their cash flow from activities like processing, transportation, and storage of energy products. Utilizing a proprietary methodology, the fund invests substantially all its assets in the index components, which are primarily exchange-listed equities. Its unique structure allocates portfolio weight based on legal structure, dedicating a significant majority (approximately 80%) to U.S. and Canadian midstream corporations and a smaller, fixed portion (approximately 20%) to U.S. midstream Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs), with holdings weighted by market capitalization within these segments. This approach, limiting MLP exposure to under 25%, aims to mitigate the tax complexities often associated with MLP-focused investments. The fund, which rebalances quarterly, is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: A strategy-driven exchange traded fund (ETF) that aims to offer investors exposure to U.S. and Canadian companies that generate the majority of their cash flow from midstream energy infrastructure activities.
description_etfcom: USAI focuses on US and Canadian midstream energy infrastructure companies that derive the majority of their revenue from the processing, transportation and storage of oil, natural gas and refined products. Holdings are selected by market cap and separated into two fixed-weight categories based upon legal structure: US & Canadian midstream companies (80%) and US midstream MLPs (20%). Holdings within each category are weighted by market cap. Because less than 25% of USAIs holdings are taxed as partnerships, it avoids the tax issues faced by many competitors in the MLP space. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_yahoo: The Advisor attempts to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities that make up the index. The index uses a proprietary, rules-based methodology to measure the performance of a portfolio of U.S. and Canadian exchange-listed equity securities of companies that generate a majority of their cash flow from certain qualifying "midstream" energy infrastructure activities. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the American Energy Independence Index. The Advisor attempts to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities that make up the index. The index uses a proprietary, rules-based methodology to measure the performance of a portfolio of U.S. and Canadian exchange-listed equity securities of companies that generate a majority of their cash flow from certain qualifying "midstream" energy infrastructure activities. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Merk Stagflation ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund, which was delisted with its final trading day on December 26, 2023, was conceived to provide exposure sensitive to stagflationary environments—periods marked by persistent inflation coupled with weak economic growth. It operated as a non-diversified, multi-asset fund following a rules-based index, allocating primarily to US Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities (TIPS), which constituted 55% to 85% of the portfolio. The remaining assets were dynamically distributed among ETFs representing gold, oil, and real estate, with each potentially ranging from 5% to 15% based on a trend-following methodology that adjusted weights according to price movements. The fund could also utilize a wholly-owned subsidiary, potentially investing up to 25% of its assets, to gain exposure to commodities.
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that allocates its exposure to the four funds, each of which represents a stagflation-sensitive asset class. The fund will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it generally will invest in all of the components of the index in approximately the same proportions as in the index. It also may invest in securities or other investments not included in the index, but which the Adviser believes will help the fund track the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 26, 2023. STGF introduces stagflation-sensitive investing, which aims to protect against persistent inflation during a period of weak economic growth. This multi-asset fund allocates among four ETFs: 1) Schwab US TIPS ETF (SCHP), 2) Vanguard Real Estate ETF (VNQ), 3) VanEck Merk Gold Trust (OUNZ), and 4) Invesco DB Oil Fund (DBO). Constituent weights are adjusted based on a trend-following methodology. Positive or negative price trends in gold, oil, and real estate will either increase or decrease respective index weights, resulting in 5% to 15% of the total asset allocation. The remaining 55% to 85% of the portfolio will be allocated to US TIPS. The fund expects to gain exposure to commodities by investing up to 25% of its net assets, in a wholly-owned subsidiary organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands. The index is rebalanced whenever a change in price trend in gold, oil or real estate is detected or any of these asset classes has exceeded its minimum or maximum allocations.

name: iShares MSCI KLD 400 Social ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle tracks a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index of approximately 400 U.S. companies selected for their positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It focuses on socially conscious investing by explicitly excluding firms significantly involved in specific industries like weapons manufacturing, vice products, nuclear energy, and genetic modification. Typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the underlying index components, the fund aims to provide reasonably market-like exposure despite its ESG screens. While it may exhibit some sector tilts, such as overweighting technology and underweighting financials and industrials compared to the broader market, these adjustments are managed to avoid substantially altering the overall risk profile. The underlying index undergoes periodic rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance ("ESG") characteristics.
description_etfcom:
DSI tracks a market cap-weighted index of 400 US companies deemed to have positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics, as determined by MSCI.

DSI is a viable choice for those wanting a socially conscious ETF while maintaining reasonably market-like exposure. The fund limits its holdings to firms deemed to be socially responsible, from an environmental, social, and governance (ESG) standpoint. In practice, this means explicitly excluding firms that are significantly involved with weapons manufacturing, vice products, nuclear energy, and genetic modification. Those firms that make the cut are then ranked by their performance according to those ESG criteria. While the fund excludes many familiar names, it avoids making huge sector bets. It overweights technology and underweights financials and industrials, but this doesn't substantially change the funds risk profile. The index is rebalanced during regular semi-annual and quarterly reviews. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund name was iShares MSCI KLD 400 Social ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI KLD 400 Social Index composed of U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance characteristics. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance ("ESG") characteristics.

name: Global X U.S. Infrastructure Development ETF
merged_description: This investment fund focuses on U.S. domestic infrastructure development by tracking a market-cap-weighted index of U.S.-listed companies. To qualify, companies must derive a majority of their revenue from the U.S. or have a stated business purpose related to infrastructure activities. The fund primarily invests (at least 80% of assets) in firms across the construction supply chain, including those involved in construction and engineering, production of raw materials and products, industrial transportation, and manufacturing or distribution of heavy equipment. Encompassing large-, mid-, and small-cap stocks while excluding MLPs, REITs, and BDCs, the portfolio undergoes annual rebalancing with individual security caps and floors to maintain diversification, emphasizing companies directly involved in U.S. infrastructure projects.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to domestic infrastructure development, including companies involved in construction and engineering; production of infrastructure raw materials, composites and products; industrial transportation; and producers/distributors of heavy construction equipment.
description_etfcom:
PAVE tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US-listed companies that derive the majority of their revenue from or have a stated business purpose related to infrastructure development.

PAVE`s definition of infrastructure includes many players in the construction supply chain, such as producers of raw materials, construction equipment producers, industrial transportation, and engineering services. Unlike most other infrastructure-themed funds, PAVE focuses on domestic infrastructure, as companies must be listed in and derive more than 50% of their revenue from the US. The Index may include large-, mid-, and small-cap companies weighted by market capitalization. MLPs, REITs and BDCs are excluded. For diversification purposes, PAVE undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalance with a single security cap of 3% and a single security floor of 0.3%.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, of the Indxx U.S. Infrastructure Development Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to domestic infrastructure development, including companies involved in construction and engineering; production of infrastructure raw materials, composites and products; industrial transportation; and producers/distributors of heavy construction equipment.

name: Xtrackers Net Zero Pathway Paris Aligned US Equity ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers exposure to U.S. large- and mid-capitalization companies selected for their alignment with a transition to a low-carbon economy, specifically targeting Net Zero pathways consistent with the Paris Agreement. It tracks an index that initially screens a broad U.S. equity universe, excluding firms involved in controversial activities, those failing environmental, social, and governance (ESG) norms or with poor ratings, and those negatively impacting UN Sustainable Development Goals. Remaining holdings are weighted not just by market cap, but are tilted based on factors like greenhouse gas reduction targets, climate disclosure standards, and green revenue. The portfolio is optimized to achieve a substantial initial carbon intensity reduction (50%) relative to its parent index, targeting a further 7% annual reduction, and potentially increasing exposure to high climate impact sectors. Committed to investing at least 80% of its assets in U.S. equities aligned with these climate objectives, the fund is non-diversified and rebalances semi-annually.
description_original: The index is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that meet certain ESG criteria. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of issuers incorporated in the United States and as considered by the Advisor to be aligned with the Paris Agreement and consistent with the Net Zero Investment Framework. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: USNZ offers an enhanced climate approach to the US large- and mid-cap space by tracking an index geared toward a low-carbon economy transition. The index initially screens out stocks from the Solactive GBS United States Large & Mid Cap Index (parent index), that are involved in controversial business activities. In addition, firms that fail to observe established norms with respect to environment, human rights, corruption, and labor rights, as well as companies with an ISS ESG Corporate Rating of D- and a negative impact on UN Sustainable Development Goals are also removed. Holdings are initially weighted by market-cap. Weights are then tilted based on: a) greenhouse gas emissions reduction targets, b) climate disclosure standards, and c) green revenue. Lastly, the portfolio is optimized to reduce carbon intensity by 50% with a target reduction of 7% year-over-year, and increased exposure to high climate impact sectors relative to its parent index. The index rebalances semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive ISS ESG United States Net Zero Pathway Enhanced Index. The index is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that meet certain ESG criteria. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of issuers incorporated in the United States and as considered by the Advisor to be aligned with the Paris Agreement and consistent with the Net Zero Investment Framework. It is non-diversified.

name: SPDR S&P Global Natural Resources ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides exposure to the global natural resources sector by tracking an index composed of 90 of the largest publicly-traded companies involved in natural resources and commodities businesses worldwide. Its core strategy involves selecting the top 30 firms by market capitalization from each of three key sectors – agriculture, energy, and metals & mining – ensuring constituents are listed on developed market exchanges. A distinctive feature is its approach to maintain balanced exposure across these three sectors, weighting each at approximately one-third of the portfolio. Within each sector, however, individual securities are weighted by market capitalization, subject to constraints capping individual stock weights at 5%, US holdings at 40%, and emerging market stocks at 15%. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities and depositary receipts comprising its underlying index, which rebalances annually.
description_original: The SPDR S&P Global Natural Resources ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Natural Resources Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to a number of the largest market cap securities in three natural resources sectors - agriculture, energy, and metals and miningMaximum weight of each sub-index is capped at one-third of the total weight of the Index
description_etfcom:
GNR tracks an index of global companies in natural resources and/or commodity businesses.

GNR offers exposure to global natural resources companies including those engaged in commodities businesses. The fund equally-weights S&P's three natural resources subindexes to evenly split weight between the metals & mining, agriculture, and energy sectors. Eligible securities will be ranked according to market cap and the top 30 companies from each subindex will be included for a total of 90 index constituents. These stocks must be listed on a developed market exchange. Selected securities will then be weighted by market-cap within each buckets, subject to constraints such that US stocks are capped at 40% and emerging market stocks are capped at 15%. In addition, no individual security must have a weight greater than 5%. The index rebalancing occurs annually.
description_yahoo: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is comprised of 90 of the largest U.S. and foreign publicly-traded companies, based on market capitalization, in natural resources and commodities businesses that meet certain investability requirements.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Natural Resources Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is comprised of 90 of the largest U.S. and foreign publicly-traded companies, based on market capitalization, in natural resources and commodities businesses that meet certain investability requirements.

name: Invesco KBW Property & Casualty Insurance ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to replicate the performance of a modified market-cap-weighted index representing companies primarily involved in the U.S. property and casualty (P&C) insurance sector. It concentrates its portfolio by generally investing at least 90% of its assets in securities within this specific index, which notably includes reinsurance firms alongside traditional P&C insurers. By design, the fund avoids broad exposure to the overall insurance industry, underweighting segments like life & health insurance and large brokerage conglomerates, which can contribute to a tilt towards smaller capitalization companies compared to the broader sector. The underlying index undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution, and the fund itself is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index designed to track the performance of companies primarily engaged in U.S. property and casualty insurance activities, as determined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
KBWP tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index focused exclusively on property & casualty insurance companies in the US.

KBWP doesn't attempt to provide broad-market exposure to the US Insurance sector. Instead, the fund focuses specifically on property & casualty insurance firms. Its holdings also have a significant position in reinsurance companies. To curate the portfolio, an index committee determines the fund constituents and a modified market-cap weighting is put into use. Notably, the portfolio underweights mega-cap insurance brokers, life & health insurance firms and other huge conglomerates, tilting the portfolio small. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted on a quarterly basis.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the KBW Nasdaq Property & Casualty IndexTM (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index designed to track the performance of companies primarily engaged in U.S. property and casualty insurance activities, as determined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.

name: LeaderShares Activist Leaders ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital growth by investing primarily in U.S.-listed equity securities, focusing on companies with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. Its core strategy involves identifying companies targeted by shareholder activists; specifically, it invests in firms where individuals identified as effective "Activist Leaders" have acquired significant positions, as evidenced by public Schedule 13D filings. These activists are selected using a quantitative methodology that evaluates their historical effectiveness. The fund dynamically manages its portfolio by tracking the ongoing investment activities of these selected activists based on their filings, a process expected to result in high portfolio turnover. Consequently, the fund's holdings may become concentrated in particular sectors or industries, and it may also utilize derivatives like options and swaps for hedging purposes or to help achieve its investment objective.
description_original: The fund will be invested in equity securities of companies listed on a U.S. exchange with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. It may focus its investments in a particular sector, industry or group of industries. The fund may utilize derivatives, such as equity options and total return swap agreements, to seek to achieve its objective and for hedging purposes.
description_etfcom:
ACTV actively selects US equity securities that are the target of shareholder activism.

ACTV aims to generate long-term capital growth by focusing on all-cap equity securities of companies whose shares have been acquired by individuals identified as Activist Leaders. The SEC requires anyone acquiring more than 5% of a companys shares, with activist intent, to file a Schedule 13D. The funds adviser applies a quantitative methodology to the 13D filings to identify and rate Activist Leaders based upon their effectiveness of achieving the stated objective and creation of positive returns in such positions. Once the Activist Leaders are selected, the funds adviser adds and removes constituents to the portfolio by following these investors activities through the 13D filings. The list of Activist Leaders will change over time. With this, ACTVs investors should anticipate frequent trading resulting in high portfolio turnover. In addition, the fund can become concentrated in a particular sector, industry or group.
description_yahoo: The fund will be invested in equity securities of companies listed on a U.S. exchange with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. It may focus its investments in a particular sector, industry or group of industries.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to generate long-term capital growth. The fund will be invested in equity securities of companies listed on a U.S. exchange with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. It may focus its investments in a particular sector, industry or group of industries.

name: Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta Paris-Aligned U.S. Large Cap Equity ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle targeted U.S. large-capitalization equities by combining a multi-factor strategy with environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria aligned with the Paris Climate Agreement's carbon reduction objectives. It sought exposure across four factors—value, momentum, quality, and low volatility—typically weighting these components equally within its index-tracking approach. The underlying index construction involved screening out companies from controversial sectors like weapons, tobacco, and fossil fuels, and those non-compliant with UN Global Compact principles, before adjusting final security weights based on factor exposures, greenhouse gas emission intensity, and low carbon impact targets. This passively managed fund rebalanced quarterly but has since been delisted, with its final trading day occurring on January 12, 2024.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its assets in securities included in its underlying index, in depositary receipts representing securities included in its underlying index and in underlying stocks in respect of depositary receipts included in its underlying index. The index is designed to deliver exposure to equity securities of large capitalization U.S. issuers.
description_etfcom:
GPAL tracks an index of tier-weighted US large-cap stocks comprising four factor sub-indices: value, momentum, quality, and low volatility. Holdings are screened and reweighted based on ESG criteria in line with the Paris Climate Agreements carbon reduction goals.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 12, 2024. GPAL is a passively managed fund that combines Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta strategy with ESG screens that are aligned with the goals of the Paris Climate Agreement, that is to combat climate change and its long-term effects. To construct the portfolio, the fund initially narrows down its reference index (Solactive US Large Cap Index) by removing companies involved in controversial industries such as weapons, tobacco, and fossil fuels. In addition, firms that are deemed non-compliant with the UN Global Compact principles are also excluded. Remaining securities are assigned with a factor score in order to create four sub-indices focusing on: value, momentum, quality, and low volatility. These four sub-indices are then combined in equal weights to form the Factor Diversity Portfolio. Final security weights are adjusted in accordance with the funds target greenhouse gas emission intensity, low carbon impact, and overall factor exposures. The index rebalances quarterly.

name: Xtrackers MSCI USA Climate Action Equity ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified, passively managed fund aims to track the performance of an index comprising US large and mid-capitalization companies recognized as leaders within their sectors for taking action related to the climate transition. Its underlying index starts with a broad US equity universe, then screens out companies involved in controversial activities, those non-compliant with established global norms (including UN Global Compact principles and SBTi goals), and the bottom quartile performers on climate risk management within each sector. From the eligible pool, the index selects the top 50% of companies per sector based on a positive assessment of climate-related factors such as science-based targets, greenhouse gas intensity, emissions track record, and green business revenue. This market-cap weighted index is rebalanced semi-annually, and the fund commits to investing at least 80% of its total assets in these constituent securities.
description_original: The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index, which is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that the underlying index’s methodology assesses as leading their sector peers in taking action relating to a climate transition. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: USCA provides a climate-friendly approach to investing in the US large- and mid-cap space. The fund tracks an index screened toward stocks considered leaders in taking actions relating to climate transition. The fund drafts its selection universe from the MSCI USA Index, removing those involved in controversial business activities. The fund also screens out firms that are non-compliant with norms on the environment, human rights, governance, and carbon reduction goals approved by the United Nations Global Compact, and other SBTi. A screen for companies with bleak climate risk management removes the bottom quarter from each sector. The remaining stocks undergo a security-level assessment based on: (i) science-based target initiative, (ii) greenhouse gas intensity, (iii) emission track record, and (iv) green business revenue. Based on the assessment, the top 50% within each sector are selected. The index is market cap-weighted and rebalances on a semi-annual basis.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the MSCI USA Climate Action Index. The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index, which is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that the underlying index’s methodology assesses as leading their sector peers in taking action relating to a climate transition. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Global Water ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides focused exposure to the global water market by investing primarily in companies that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries. It seeks to track the investment results of the NASDAQ OMX Global Water Index, which employs a liquidity-weighted methodology and includes global exchange-listed securities (including ADRs and GDRs) from the US, developed, and emerging markets, with a focus on large- to mid-cap firms. Generally investing at least 90% of its assets in index components using full replication, the fund features a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio. A unique characteristic is its exclusive inclusion of companies identified as participating in the 'Green Economy' by SustainableBusiness.com LLC, with the underlying index undergoing quarterly rebalancing and annual reconstitution.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that are based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of securities of global exchange-listed companies located in the United States, as well as developed and emerging markets throughout the world, that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PIO tracks a liquidity-weighted index of global companies that create products to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries.
