While holdings may include global stocks, a significant portion is expected to be directed toward the US and Europe. The fund may enter lending transactions.
description_yahoo: Under normal circumstances, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in publicly listed companies that derive at least 50% of revenues from products or services related to GLP-1 and the treatment of cardiovascular diseases and/or metabolic diseases, as defined by the Centers for Diseases Control and Preventions. The fund generally is expected to consist of more than 15 companies but not more than 100 companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term growth of capital. Under normal circumstances, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, which include borrowings for investment purposes, in publicly listed companies that derive at least 50% of revenues from products or services related to GLP-1 and the treatment of cardiovascular diseases and/or metabolic diseases, as defined by the Centers for Diseases Control and Preventions. The fund generally is expected to consist of more than 15 companies but not more than 100 companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Nasdaq Semiconductor ETF
merged_description: This investment fund provides exposure to the U.S. semiconductor sector by primarily investing in securities selected for high liquidity and weighted according to multiple factors. It targets the 30 most liquid U.S. semiconductor stocks, identified based on their average daily trading volume over three months. These holdings are then weighted using a composite score derived from value (cash flow to price), volatility (trailing one-year), and growth (average historical price returns) characteristics. To manage concentration, weighting caps are applied, limiting individual security allocations, while the fund commits at least 90% of its net assets to these components. The underlying strategy involves annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing, and the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks and depository receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the semiconductor sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and weighted based upon their cumulative score on three investing factors: volatility, value and growth. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FTXL tracks an index of highly liquid semiconductor stocks weighted according to various factors. While many funds perform a basic liquidity screen as part of their index construction and rebalancing, FTXL is noteworthy because it goes beyond the basic screen and uses liquidity selection. The 30 most liquid semiconductor stocks in the US are chosen for inclusion in the index as determined by the average daily traded volume over three months. The securities are then ranked and weighed according to value, volatility, and growth factors. Value is measured using a cash flow to price metric. The trailing one- year volatility provides another factor. Growth is considered using the average of the 3, 6, 9, and 12-month price return. The five highest ranking securities will be capped at 8% and the remaining securities will be capped at 4%. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the semiconductor sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and ranking. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of the Nasdaq US Smart Semiconductor TM Index. The fund invests at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the semiconductor sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and ranking. It is non-diversified.

name: iShares Select Dividend ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle focuses on providing exposure to U.S. companies characterized by relatively high and sustainable dividend payments. It tracks an index comprising approximately 100 U.S. stocks, selected from a broad market-cap universe primarily based on dividend yield. The index methodology incorporates robust sustainability screens, evaluating factors like five-year dividend growth, payout ratios, and payment history to favor companies with consistent and potentially rising dividends. Selected securities, which can include REITs, are then dividend-weighted. The fund aims to invest at least 80% of its assets in these index components or economically similar investments, often resulting in exposure that tilts towards smaller firms compared to the broader market.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the U.S.'s leading stocks by dividend yield.
description_etfcom:
DVY tracks a dividend-weighted index of US companies. The index selects roughly 100 stocks based on dividend yield from a broad market-cap universe.

DVY offers exposure to the US high-dividend space that skews toward smaller firms paying consistent dividends. The fund's dividend yield is, in theory at least, sustainable: DVY's methodology has a robust sustainability screen, designed to ensure companies pay steady and rising dividends by using five-year dividend growth, payout ratio, and payment history criteria. REITs are allowed, and stocks that make the cut are dividend-weighted.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Dividend Index composed of relatively high dividend paying U.S. equities. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the U.S.'s leading stocks by dividend yield.

name: Schwab Crypto Thematic ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund passively seeks to track the total return of an index designed to offer global exposure to companies poised to benefit from the development or utilization of cryptocurrencies, digital assets, and blockchain technology. It targets firms involved in activities such as validating consensus mechanisms, enabling crypto-based transactions, or developing blockchain applications. Crucially, the fund does not invest directly in cryptocurrencies or digital assets. Company selection and weighting rely significantly on a proprietary natural language processing (NLP) algorithm that assesses thematic relevance based on regulatory and patent filings, alongside liquidity and investability screens. The resulting portfolio typically holds up to 50 global equities, weighted by thematic relevance, and is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_original: The fund will not invest in cryptocurrency or digital assets directly. The investment adviser typically seeks to track the total return of the index by replicating the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
STCE tracks an index of globally listed companies that enable the cryptocurrency ecosystem. The fund selects and weights companies based on thematic relevance through a proprietary NLP algorithm.

STCE is passively managed to hold global equities, including depositary receipts, of companies involved in validating consensus mechanisms for crypto or other digital assets, enabling the use of crypto or other digital assets to buy or sell goods and services, and applications of blockchain and other distributed ledger technology. The index determines relevance and exposure to the theme by applying a proprietary natural language processing (NLP) algorithm. Each company is scored for thematic relevance based on regulatory and patent filings. Eligible companies also undergo liquidity and investability screens and are reviewed to ensure positive exposure to the theme. The remaining companies are ranked by a composite of their relevance score and weight in the previous rebalancing. The resulting portfolio of up to 50 companies is also weighted based on thematic relevance, subject to minimum and maximum weight constraints. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the total return of the Schwab Crypto Thematic Index that is designed to deliver global exposure to companies that may benefit from the development or utilization of cryptocurrencies (including bitcoin) and other digital assets, and the business activities connected to blockchain and other distributed ledger technology. The fund will not invest in cryptocurrency or digital assets directly. The investment adviser typically seeks to track the total return of the index by replicating the index. It is non-diversified.

name: FlexShares Morningstar Global Upstream Natural Resources Index Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to mirror the performance of a global index targeting upstream natural resources companies across both developed and emerging markets. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent equity securities, including ADRs and GDRs. The fund offers exposure not only to traditional natural resource sectors like energy, agriculture, metals, timber, and water but also uniquely incorporates related upstream businesses such as containers and packaging, paper and forest products, and associated commercial services. Its underlying index uses a proprietary methodology to select approximately 120 stocks, applying regional and sector weighting caps to promote broader diversification within the theme and reduce concentration in dominant names. Although designed for breadth within its specific market focus, the fund is classified as non-diversified and undergoes semi-annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The index reflects the performance of a selection of equity securities that are traded in or are issued by companies classiified as developed or emerging markets, as determined by the index provider pursuant to its index methodology. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GUNR tracks an index of global companies that operate, manage or produce natural resources in energy, agriculture, metals, timber or water.

GUNR approaches the global natural resources industry with a few twists. The fund provides exposure in traditional natural resources industries, particularly in energy, agriculture, precious or industrial metals, timber and water. Notably, GUNR extends its coverage to include 'upstream' businesses like containers and packaging, commercial services, and paper and forest products. To curate the portfolio, the funds underlying index selects 120 stocks using a proprietary methodology. It then caps weightings at the regional and sector level, minimizing the impact of firms of more popular names in the portfolio. Overall, GUNR has a broad and diverse take on a market that lends itself to concentration. The index is reconstituted semi-annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to the performance of a selection of equity securities that are traded in or are issued by companies classified as developed or emerging markets, as determined by the index provider pursuant to its index methodology. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Morningstar® Global Upstream Natural Resources IndexSM. The index is designed to the performance of a selection of equity securities that are traded in or are issued by companies classified as developed or emerging markets, as determined by the index provider pursuant to its index methodology. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index.

name: SPDR Bloomberg SASB Emerging Markets ESG Select ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund provided exposure to large- and mid-cap emerging market equities selected according to specific environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria, although it has since been delisted (last trading day April 11, 2023). Its core strategy involved tracking an index by first applying exclusionary screens to remove companies linked to controversial weapons, tobacco, thermal coal, and other specified activities. Remaining securities were evaluated using an "R-Factor" score, assessing financially material ESG issues and corporate governance practices. The final portfolio composition, which invested at least 80% of its assets in index securities or related depositary receipts, was quantitatively optimized to maximize the *overall* fund's R-Factor score rather than strictly holding the highest-rated individual stocks, and it underwent quarterly rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
REMG tracks an index of large- and mid-cap stocks from the emerging markets, that exhibit environmental, social, and governance characteristics.

The fund is delisted The last day of trading on an exchange is April 11, 2023. REMG provides broad exposure to the large- and mid-cap emerging markets space utilizing an ESG overlay. The selection process begins with an exclusionary screen which removes companies involved in and/or derive significant revenue from: Extreme Event Controversies, Controversial Weapons, UN Global Compact Violations, Civilian Firearms, Thermal Coal Extraction, and Tobacco. Remaining securities are each assigned an R-Factor score, which is calculated based on two components: 1) the ESG component which seeks to identify ESG issues that are financially material to a firm, and 2) the corporate governance component which addresses topics such as shareholder rights, board independence, and executive compensation. The final selection and weighting is determined through a quantitative process designed to maximize the funds overall R-Factor score, thus, resulting in a portfolio that does not necessarily hold the highest-scored securities. The index rebalances quarterly.

name: iShares Evolved U.S. Technology ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle offers exposure to U.S. companies across large, mid, and small capitalizations identified as having technology exposure via a proprietary, forward-looking classification system. Investing at least 80% of its assets in U.S. listed common stock, it focuses on companies within the "Technology Evolved Sector"—those exhibiting economic characteristics historically correlated with traditional technology firms, including related infrastructure and security players. Utilizing data science and text analysis of public filings, this unique methodology allows companies to potentially span multiple evolved sectors, differing from traditional single-sector assignments. Holdings are weighted by market capitalization, targeting increased exposure to firms scoring highly on technological capabilities, revenues, and production. As a non-diversified fund employing this distinct classification approach, which is reviewed quarterly, its investment returns may not directly mirror those of traditional technology sector benchmarks.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in U.S. listed common stock of large-, mid- and small-capitalization technology companies. It will hold common stock of those companies that fall into the Technology Evolved Sector which have economic characteristics that have been historically correlated with companies traditionally defined as technology companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: IETC is part of an iShares sector suite that redefines the US market into evolved sectors by using text analysis and data science to group similar firms. This forward-looking, proprietary classification system based on public filings, allows a company to be classified into multiple sectors rather than being solely assigned to a single sector. The fund provides exposure to the information technology evolved sector, including tech-related firms in the infrastructure and security industries. Though these companies have economic characteristics correlated to the traditional IT sector, the fund may not provide the same investment returns. Holdings are weighted by market cap, targeting an increased exposure to companies scoring highly on technological capabilities, revenues, and production in the US and select global markets. Sectors are reviewed quarterly and may change over time. Prior to Dec. 1, 2022, the fund name was iShares Evolved US Technology ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide access to U.S. companies with technology exposure, as classified using a proprietary classification system. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in U.S. listed common stock of large-, mid- and small-capitalization technology companies. It will hold common stock of those companies that fall into the Technology Evolved Sector which have economic characteristics that have been historically correlated with companies traditionally defined as technology companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Xtrackers MSCI USA ESG Leaders Equity ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle focuses on U.S. large- and mid-capitalization companies selected for their strong environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It aims to track a market-cap weighted index composed of these ESG leaders by investing directly in the component securities, generally mirroring their index weightings. The strategy involves screening potential investments using specific ESG rating methodologies, automatically excluding companies involved in severe business controversies or operating in industries such as alcohol, tobacco, gambling, weapons, and nuclear power. During periodic rebalancing, the portfolio construction prioritizes companies with higher ESG ratings and larger market capitalizations within each sector, typically aiming to represent about half the available sector market cap. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in U.S. equities and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The index consists of large- and medium-capitalization companies in the U.S. market. The fund invests directly in the component securities of the index in substantially the same weightings in which they are represented in the index. It will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of issuers incorporated in the United States.
description_etfcom:
USSG tracks a market cap-weighted index of US large- and mid-cap stocks, screened for environmental, social, and governance characteristics.

USSG holds a basket of companies that score highly for environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors. The funds index uses MSCIs ESG rating methodology to assign a score to all US large- and mid-cap stocks. The index automatically screens out companies involved in severe business controversies as well as those companies engaged in alcohol, tobacco, gambling, weapons and nuclear power. The fund may include US companies outside the index as long as it has a BB MSCI ESG Rating and an MSCI ESG Controversies Score of 3 or above. At triannual rebalance, the fund selects about half the available market cap in each sector, emphasizing higher ESG ratings, larger firms, and current constituents. Prior to Feb. 3, 2025, the fund was named Xtrackers MSCI USA ESG Leaders Equity ETF, and tracked MSCI USA ESG Leaders Index.

name: Invesco DWA Healthcare Momentum ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund invests primarily in U.S. healthcare companies demonstrating powerful relative strength, commonly known as price momentum. It aims to track an underlying index composed of at least 30 such securities, selected and weighted based on these momentum characteristics, by investing at least 90% of its assets in the index's components using a full replication strategy. Consequently, the fund often presents a distinct, growth-focused profile compared to traditional healthcare benchmarks, typically emphasizing biotechnology and research sectors, tilting towards smaller companies, and exhibiting higher risk. The portfolio undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the healthcare sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_etfcom:
PTH tracks an index of U.S. healthcare firms selected and weighted by price momentum.

PTH provides an alternate take on US healthcare firms, with a lot of emphasis on the biotech and research sector compared to our more pharma and provider-focused neutral benchmark. PTH has been around for a while but changed indexes in 2014 to adopt a momentum-weighted Dorsey-Wright relative strength index. This has contributed to the fund's sharp pivot away from neutral segment exposure toward growth sectors. Unsurprisingly, the fund tilts small and carries considerably more risk. The fund selects the top, at least 30 stocks, with the highest momentum scores in the healthcare space. The fund uses a full replication indexing strategy. Overall, PTH offers a different, growth-focused take on healthcare. Investors should consider all-in costs of holding the fund. The fund is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco DWA Healthcare Momentum ETF.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Healthcare Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the healthcare sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.

name: John Hancock Multifactor Health Care ETF
merged_description: This investment fund focuses on the U.S. healthcare sector by tracking an index designed to apply a multifactor approach. Typically investing at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that make up its index, the fund operates as a non-diversified portfolio.

name: InfraCap MLP ETF
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks total return primarily by investing in equity securities of energy infrastructure Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs). Under normal conditions, it invests at least 80% of its assets (plus any borrowings) in this sector, holding a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio typically comprising 25-50 MLPs involved in collecting, processing, storing, or transporting energy products. The fund's strategy emphasizes generating significant cash distributions, which are paid out monthly—a distinct feature compared to typical quarterly payouts in the space. To potentially enhance income and manage risk, the managers may employ leverage, shorting, and options strategies. Structurally, it operates as a C-corporation, paying taxes at the fund level, which generally allows distributions to shareholders to be tax-deferred.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of MLPs in the energy infrastructure sector. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
AMZA is a complex, actively managed fund that invests in midstream MLPs that collect, process, store, or transport energy products. Structured as a C-corporation, the ETF pays taxes at the fund level.

AMZA stands out in the MLP space for its active management and monthly distribution frequency since most other MLP ETFs track indices and pay quarterly distributions. The funds active managers, Infrastructure Capital Advisors, intend to hold a concentrated portfolio of 25-50 MLPs, and expect cash distributions to comprise a significant portion of the funds total return. In addition, the fund employs leverage, shorting, and options strategies in an effort to enhance income and manage risk. Structured as a C-corporation, AMZA pays corporate taxes on gains, with the upside that its distributions are generally tax-deferred.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks total return primarily through investments in equity securities of publicly traded master limited partnerships and limited liability companies taxed as partnerships ("MLPs"). name: iShares Inflation Hedged High Yield Bond ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to lessen the impact of inflation on a portfolio primarily composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, high-yield corporate bonds by tracking a specialized index. Its strategy involves holding a core position in high-yield bonds, often achieved through an underlying ETF, complemented by an overlay of inflation swap contracts with varying maturities. Through these swaps, the fund exchanges fixed payments received from its bond holdings for floating payments tied to inflation rates, thereby hedging against *expected* inflation rather than the actual rate itself. Consequently, its performance relative to unhedged high-yield bonds largely depends on whether inflation exceeds market expectations. The fund commits to investing at least 80% of its assets in its index components, is classified as non-diversified, and operates as a commodity pool due to its use of derivatives like swaps, which are rebalanced daily and restructured monthly.
description_original: The underlying index is designed to minimize the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, high yield corporate bonds. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in component securities and instruments in the fund’s underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: HYGI follows an index that combines a long position in iShares iBoxx USD High Yield Corporate Bond ETF (HYG) with an overlay of inflation swaps. The fund includes a fixed number of HYGs shares and a series of up to 10 inflation swap contracts with different maturities, intended to hedge the portfolios inflation risk at key points on the yield curve. By entering these swaps, the fund agrees to give up a portion of the fixed payments it receives from HYGs bond portfolio in exchange for floating payments tied to the inflation rate. Since inflation is already priced into the market for bonds, the fund effectively hedges inflation expectations rather than the inflation rate itself. Thus, even if inflation rises, HYGI will underperform HYG if the rise is less than expected, and will outperform (before costs) when inflation exceeds expectations. The weights of the swaps are rebalanced daily and restructured monthly. Due to the use of derivatives, the fund is registered as a commodity pool.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the BlackRock Inflation Hedged High Yield Bond Index designed to mitigate the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, high yield corporate bonds. The underlying index is designed to minimize the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, high yield corporate bonds. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in component securities and instruments in the fund’s underlying index. It is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily Electric and Autonomous Vehicles Bull 2X Shares
merged_description: This investment fund aims to deliver 200% of the daily performance, before fees and expenses, of an index tracking US-listed electric and autonomous vehicle companies. The underlying index focuses on firms deriving significant revenue from this sector, including manufacturers, enablers, and technology developers, subject to market capitalization and liquidity requirements. Index constituents are liquidity-weighted with individual caps and undergo quarterly rebalancing and annual reconstitution. To achieve its leveraged objective, the fund primarily invests (at least 80% of net assets) in financial instruments like swap agreements, index securities, and related ETFs. As a non-diversified fund providing 2x daily leverage that resets each day, it is intended for short-term exposure and should not be expected to provide two times the index return over periods longer than a single day.
description_original: The index is designed to track the performance of electric and autonomous vehicles companies. The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
EVAV tracks 2x the daily price movements of a liquidity-weighted index of US-listed electric and autonomous vehicles companies.

EVAV provides daily 2x exposure to an index of companies in the autonomous electric vehicles industry. The fund will comprise those that derive at least 50% of their revenue from engagements in specified sub-themes, such as manufacturers, enablers, and software and technology developers. Besides liquidity and tradability requirements, eligible securities must be listed on a US exchange, and have a market-cap of at least 500 million USD. The largest 25 pure-play companies will comprise the index, with quasi-play firms completing the roster if few pure-plays qualify. Selected constituents will then be assigned a weighting in accordance with their 6-month average daily value traded, with individual capping at 8%. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually. As a leveraged product with 2x factor that resets daily, EVAV is not a buy-and-hold investment and should not be expected to provide index leverage return greater than a one day period.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to track the performance of electric and autonomous vehicles companies. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 200% of the daily performance of the Indxx US Electric and Autonomous Vehicles Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 2X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. It is non-diversified.

name: Xtrackers S&P SmallCap 600 ESG ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focused on U.S. small-cap stocks, selecting constituents from the S&P SmallCap 600 Index based on specific environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. Its underlying index aimed to represent 75% of the float-adjusted market capitalization within each GICS industry group of the parent index, primarily using ESG scores for selection. The methodology involved several exclusionary screens, removing companies engaged in tobacco, weapons, and thermal coal businesses, those with low Global Compact scores or flagged ESG controversies, and firms ranking in the bottom 25% for ESG scores within their respective industry groups. Selected companies were market-cap weighted and rebalanced annually, with the fund investing at least 80% of its assets in these components while being classified as non-diversified. Notably, this security has been delisted, ceasing trading on exchanges after May 24, 2024.
description_original: The index seeks to target 75% of the float market capitalization (i.e., the amount of stock which is available for trading by the general public) of each Global Industry Classification Standard Industry Group (“GICS Industry Group”) within the S&P SmallCap 600 Index, using an ESG score as the defining characteristic. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities of the index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is May 24, 2024. SMLE selects securities from the S&P SmallCap 600 Index that meet ESG screens, while maintaining similar risk and return as the index. Using various exclusionary screens, the fund eliminates companies: (1) involved in tobacco, weapons, and thermal coal, (2) those with Global Compact (GC) scores ranked in the bottom 5% of all UNGC-scored companies globally, (3) firms with ESG risks flagged by released Media and Stakeholder Analysis (MSA), and (4) those with S&P DJI ESG scores within the bottom 25% from each GICS industry group. Remaining companies are then ranked in descending order of their S&P DJI ESG scores, selecting securities until 75% of each industry groups market-cap is reached. Constituents are weighted by market-cap and rebalanced annually. Overall, SMLEs ESG take on the US small-cap stocks makes it a great complement to SNPE and MIDE which are Xtrackers ESG view on the US total market and midcaps, respectively.
description_yahoo: The index seeks to target 75% of the float-adjusted market capitalization (i.e., the amount of stock that is available for trading by the general public) of each GICS Industry Group within the S&P SmallCap 600 Index, using the ESG scores assigned to the companies in the Eligible Universe by the index provider as the determining factor. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities of the index.

name: WisdomTree Growth Leaders Fund
merged_description: This fund focused on providing exposure to global growth companies, across various sectors, that generated revenue from modern platforms or digital marketplaces, such as those involved in payments, social networking, gaming, and content development. It specifically targeted companies demonstrating at least 7% compound annual revenue growth over the trailing three years. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in components mirroring its underlying index, the fund was non-diversified. The index methodology utilized a blend of equal and market-cap weighting, applied issuer caps, limited exposure to non-US and Chinese companies, incorporated adjustments based on trading volume, and was reconstituted annually. Importantly, this fund has been closed and delisted, with its final day of trading occurring on October 20, 2023.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of companies which have experienced revenue growth and generate revenue from business lines active in modern platforms or digital marketplaces based upon several factors. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20, 2023. The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20, 2023. PLAT provides exposure to growth companies from all sectors with business lines active in modern platforms or digital marketplaces. Common eligible businesses may include: payment, social networking, social gaming, and content and development. The fund considers growth companies as those with at least 7% compound annual revenue growth over the trailing three years. The index is weighted by the securities average equal and market weights, capped at 9% per issuer. Then, a volume factor adjustment is implemented wherein stocks with lower trading volume are underweighted and the reduction in weight is reallocated pro rata among the other securities. Additionally, non-US issuers are capped at 12% and Chinese issuers are capped at 5%. The Index is reconstituted and rebalanced annually. Prior to August 1, 2020, PLAT was named the WisdomTree Modern Tech Platforms Fund.

name: KraneShares Trust
merged_description: This fund seeks long-term capital growth by investing primarily in the global "blue economy," focusing on companies whose economic activities positively impact ocean sustainability. Under normal market conditions, it allocates at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings) to these ocean-related companies, which can span diverse sectors such as water infrastructure, waste management, renewable energy, and logistics. Utilizing proprietary analysis, the strategy identifies a concentrated portfolio of 30-50 companies of various sizes and industries, categorized as Ocean Leaders, Solutions, or Improvers, with a prioritization on those actively improving their ocean impact. The fund believes this focus on ocean sustainability offers potential for above-average growth, especially as ESG factors become increasingly significant to investors, and retains the flexibility to divest from companies not showing sufficient progress. This investment vehicle is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in Ocean Related Companies. The Sub-Adviser believes that investing in Ocean Related Companies offers the potential for above-average long-term growth, especially if environmental, social and corporate governance (“ESG”) factors continue to become more consequential to investors. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: KSEA aims to achieve long-term growth by investing in companies with economic activities positively impacting the ocean or operating within the blue economy. This includes sectors such as water infrastructure, waste management, renewable energy, and logistics, with a global focus. The fund categorizes its investments into three groups: Ocean Leaders, Ocean Solutions and Ocean Improvers. These are firms with strong ocean sustainability practices, offering products or services addressing sustainable ocean impact, and those actively working to reduce their impact on the ocean and its resources respectively. Ocean Improvers are prioritized among the three. The funds selection process utilizes proprietary analysis methods to identify 30-50 companies of any size and industry that align with the investment criteria. Additionally, KSEA retains the option to divest from companies that fail to show progress in terms of ocean sustainability or if better investment opportunities arise.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The Sub-Adviser believes that investing in Ocean Related Companies offers the potential for above-average long-term growth, especially if environmental, social and corporate governance (“ESG”) factors continue to become more consequential to investors. The fund is non-diversified.

name: YieldMax NFLX Option Income Strategy ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund primarily seeks to generate monthly income, with a secondary objective of providing exposure to the share price movements of a specific underlying stock, albeit with a cap on potential upside gains. It implements a synthetic covered call strategy using options, creating synthetic long exposure to the stock while simultaneously writing short-term, out-of-the-money call options against it to generate income. This structure limits participation in the underlying stock's potential appreciation. Importantly, the fund does not hold the actual stock, passing no dividends to investors, but it does expose them to the full downside risk. US Treasurys serve as collateral, and the fund adheres to its strategy consistently, irrespective of market conditions, without adopting temporary defensive measures.
description_original: The fund will seek to employ its investment strategy as it relates to NFLX regardless of whether there are periods adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not seek to take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: NFLY aims to generate monthly income while providing exposure to the price returns of Netflix stock (NFLX), subject to a cap on potential gains. The fund utilizes a synthetic covered call strategy via standardized exchange-traded and FLEX options, which consists of three elements: i) synthetic long exposure, ii) covered call writing, and iii) US Treasurys for collateral. The synthetic long exposure seeks to replicate the price movements of NFLX by purchasing and selling at-the-money calls and puts that have one- to six-month terms. To generate income, the fund writes call options with an expiration of one month or less and a strike price of approximately 0%-15% above NFLXs current share price. This limits participation in potential gains if NFLX shares increase in value. The short put positions fully expose investors to the downside of the stock. Note: the fund does not invest directly in Netflix stocks. Thus, investors are not entitled to any NFLX dividends.
description_yahoo: The fund will employ its investment strategy as it relates to NFLX regardless of whether there are periods of adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks current income; the secondary investment objective is to seek exposure to the share price of the common stock of Netflix, Inc., subject to a limit on potential investment gains. The fund will employ its investment strategy as it relates to NFLX regardless of whether there are periods of adverse market, economic, or other conditions and will not take temporary defensive positions during such periods. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Dynamic Leisure and Entertainment ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund focuses on the U.S. leisure and entertainment sector by tracking a specialized index. Instead of using traditional market-cap weighting, it employs a quantitative, multi-factor methodology to select approximately 30 stocks based on criteria like price and earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. Its underlying index utilizes a tiered equal-weighting approach, aiming to reduce concentration in mega-cap stocks and provide more even exposure across company sizes within the sector, including holdings like restaurant chains often excluded elsewhere. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities comprising this index, is classified as non-diversified, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying intellidex. The underlying intellidex was composed of common stocks of U.S. leisure and entertainment companies. These companies are engaged principally in the design, production or distribution of goods or services in the leisure and entertainment industries. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
PEJ tracks a multi-factor, tiered equal-weighted index of US entertainment and leisure industry stocks.

PEJ selects US stocks using quant screens rather than delivering a market-cap-weighted basket that reflects the industry. Its stock selection process is a bit opaque beyond the broad descriptions of its screens: fundamental, timeliness, valuation and risk. Specifically, stocks are evaluated based on five factors: price momentum, earnings momentum, quality, management action, and value. PEJ holds about 30 stocks, including restaurant chains, which are excluded from other funds in the leisure & entertainment segment. The indexs tier weighting reduces concentrations in mega-caps and evenly weights the group of companies across size. The fund and the index are rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly in February, May, August and November. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco Dynamic Leisure & Entertainment ETF.

name: First Trust Nasdaq Bank ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund invests at least 90% of its assets in the common stocks and depository receipts comprising its underlying index, focusing on the U.S. banking sector. It specifically targets the 30 most liquid U.S. banking companies, including those involved in various financial services. Rather than market-cap weighting, the fund employs a factor-based approach, weighting selected holdings based on a cumulative score derived from volatility (trailing one-year), value (cash flow to price), and growth (average price returns). Individual holdings are capped at 8%, and the portfolio undergoes annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalancing to maintain its strategic exposure to banking stocks demonstrating these specific factor characteristics.

The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the banking sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and weighted based upon their cumulative score on three investing factors: volatility, value and growth. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
FTXO tracks an index composed of the most liquid US banking companies. Holdings are selected by their liquidity, and weighted based on volatility, value, and growth factors.

FTXO invests in liquid US banking companies, ranked and weighted by their volatility, value, and growth factors. The fund selects the 30 most liquid banking stocks, including companies involved in financial services, retail banking, loans, and transactions. These stocks are ranked based on their trailing one-year volatility, cash flow to price, and their average three-, six-, nine-, and twelve-month price returns, and weighted according to their respective scores. No single constituent can hold more than 8% of the total holdings. The index undergoes annual reconstitution and quarterly rebalance.
description_yahoo: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The index is designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies comprising the banking sector that have been selected based upon their liquidity and ranking. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Vanguard U.S. Growth Fund Admiral Shares
merged_description: This investment vehicle targets long-term capital appreciation through investments primarily in large-capitalization U.S. stocks. Its core investment concept involves identifying companies with above-average earnings growth potential whose shares trade at reasonable prices relative to expected earnings. Reflecting its domestic focus, the fund normally allocates at least 80% of its assets to securities issued by U.S. companies. It utilizes multiple investment advisors to manage its portfolio and is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests mainly in large-capitalization stocks of U.S. companies considered to have above-average earnings growth potential and reasonable stock prices in comparison with expected earnings. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies. The manager uses multiple investment advisors. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. name: Nuveen ESG Small-Cap ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle provides exposure to U.S. small-capitalization companies selected based on specific environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. It tracks a multi-factor-weighted index derived from a broad U.S. small-cap benchmark, screening potential holdings for factors such as climate impact, resource management, employee relations, product safety, corporate governance, and business ethics. Furthermore, the strategy explicitly excludes companies with significant involvement in alcohol, tobacco, firearms, gambling, and nuclear weapons. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in these index components, the fund utilizes a multi-factor weighting approach aiming to maintain certain characteristics similar to the broader small-cap market, with its underlying index rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index. The index is comprised of equity securities issued by small-capitalization companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") criteria.
description_etfcom:
NUSC tracks a multi-factor-weighted index of small-cap companies listed on US exchanges. Holdings are screened for environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria.

NUSC takes the popular ESG theme and slices it specifically within the small-cap space. The fund`s underlying index is derived from the MSCI USA Small Cap Index (the parent index), with further screening for environmental, social, and governance criteria. Environmental factors include impact on climate change, natural resource use, and emission management. Social categories include relationships with employees and suppliers, and product safety. Lastly, the governance criteria look at corporate governance and business ethics. Additionally, the index stays away from companies with involvement in alcohol, tobacco, firearms, gambling and nuclear weapons. The portfolio is weighted according to a multi-factor optimization algorithm that aims to keep holdings and performance similar to the parent index. The underlying index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly starting each February. Sibling fund NULC applies the same strategy to US large caps.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results, before fees and expenses, of the TIAA ESG USA Small-Cap Index (the "index"). Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index. The index is comprised of equity securities issued by small-capitalization companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") criteria.

name: iPath S&P MLP ETN
merged_description: This investment product provides exposure to an index of leading partnerships, specifically Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs) and publicly traded Limited Liability Companies with similar structures and tax benefits. These entities are classified within the GICS Energy Sector and Gas Utilities Industry, trade on major U.S. exchanges, and are selected for the index calculated and maintained by S&P Dow Jones Indices. The core concept is to offer investors access to the performance of these U.S.-based energy and utility-focused partnership structures.
description_original: The index is designed to provide exposure to leading partnerships that trade on major U.S. exchanges and are classified in the GICS Energy Sector and GICS Gas Utilities Industry according to the Global Industry Classification Standard® ("GICS"). It includes both master limited partnerships ("MLPs") and publicly traded limited liability companies which have a similar legal structure to MLPs and share the same tax benefits as MLPs (collectively, the "index constituents"). The index is calculated, maintained and published by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to provide exposure to leading partnerships that trade on major U.S. exchanges and are classified in the GICS Energy Sector and GICS Gas Utilities Industry according to the Global Industry Classification Standard® (“GICS”). It includes both master limited partnerships (“MLPs”) and publicly traded limited liability companies which have a similar legal structure to MLPs and share the same tax benefits as MLPs (collectively, the “index constituents”). The index is calculated, maintained and published by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC.

name: WisdomTree New Economy Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund invests globally in REITs and real estate-related companies, including ADRs, that are linked to or support the 'new economy'. Constituents are selected and weighted based on proprietary scores evaluating their exposure—often via tenants—to technology, life sciences, e-commerce, and modern logistics. The methodology also screens out companies with high leverage, adjusting initial market-cap weights based on technology and growth/valuation factors. Seeking to invest primarily in index components, the portfolio is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index selects constituents from a parent universe of global equity securities, including ADRs, of listed real estate investment trusts (“REITs”) and companies identified as being significantly real estate related. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: WTRE targets technology-focused real estate companies globally. Each eligible company is assigned a Technology Score based on two factors: 1) revenue received from the technology, life sciences, and R&D sectors, either directly or indirectly through its tenants that are engaged in such industries, and 2) the extent to which the constituent and/or its tenants enable or are exposed to sciences, e-commerce, or new economy logistics. The highest scoring firms are selected and are further screened to exclude highly levered companies with debt to total market-cap above 70%. Holdings are initially weighted based on market-cap. These weights are adjusted based on a combination of each constituents Technology and New Economy (growth and valuation rank) scores. The index rebalances and reconstitutes semi-annually. Prior to April 20, 2022, the fund traded as the WisdomTree Global ex-US Real Estate Fund (Ticker: DRW) and tracked a WisdomTree Index that utilizes a dividend-focused strategy.

name: Litman Gregory Funds Trust IMGP
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks dividend income and long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily (at least 80% of its assets) in a concentrated portfolio of 30 to 40 U.S. large-cap companies. The core strategy focuses on selecting firms with high, stable, and growing dividends, emphasizing those with strong track records of quarterly payments and expectations of increasing dividends over the next five years. Selection criteria include evaluating current dividend yield (often relative to the S&P 500 index), dividend stability (assessed via balance sheet strength and leverage), and potential for dividend growth (considering factors like ROE). While focusing on U.S. equities, the fund retains flexibility to invest up to 15% of its assets in foreign securities.
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in common stocks of U.S. companies that pay dividends annually, with an emphasis on stocks that have a strong track record of paying quarterly dividends or that are expected to increase their dividends over the next one to five years.
description_etfcom:
BDVG seeks income and long-term capital appreciation through an actively managed portfolio of 30 to 40 US large-cap companies with high, stable, and growing dividends.

BDVG offers a dividend-skewed take on the US large-cap equity space. The fund targets 30 to 40 dividend-paying companies that have a strong track record of paying quarterly dividends and are expected to increase their dividends over the next five years. The sub-adviser selects such companies based on current dividend yield, dividend stability, as well as history of and potential for dividend growth. The fund seeks to invest in companies with a current dividend yield that is at least as high as the S&P 500 Index average yield, or if not, have a clear path to paying higher dividends. Each firms balance sheet is evaluated, including the amount of company leverage that may potentially impact dividend stability. Lastly, the fund utilizes the companys ROE to assess prospects for dividend growth. The sub-adviser focuses on a companys regular, periodic dividends but may also consider past payments of special dividends. The fund may invest up to 15% of its net assets in foreign securities.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks dividend income and long-term capital appreciation. The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to achieve its objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in common stocks of U.S. companies that pay dividends annually, with an emphasis on stocks that have a strong track record of paying quarterly dividends or that are expected to increase their dividends over the next one to five years.

name: iShares U.S. Energy ETF
merged_description: This investment fund aims to track the performance of the U.S. large-cap energy sector by following the Russell 1000 Energy RIC 22.5/45 Capped Index. It holds a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio primarily composed of large U.S. companies involved in oil and gas production and distribution. The fund utilizes a market-capitalization weighting methodology, subject to regulatory constraints limiting single security weights to 22.5% and the aggregate weight of positions exceeding 4.5% to 45%. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in its index's component securities or economically similar investments, the fund rebalances its holdings quarterly to maintain alignment with its target index.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the energy sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
IYE tracks a market-cap-weighted index of large-cap US companies in the energy industry.

IYE covers the energy segment of the US large-cap equity market. The fund holds a concentrated portfolio of companies that facilitate production and distribution of oil and gas. The underlying index is part of Russells US large cap sector indicesa series of representative indices that integrates ICBs sector classification framework on Russell 1000. Holdings are market-cap-weighted, subject to regulatory capping which limits single security weights at 22.5% and aggregate weight of securities exceeding 4.5% allocation at 45%. Index rebalancing occurs quarterly. Prior to September 20, 2021, the fund tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Oil & Gas Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Russell 1000 Energy RIC 22.5/45 Capped Index composed of U.S. equities in the energy sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the energy sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Fallen Knives ETF
merged_description: This investment fund focuses on U.S. equity securities that have experienced significant share price declines over the prior year. However, its selection process targets only those companies demonstrating financial health, suggesting a potential for future share price recovery. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities comprising an underlying index designed to capture these specific characteristics, or in investments with similar economic features. It should be noted that this fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities that comprise the index or investments with economic characteristics similar to the securities included in the index. The index is designed by Indxx, LLC to consist of U.S. equity securities that have experienced considerable share price declines over the prior year but have financial health, suggesting that the security has potential for share price recovery in the future. It is non-diversified.

name: First Trust Emerging Markets Local Currency Bond ETF
merged_description: Seeking maximum total return and current income, this actively managed fund primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in bonds, notes, and bills issued or guaranteed by entities within emerging market countries. Crucially, these debt instruments are denominated in the local currencies of the issuers, covering any maturity or credit quality, including unrated securities. This local currency exposure makes foreign exchange volatility a significant driver of total returns, alongside potential impacts stemming from US interest rate fluctuations affecting local rates or currency movements. The fund operates as a non-diversified portfolio, allowing for discretionary investment decisions within its strategy.
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in bonds, notes and bills issued or guaranteed by entities incorporated or domiciled in emerging market countries (collectively, "Bonds") that are denominated in the local currency of the issuer. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: FEMB provides exposure to the emerging-market sovereign bond fund space. Like other funds that hold debt denominated in local currencies, FX volatilities will be material drivers in the funds total return, both upside and downside. Additionally, underpinned by the interest-rate parity model, the impact of interest-rate volatilities in the US will manifest itself either in the forms of local interest rates or FX volatilities. As such, investors of foreign sovereign debts are not fully shielded from interest-rate volatilities in the US. The fund invests in bonds of any maturity or credit quality, including unrated securities. As an actively managed fund, FEMB can make certain investment decisions at its discretion.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks maximum total return and current income. Under normal market conditions, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in bonds, notes and bills issued or guaranteed by entities incorporated or domiciled in emerging market countries (collectively, "Bonds") that are denominated in the local currency of the issuer. It is non-diversified.

name: Loncar China BioPharma ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle focused on tracking the growth of China's pharmaceutical and biotech (biopharma) sector by passively investing in companies involved in these industries. Its portfolio included pharmaceutical and biotech firms, drug manufacturers, diagnostics companies, and biopharma service providers, while deliberately excluding basic ingredient manufacturers to emphasize innovation. The underlying index employed a modified equal-weighting strategy, where initial equal weights were adjusted based on market capitalization tiers, and was reconstituted biannually. It is important to note that this fund was delisted in October 2023 and subsequently merged into a different investment vehicle.
description_original: The Advisor attempts to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities and depositary receipts that make up the index. The index seeks to track the performance of a modified equal-weighted portfolio of companies directly involved in the growth of China's pharmaceutical and biotech related industries.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of tradingon an exchange is october 20,2023. his fund is being merged into the Range Cancer Therapeutics ETF (ticker: CNCR) after the market close on October 26, 2023. CHNA targets Chinas pharmaceutical and biotech (biopharma) sector. The fund includes pharmaceutical companies, biotech companies, drug manufacturers, diagnostics companies, wholesalers or distributors of biopharma products, and biopharma service providers. It is worth noting that manufacturers of pharmaceutical ingredients are excluded, as the fund focuses on innovation in the sector. CHNA uses a tiered weighting system. Starting from equal weight, all qualified constituents are assigned a weight adjustment based on market cap. Large cap stocks get a 140% adjustment, midcaps 100%, and small-caps 70%. The index is reconstituted on every second Monday of each February and August.

name: Direxion S&P 500 High minus Low Quality ETF
merged_description: This non-diversified fund implements a specific quality-focused investment strategy within the S&P 500 universe by tracking a benchmark index. It establishes a 150% long exposure to high-quality S&P 500 stocks while simultaneously maintaining a 50% short exposure to the lowest-quality stocks within the same index. This 150/50 structure is designed to capture the performance difference between high and low-quality companies. The fund primarily invests in the underlying securities of the long portion of the strategy, and its target index incorporates a 0.30% decrement feature.
description_original: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the S&P 500Â® 150/50 Quality 0.30% Decrement Index. The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in securities that comprise the Long Component of the index or shares of exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") on the Long Component of the index. The index consists of a portfolio that has 150% long exposure to the S&P 500Â® Quality Index (the "Long Component") and 50% short (or inverse) exposure to the S&P 500Â® Quality - Lowest Quintile Index (the "Short Component"). It is non-diversified.

The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the S&P 500Â® 150/50 Quality 0.30% Decrement Index.
 The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in securities that comprise the Long Component of the index or shares of exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") on the Long Component of the index. The index consists of a portfolio that has 150% long exposure to the S&P 500Â® Quality Index (the "Long Component") and 50% short (or inverse) exposure to the S&P 500Â® Quality - Lowest Quintile Index (the "Short Component").
