name: VanEck ChiNext ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to closely replicate the performance of the ChiNext Index, which comprises the 100 largest and most liquid China A-shares listed on the ChiNext Market of the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. By normally investing at least 80% of its assets in these constituent securities, the fund offers targeted exposure to innovative smaller and medium-sized enterprises, often focused on technology and consumer sectors, which may operate under less stringent listing requirements. Utilizing the RQFII quota system, it provides direct investment access to these mainland-listed A-shares, representing a niche approach to participating in this specific growth-oriented segment of the Chinese equity market.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index is a free-float adjusted index intended to track the performance of the 100 largest and most liquid stocks listed and trading on the ChiNext Market of the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. The index is comprised of China A-shares (“A-shares”).
description_etfcom: CNXT is one of the more innovative China ETFs to launch in years. Its a highly niche-y ETF that targets 100 of the largest stocks listed on Shenzhens SME and ChiNext Boards, which cater to smaller- and medium-size enterprise companies. Many companies included in the index tilt toward tech and consumer-related companies and startups needing less stringent listing requirements. CNXT is part of a new class of China funds called RQFII ETFs, which directly hold mainland-listed shares through a quota system. Prior to Dec. 10, 2021, the fund was named VanEck Vectors ChinaAMC SME-ChiNext ETF and tracked the SME-ChiNext 100 Index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the ChiNext Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index is a free-float adjusted index intended to track the performance of the 100 largest and most liquid stocks listed and trading on the ChiNext Market of the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. The index is comprised of China A-shares (“A-shares”).

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Consumer Discretionary ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund provides exposure to the US consumer discretionary sector by tracking an equal-weighted index comprising all constituents of the S&P 500® Consumer Discretionary Index. These components are common stocks from the S&P 500® Index classified within the consumer discretionary sector according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). By assigning equal weight to each holding, the fund avoids concentration in the largest companies typical of market-cap weighting and increases relative exposure to mid-cap firms within the S&P 500 universe, although its holdings are limited to S&P 500 components. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in these underlying securities and rebalances its portfolio quarterly.
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Consumer Discretionary Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the consumer discretionary sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_etfcom:
RSPD tracks an equal-weighted index of large-cap US Consumer Discretionary stocks drawn from the S&P 500.

RSPD provides a unique but not radical alternative to market-cap-weighted consumer discretionary exposure in the US. Basically, the fund equal-weights all stocks in the S&P 500 Consumer Discretionary Index, whose composition is determined by an S&P Committee. Equal-weighting avoids concentration in large firms, while significantly increasing midcap exposure compared to the broad sector. RSPD's tilt toward smaller firms is limited by its universethe S&P 500which excludes small-caps. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to June 7, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker RCD.
description_yahoo: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Consumer Discretionary Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the consumer discretionary sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard ("GICS").

name: Direxion Nanotechnology ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle focuses on the nanotechnology industry, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in securities that make up its underlying index or in investments with similar economic characteristics. The index, provided by S&P Dow Jones Indices, is designed to measure the performance of U.S.-listed securities, including depositary receipts, from companies involved in nanotechnology. Notably, the fund operates as a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities that comprise the index or investments with economic characteristics similar to the securities included in the index. The index is provided by S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC (the “index provider”) and is designed to measure the performance of U.S.-listed securities, including depositary receipts, of companies involved in the nanotechnology industry. The fund is non-diversified.

name: AI Powered International Equity ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily invests in equity securities or depositary receipts of companies in developed markets outside the United States. Its investment strategy relies on a proprietary, quantitative model utilizing artificial intelligence, which was developed by the fund's technology-based adviser specializing in AI investment solutions and runs on the Watson™ platform. Reflecting its focused approach, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund is actively managed and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in equity securities (or depositary receipts) of companies in developed markets outside the United States based on the results of a proprietary, quantitative model (the "EquBot Model") developed by the adviser that runs on the Watson™ platform. Its investment adviser is a technology based company focused on applying artificial intelligence ("AI") based solutions to investment analyses. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Teucrium Wheat Fund
merged_description: This investment vehicle offers focused exposure to the price movements of wheat by investing in a portfolio of futures contracts. Rather than concentrating solely on the nearest-term contract, it aims to mitigate the effects of contango by holding Chicago Board of Trade wheat futures with three distinct expiration dates: the second-to-expire (weighted 35%), third-to-expire (30%), and the subsequent December contract (35%). While designed for potentially smoother performance across futures roll periods, this specific contract selection may occasionally lag spot or front-month price movements. The fund, which typically invests fully in these futures along with cash or cash equivalents, operates under a structure that requires investors to handle a K-1 tax form.
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing in Benchmark Component Futures Contracts. Under normal market conditions, the manager expects that 100% of the fund’s assets will be invested in benchmark component futures contracts and in cash and cash equivalents.
description_etfcom:
WEAT tracks an index of wheat futures contracts. It reflects the performance of wheat by holding Chicago Board of Trade wheat futures contracts with three different expiration dates.

WEAT avoids the front-month contract in its aim to provide exposure to wheat futures. Instead it holds the 2nd to expiration, 3rd to expiration and the subsequent December contracts to mitigate the impact of contango, weighting the contracts 35%, 30% and 35%, respectively. This approach should have some success in contango mitigation but may lag front month at times. The fund's structure means a K-1 at tax time and a blended tax rate.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investors with a cost-efficient way to gain price exposure to the wheat market for future delivery. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing in Benchmark Component Futures Contracts. Under normal market conditions, the manager expects that 100% of the fund’s assets will be invested in benchmark component futures contracts and in cash and cash equivalents.

name: iShares ESG MSCI USA Min Vol Factor ETF
merged_description: This passively managed ETF offers exposure to U.S. large- and mid-capitalization stocks selected simultaneously for lower volatility characteristics, favorable environmental, social, and governance (ESG) profiles, and reduced carbon exposure relative to the broader U.S. equity market. Its underlying index methodology specifically excludes companies linked to tobacco, controversial weapons, civilian firearms, certain climate change-related activities, and severe business controversies. Following these exclusions, an optimization process selects and weights the remaining securities aiming to achieve the combined objectives of minimum volatility and enhanced ESG/carbon attributes compared to its parent index. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in its index components, is considered non-diversified, and undergoes semi-annual rebalancing.
description_original: The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of large- and mid-capitalization U.S. equity securities that reflect the performance of a minimum volatility strategy and, relative to the MSCI USA Index, have higher favorable ESG characteristics and lower carbon exposure. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
ESMV tracks an index of large- and mid-cap US stocks that have low volatility and positive ESG characteristics.

ESMV is a passively managed ETF that provides exposure to large- and mid-cap US stocks that have low volatility, reduced carbon exposure, and positive ESG characteristics. The fund selects stocks from its parent index, the MSCI USA Index, and excludes those associated with tobacco, controversial weapons, civilian firearms, and certain climate change-related activities, as well as those involved in severe business controversies. Severe business controversies are based on MSCI ESG Controversy Scores. Companies without a controversy score or not assessed by the index provider are also excluded. Securities are rated and ranked in comparison to industry peers based on ESG characteristics and resilience to ESG risks to their industry. The fund then applies an optimizer to select and weight securities, aiming to achieve lower volatility and better ESG qualities relative to the parent index. The index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Minimum Volatility Extended ESG Reduced Carbon Target Index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of large- and mid-capitalization U.S. equity securities that reflect the performance of a minimum volatility strategy and, relative to the MSCI USA Index, have higher favorable ESG characteristics and lower carbon exposure. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.

name: Direxion Daily Healthcare Bull 3X Shares
merged_description: This investment vehicle is designed to deliver three times the daily performance, before fees and expenses, of the Health Care Select Sector Index. It achieves this 3x daily leveraged exposure by investing at least 80% of its net assets in a combination of financial instruments, potentially including swaps, index securities, and related ETFs. The underlying index, a market-cap weighted sub-index of the S&P 500, focuses on domestic companies within various healthcare sectors like pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, equipment, and services, with significant weight often allocated to large-cap firms. As a non-diversified fund engineered for short-term tactical trading rather than long-term investment, its returns over periods longer than a single day can significantly deviate from 3x the index performance due to daily compounding effects. Potential volatility and trading costs are important factors for investors considering this instrument.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index includes domestic companies from the healthcare sector, which includes: pharmaceuticals; health care equipment and supplies; health care providers and services; biotechnology; life sciences tools and services; and etc. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
CURE provides 3x levered exposure to a market cap weighted sub-index of the S&P 500 that tracks the performance of US listed health care companies.

As a levered product, CURE is not a buy-and-hold ETF, it's a short-term tactical instrument. Like many levered funds, it delivers 3x exposure only for one day. Over longer periods, returns can vary significantly from 3x of its underlying index, which covers some of the biggest healthcare nameslike J&J, Pfizer, and Merckin the space, and those heavyweights comprise a large share of CURE's cap-weighted, S&P 500-only portfolio. As a short-term product, CURE's expense ratio is less important than all in trading costs. Trading can be volatile. Check the latest Tradability data on this page.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index includes domestic companies from the healthcare sector, which includes: pharmaceuticals; health care equipment and supplies; health care providers and services; biotechnology; life sciences tools and services; and health care technology. It is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the Health Care Select Sector Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index includes domestic companies from the healthcare sector, which includes: pharmaceuticals; health care equipment and supplies; health care providers and services; biotechnology; life sciences tools and services; and health care technology. It is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Ultra Telecommunications
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to deliver twice (2x) the daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of the S&P Communication Services Select Sector Index. The underlying index measures the performance of communication services companies included within the S&P 500. To achieve its objective, the fund utilizes financial instruments to gain leveraged exposure, normally investing at least 80% of its assets in index components or economically similar instruments, resulting in a non-diversified portfolio. As a product featuring daily leverage and rebalancing, it is intended as a short-term tactical instrument, as long-term returns can significantly diverge from the underlying index performance due to the effects of daily compounding.
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the telecommunications sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
LTL provides 2x exposure to a market-cap-weighted index of US fixed-line and mobile telephone companies.

LTL provides 2x leveraged exposure to the Dow Jones US Select Telecommunications Index, a market-cap-weighted index of US telecom companies. Specifically, it holds a concentrated portfolio of firms involved in fixed line (regional and long-distance) and mobile telephone services (cellular, satellite, and paging). As a geared product with 2x factor that rebalances daily, LTL is not a buy-and-hold ETF, its a short-term tactical instrument. As a result, long-term returns can vary significantly from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to March 20, 2023, the fund was called ProShares Ultra Telecommunications that tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Select Telecommunications Index.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to measure the performance of communication services companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Communication Services Select Sector Index. The index is designed to measure the performance of communication services companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Dimensional - Emerging Markets High Profitability ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in large-cap companies within emerging markets, potentially including those in frontier markets. The core strategy centers on identifying and purchasing securities of companies demonstrating high profitability, often assessed relative to industry peers within the same country or region, or based on metrics such as earnings compared to book value. While considering market capitalization, the advisor retains significant discretion to adjust portfolio holdings and weightings based on factors like profitability characteristics, price momentum, and other investment criteria, aiming for a diversified portfolio across various sectors, industries, and countries to manage risk.
description_original: The Portfolio is designed to purchase securities of large companies associated with emerging markets that the Advisor determines to have high profitability relative to other large companies in the same country or region at the time of purchase. The Advisor intends to purchase securities of large companies that are associated with emerging markets, which may include frontier markets (emerging market countries in an earlier stage of development).
description_etfcom:
DEHP actively selects large-cap emerging markets companies exhibiting high profitability characteristics, seeking to provide long-term capital appreciation.

DEHP is an actively managed fund that provides a high profitability solution in aim of achieving long-term capital appreciation, whilst balancing risk by allocating investments across various sectors, industries, and countries. The fund holds a diversified portfolio of large emerging market companies deemed to have high profitability, after exhibiting high earnings or profits from operations in relation to its book value. While the fund claims to be market-cap-weighted, the advisor has full discretion to adjust a securitys exposure and increase or decrease emphasis on (or exclude) certain companies after taking into account several short-term factors like price momentum and investment characteristics, which are also the basis for stock selection.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. The Portfolio is designed to purchase securities of large companies associated with emerging markets that the Advisor determines to have high profitability relative to other large companies in the same country or region at the time of purchase. The Advisor intends to purchase securities of large companies that are associated with emerging markets, which may include frontier markets (emerging market countries in an earlier stage of development).

name: Direxion Daily S&P Expanded Tech Software Sector Bull 2X Shares
merged_description: This financial product provided 2x daily leveraged exposure tied to the performance of the S&P North American Expanded Technology Software Index. The underlying index consisted of market-cap-weighted U.S. and Canadian stocks primarily classified within the application, systems, and home entertainment software sub-industries, incorporating an 8.5% cap on individual security weights to enhance diversification within the concentrated sector. To achieve its leveraged objective, the non-diversified fund invested primarily in financial instruments such as swap agreements, securities tracking the index, and related ETFs. Due to its daily reset mechanism, this product was intended for very short-term holding periods, typically a single trading day, as compounding effects could cause its long-term returns to diverge significantly from the stated 2x daily target. Importantly, this instrument was delisted, with its final trading day on April 21, 2023.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index measures the performance of U.S. and Canadian stocks that are classified in the application software, systems software and home entertainment software sub-industries of the GICS information technology sector. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
SWAR provides 2x daily leveraged exposure to a market-cap-weighted index of US and Canadian software companies.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 21, 2023. SWAR is a 2x leveraged bet on the S&P North American Expanded Technology Software Index an index of US and Canadian stocks that are classified in the application software, systems software and home entertainment software sub-industries of the GICS information technology sector. The index is market-cap weighted, and caps individual security weights at 8.5% to provide more diverse exposure to a concentrated industry. Like most leveraged products with daily resets, SWAR is not intended to be held for more than one trading day. For longer periods, the effects of compounding may cause it to drift materially from the 200% exposure it promises to provide to the index.
description_yahoo: The index measures the performance of the constituents of the S&P North American Technology Software Index as well as certain eligible supplemental stocks. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index which provide returns consistent with the objective. It is non-diversified.

name: Nuveen Short-Term REIT ETF
merged_description: This fund tracks an index targeting U.S. REITs specifically chosen for their shorter-than-average lease durations, focusing on sectors like apartments, hotels, self-storage, and manufactured homes where such leases are common. It invests at least 80% of its assets in these equity REITs, which are drawn from a broader index of U.S.-listed REITs meeting minimum market capitalization ($200 million) and revenue criteria (at least 75% from real estate ownership/operation). Holdings are weighted by float-adjusted market capitalization, with individual positions capped at 5% upon rebalancing. The fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in REITs. The index is a subset of the Dow Jones U.S. Select REIT Index, which generally includes equity REITs traded on a national securities exchange in the U.S. that derive at least 75% of their total revenue from the ownership and operation of real estate assets and that have a minimum total market capitalization of $200 million at the time of their inclusion. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
NURE tracks an index composed of U.S. REITs that typically have shorter-term lease durations than average.

NURE`s indexa subset of the Dow Jones U.S. Select REIT Indexfocuses on REITs with short-term lease agreements. Specifically, the fund selects REITs that hold apartment buildings, hotels, self-storage facilities, and manufactured homes. Selected REITs are weighted by float-adjusted market capitalization, with no single holding comprising more than 5% of the index at each rebalance date.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Short-Term REIT Index. The fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in REITs. The index is a subset of the Dow Jones U.S. Select REIT Index, which generally includes equity REITs traded on a national securities exchange in the U.S. that derive at least 75% of their total revenue from the ownership and operation of real estate assets and that have a minimum total market capitalization of $200 million at the time of their inclusion. It is non-diversified.

name: Capital Link Global Fintech Leaders ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund, which was delisted with its final trading day on May 22, 2024, previously focused on tracking an index of global companies considered leaders in financial technology. It normally invested at least 80% of its assets in index components selected from developed and emerging markets using a natural language processing algorithm and proprietary sentiment scores. These companies were categorized as either 'Digital Asset Providers,' focused on enhancing operations, security, and creating digital assets, or 'Solutions Providers,' assisting in the adoption of new technologies. Index constituents were equally weighted and capped to limit concentration, representing an evolution from the fund's earlier focus on the blockchain theme under a different name and index prior to late 2021.
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of the index. The index was designed by the index provider to measure the performance of a diversified group of publicly-listed companies considered to be Fintech Leaders.
description_etfcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is May 22, 2024. KOIN begins its portfolio construction by screening companies from developed and emerging markets using an NLP algorithm. Then, stocks are grouped into two stakeholder categories: Digital Asset Providers (companies that use technology to increase operational sciences, optimize settlement processes, enhance the customer experience, increase data security/integrity and create digital assets) or Solutions Providers (companies that assist in the adoption and implementation of the latest technologies and applications). Index components are selected based on their proprietary sentiment score rankings. Additionally, they are capped in order to limit overconcentration to a certain category and weighted equally. Prior to Dec. 16, 2021, the fund was known as Capital Link NextGen Protocol ETF and tracked the ATFI Global NextGen Fintech Index. It also previously had exposure focused on the blockchain theme.

name: Global X Data Center REITs & Digital Infrastructure ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund offers targeted exposure to the global digital infrastructure sector, encompassing companies from both developed and emerging markets. It primarily invests in firms significantly involved in the ownership, operation, development, and hardware manufacturing related to data centers and cellular towers. Following a rules-based index methodology that emphasizes companies active in these specific areas, the fund tends to hold a significant concentration in real estate-related entities alongside digital hardware firms. The portfolio generally employs a market-capitalization weighting approach with caps to limit concentration, undergoes semi-annual rebalancing, and invests at least 80% of its assets in securities reflecting its underlying index strategy, including ADRs and GDRs. Notably, the fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets, plus borrowings for investments purposes, in the securities of the Solactive Data Center REITs & Digital Infrastructure Index and in ADRs and GDRs based on the securities in the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the fields of data centers, cellular towers, and/or digital infrastructure hardware. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: DTCR invests in firms from both developed and emerging markets that derive the bulk of their revenues in Data Center REITs and Digital Infrastructure. These firms are involved in the ownership, operation, and development of data centers and cellular towers. Also included are the digital infrastructure hardware firms that manufacture, design, or assemble the servers or other hardware for data centers and cellular towers. The underlying index uses an algorithm that ranks these firms based on the frequency of specific keywords and will primarily include real estate companies. The resulting portfolio is weighted by market cap, with weight constraints imposed to limit concentration to larger caps. The index undergoes semi-annual rebalance and reconstitution. Prior to April 1, 2024, the fund traded under the ticker VPN and has since removed REITs from its fund name.

name: IQ U.S. Mid Cap R&D Leaders ETF
merged_description: This fund focused on U.S. mid-cap companies considered leaders in innovation, tracking an index of 100 firms selected and weighted based on the highest dollar amount spent on research and development (R&D) during the most recent year, starting from the Russell Mid Cap universe. The strategy was rooted in the idea that significant R&D investment indicates strong growth potential and the capacity to develop new products or services. The index reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly, with a 5% cap on individual holdings. The fund typically invested at least 80% of its assets in these index constituents and was structured as non-diversified. Trading in this security ceased on exchanges following its delisting in late 2023.
description_original: The underlying index seeks to provide exposure to innovative companies by investing in the equities of U.S. mid cap companies that have high research and development (“R&D”) spending. The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in the investments included in its underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
MRND tracks an index of 100 mid-cap US companies selected and weighted based on the most recently reported one year research and development (R&D) spending.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 12, 2023. MRND focuses on mid-cap US companies with the highest expenditures on research and development (R&D). This is intended for innovation and development of concepts for new products or services by which the company can increase revenues. The issuer believes R&D spending is an indicator of a firms growth potential and expansion capabilities. Starting with the Russell Mid Cap Index constituents, the fund selects and weights the top 100 companies based on the most recently reported dollar amount of R&D spending during the previous year. The fund pulls the R&D data from a FactSet standardized table which aims to reconcile companies reporting differences. The index reconstitutes and rebalances quarterly so that no individual security exceeds 5% weight. LRND is part of IndexIQs Research and Development ETFs suite along with LRND and WRND, which focuses on US large-caps and global equities, respectively.

name: ProShares Ultra Consumer Services
merged_description: This investment vehicle seeks to provide double (2x) the daily performance, before fees and expenses, of a market-capitalization-weighted index representing the U.S. consumer discretionary sector within the S&P 500. The index includes companies involved in automobiles, consumer durables and apparel, consumer services, and retailing. Utilizing financial instruments, the fund normally gains leveraged exposure equivalent to at least 80% of its assets to index components or economically similar investments. Characterized as non-diversified and employing daily leverage resets, this fund is intended for short-term, tactical trading rather than long-term investment, as compounding effects can cause its returns to deviate significantly from the underlying index over extended periods.
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the consumer services industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
UCC provides 2x exposure to a market cap-weighted index of US consumer discretionary stocks drawn from the S&P 500.

UCC provides 2x the daily performance of a market cap-weighted index representing the consumer discretionary sector of the S&P 500. The underlying index, which is an S&P Select Sector Index, includes automobiles & components, consumer durables and apparel, consumer services, and retailing. As a levered product with daily resets, UCC is not a buy-and-hold investment, it's a short-term tactical instrument. As a result, long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to March 20, 2023, the fund traded as the Proshares Ultra Consumer Services and tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Consumer Services Index.
description_yahoo: The index is designed to measure the performance of consumer discretionary companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Consumer Discretionary Select Sector Index. The index is designed to measure the performance of consumer discretionary companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Evolved U.S. Healthcare Staples ETF
merged_description: This fund concentrates its investments, allocating at least 80% of its net assets under normal conditions, into U.S. listed common stocks of companies across large, mid, and small capitalizations. Its core strategy targets firms classified within the "Healthcare Staples Evolved Sector," specifically focusing on those involved in healthcare equipment and services. The selection process identifies companies whose economic characteristics have historically correlated with traditional players in this specific healthcare segment. Notably, this fund follows a non-diversified investment approach.
description_original: The fund invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets in U.S. listed common stock of large-, mid- and small-capitalization healthcare equipment and services companies. It will hold common stock of those companies that fall into the Healthcare Staples Evolved Sector which have economic characteristics that have been historically correlated with companies traditionally defined as healthcare equipment and services companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Amplify BlackSwan ISWN ETF
merged_description: This investment strategy focuses on mitigating the impact of unpredictable market declines ("Black Swan" events) while still offering potential for capital appreciation. It achieves this by allocating approximately 90% of its portfolio to U.S. Treasury securities, often employing a laddered structure targeting intermediate duration, intended to provide capital protection. The remaining 10% is invested in long-dated call options (LEAPs) on an ETF that provides exposure to developed equity markets outside of North America. These options, which offer the potential for equity market participation, are typically rolled semi-annually. The fund aims to invest at least 80% of its assets in these underlying index components and is considered non-diversified.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index, which will primarily include U.S. Treasury securities and long-dated call options ("LEAP Options") on the iShares MSCI EAFE ETF ("EFA"). The index seeks to provide returns by allocating approximately 10% of its index market capitalization to a portfolio of LEAP Options on EFA and approximately 90% of its index market capitalization in a portfolio of U.S. Treasury securities. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: ISWN expands Amplifys suite of ETFs attempting to hedge against unpredictable market events referred to as Black Swans. To provide capital protection, the fund holds 90% of its exposure in laddered US Treasury securities targeting a duration within 6 months of the 10-Year Note. The remaining 10% of the portfolio is used to buy in-the-money, long-term call options on the iShares MSCI EAFE ETF (ticker: EFA). EFA provides exposure to the equity markets of developed countries outside of North America. The call options provide the equity exposure and will have expirations of either June or December. At their expiration, the options will be rolled to the following year. Therefore, the index will be reconstituted and rebalanced every June and December. The call options selected will generally have a delta of 70 at the time of purchase, meaning that for every $1.00 of movement in the EFA share price, each option should have a corresponding $0.70 gain or loss.
description_yahoo: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index, which will primarily include U.S. Treasury securities and long-dated call options ("LEAP Options") on the iShares MSCI EAFE ETF ("EFA"). The index seeks to provide returns by allocating approximately 10% of its index market capitalization to a portfolio of LEAP Options on EFA and approximately 90% of its index market capitalization in a portfolio of U.S. Treasury securities. The fund is non-diversified.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that generally correspond (before fees and expenses) to the price and yield of the S-Network International BlackSwan Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index, which will primarily include U.S. Treasury securities and long-dated call options ("LEAP Options") on the iShares MSCI EAFE ETF ("EFA"). The index seeks to provide returns by allocating approximately 10% of its index market capitalization to a portfolio of LEAP Options on EFA and approximately 90% of its index market capitalization in a portfolio of U.S. Treasury securities. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Xtrackers Bloomberg US Investment Grade Corporate ESG ETF
merged_description: This fund offers exposure to US investment-grade corporate bonds primarily from industrial, utility, and financial issuers, selected through an Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) framework. Investing at least 80% of its assets in components of its underlying index, it aims to reflect the broad characteristics of the Bloomberg US Corporate Index while incorporating ESG considerations. The index construction involves screening for high ESG scores based on MSCI criteria, excluding companies with significant negative ESG controversies, and then reweighting the remaining bonds to largely match the sector, maturity, and rating profile of the parent index, with monthly rebalancing. Please note, this security is scheduled for delisting, with March 13, 2024, marking its final day of trading on an exchange.
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets, but typically far more, in instruments that comprise the underlying index. The index generally aims to keep the broad characteristics of its parent index, the Bloomberg Barclays US Corporate Index (an investment grade corporate bond universe), resulting in a broad investment grade fixed income market exposure with ESG aspects.
description_etfcom:
ESCR tracks an index of US investment-grade corporate bonds that are screened for ESG aspects.

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is March 13, 2024. ESCR provides exposure to investment-grade, US-dollar-denominated corporate bonds screened for ESG criteria defined by MSCI. The Parent Index includes investment-grade securities from industrial, utility and financial institutions issuers only. The securities are then screened for high ESG scores. Companies with controversies regarding negative ESG impact of operations, products or services are excluded. The remaining companies are included in the underlying index and reweighted to match the same sector, maturity and rating exposure of the parent index. The index is rebalanced monthly. Prior to May 12, 2020, the fund was named Xtrackers Investment Grade Bond - Interest Rate Hedged ETF, used ticker IGIH, and tracked the Solactive Investment Grade Corporate Bond- Interest Rate Hedged Index. On Aug. 24, 2021, the fund name and index name changed as a result of the rebranding of Bloomberg Barclays fixed income indices to Bloomberg Indices.
description_yahoo: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets, but typically far more, in instruments that comprise the underlying index. The index generally aims to keep the broad characteristics of its parent index, the Bloomberg US Corporate Index (an investment grade corporate bond universe), resulting in a broad investment grade fixed income market exposure with ESG aspects.

name: BlackRock U.S. Carbon Transition Readiness ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle targets long-term capital appreciation by focusing on large- and mid-capitalization U.S. equities, selected from the Russell 1000 Index, believed to be better positioned for the transition to a low-carbon economy. It seeks to outperform the price and yield performance of the Russell 1000 Index by utilizing proprietary scoring criteria based on research to assess companies' low-carbon transition readiness relative to their industry peers. This assessment considers factors including fossil fuels exposure, clean technology adoption, energy management, waste management, and water management. The strategy emphasizes overweighting firms with favorable scores while managing risk, potentially incorporating evaluations of corporate governance. Investing at least 80% of its assets in U.S. equity securities, the fund maintains flexibility to hold Russell 1000 components potentially outside the core transition theme and operates as a non-diversified portfolio.
description_original: The fund seeks to outperform the price and yield performance of the Russell 1000 ®Index by optimizing for LCETR scores criteria based on proprietary BFA research. It invests at least 80% of its net assets in equities of issuers listed in the U.S.A. The adviser selects portfolio securities that are components of the index. The index is a subset of the Russell 3000 Index, which measures the performance of the broad U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: LCTU gears towards low-carbon economy while trying to outperform its benchmark, the Russell 1000 Index a broad equity index of the 1,000 largest US firms. To select securities from the Russell 1000, the fund uses proprietary scoring criteria to assess the readiness of companies for a low-carbon economy transition, relative to their industry peers. The transition readiness score includes five segments: Fossil Fuels, Clean Technology, Energy Management, Waste Management and Water Management. LCTU overweights high-scoring firms while mitigating risk. In addition to this strategy, firms may also be evaluated for good governance. Despite the low-carbon footprint bias, the fund adviser may still opt to invest in Russell 1000 securities that could be considered outside of green economy investing.
description_yahoo: The fund seeks to outperform the price and yield performance of the Russell 1000 ®Index before including Fund expenses by optimizing for LCETR scores criteria based on proprietary BFA research. It invests at least 80% of its net assets plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of issuers listed in the United States of America.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing in large- and mid-capitalization U.S. equities that may be better positioned to benefit from the transition to a low-carbon economy. The fund seeks to outperform the price and yield performance of the Russell 1000 ®Index before including Fund expenses by optimizing for LCETR scores criteria based on proprietary BFA research. It invests at least 80% of its net assets plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of issuers listed in the United States of America.

name: USCF ESG Dividend Income Fund
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily seeks a high level of current income, with income growth as a secondary objective. It invests in a concentrated portfolio of 30 to 45 U.S.-listed, dividend-paying and dividend-growth companies, which may include American Depositary Receipts (ADRs) or companies domiciled outside the U.S. The selection process employs a bottom-up approach, equally weighing detailed financial analysis—focusing on metrics like dividend yield, growth prospects, balance sheet strength, cash flow generation, and valuation—with specific Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) criteria. This ESG screening filters out companies involved in controversial practices and evaluates factors such as disclosures, human rights policies, and corporate board structure, ensuring alignment with the fund's responsible investing mandate alongside its income generation goals.
description_original: The fund seeks a high level of current income and, as a secondary objective, growth of income, by investing in U.S. exchange-traded dividend-paying and dividend-growth companies that meet the fund’s ESG criteria. The fund may also invest in U.S. exchange-traded equity securities of issuers domiciled outside the U.S., including ADRs.
description_etfcom: UDI is an actively managed fund that seeks a high level of current income by investing in dividend-paying US-listed companies, which may include ADRs and companies domiciled outside the US. To identify the eligible universe, the sub-adviser evaluates companies using a bottom-up process and quantitative research, including key metrics like dividend yield, prospects for dividend growth, balance sheet strength, dividend coverage, and low valuations. Eligible companies must also meet the sub-advisors criteria of persistent cash flow generation, and commitment to pay and grow the dividend. Furthermore, an ESG filter is used to screen out companies involved in controversial practices, as well as companies that do not meet the advisors ESG criteria ---specifically, ESG disclosures, human rights record and policies, and corporate board structure. A final portfolio of 30 to 45 companies is constructed by considering both the financial and ESG profile of each candidate, equally.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks a high level of current income; growth of income is a secondary objective. The fund seeks a high level of current income and, as a secondary objective, growth of income, by investing in U.S. exchange-traded dividend-paying and dividend-growth companies that meet the fund’s ESG criteria. The fund may also invest in U.S. exchange-traded equity securities of issuers domiciled outside the U.S., including ADRs.

name: Pacer Data & Infrastructure Real Estate ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund utilizes a passive, index-tracking strategy to provide exposure to global developed market companies significantly engaged in data and infrastructure real estate. It specifically targets companies deriving at least 85% of their earnings or revenue from real estate operations within this sector, such as data centers and communication towers. Holdings are selected based on criteria including market capitalization and liquidity, often drawing from established global property and infrastructure indices, and are weighted by market capitalization with a cap on individual securities. While the portfolio is expected to include a substantial allocation to Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs), which may employ leverage, the fund itself is not leveraged. The underlying index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_original: A strategy-driven exchange traded fund (ETF) that aims to offer investors exposure to global developed market companies that generate a significant amount of their revenue from real estate operations in the data and infrastructure sector.
description_etfcom:
SRVR tracks a market cap-weighted index of real estate companies from developed markets that are related to data and infrastructure.

SRVR concentrates on developed market companies that derive at least 85% of their earnings from real estate properties related to data and infrastructure. This includes firms that own or manage real estate used for storage, computation, or transmission of data, such as data centers and communication towers. Companies in the GPR 250 and the GPR Pure infrastructure Indices that meet certain market cap and liquidity thresholds, are included in the portfolio. A significant portion of the fund is expected to be composed of REITs, which may be highly leveraged. the fund itself is not leveraged. Holdings are weighted by market-cap, with single security weights capped at 15%. The index reconstitutes and rebalances quarterly. Before Dec. 3, 2021, the index was called Benchmark Data & Infrastructure Real Estate SCTR Index. Prior to Nov. 1, 2022, the fund name and index were Pacer Benchmark Data & Infrastructure Real Estate SCTR ETF and Kelly Data Center & Tech Infrastructure Index, respectively.
description_yahoo: The advisor employs a “passive management” (or indexing) investment approach designed to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is generally composed of equity securities of developed markets companies that derive at least 85% of their earnings or revenues from real estate operations in the data and infrastructure real estate sectors (“Eligible Companies”).
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive GPR Data & Infrastructure Real Estate Index (the “index”). The advisor employs a “passive management” (or indexing) investment approach designed to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is generally composed of equity securities of developed markets companies that derive at least 85% of their earnings or revenues from real estate operations in the data and infrastructure real estate sectors (“Eligible Companies”).

name: WisdomTree Managed Futures Strategy Fund
merged_description: This actively managed, non-diversified exchange-traded fund aims to achieve positive total returns in both rising and falling markets, seeking performance uncorrelated with broad equity or fixed income returns. It primarily invests (at least 80% of net assets plus borrowings) in a managed futures strategy, utilizing long and short positions across commodity, currency, and Treasury futures contracts. While actively managed, its approach seeks to emulate a rules-based benchmark index that identifies positions based on multi-period momentum signals. The strategy systematically screens out the most volatile futures contracts, equally weights the remainder, reduces exposure when momentum signals conflict (partially replacing with Treasurys), and avoids short positions in energy futures, thereby favoring clear trends while managing volatility.
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in "managed futures". It is an actively managed exchange traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve positive total returns in rising or falling markets that are not directly correlated to broad market equity or fixed income returns. It is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
WTMF is actively managed to provide positive returns in rising and falling markets. The fund seeks to emulate the returns of an index that takes long and short positions in currency, commodity, and Treasury futures.

WTMF seeks positive, uncorrelated returns using long and short positions in commodity, currency, and Treasury futures. The ETF does not explicitly track an index, but nonetheless, aims to provide the returns of a WisdomTree benchmark index. The index selects from 24 diversified, near-month futures contracts. At each monthly rebalance, the four most volatile contracts are screened out while the rest are assigned equal weight. Long and short positions are determined by the contracts' 3-, 6-, and 12-month momentum signals. If there is a conflict between the three signals, the majority will determine the direction and the position will be reduced, one-third will be replaced with short-term Treasurys. The index will not take short positions in energy futures. Overall, the strategy favors clear momentum trends without excessive volatility. Prior to July 1 2016, the fund traded under the ticker WDTI and aimed to emulate the DTI, a well-known managed futures index.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to provide investors with positive total returns in rising or falling markets. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in "managed futures". It is an actively managed exchange traded fund ("ETF") that seeks to achieve positive total returns in rising or falling markets that are not directly correlated to broad market equity or fixed income returns. It is non-diversified.

name: VanEck Africa Index ETF
merged_description: This fund seeks to replicate the performance of an index providing broad exposure to the African economy, investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's constituent securities. The underlying index utilizes a distinctive weighting approach incorporating both gross domestic product (GDP) and market capitalization, thereby emphasizing the economic footprint of countries across the continent rather than purely market value. Eligibility extends beyond companies incorporated in Africa to include those based elsewhere but generating a majority (at least 50%) of their revenues or holding significant related assets within the continent, ensuring comprehensive, continent-wide representation across all market capitalizations. To maintain diversification, the index includes a minimum of 25 constituents and caps individual security weights at 8%.
description_original: The fund normallyinvests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund’s benchmark index. The index includes securities of African companies. African companies generally include local listings of companies that are incorporated in Africa and listings of companies incorporated outside of Africa but that have at least 50% of their revenues/related assets in Africa.
description_etfcom:
AFK tracks a GDP and market-cap-weighted index of companies generating a majority of their revenues in Africa.

AFK provides exposure to the whole African continent and not just South Africa. The fund focuses on gross domestic product (GDP) rather than market cap. This places the emphasis on each country's economic footprint rather than the market value of equity. The index takes a broad approach to eligibility: It includes companies from all caps that earn a majority of revenues in Africa, rather than restricting eligibility to companies domiciled in the continent. A minimum of 25 constituents will compose the index and their weights are capped at 8%. The index is reviewed quarterly, while GDPs are reviewed annually in June.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® GDP Africa Index. The fund normallyinvests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund’s benchmark index. The index includes securities of African companies. African companies generally include local listings of companies that are incorporated in Africa and listings of companies incorporated outside of Africa but that have at least 50% of their revenues/related assets in Africa.

name: BlackRock Future Climate and Sustainable Economy ETF
merged_description: This actively managed fund, scheduled for delisting with its final trading day on August 12, 2024, aimed to maximize total return by investing globally across market capitalizations in companies believed to advance the transition to a lower carbon economy. Its relatively concentrated, non-diversified portfolio targeted multiple subthemes driven by this future climate concept, including clean power, resource efficiency, sustainable nutrition, biodiversity, and clean transport. The investment strategy incorporated proprietary environmental assessments, sought alignment with Paris Climate Agreement goals and sector-specific targets, and applied exclusions for certain high-emission industries and violators of the UN Global Compact, while striving for an aggregate environmental assessment and overall ESG score superior to the MSCI ACWI Multiple Industries Select Index.
description_original: The fund seeks to maximize total return by primarily investing in companies that BFA believes are furthering the transition to a lower carbon economy. It will also seek to invest in a portfolio of equity securities that, in BFA’s view, has an aggregate environmental assessment that is better than the aggregate environmental assessment of the MSCI ACWI Multiple Industries Select Index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is August 12, 2024. BECO is actively managed to hold globally-listed companies of any market-cap that are believed to help further the transition to a lower carbon economy, including those involved in sustainable energy, circular economy, and the future of transport and nutrition. Eligible companies are assessed for proprietary environmental criteria such as metrics related to carbon intensity and carbon emissions. BECO seeks to align with the goals of the Paris Climate Agreement, which aims for net-zero greenhouse gas emissions by 2050. The fund also includes sector-specific alignment targets for select sectors and does not intend to invest in certain higher emission industries and in companies violating the UN Global Compact. Additionally, the fund attempts to have a better aggregate environmental assessment and overall ESG score than its benchmark, the MSCI ACWI Multiple Industries Select Index.
description_yahoo: In normal market conditions, the fund will seek to invest in a relatively concentrated portfolio of equity securities across multiple subthemes driven by this future climate theme, including (without limitation) clean power, resource efficiency, sustainable nutrition, biodiversity and clean transport. The fund is non-diversified.

name: U.S. Global GO GOLD and Precious Metal Miners ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund employs a fundamentally driven strategy focused on global precious metal mining companies. It normally invests at least 80% of its assets in firms deriving over half their revenue from precious metals, ensuring a minimum 20% allocation specifically to gold-focused miners. Utilizing exchange-listed common stock and ADRs from U.S. and international markets, including emerging economies, its scope uniquely extends beyond traditional miners to include royalty and streaming companies. The underlying index uses fundamental screening—favoring efficient firms with lower debt—and consists of 28 holdings weighted via a distinct four-tier structure, which concentrates capital in a few top-tier North American gold and silver miners meeting stringent criteria. Reflecting this targeted approach, the fund is non-diversified.
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in Precious Metals Companies and at least 20% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in Precious Metals Companies that primarily derive their revenue from gold. The index is composed of the exchange-listed common stock (or American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs")) of U.S. and international (including emerging markets) companies that earn at least 50 percent of their aggregate revenue from precious metals. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
GOAU tracks an index of 28 precious metal mining firms listed in the US, Canada, Australia, Hong Kong or South Africa. Holdings are selected by fundamental factors and weighted in fixed tiers.

GOAU provides an alternate take on the mining space by using fundamental analysis and complex tiered weighting. Unlike some competitors, the fund includes royalty and streaming companies, which provide capital to mining start-ups in exchange for a stake in the eventual production. GOAU starts by screening out mining firms that are financed primarily with debt. Miners in the top 10% by revenue per employee are deemed as priority firms. The index scores priority firms by revenue/employees, operating cash flow/employees, and gross margin, and other firms by operating cash flow/enterprise value. GOAU builds its portfolio by filling a fixed, four-tier bracket of 28 names, starting with the highest-scored priority companies and then moving down the list of other firms. Tier 1 contains three names, weighted at 10% each, which must be gold or silver miners directly listed in the US or Canada, with at least a $1 billion market cap. Requirements become less stringent with each succeeding tier.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the U.S. Global Go Gold and Precious Metal Miners Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in Precious Metals Companies and at least 20% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in Precious Metals Companies that primarily derive their revenue from gold. The index is composed of the exchange-listed common stock (or American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs")) of U.S. and international (including emerging markets) companies that earn at least 50 percent of their aggregate revenue from precious metals. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Guru Index ETF
merged_description: This investment vehicle aims to replicate the high-conviction equity holdings of select large hedge funds by tracking an index derived from their public Form 13F filings. It primarily invests, dedicating at least 80% of its assets, in the top U.S.-listed equity positions disclosed by these managers, potentially including American and Global Depositary Receipts representing these stocks. Utilizing a "copycat" approach, the fund equally weights the selected securities. While offering a transparent method to mimic accomplished stock-pickers, its strategy relies on lagged quarterly data, which may not reflect the most current hedge fund positioning. The underlying portfolio is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually based on updated filings.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of the top U.S. listed equity positions reported on Form 13F by a select group of entities characterized as hedge funds.
description_etfcom:
GURU tracks an equal-weighted index that attempts to mimic concentrated equity positions taken by large hedge funds, as reported in public filings.

GURU selects firms using a copycat approach, piggybacking on accomplished stock-pickers. The fund's index looks at published holdings of large hedge funds, focusing on those with concentrated stakes in US-listed securities. Securities selected in this manner are equally weighted. GURU's free-riding method is intuitive and transparent, but basing a portfolio on lagged quarterly snapshots of nimble hedge funds also comes with difficulties. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive Guru Index ("underlying index"). The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of the top U.S. listed equity positions reported on Form 13F by a select group of entities characterized as hedge funds.

name: USCF ETF Trust - USCF Sustainable Commodity Strategy Fund
merged_description: Focusing on sustainability, this actively managed fund seeks total return through broad exposure to commodities linked to three core themes: agriculture, renewable energy, and electrification. Investment exposure is achieved primarily via commodity derivatives, potentially held directly or through a subsidiary, and may also include related equity securities economically tied to these commodities. The portfolio targets approximately equal weighting across the three themes, utilizing a proprietary methodology that analyzes commodity usage and environmental impact to favor those with higher demand derived from sustainable applications. Furthermore, the fund aims for an approximate net-zero carbon footprint by purchasing an equivalent amount of carbon offsets annually. This fund is classified as non-diversified.
description_original: The fund advisor seeks to provide broad exposure to commodities across three different sustainability focused themes: agriculture, renewable energy and electrification. In order to provide such exposure, the fund will invest primarily in derivatives instruments for which the underlying assets are commodities and equity securities that are economically tied to particular commodities. The fund’s exposure to each of the three sustainability themes will be approximately equally weighted. The fund is non-diversified.
description_etfcom:
ZSC actively invests in commodity derivatives economically tied to the agriculture, renewable energy and electrification industry. The three themes are expected to be equally weighted within the portfolio.

ZSC seeks to provide exposure across three different sustainability themes: agriculture, renewable energy, and electrification. The fund gains exposure through the use of commodity derivatives, either directly or indirectly through a wholly-owned Cayman Island subsidiary. Within each of the sustainability themes, a proprietary, multi-factor methodology considers each commodity's primary use, secondary and potential uses, and their environmental impact. As a result of this selection process, the fund will invest more heavily in commodities that have a higher percentage of their total demand derived from sustainable uses. Yet, ZSC aims to equally weight the portfolio across the three themes. The fund may also invest in related equity securities in order to construct the representative exposure. On an annual basis, an equivalent amount of carbon offset investments are purchased to achieve an approximate net-zero carbon footprint of the funds portfolio.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks total return. The fund advisor seeks to provide broad exposure to commodities across three different sustainability focused themes: agriculture, renewable energy and electrification. In order to provide such exposure, the fund will invest primarily in derivatives instruments for which the underlying assets are commodities and equity securities that are economically tied to particular commodities. The fund’s exposure to each of the three sustainability themes will be approximately equally weighted. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Global X Alternative Income ETF
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks income by tracking an index focused on diverse, alternative asset classes selected for high dividend yield and low volatility. It invests primarily (at least 80% of assets) in index components, including depositary receipts (ADRs/GDRs), which are allocated across five distinct categories: infrastructure (comprising MLPs and related companies), real estate, preferred securities, emerging market bonds, and covered calls, often utilizing specialized ETFs for exposure within some categories. Each asset category is capped at 20% of the portfolio, with underlying constituents typically equally weighted within their respective groups. The portfolio is reconstituted annually and subject to potential quarterly rebalancing based on category weight deviations.
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is intended to provide exposure to five income-producing categories: Master Limited Partnerships ("MLPs") and Infrastructure, Real Estate, Preferreds, Emerging Market Bonds and Covered Calls.
description_etfcom:
ALTY tracks an index consisting of a variety of assets such as equity, debt securities and covered calls. Selected based on high dividend yield and low volatility.

ALTY takes a broad, multi-asset approach in its quest for income. The portfolio breaks down into five buckets: infrastructure (MLPs, infrastructure-themed equities), and ETFs with exposure to real estate (via SRET), preferreds (via PFFD), emerging market bonds (via EMBD) and covered calls (via QYLD). The infrastructure bucket has 16 companies, 8 representing MLPs and 8 for US infrastructure. They are selected for high trailing dividend yield and low trailing volatility. The index caps each asset class at 20%, and then within each asset class the constituents are equally weighted. The index is reconstituted annually, but may rebalance quarterly if the weight of any buckets deviates more than 3% from its target. Prior to Sep 28, 2021, ALTY was known as the Global X SuperDividend Alternatives ETF, its previous strategy focused dividends in the selection process and weighted for equal risk contribution based on trailing volatility.
description_morningstar: The investment seeks to track, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the Indxx SuperDividend® Alternatives Index ("underlying index"). The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is intended to provide exposure to five income-producing categories: Master Limited Partnerships ("MLPs") and Infrastructure, Real Estate, Preferreds, Emerging Market Bonds and Covered Calls.
